CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.


CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    rv_ceo_name = ``.

    DATA lv_emp_count TYPE i.
    SELECT COUNT( * ) FROM zemp_master INTO @lv_emp_count.
    IF lv_emp_count = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_org TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zorg_structure WITH EMPTY KEY.
    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM zorg_structure
      INTO TABLE @lt_org.

    IF lt_org IS INITIAL.
      IF lv_emp_count = 1.
        SELECT SINGLE name
          FROM zemp_master
          INTO @DATA(lv_single_name).
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_single_name IS NOT INITIAL.
          rv_ceo_name = lv_single_name.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_sup TYPE SORTED TABLE OF zorg_structure-supervisor_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT lt_org ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_org>).
      IF <ls_org>-employee_id IS INITIAL OR <ls_org>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT <ls_org>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_sup.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_ceo_ids TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zemp_master-employee_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

    SELECT employee_id
      FROM zemp_master
      INTO TABLE @DATA(lt_all_emp_ids).

    LOOP AT lt_all_emp_ids ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_empid>).
      READ TABLE lt_sup WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <lv_empid> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        APPEND <lv_empid> TO lt_ceo_ids.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_ceo_ids ) <> 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo_id) = lt_ceo_ids[ 1 ].

    SELECT SINGLE name
      FROM zemp_master
      WHERE employee_id = @lv_ceo_id
      INTO @DATA(lv_ceo_name).
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_ceo_name IS INITIAL.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_map TYPE HASHED TABLE OF zorg_structure WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.
    lt_map = lt_org.

    DATA lt_seen TYPE HASHED TABLE OF zemp_master-employee_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT lt_org ASSIGNING <ls_org>.
      CLEAR lt_seen.
      DATA(lv_curr) = <ls_org>-employee_id.

      WHILE lv_curr IS NOT INITIAL.
        READ TABLE lt_seen WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_curr TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        INSERT lv_curr INTO TABLE lt_seen.

        IF lv_curr = lv_ceo_id.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_map WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = lv_curr INTO DATA(ls_next).
        IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR ls_next-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
          CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        lv_curr = ls_next-supervisor_id.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_ceo_name = lv_ceo_name.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    rv_ceo_name = ``.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.

    TYPES ty_id TYPE c LENGTH 20.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_emp,
             employee_id TYPE ty_id,
             name        TYPE c LENGTH 80,
           END OF ty_emp.
    TYPES ty_emp_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_emp WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_edge.
    TYPES ty_edge_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_emp   TYPE ty_emp_tab.
    DATA lt_edges TYPE ty_edge_tab.

    SELECT employee_id, name
      FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
      INTO TABLE @lt_emp.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lt_emp IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_edges.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lt_edges IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SORT lt_edges BY employee_id.
    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e>) FROM 2.
      IF <e>-employee_id = lt_edges[ sy-tabix - 1 ]-employee_id.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_supervisors TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      INSERT <e>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_supervisors.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_candidates TYPE ty_emp_tab.
    LOOP AT lt_emp ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<emp>).
      READ TABLE lt_supervisors WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <emp>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        APPEND <emp> TO lt_candidates.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_candidates ) <> 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo_id) = lt_candidates[ 1 ]-employee_id.

    DATA lt_incoming TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_incoming.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_incoming ) <> lines( lt_emp ) - 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_incoming WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_ceo_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_emp ASSIGNING <emp>.
      IF <emp>-employee_id <> lv_ceo_id.
        READ TABLE lt_incoming WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <emp>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_adj,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_adj.
    TYPES ty_adj_tab TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_adj WITH NON-UNIQUE KEY supervisor_id.

    DATA lt_adj TYPE ty_adj_tab.
    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_adj( supervisor_id = <e>-supervisor_id employee_id = <e>-employee_id ) INTO TABLE lt_adj.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_queue   TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_visited TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    APPEND lv_ceo_id TO lt_queue.

    WHILE lt_queue IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA(lv_curr) = lt_queue[ 1 ].
      DELETE lt_queue INDEX 1.

      READ TABLE lt_visited WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_curr TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT lv_curr INTO TABLE lt_visited.

      LOOP AT lt_adj INTO DATA(ls_adj) WHERE supervisor_id = lv_curr.
        APPEND ls_adj-employee_id TO lt_queue.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_visited ) <> lines( lt_emp ).
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_ceo_name = lt_candidates[ 1 ]-name.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.

    DATA lv_emp_cnt TYPE i.
    DATA lv_name_single TYPE string.
    DATA lv_ceo_name_db TYPE string.

    SELECT COUNT( * ) FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER') INTO @lv_emp_cnt.
    IF lv_emp_cnt = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_org,
             employee_id   TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             supervisor_id TYPE c LENGTH 20,
           END OF ty_org.
    TYPES ty_org_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_org WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_empid TYPE c LENGTH 20.

    DATA lt_org TYPE ty_org_tab.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_org.

    IF lt_org IS INITIAL.
      IF lv_emp_cnt = 1.
        SELECT SINGLE name
          FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
          INTO @lv_name_single.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_name_single IS NOT INITIAL.
          rv_ceo_name = lv_name_single.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_emp_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_sup_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT lt_org ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_org>).
      INSERT <ls_org>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_emp_ids.
      INSERT <ls_org>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_sup_ids.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_emp_ids ) <> lines( lt_org ).
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_candidates TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_empid WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_sup_ids ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_sup>).
      READ TABLE lt_emp_ids WITH KEY table_line = <lv_sup> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        APPEND <lv_sup> TO lt_candidates.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_candidates ) <> 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo_id) = lt_candidates[ 1 ].

    SELECT SINGLE name
      FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
      WHERE employee_id = @lv_ceo_id
      INTO @lv_ceo_name_db.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_ceo_name_db IS INITIAL.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_edges TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_org WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.
    lt_edges = CORRESPONDING #( lt_org ).

    DATA lt_seen TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA(lv_current) = lv_ceo_id.
    DATA(lv_steps) = 0.

    DO.
      IF lv_steps >= lv_emp_cnt.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_seen WITH KEY table_line = lv_current TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT lv_current INTO TABLE lt_seen.

      READ TABLE lt_edges WITH KEY employee_id = lv_current ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_edge>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_current = <ls_edge>-supervisor_id.
      lv_steps += 1.
    ENDDO.

    IF lines( lt_seen ) <> lv_emp_cnt.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_ceo_name = lv_ceo_name_db.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  FOR TESTING
  DURATION SHORT
  RISK LEVEL HARMLESS
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    TYPES ty_empid TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_emp,
             employee_id TYPE ty_empid,
             name        TYPE c LENGTH 80,
           END OF ty_emp.
    TYPES ty_emp_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_emp WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_rel,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_empid,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_empid,
           END OF ty_rel.
    TYPES ty_rel_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_rel WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS read_employees
      RETURNING VALUE(rt_emp) TYPE ty_emp_tab.
    CLASS-METHODS read_relations
      RETURNING VALUE(rt_rel) TYPE ty_rel_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.

    DATA(lt_emp) = read_employees( ).
    IF lt_emp IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lt_rel) = read_relations( ).
    IF lt_rel IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SORT lt_rel BY employee_id.
    DELETE ADJACENT DUPLICATES FROM lt_rel COMPARING employee_id.
    IF lt_rel IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lines( lt_rel ) <> lines( lt_emp ) - 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_sup TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    lt_sup = VALUE #( FOR r IN lt_rel ( r-supervisor_id ) ).

    DATA lt_candidates TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_empid WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_emp ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e>).
      IF NOT line_exists( lt_sup[ table_line = <e>-employee_id ] ).
        APPEND <e>-employee_id TO lt_candidates.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_candidates ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_ceo_id TYPE ty_empid.
    READ TABLE lt_candidates INDEX 1 INTO lv_ceo_id.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_ceo_id IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_rel WITH KEY employee_id = lv_ceo_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS BINARY SEARCH.
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_emp ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ceo>) WITH KEY employee_id = lv_ceo_id.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <ceo>-name IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_ceo_name = <ceo>-name.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD read_employees.
    CLEAR rt_emp.

    DATA lv_tab TYPE tabname.
    lv_tab = 'ZEMP_MASTER'.

    SELECT SINGLE tabname
      FROM dd02l
      INTO @DATA(lv_exists)
      WHERE tabname = @lv_tab
        AND as4local = 'A'.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SELECT employee_id, name
      FROM (lv_tab)
      INTO TABLE @rt_emp.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD read_relations.
    CLEAR rt_rel.

    DATA lv_tab TYPE tabname.
    lv_tab = 'ZORG_STRUCTURE'.

    SELECT SINGLE tabname
      FROM dd02l
      INTO @DATA(lv_exists)
      WHERE tabname = @lv_tab
        AND as4local = 'A'.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM (lv_tab)
      INTO TABLE @rt_rel.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.

    DATA lv_name_field TYPE string.

    DATA lo_tab_emp TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.
    DATA lo_tab_org TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.
    DATA lo_line_emp TYPE REF TO cl_abap_structdescr.

    TRY.
        lo_tab_emp ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZEMP_MASTER' ).
        lo_tab_org ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZORG_STRUCTURE' ).
      CATCH cx_sy_dyn_call_illegal_type.
        RETURN.
      CATCH cx_root.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    lo_line_emp ?= lo_tab_emp->get_table_line_type( ).

    CLEAR lv_name_field.
    LOOP AT lo_line_emp->get_components( ) ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<c>).
      IF to_upper( <c>-name ) = 'NAME'.
        lv_name_field = <c>-name.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
    IF lv_name_field IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lr_emp TYPE REF TO data.
    DATA lr_org TYPE REF TO data.
    CREATE DATA lr_emp TYPE HANDLE lo_tab_emp.
    CREATE DATA lr_org TYPE HANDLE lo_tab_org.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_emp> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_org> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
    ASSIGN lr_emp->* TO <lt_emp>.
    ASSIGN lr_org->* TO <lt_org>.

    TRY.
        SELECT *
          FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
          INTO TABLE @<lt_emp>.
      CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error.
        RETURN.
      CATCH cx_root.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF <lt_emp> IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TRY.
        SELECT *
          FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
          INTO TABLE @<lt_org>.
      CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error.
        RETURN.
      CATCH cx_root.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF <lt_org> IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_emp_set TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT <lt_emp> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_emp>).
      FIELD-SYMBOLS <empid> TYPE any.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO <empid>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <empid> IS INITIAL.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT |{ <empid> }| INTO TABLE lt_emp_set.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_emp_set ) <> lines( <lt_emp> ).
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_supervisors TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_seen_employees TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT <lt_org> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_org>).
      FIELD-SYMBOLS <eid> TYPE any.
      FIELD-SYMBOLS <sid> TYPE any.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID'   OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <eid>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'SUPERVISOR_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <sid>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <eid> IS INITIAL OR <sid> IS INITIAL.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_eid) = |{ <eid> }|.
      DATA(lv_sid) = |{ <sid> }|.

      READ TABLE lt_emp_set WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_eid TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_emp_set WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_sid TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT lv_eid INTO TABLE lt_seen_employees.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT lv_sid INTO TABLE lt_supervisors.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA(lv_emp_count) = lines( lt_emp_set ).
    IF lines( <lt_org> ) <> lv_emp_count - 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lines( lt_seen_employees ) <> lines( <lt_org> ).
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_candidates TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_emp_set ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<id>).
      READ TABLE lt_supervisors WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <id> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        APPEND <id> TO lt_candidates.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
    IF lines( lt_candidates ) <> 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo_id) = lt_candidates[ 1 ].

    DATA lt_reached TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.

    INSERT lv_ceo_id INTO TABLE lt_reached.
    APPEND lv_ceo_id TO lt_queue.

    WHILE lt_queue IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA(lv_cur) = lt_queue[ 1 ].
      DELETE lt_queue INDEX 1.

      LOOP AT <lt_org> ASSIGNING <ls_org>.
        FIELD-SYMBOLS <eid2> TYPE any.
        FIELD-SYMBOLS <sid2> TYPE any.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID'   OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <eid2>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'SUPERVISOR_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <sid2>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        IF |{ <eid2> }| = lv_cur.
          DATA(lv_child) = |{ <sid2> }|.
          READ TABLE lt_reached WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_child TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            INSERT lv_child INTO TABLE lt_reached.
            APPEND lv_child TO lt_queue.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_reached ) <> lv_emp_count.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <lt_emp> ASSIGNING <ls_emp>.
      FIELD-SYMBOLS <empid3> TYPE any.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO <empid3>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF |{ <empid3> }| = lv_ceo_id.
        FIELD-SYMBOLS <nm> TYPE any.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT lv_name_field OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO <nm>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        rv_ceo_name = |{ <nm> }|.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    rv_ceo_name = ``.

    TYPES ty_empid TYPE c LENGTH 20.

    DATA lo_emp_tabdescr TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.
    DATA lo_org_tabdescr TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.

    TRY.
        lo_emp_tabdescr ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZEMP_MASTER' ).
        lo_org_tabdescr ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZORG_STRUCTURE' ).
      CATCH cx_sy_type_not_found cx_sy_move_cast_error.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    DATA lr_emp_tab TYPE REF TO data.
    DATA lr_org_tab TYPE REF TO data.
    CREATE DATA lr_emp_tab TYPE HANDLE lo_emp_tabdescr.
    CREATE DATA lr_org_tab TYPE HANDLE lo_org_tabdescr.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_emp> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_org> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    ASSIGN lr_emp_tab->* TO <lt_emp>.
    ASSIGN lr_org_tab->* TO <lt_org>.

    SELECT *
      FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
      INTO TABLE @<lt_emp>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lt_emp> IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SELECT *
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @<lt_org>.

    DATA lt_emp_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT <lt_emp> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_emp>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<emp_id_any>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <emp_id_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT CONV ty_empid( <emp_id_any> ) INTO TABLE lt_emp_ids.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_subordinates TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_supervisors  TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT <lt_org> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_org>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID'   OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<org_emp_any>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'SUPERVISOR_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<org_sup_any>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <org_emp_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <org_sup_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_emp) = CONV ty_empid( <org_emp_any> ).
      DATA(lv_sup) = CONV ty_empid( <org_sup_any> ).

      IF line_exists( lt_emp_ids[ table_line = lv_emp ] ) AND
         line_exists( lt_emp_ids[ table_line = lv_sup ] ).
        INSERT lv_emp INTO TABLE lt_subordinates.
        INSERT lv_sup INTO TABLE lt_supervisors.
      ELSE.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_ceo_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT lt_emp_ids ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<id>).
      IF NOT line_exists( lt_supervisors[ table_line = <id> ] ).
        INSERT <id> INTO TABLE lt_ceo_ids.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_ceo_ids ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_ceo_id TYPE ty_empid.
    lv_ceo_id = lt_ceo_ids[ 1 ].

    IF lines( <lt_org> ) <> lines( lt_subordinates ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lines( <lt_org> ) > 0 AND NOT line_exists( lt_subordinates[ table_line = lv_ceo_id ] ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_next_by_emp TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT <lt_org> ASSIGNING <ls_org>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID'   OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <org_emp_any>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'SUPERVISOR_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <org_sup_any>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <org_emp_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <org_sup_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT |{ CONV ty_empid( <org_emp_any> ) }#{ CONV ty_empid( <org_sup_any> ) }| INTO TABLE lt_next_by_emp.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_visited TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE ty_empid.
    lv_curr = lv_ceo_id.

    DO.
      IF line_exists( lt_visited[ table_line = lv_curr ] ).
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT lv_curr INTO TABLE lt_visited.

      IF lines( lt_visited ) = lines( lt_emp_ids ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lv_pair TYPE string.
      READ TABLE lt_next_by_emp WITH KEY table_line = |{ lv_curr }#| TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lv_found TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
      LOOP AT lt_next_by_emp INTO lv_pair WHERE table_line CP |{ lv_curr }#*|.
        DATA(lv_sup_str) = substring_after( val = lv_pair sub = |{ lv_curr }#| ).
        lv_curr = CONV ty_empid( lv_sup_str ).
        lv_found = abap_true.
        EXIT.
      ENDLOOP.
      IF lv_found = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    LOOP AT <lt_emp> ASSIGNING <ls_emp>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO <emp_id_any>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <emp_id_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF CONV ty_empid( <emp_id_any> ) = lv_ceo_id.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'NAME' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<name_any>).
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <name_any> IS ASSIGNED.
          rv_ceo_name = CONV string( <name_any> ).
        ENDIF.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.

    TYPES: ty_emp_id TYPE c LENGTH 20,
           ty_name   TYPE c LENGTH 80,
           BEGIN OF ty_emp,
             employee_id TYPE ty_emp_id,
             name        TYPE ty_name,
           END OF ty_emp,
           ty_emp_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_emp WITH EMPTY KEY,
           BEGIN OF ty_org,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_emp_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_emp_id,
           END OF ty_org,
           ty_org_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_org WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_emp TYPE ty_emp_tab.
    DATA lt_org TYPE ty_org_tab.

    SELECT employee_id, name
      FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
      INTO TABLE @lt_emp.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lt_emp IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_org.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      CLEAR lt_org.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_all_emp TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_emp_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    lt_all_emp = VALUE #( FOR <er> IN lt_emp ( <er>-employee_id ) ).

    DATA lt_supervisors TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_emp_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    lt_supervisors = VALUE #( FOR <or> IN lt_org ( <or>-supervisor_id ) ).

    DATA lt_candidates TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_emp_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_emp ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<emp>).
      READ TABLE lt_supervisors WITH KEY table_line = <emp>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        APPEND <emp>-employee_id TO lt_candidates.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_candidates ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo_id) = lt_candidates[ 1 ].

    LOOP AT lt_org ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<org>).
      READ TABLE lt_all_emp WITH KEY table_line = <org>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      READ TABLE lt_all_emp WITH KEY table_line = <org>-supervisor_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_emp_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_stack   TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_emp_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

    APPEND lv_ceo_id TO lt_stack.

    WHILE lt_stack IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA(lv_idx) = lines( lt_stack ).
      READ TABLE lt_stack INDEX lv_idx INTO DATA(lv_curr).
      DELETE lt_stack INDEX lv_idx.

      READ TABLE lt_visited WITH KEY table_line = lv_curr TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT lv_curr INTO TABLE lt_visited.

      LOOP AT lt_org ASSIGNING <org> WHERE supervisor_id = lv_curr.
        READ TABLE lt_visited WITH KEY table_line = <org>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          APPEND <org>-employee_id TO lt_stack.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_visited ) <> lines( lt_emp ).
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_emp ASSIGNING <emp> WITH KEY employee_id = lv_ceo_id.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <emp>-name IS INITIAL.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_ceo_name = <emp>-name.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.

    IF NOT cl_abap_dbfeatures=>use_features( VALUE #( ( cl_abap_dbfeatures=>ddl ) ) ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_ceo_id TYPE string.

    SELECT SINGLE ceo_id
      FROM (
        SELECT employee_id AS ceo_id,
               COUNT( * ) OVER ( )                       AS ceo_cnt,
               ( SELECT COUNT( * ) FROM zemp_master )     AS emp_cnt,
               ( SELECT COUNT( * ) FROM zorg_structure )  AS rel_cnt
          FROM zemp_master AS e
          WHERE NOT EXISTS (
            SELECT 1 FROM zorg_structure AS s
              WHERE s~supervisor_id = e~employee_id
          )
      ) AS x
      WHERE x~ceo_cnt = 1
        AND x~rel_cnt = x~emp_cnt - 1
      INTO @lv_ceo_id.

    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_ceo_id IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SELECT SINGLE name
      FROM zemp_master
      WHERE employee_id = @lv_ceo_id
      INTO @DATA(lv_name).

    IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_name IS NOT INITIAL.
      rv_ceo_name = lv_name.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_ceo_name
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_ceo_name) TYPE string.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_ceo IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_ceo_name.
    CLEAR rv_ceo_name.

    DATA lo_struct_emp TYPE REF TO cl_abap_structdescr.
    DATA lo_struct_org TYPE REF TO cl_abap_structdescr.
    DATA lo_table_emp  TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.
    DATA lo_table_org  TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.

    TRY.
        lo_struct_emp ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZEMP_MASTER' ).
        lo_struct_org ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZORG_STRUCTURE' ).
        lo_table_emp = cl_abap_tabledescr=>create( p_line_type = lo_struct_emp ).
        lo_table_org = cl_abap_tabledescr=>create( p_line_type = lo_struct_org ).
      CATCH cx_sy_type_not_found cx_sy_move_cast_error.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_emp> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <lt_org> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <ls_emp> TYPE any,
                   <ls_org> TYPE any,
                   <lv>     TYPE any.

    DATA lr_emp TYPE REF TO data.
    DATA lr_org TYPE REF TO data.

    CREATE DATA lr_emp TYPE HANDLE lo_table_emp.
    CREATE DATA lr_org TYPE HANDLE lo_table_org.

    ASSIGN lr_emp->* TO <lt_emp>.
    ASSIGN lr_org->* TO <lt_org>.
    IF <lt_emp> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lt_org> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TRY.
        SELECT *
          FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
          INTO TABLE @<lt_emp>.

        SELECT *
          FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
          INTO TABLE @<lt_org>.
      CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error cx_sy_open_sql_db.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lines( <lt_emp> ) = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TYPES ty_empid TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    TYPES ty_name  TYPE c LENGTH 80.

    DATA lt_emp_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_sub_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_sup_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT <lt_emp> ASSIGNING <ls_emp>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO <lv>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lv> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lv> IS INITIAL.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT CONV ty_empid( <lv> ) INTO TABLE lt_emp_ids.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT <lt_org> ASSIGNING <ls_org>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_eid>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'SUPERVISOR_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_sid>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lv_eid> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lv_sid> IS NOT ASSIGNED
         OR <lv_eid> IS INITIAL OR <lv_sid> IS INITIAL.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_empid) = CONV ty_empid( <lv_eid> ).
      DATA(lv_supid) = CONV ty_empid( <lv_sid> ).

      IF NOT line_exists( lt_emp_ids[ table_line = lv_empid ] )
         OR NOT line_exists( lt_emp_ids[ table_line = lv_supid ] ).
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT lv_empid INTO TABLE lt_sub_ids.
      INSERT lv_supid INTO TABLE lt_sup_ids.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_ceo_ids TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_empid WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_emp_ids ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_empid2>).
      IF NOT line_exists( lt_sup_ids[ table_line = <lv_empid2> ] ).
        APPEND <lv_empid2> TO lt_ceo_ids.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_ceo_ids ) <> 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo_id) = lt_ceo_ids[ 1 ].

    IF line_exists( lt_sub_ids[ table_line = lv_ceo_id ] ).
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lines( <lt_org> ) <> lines( <lt_emp> ) - 1.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_seen TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    INSERT lv_ceo_id INTO TABLE lt_seen.

    DATA lt_frontier TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_empid WITH EMPTY KEY.
    APPEND lv_ceo_id TO lt_frontier.

    WHILE lt_frontier IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA lt_next TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_empid WITH EMPTY KEY.

      LOOP AT lt_frontier ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_curr>).
        LOOP AT <lt_org> ASSIGNING <ls_org>.
          ASSIGN COMPONENT 'SUPERVISOR_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <lv_sid>.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lv_sid> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
            CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          IF CONV ty_empid( <lv_sid> ) <> <lv_curr>.
            CONTINUE.
          ENDIF.

          ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_org> TO <lv_eid>.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lv_eid> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
            CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.

          DATA(lv_child) = CONV ty_empid( <lv_eid> ).
          IF line_exists( lt_seen[ table_line = lv_child ] ).
            CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.

          INSERT lv_child INTO TABLE lt_seen.
          APPEND lv_child TO lt_next.
        ENDLOOP.
      ENDLOOP.

      lt_frontier = lt_next.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_seen ) <> lines( <lt_emp> ).
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo_name_c80) = VALUE ty_name( ).

    LOOP AT <lt_emp> ASSIGNING <ls_emp>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'EMPLOYEE_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO <lv_eid>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lv_eid> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF CONV ty_empid( <lv_eid> ) <> lv_ceo_id.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'NAME' OF STRUCTURE <ls_emp> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_name>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lv_name> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lv_name> IS INITIAL.
        CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_ceo_name_c80 = CONV ty_name( <lv_name> ).
      EXIT.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_ceo_name_c80 IS INITIAL.
      CLEAR rv_ceo_name.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_ceo_name = lv_ceo_name_c80.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: ty_num TYPE int8.
    TYPES: ty_nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_subarray_sum
      IMPORTING
        nums TYPE ty_nums
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_num.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_subarray_sum.
    IF nums IS INITIAL.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA current_sum TYPE ty_num.
    DATA min_sum     TYPE ty_num.
    DATA first       TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    LOOP AT nums INTO DATA(n).
      IF first = abap_true.
        current_sum = n.
        min_sum     = n.
        first = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        IF current_sum < 0.
          current_sum = current_sum + n.
        ELSE.
          current_sum = n.
        ENDIF.

        IF current_sum < min_sum.
          min_sum = current_sum.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = min_sum.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS min_subarray_sum
      IMPORTING
        it_nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_min_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_subarray_sum.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <n>   TYPE any,
                   <n_i> TYPE i.

    DATA: lv_current_min TYPE i,
          lv_global_min  TYPE i,
          lv_value       TYPE i,
          lv_first       TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    LOOP AT it_nums ASSIGNING <n>.
      ASSIGN <n> TO <n_i> CASTING.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_value = <n_i>.
      ELSE.
        lv_value = <n>.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_current_min = lv_value.
        lv_global_min  = lv_value.
        lv_first = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_current_min = nmin( val1 = lv_value val2 = lv_current_min + lv_value ).
        lv_global_min  = nmin( val1 = lv_global_min val2 = lv_current_min ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_first = abap_true.
      rv_min_sum = 0.
    ELSE.
      rv_min_sum = lv_global_min.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS min_subarray_sum
      IMPORTING
        nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE syindex.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_subarray_sum.
    DATA: lv_curr  TYPE syindex,
          lv_min   TYPE syindex,
          lv_first TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_num   TYPE syindex.

    LOOP AT nums INTO lv_num.
      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_curr  = lv_num.
        lv_min   = lv_num.
        lv_first = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_curr = nmin( val1 = lv_num val2 = lv_curr + lv_num ).
        lv_min  = nmin( val1 = lv_min val2 = lv_curr ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = lv_min.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS min_subarray_sum
      IMPORTING
        nums          TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sytabix WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE sytabix.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_subarray_sum.
    DATA: lv_first   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_curr    TYPE sytabix,
          lv_min_sum TYPE sytabix.

    LOOP AT nums INTO DATA(lv_num).
      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_curr    = lv_num.
        lv_min_sum = lv_num.
        lv_first   = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_curr = nmin( val1 = lv_num val2 = lv_curr + lv_num ).
        lv_min_sum = nmin( val1 = lv_min_sum val2 = lv_curr ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = lv_min_sum.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS min_subarray_sum
      IMPORTING
        it_nums TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_min_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_subarray_sum.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_val> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_first   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_min_end TYPE i,
          lv_min_sof TYPE i,
          lv_val_i   TYPE i.

    LOOP AT it_nums ASSIGNING <lv_val>.
      lv_val_i = <lv_val>.

      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_min_end = lv_val_i.
        lv_min_sof = lv_val_i.
        lv_first = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        IF lv_min_end + lv_val_i < lv_val_i.
          lv_min_end = lv_min_end + lv_val_i.
        ELSE.
          lv_min_end = lv_val_i.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_min_end < lv_min_sof.
          lv_min_sof = lv_min_end.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_min_sum = lv_min_sof.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS min_subarray_sum
      IMPORTING
        nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF integer
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE integer.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_subarray_sum IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD min_subarray_sum.
    DATA: lv_first   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_min_end TYPE integer,
          lv_min_all TYPE integer,
          lv_num     TYPE integer.

    LOOP AT nums INTO lv_num.
      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_min_end = lv_num.
        lv_min_all = lv_num.
        lv_first = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        IF lv_min_end + lv_num < lv_num.
          lv_min_end = lv_min_end + lv_num.
        ELSE.
          lv_min_end = lv_num.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_min_end < lv_min_all.
          lv_min_all = lv_min_end.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = lv_min_all.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(ro_result) TYPE REF TO data.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.
    DATA lv_sum_abs   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sign_prod TYPE i.
    DATA lv_out       TYPE i.
    DATA lv_tmp       TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_val> TYPE i.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_res> TYPE i.

    IF it_arr IS INITIAL.
      ro_result = REF #( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_sum_abs = 0.
    lv_sign_prod = 1.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING <lv_val>.
      IF <lv_val> < 0.
        lv_tmp = <lv_val>.
        lv_tmp = lv_tmp * -1.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + lv_tmp.
        lv_sign_prod = lv_sign_prod * -1.
      ELSEIF <lv_val> = 0.
        lv_sign_prod = 0.
        EXIT.
      ELSE.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + <lv_val>.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_out = lv_sum_abs * lv_sign_prod.

    CREATE DATA ro_result TYPE i.
    ASSIGN ro_result->* TO <lv_res>.
    <lv_res> = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_val> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    DATA lv_sum_abs   TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_sign_prod TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_i         TYPE i.

    CLEAR ro_result.

    IF it_arr IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING <ls_row>.
      ASSIGN <ls_row> TO <lv_val>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          lv_i = CONV i( <lv_val> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + abs( lv_i ).

      IF lv_i = 0.
        lv_sign_prod = 0.
      ELSEIF lv_sign_prod <> 0 AND lv_i < 0.
        lv_sign_prod = lv_sign_prod * -1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    CREATE DATA ro_result TYPE i.
    ASSIGN ro_result->* TO <lv_any>.
    <lv_any> = lv_sum_abs * lv_sign_prod.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

    DATA lv_mag       TYPE i.

    IF it_arr IS INITIAL.
      rr_result = REF #( ).

    ENDIF.

    lv_sum_mag = 0.
    lv_sign_prod = 1.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_val.
      IF lv_val < 0.
        lv_mag = lv_val.
        lv_mag = lv_mag * -1.
        lv_sum_mag = lv_sum_mag + lv_mag.
        lv_sign_prod = lv_sign_prod * -1.
      ELSEIF lv_val > 0.
        lv_sum_mag = lv_sum_mag + lv_val.
      ELSE.
        lv_sign_prod = 0.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
