  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rr_result) TYPE REF TO syindex.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.
    DATA lr_result TYPE REF TO syindex.
    DATA lv_sum    TYPE syindex VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_sign   TYPE i VALUE 1.

    IF lines( it_arr ) = 0.
      CLEAR lr_result.
      rr_result = lr_result.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      lv_sum = lv_sum + abs( <n> ).

      IF <n> = 0.
        lv_sign = 0.
        EXIT.
      ELSEIF <n> < 0.
        lv_sign = lv_sign * -1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    lr_result = NEW syindex( lv_sum * lv_sign ).
    rr_result = lr_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(ro_result) TYPE REF TO data.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.
    IF it_arr IS INITIAL.
      ro_result = REF #( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_sum_abs   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sign_prod TYPE i.
    DATA lv_n         TYPE i.
    DATA lv_result    TYPE i.

    lv_sum_abs = 0.
    lv_sign_prod = 1.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_n.
      IF lv_n < 0.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + lv_n.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs * -1.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs * -1.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs - lv_n.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + ( lv_n * -2 ).
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs - ( lv_n * -2 ).
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + ( lv_n * -1 ).
        lv_sign_prod = lv_sign_prod * -1.
      ELSE.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + lv_n.
        IF lv_n = 0.
          lv_sign_prod = 0.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    CLEAR lv_sum_abs.
    lv_sign_prod = 1.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_n.
      IF lv_n < 0.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs - lv_n.
        lv_sign_prod = lv_sign_prod * -1.
      ELSE.
        lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + lv_n.
        IF lv_n = 0.
          lv_sign_prod = 0.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_result = lv_sum_abs * lv_sign_prod.

    GET REFERENCE OF lv_result INTO ro_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.
    IF it_arr IS INITIAL.
      rv_result = ``.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_sum_mag) TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0 VALUE '0'.
    DATA(lv_sign_prod) TYPE p LENGTH 1 DECIMALS 0 VALUE '1'.
    DATA(lv_has_zero) TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<s>).
      DATA(lv_n) TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.
      lv_n = CONV p( <s> ).

      IF lv_n = 0.
        lv_has_zero = abap_true.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_n < 0.
        lv_sign_prod = lv_sign_prod * -1.
        lv_sum_mag = lv_sum_mag + ( lv_n * -1 ).
      ELSE.
        lv_sum_mag = lv_sum_mag + lv_n.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA(lv_result) TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.
    IF lv_has_zero = abap_true.
      lv_result = 0.
    ELSE.
      lv_result = lv_sum_mag * lv_sign_prod.
    ENDIF.

    rv_result = |{ lv_result }|.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs
      IMPORTING
        arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE REF TO data.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.
    IF lines( arr ) = 0.
      result = REF #( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA: sum_abs      TYPE i VALUE 0,
          sign_product TYPE i VALUE 1,
          n            TYPE syindex,
          abs_n        TYPE i,
          final_value  TYPE i.

    LOOP AT arr INTO n.
      IF n = 0.
        sign_product = 0.
      ELSEIF n < 0.
        sign_product = sign_product * -1.
      ENDIF.

      abs_n = n.
      IF abs_n < 0.
        abs_n = abs_n * -1.
      ENDIF.
      sum_abs = sum_abs + abs_n.
    ENDLOOP.

    final_value = sum_abs * sign_product.

    CREATE DATA result TYPE i.
    DATA lr_any TYPE REF TO data.
    lr_any = result.
    ASSIGN lr_any->* TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<r>).
    <r> = final_value.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES tt_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE tt_arr
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rr_result) TYPE REF TO i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.
    DATA lv_sum_abs   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sign_prod TYPE i.
    DATA lv_val       TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sign      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_out       TYPE i.

    READ TABLE it_arr INDEX 1 TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rr_result = REF #( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_sum_abs = 0.
    lv_sign_prod = 1.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_val.
      IF lv_val = 0.
        lv_sign = 0.
      ELSEIF lv_val > 0.
        lv_sign = 1.
      ELSE.
        lv_sign = -1.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sign_prod = lv_sign_prod * lv_sign.
      lv_sum_abs = lv_sum_abs + abs( lv_val ).
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_out = lv_sum_abs * lv_sign_prod.

    GET REFERENCE OF lv_out INTO rr_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS prod_signs
      IMPORTING
        arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE REF TO data.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_signs IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD prod_signs.
    DATA sum_abs   TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.
    DATA sign_prod TYPE i.
    DATA n         TYPE i.
    DATA val       TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.

    IF arr[] IS INITIAL.
      result = REF #( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    CLEAR sum_abs.
    sign_prod = 1.

    LOOP AT arr INTO n.
      sum_abs = sum_abs + abs( n ).

      IF n = 0.
        sign_prod = 0.
      ELSEIF n < 0.
        sign_prod = sign_prod * -1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    val = sum_abs * sign_prod.
    GET REFERENCE OF val INTO result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_row     TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_grid    TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_row WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_path) TYPE ty_int_tab.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD min_path.
    rt_path = VALUE ty_int_tab( ).
    IF k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_grid TYPE ty_grid.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <in_grid> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <in_row>  TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <cell>    TYPE any.

    ASSIGN grid TO <in_grid>.
    IF <in_grid> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR lines( <in_grid> ) = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <in_grid> ASSIGNING <in_row>.
      DATA(lt_row) = VALUE ty_row( ).
      LOOP AT <in_row> ASSIGNING <cell>.
        DATA(lv_i) = 0.
        TRY.
            lv_i = CONV i( <cell> ).
          CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
            lv_i = 0.
        ENDTRY.
        APPEND lv_i TO lt_row.
      ENDLOOP.
      APPEND lt_row TO lt_grid.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA n_rows TYPE i.
    n_rows = lines( lt_grid ).
    IF n_rows = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA n_cols TYPE i.
    READ TABLE lt_grid INDEX 1 INTO lt_row.
    n_cols = lines( lt_row ).
    IF n_cols = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA best_start_val TYPE i VALUE 2147483647.
    DATA best_r TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA best_c TYPE i VALUE 1.

    DATA r TYPE i.
    DATA c TYPE i.
    DATA row TYPE ty_row.
    DATA val TYPE i.

    r = 1.
    LOOP AT lt_grid INTO row.
      c = 1.
      LOOP AT row INTO val.
        IF val < best_start_val.
          best_start_val = val.
          best_r = r.
          best_c = c.
        ENDIF.
        c += 1.
      ENDLOOP.
      r += 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA cur_r TYPE i.
    DATA cur_c TYPE i.
    cur_r = best_r.
    cur_c = best_c.

    DO k TIMES.
      READ TABLE lt_grid INDEX cur_r INTO row.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE row INDEX cur_c INTO val.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND val TO rt_path.

      IF sy-index = k.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      DATA next_r TYPE i VALUE 0.
      DATA next_c TYPE i VALUE 0.
      DATA next_val TYPE i VALUE 2147483647.

      DATA cand_r TYPE i.
      DATA cand_c TYPE i.
      DATA cand_val TYPE i.
      DATA cand_row TYPE ty_row.

      cand_r = cur_r - 1.
      cand_c = cur_c.
      IF cand_r >= 1.
        READ TABLE lt_grid INDEX cand_r INTO cand_row.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE cand_row INDEX cand_c INTO cand_val.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND cand_val < next_val.
            next_val = cand_val.
            next_r = cand_r.
            next_c = cand_c.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cand_r = cur_r + 1.
      cand_c = cur_c.
      IF cand_r <= n_rows.
        READ TABLE lt_grid INDEX cand_r INTO cand_row.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE cand_row INDEX cand_c INTO cand_val.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND cand_val < next_val.
            next_val = cand_val.
            next_r = cand_r.
            next_c = cand_c.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cand_r = cur_r.
      cand_c = cur_c - 1.
      IF cand_c >= 1.
        READ TABLE lt_grid INDEX cand_r INTO cand_row.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE cand_row INDEX cand_c INTO cand_val.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND cand_val < next_val.
            next_val = cand_val.
            next_r = cand_r.
            next_c = cand_c.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cand_r = cur_r.
      cand_c = cur_c + 1.
      IF cand_c <= n_cols.
        READ TABLE lt_grid INDEX cand_r INTO cand_row.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE cand_row INDEX cand_c INTO cand_val.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND cand_val < next_val.
            next_val = cand_val.
            next_r = cand_r.
            next_c = cand_c.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      IF next_r = 0 OR next_c = 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      cur_r = next_r.
      cur_c = next_c.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE ANY TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_values) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_path.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_pos,
             r TYPE i,
             c TYPE i,
           END OF ty_pos.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <row>  TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <val>  TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_n          TYPE i,
          lv_r          TYPE i,
          lv_c          TYPE i,
          lv_min_val    TYPE i,
          ls_min_pos    TYPE ty_pos,
          lv_start_val  TYPE i,
          lv_start_r    TYPE i,
          lv_start_c    TYPE i,
          lv_curr_r     TYPE i,
          lv_curr_c     TYPE i,
          lv_rem        TYPE i,
          lv_best_val   TYPE i,
          ls_best_pos   TYPE ty_pos,
          lv_dr         TYPE i,
          lv_dc         TYPE i,
          lv_nr         TYPE i,
          lv_nc         TYPE i,
          lv_d          TYPE i,
          lv_min_dist   TYPE i,
          lv_next_to_st TYPE abap_bool.

    CLEAR rt_values.

    IF k < 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    ASSIGN grid TO <grid>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_n = lines( <grid> ).
    IF lv_n < 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_min_val = 2147483647.
    ls_min_pos-r = 1.
    ls_min_pos-c = 1.

    lv_r = 0.
    LOOP AT <grid> ASSIGNING <row>.
      lv_r = lv_r + 1.
      lv_c = 0.
      LOOP AT <row> ASSIGNING <val>.
        lv_c = lv_c + 1.
        IF CONV i( <val> ) < lv_min_val.
          lv_min_val = CONV i( <val> ).
          ls_min_pos-r = lv_r.
          ls_min_pos-c = lv_c.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_start_val = lv_min_val.
    lv_start_r   = ls_min_pos-r.
    lv_start_c   = ls_min_pos-c.

    APPEND lv_start_val TO rt_values.

    IF k = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_curr_r = lv_start_r.
    lv_curr_c = lv_start_c.
    lv_rem    = k - 1.

    WHILE lv_rem > 0.

      lv_next_to_st = abap_false.
      IF ( abs( lv_curr_r - lv_start_r ) + abs( lv_curr_c - lv_start_c ) ) = 1.
        lv_next_to_st = abap_true.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_next_to_st = abap_true.
        APPEND lv_start_val TO rt_values.
        lv_curr_r = lv_start_r.
        lv_curr_c = lv_start_c.
        lv_rem = lv_rem - 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_best_val = 2147483647.
      ls_best_pos-r = lv_curr_r.
      ls_best_pos-c = lv_curr_c.

      DO 4 TIMES.
        CASE sy-index.
          WHEN 1.
            lv_dr = -1. lv_dc = 0.
          WHEN 2.
            lv_dr = 1.  lv_dc = 0.
          WHEN 3.
            lv_dr = 0.  lv_dc = -1.
          WHEN 4.
            lv_dr = 0.  lv_dc = 1.
        ENDCASE.

        lv_nr = lv_curr_r + lv_dr.
        lv_nc = lv_curr_c + lv_dc.

        IF lv_nr < 1 OR lv_nr > lv_n.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE <grid> INDEX lv_nr ASSIGNING <row>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_nc < 1 OR lv_nc > lines( <row> ).
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE <row> INDEX lv_nc ASSIGNING <val>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        lv_d = abs( lv_nr - lv_start_r ) + abs( lv_nc - lv_start_c ).

        lv_min_dist = 0.
        IF lv_rem > 1 AND lv_d > 0.
          lv_min_dist = lv_d - 1.
          IF lv_min_dist < 0.
            lv_min_dist = 0.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_rem - 1 < lv_min_dist.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        IF CONV i( <val> ) < lv_best_val.
          lv_best_val = CONV i( <val> ).
          ls_best_pos-r = lv_nr.
          ls_best_pos-c = lv_nc.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      APPEND lv_best_val TO rt_values.
      lv_curr_r = ls_best_pos-r.
      lv_curr_c = ls_best_pos-c.
      lv_rem = lv_rem - 1.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_path) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_path.
    rt_path = VALUE #( ).
    IF k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <row>  TYPE any,
                   <cell> TYPE any.

    DATA n_rows TYPE i.
    n_rows = lines( grid ).
    IF n_rows <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA n_cols TYPE i VALUE 0.
    READ TABLE grid ASSIGNING <row> INDEX 1.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <row> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT n_cols + 1 OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      n_cols = n_cols + 1.
    ENDDO.

    IF n_cols <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA min_val TYPE i VALUE 2147483647.
    DATA start_r TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA start_c TYPE i VALUE 1.

    DATA r TYPE i.
    DATA c TYPE i.
    DATA v TYPE i.

    r = 0.
    LOOP AT grid ASSIGNING <row>.
      r = r + 1.
      c = 0.
      DO n_cols TIMES.
        c = c + 1.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT c OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
        TRY.
            v = <cell>.
          CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
            CONTINUE.
        ENDTRY.
        IF v < min_val.
          min_val = v.
          start_r = r.
          start_c = c.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA cur_r TYPE i.
    DATA cur_c TYPE i.
    cur_r = start_r.
    cur_c = start_c.

    READ TABLE grid ASSIGNING <row> INDEX cur_r.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <row> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT cur_c OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <cell> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    TRY.
        v = <cell>.
      CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.
    APPEND v TO rt_path.

    IF k = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA best_next_val TYPE i.
    DATA best_next_r   TYPE i.
    DATA best_next_c   TYPE i.
    DATA cand_val      TYPE i.
    DATA cand_r        TYPE i.
    DATA cand_c        TYPE i.

    DO k - 1 TIMES.
      best_next_val = 2147483647.
      best_next_r = cur_r.
      best_next_c = cur_c.

      cand_r = cur_r - 1.
      cand_c = cur_c.
      IF cand_r BETWEEN 1 AND n_rows AND cand_c BETWEEN 1 AND n_cols.
        READ TABLE grid ASSIGNING <row> INDEX cand_r.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <row> IS ASSIGNED.
          ASSIGN COMPONENT cand_c OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <cell> IS ASSIGNED.
            TRY.
                cand_val = <cell>.
              CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
                cand_val = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF cand_val < best_next_val.
              best_next_val = cand_val.
              best_next_r = cand_r.
              best_next_c = cand_c.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cand_r = cur_r + 1.
      cand_c = cur_c.
      IF cand_r BETWEEN 1 AND n_rows AND cand_c BETWEEN 1 AND n_cols.
        READ TABLE grid ASSIGNING <row> INDEX cand_r.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <row> IS ASSIGNED.
          ASSIGN COMPONENT cand_c OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <cell> IS ASSIGNED.
            TRY.
                cand_val = <cell>.
              CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
                cand_val = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF cand_val < best_next_val.
              best_next_val = cand_val.
              best_next_r = cand_r.
              best_next_c = cand_c.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cand_r = cur_r.
      cand_c = cur_c - 1.
      IF cand_r BETWEEN 1 AND n_rows AND cand_c BETWEEN 1 AND n_cols.
        READ TABLE grid ASSIGNING <row> INDEX cand_r.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <row> IS ASSIGNED.
          ASSIGN COMPONENT cand_c OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <cell> IS ASSIGNED.
            TRY.
                cand_val = <cell>.
              CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
                cand_val = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF cand_val < best_next_val.
              best_next_val = cand_val.
              best_next_r = cand_r.
              best_next_c = cand_c.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cand_r = cur_r.
      cand_c = cur_c + 1.
      IF cand_r BETWEEN 1 AND n_rows AND cand_c BETWEEN 1 AND n_cols.
        READ TABLE grid ASSIGNING <row> INDEX cand_r.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <row> IS ASSIGNED.
          ASSIGN COMPONENT cand_c OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <cell> IS ASSIGNED.
            TRY.
                cand_val = <cell>.
              CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
                cand_val = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF cand_val < best_next_val.
              best_next_val = cand_val.
              best_next_r = cand_r.
              best_next_c = cand_c.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cur_r = best_next_r.
      cur_c = best_next_c.
      APPEND best_next_val TO rt_path.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid   TYPE any TABLE
        k      TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_result.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_cell,
             val TYPE i,
           END OF ty_cell.
    TYPES ty_cells TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_cell WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_key,
             pos_id TYPE i,
             rem    TYPE i,
           END OF ty_key.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_dp,
             pos_id TYPE i,
             rem    TYPE i,
             nxt_id TYPE i,
           END OF ty_dp.
    TYPES ty_dp_tab TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_dp WITH UNIQUE KEY pos_id rem.

    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_nei_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int_tab WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS read_grid_dim
      IMPORTING grid_any TYPE any TABLE
      RETURNING VALUE(n) TYPE i.

    CLASS-METHODS build_cells_from_any
      IMPORTING
        grid_any TYPE any TABLE
        n        TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(cells) TYPE ty_cells.

    CLASS-METHODS get_neighbors
      IMPORTING n TYPE i
      RETURNING VALUE(nei) TYPE ty_nei_tab.

    CLASS-METHODS compute_dp
      IMPORTING
        n     TYPE i
        cells TYPE ty_cells
        nei   TYPE ty_nei_tab
        k     TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(dp) TYPE ty_dp_tab.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD read_grid_dim.
    n = lines( grid_any ).
    IF n < 1.
      n = 0.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD build_cells_from_any.
    cells = VALUE #( ).
    IF n <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <row_any> TYPE any,
                   <row_tab> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <v_any>   TYPE any.

    LOOP AT grid_any ASSIGNING <row_any>.
      ASSIGN <row_any> TO <row_tab>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR cells.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA row_len TYPE i.
      row_len = lines( <row_tab> ).
      IF row_len <> n.
        CLEAR cells.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT <row_tab> ASSIGNING <v_any>.
        TRY.
            APPEND VALUE ty_cell( val = CONV i( <v_any> ) ) TO cells.
          CATCH cx_root.
            CLEAR cells.
            RETURN.
        ENDTRY.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD get_neighbors.
    nei = VALUE #( ).
    DATA total TYPE i.
    total = n * n.

    DO total TIMES.
      APPEND VALUE ty_int_tab( ) TO nei.
    ENDDO.

    DATA r TYPE i.
    DATA c TYPE i.
    DATA id TYPE i.

    r = 1.
    WHILE r <= n.
      c = 1.
      WHILE c <= n.
        id = ( r - 1 ) * n + c.
        READ TABLE nei INDEX id ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<list>).
        CLEAR <list>.
        IF r > 1.
          APPEND ( ( r - 2 ) * n + c ) TO <list>.
        ENDIF.
        IF r < n.
          APPEND ( r * n + c ) TO <list>.
        ENDIF.
        IF c > 1.
          APPEND ( ( r - 1 ) * n + ( c - 1 ) ) TO <list>.
        ENDIF.
        IF c < n.
          APPEND ( ( r - 1 ) * n + ( c + 1 ) ) TO <list>.
        ENDIF.
        c += 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      r += 1.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD compute_dp.
    dp = VALUE #( ).
    IF k <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA total TYPE i.
    total = n * n.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_best,
             nxt_id TYPE i,
             val    TYPE i,
           END OF ty_best.
    TYPES ty_best_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_best WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA rem TYPE i.
    rem = 1.
    WHILE rem <= k - 1.
      DATA best_next TYPE ty_best_tab.
      best_next = VALUE #( FOR i = 1 WHILE i <= total ( nxt_id = 0 val = 2147483647 ) ).

      DATA u TYPE i VALUE 1.
      WHILE u <= total.
        READ TABLE nei INDEX u ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<nei_u>).
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <nei_u> IS NOT INITIAL.
          LOOP AT <nei_u> INTO DATA(v).
            READ TABLE cells INDEX v INTO DATA(cell_v).
            READ TABLE best_next INDEX u INTO DATA(best_u).

            IF cell_v-val < best_u-val.
              best_u-val = cell_v-val.
              best_u-nxt_id = v.
              MODIFY best_next FROM best_u INDEX u.
            ELSEIF cell_v-val = best_u-val AND best_u-nxt_id <> 0.
              DATA take_v TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
              IF rem = 1.
                IF v < best_u-nxt_id.
                  take_v = abap_true.
                ENDIF.
              ELSE.
                DATA e_old TYPE ty_dp.
                DATA e_new TYPE ty_dp.
                READ TABLE dp WITH TABLE KEY pos_id = best_u-nxt_id rem = rem - 1 INTO e_old.
                READ TABLE dp WITH TABLE KEY pos_id = v              rem = rem - 1 INTO e_new.
                IF sy-subrc = 0.
                  IF e_new-nxt_id < e_old-nxt_id.
                    take_v = abap_true.
                  ENDIF.
                ENDIF.
              ENDIF.
              IF take_v = abap_true.
                best_u-nxt_id = v.
                MODIFY best_next FROM best_u INDEX u.
              ENDIF.
            ENDIF.
          ENDLOOP.
        ENDIF.
        u += 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      u = 1.
      WHILE u <= total.
        READ TABLE best_next INDEX u INTO DATA(b).
        INSERT VALUE ty_dp( pos_id = u rem = rem nxt_id = b-nxt_id ) INTO TABLE dp.
        u += 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      rem += 1.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD min_path.
    result = VALUE #( ).

    IF k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA n TYPE i.
    n = read_grid_dim( grid ).
    IF n < 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA total TYPE i.
    total = n * n.
    IF total <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA cells TYPE ty_cells.
    cells = build_cells_from_any( grid_any = grid n = n ).
    IF lines( cells ) <> total.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA start_id TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA min_val TYPE i VALUE 2147483647.
    DO total TIMES.
      READ TABLE cells INDEX sy-index INTO DATA(cell).
      IF cell-val < min_val.
        min_val = cell-val.
        start_id = sy-index.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    DATA nei TYPE ty_nei_tab.
    nei = get_neighbors( n ).

    DATA dp TYPE ty_dp_tab.
    dp = compute_dp( n = n cells = cells nei = nei k = k ).

    DATA cur TYPE i.
    cur = start_id.

    DO k TIMES.
      READ TABLE cells INDEX cur INTO cell.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CLEAR result.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      APPEND cell-val TO result.

      IF sy-index = k.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      DATA e TYPE ty_dp.
      READ TABLE dp WITH TABLE KEY pos_id = cur rem = ( k - sy-index ) INTO e.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR e-nxt_id <= 0.
        CLEAR result.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      cur = e-nxt_id.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path_grid DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_path TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE ANY TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_path) TYPE ty_path.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path_grid IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_path.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_cell,
             r TYPE i,
             c TYPE i,
             v TYPE i,
           END OF ty_cell.
    TYPES ty_cells TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_cell WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_idx_set TYPE SORTED TABLE OF i WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    DATA lv_n     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_total TYPE i.

    DATA lt_cells TYPE ty_cells.
    DATA ls_cell  TYPE ty_cell.

    DATA lt_reach TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF abap_bool WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_next  TYPE ty_idx_set.
    DATA lt_new_front TYPE ty_idx_set.

    DATA lv_r   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <row_any> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <row_tab> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <val>     TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <b>       TYPE abap_bool.

    CLEAR rt_path.

    lv_n = lines( grid ).
    IF lv_n < 1 OR k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT grid ASSIGNING <row_any>.
      ASSIGN <row_any> TO <row_tab> CASTING.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF lines( <row_tab> ) <> lv_n.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_total = lv_n * lv_n.

    DO lv_n TIMES.
      lv_r = sy-index.
      READ TABLE grid INDEX lv_r ASSIGNING <row_any>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN <row_any> TO <row_tab> CASTING.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DO lv_n TIMES.
        lv_c = sy-index.
        READ TABLE <row_tab> INDEX lv_c ASSIGNING <val>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        ls_cell-r = lv_r.
        ls_cell-c = lv_c.
        ls_cell-v = CONV i( <val> ).
        APPEND ls_cell TO lt_cells.
      ENDDO.
    ENDDO.

    SORT lt_cells BY v ASCENDING.
    READ TABLE lt_cells INDEX 1 INTO ls_cell.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    APPEND ls_cell-v TO rt_path.
    IF k = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    CLEAR lt_reach.
    DO lv_total TIMES.
      APPEND abap_false TO lt_reach.
    ENDDO.

    lv_idx = ( ls_cell-r - 1 ) * lv_n + ls_cell-c.
    READ TABLE lt_reach INDEX lv_idx ASSIGNING <b>.
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      <b> = abap_true.
    ENDIF.

    DO k - 1 TIMES.
      CLEAR lt_next.

      DO lv_total TIMES.
        lv_idx = sy-index.
        READ TABLE lt_reach INDEX lv_idx ASSIGNING <b>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <b> <> abap_true.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        lv_r = ( lv_idx - 1 ) DIV lv_n + 1.
        lv_c = ( lv_idx - 1 ) MOD lv_n + 1.

        IF lv_r > 1.
          INSERT ( ( lv_r - 2 ) * lv_n + lv_c ) INTO TABLE lt_next.
        ENDIF.
        IF lv_r < lv_n.
          INSERT ( lv_r * lv_n + lv_c ) INTO TABLE lt_next.
        ENDIF.
        IF lv_c > 1.
          INSERT ( ( lv_r - 1 ) * lv_n + ( lv_c - 1 ) ) INTO TABLE lt_next.
        ENDIF.
        IF lv_c < lv_n.
          INSERT ( ( lv_r - 1 ) * lv_n + ( lv_c + 1 ) ) INTO TABLE lt_next.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      DATA(lv_pick_val) = 0.
      DATA(lv_pick_idx) = 0.

      LOOP AT lt_cells INTO ls_cell.
        lv_pick_idx = ( ls_cell-r - 1 ) * lv_n + ls_cell-c.
        READ TABLE lt_next WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_pick_idx TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          lv_pick_val = ls_cell-v.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      APPEND lv_pick_val TO rt_path.

      CLEAR lt_new_front.
      LOOP AT lt_next INTO lv_idx.
        lv_r = ( lv_idx - 1 ) DIV lv_n + 1.
        lv_c = ( lv_idx - 1 ) MOD lv_n + 1.

        READ TABLE grid INDEX lv_r ASSIGNING <row_any>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        ASSIGN <row_any> TO <row_tab> CASTING.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE <row_tab> INDEX lv_c ASSIGNING <val>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND CONV i( <val> ) = lv_pick_val.
          INSERT lv_idx INTO TABLE lt_new_front.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      CLEAR lt_reach.
      DO lv_total TIMES.
        APPEND abap_false TO lt_reach.
      ENDDO.

      LOOP AT lt_new_front INTO lv_idx.
        READ TABLE lt_reach INDEX lv_idx ASSIGNING <b>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          <b> = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE ANY TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_result.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD min_path.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <row>  TYPE any,
                   <v>    TYPE any.

    ASSIGN grid TO <grid>.
    IF <grid> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA n TYPE i.
    n = lines( <grid> ).
    IF n <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA row_len TYPE i VALUE 0.

    READ TABLE <grid> ASSIGNING <row> INDEX 1.
    IF <row> IS ASSIGNED.
      TRY.
          row_len = lines( <row> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_itab_line_not_found cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_ref_is_initial cx_sy_dyn_call_illegal_type.
          row_len = 0.
      ENDTRY.
    ENDIF.

    IF row_len <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA: min_val TYPE i VALUE 2147483647,
          min_r   TYPE i VALUE 1,
          min_c   TYPE i VALUE 1.

    DATA r TYPE i.
    DATA c TYPE i.

    r = 0.
    LOOP AT <grid> ASSIGNING <row>.
      r = r + 1.
      DATA col_tab_ref TYPE REF TO data.
      GET REFERENCE OF <row> INTO col_tab_ref.
      ASSIGN col_tab_ref->* TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<col_tab>) TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
      IF <col_tab> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      c = 0.
      LOOP AT <col_tab> ASSIGNING <v>.
        c = c + 1.
        DATA cell_val TYPE i.
        TRY.
            cell_val = CONV i( <v> ).
          CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow cx_sy_move_cast_error.
            RETURN.
        ENDTRY.
        IF cell_val < min_val.
          min_val = cell_val.
          min_r = r.
          min_c = c.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDLOOP.

    APPEND min_val TO result.
    IF k = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA curr_r TYPE i.
    DATA curr_c TYPE i.
    curr_r = min_r.
    curr_c = min_c.

    DO k - 1 TIMES.
      DATA best_val TYPE i VALUE 2147483647.
      DATA best_r   TYPE i VALUE 0.
      DATA best_c   TYPE i VALUE 0.

      DATA try_r TYPE i.
      DATA try_c TYPE i.

      DO 4 TIMES.
        CASE sy-index.
          WHEN 1.
            try_r = curr_r - 1.
            try_c = curr_c.
          WHEN 2.
            try_r = curr_r + 1.
            try_c = curr_c.
          WHEN 3.
            try_r = curr_r.
            try_c = curr_c - 1.
          WHEN 4.
            try_r = curr_r.
            try_c = curr_c + 1.
        ENDCASE.

        IF try_r BETWEEN 1 AND n AND try_c BETWEEN 1 AND row_len.
          READ TABLE <grid> ASSIGNING <row> INDEX try_r.
          IF <row> IS ASSIGNED.
            DATA col_tab_ref2 TYPE REF TO data.
            GET REFERENCE OF <row> INTO col_tab_ref2.
            ASSIGN col_tab_ref2->* TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<col_tab2>) TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
            IF <col_tab2> IS ASSIGNED.
              READ TABLE <col_tab2> ASSIGNING <v> INDEX try_c.
              IF <v> IS ASSIGNED.
                DATA nval TYPE i.
                TRY.
                    nval = CONV i( <v> ).
                  CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow cx_sy_move_cast_error.
                    CONTINUE.
                ENDTRY.

                IF best_r = 0 OR nval < best_val.
                  best_val = nval.
                  best_r = try_r.
                  best_c = try_c.
                ENDIF.
              ENDIF.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      IF best_r = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND best_val TO result.
      curr_r = best_r.
      curr_c = best_c.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE ANY TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_path.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <row>  TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <cell> TYPE any.

    ASSIGN grid TO <grid>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA n TYPE i.
    n = lines( <grid> ).
    IF n <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA total TYPE i.
    total = n * n.

    DATA: lt_pos_r TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY,
          lt_pos_c TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DO total TIMES.
      APPEND 0 TO lt_pos_r.
      APPEND 0 TO lt_pos_c.
    ENDDO.

    DATA r TYPE i.
    DATA c TYPE i.
    DATA v TYPE i.

    r = 1.
    LOOP AT <grid> ASSIGNING <row>.
      c = 1.
      LOOP AT <row> ASSIGNING <cell>.
        TRY.
            v = CONV i( <cell> ).
          CATCH cx_root.
            v = 0.
        ENDTRY.
        IF v >= 1 AND v <= total.
          lt_pos_r[ v ] = r.
          lt_pos_c[ v ] = c.
        ENDIF.
        c += 1.
      ENDLOOP.
      r += 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA start_val TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA cur_r TYPE i.
    DATA cur_c TYPE i.
    cur_r = lt_pos_r[ start_val ].
    cur_c = lt_pos_c[ start_val ].

    IF cur_r <= 0 OR cur_c <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    APPEND start_val TO result.
    IF k = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA: best_val TYPE i,
          best_r   TYPE i,
          best_c   TYPE i,
          nr       TYPE i,
          nc       TYPE i.

    DATA steps TYPE i.
    steps = k - 1.

    DO steps TIMES.
      best_val = 2147483647.
      best_r = 0.
      best_c = 0.

      nr = cur_r - 1. nc = cur_c.
      IF nr >= 1 AND nr <= n AND nc >= 1.
        ASSIGN <grid>[ nr ] TO <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND nc <= lines( <row> ).
          ASSIGN <row>[ nc ] TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            TRY.
                v = CONV i( <cell> ).
              CATCH cx_root.
                v = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF v < best_val.
              best_val = v. best_r = nr. best_c = nc.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      nr = cur_r + 1. nc = cur_c.
      IF nr >= 1 AND nr <= n AND nc >= 1.
        ASSIGN <grid>[ nr ] TO <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND nc <= lines( <row> ).
          ASSIGN <row>[ nc ] TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            TRY.
                v = CONV i( <cell> ).
              CATCH cx_root.
                v = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF v < best_val.
              best_val = v. best_r = nr. best_c = nc.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      nr = cur_r. nc = cur_c - 1.
      IF nr >= 1 AND nr <= n AND nc >= 1.
        ASSIGN <grid>[ nr ] TO <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND nc <= lines( <row> ).
          ASSIGN <row>[ nc ] TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            TRY.
                v = CONV i( <cell> ).
              CATCH cx_root.
                v = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF v < best_val.
              best_val = v. best_r = nr. best_c = nc.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      nr = cur_r. nc = cur_c + 1.
      IF nr >= 1 AND nr <= n AND nc >= 1.
        ASSIGN <grid>[ nr ] TO <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND nc <= lines( <row> ).
          ASSIGN <row>[ nc ] TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            TRY.
                v = CONV i( <cell> ).
              CATCH cx_root.
                v = 2147483647.
            ENDTRY.
            IF v < best_val.
              best_val = v. best_r = nr. best_c = nc.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      IF best_r = 0 OR best_c = 0 OR best_val = 2147483647.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND best_val TO result.
      cur_r = best_r.
      cur_c = best_c.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_path TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE ANY TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_path) TYPE ty_path.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD min_path.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_cell,
             r   TYPE i,
             c   TYPE i,
             val TYPE i,
           END OF ty_cell.
    TYPES ty_cells TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_cell WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_pos,
             r TYPE i,
             c TYPE i,
           END OF ty_pos.
    TYPES ty_pos_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_pos WITH EMPTY KEY.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <row>  TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <cell> TYPE any.

    ASSIGN grid TO <grid>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_n) = lines( <grid> ).
    IF lv_n <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_cells TYPE ty_cells.

    DO lv_n TIMES.
      DATA(lv_r) = sy-index.
      READ TABLE <grid> INDEX lv_r ASSIGNING <row>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_m) = lines( <row> ).
      DO lv_m TIMES.
        DATA(lv_c) = sy-index.
        READ TABLE <row> INDEX lv_c ASSIGNING <cell>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.
        APPEND VALUE ty_cell(
                 r   = lv_r
                 c   = lv_c
                 val = CONV i( <cell> ) ) TO lt_cells.
      ENDDO.
    ENDDO.

    IF lt_cells IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SORT lt_cells BY val ASCENDING.

    DATA(ls_start) = lt_cells[ 1 ].

    DATA lt_best_path TYPE ty_path.
    DATA lt_curr_path TYPE ty_path.

    DATA ls_cur TYPE ty_cell.
    ls_cur = ls_start.
    APPEND ls_cur-val TO lt_curr_path.

    IF k = 1.
      rt_path = lt_curr_path.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO k - 1 TIMES.
      DATA lt_nb TYPE ty_pos_tab.
      CLEAR lt_nb.

      IF ls_cur-r > 1.
        APPEND VALUE ty_pos( r = ls_cur-r - 1 c = ls_cur-c ) TO lt_nb.
      ENDIF.
      IF ls_cur-r < lv_n.
        APPEND VALUE ty_pos( r = ls_cur-r + 1 c = ls_cur-c ) TO lt_nb.
      ENDIF.
      IF ls_cur-c > 1.
        APPEND VALUE ty_pos( r = ls_cur-r c = ls_cur-c - 1 ) TO lt_nb.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE <grid> INDEX ls_cur-r ASSIGNING <row>.
      DATA(lv_cur_m) = 0.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_cur_m = lines( <row> ).
      ENDIF.
      IF ls_cur-c < lv_cur_m.
        APPEND VALUE ty_pos( r = ls_cur-r c = ls_cur-c + 1 ) TO lt_nb.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lv_min_val TYPE i VALUE 2147483647.
      DATA ls_min_pos TYPE ty_pos.
      DATA lv_found   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

      LOOP AT lt_nb INTO DATA(ls_nb).
        READ TABLE <grid> INDEX ls_nb-r ASSIGNING <row>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.
        READ TABLE <row> INDEX ls_nb-c ASSIGNING <cell>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lv_val) = CONV i( <cell> ).
        IF lv_val < lv_min_val.
          lv_min_val = lv_val.
          ls_min_pos = ls_nb.
          lv_found = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF lv_found = abap_false.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND lv_min_val TO lt_curr_path.
      ls_cur-r = ls_min_pos-r.
      ls_cur-c = ls_min_pos-c.
      ls_cur-val = lv_min_val.
    ENDDO.

    rt_path = lt_curr_path.

  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_path TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS min_path
      IMPORTING
        grid TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        k    TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_path) TYPE ty_path.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_min_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD min_path.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <row>  TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <cell> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ival> TYPE i.

    DATA: n        TYPE i,
          m        TYPE i,
          r        TYPE i,
          c        TYPE i,
          nr       TYPE i,
          nc       TYPE i,
          min_val  TYPE i,
          min_r    TYPE i,
          min_c    TYPE i,
          cur_r    TYPE i,
          cur_c    TYPE i,
          cur_val  TYPE i,
          best_val TYPE i,
          best_r   TYPE i,
          best_c   TYPE i,
          v        TYPE i.

    rt_path = VALUE #( ).

    IF k <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    ASSIGN grid TO <grid>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    n = lines( <grid> ).
    IF n <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE <grid> INDEX 1 ASSIGNING <row>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    m = lines( <row> ).
    IF m <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    min_val = 2147483647.
    min_r = 1.
    min_c = 1.

    DO n TIMES.
      r = sy-index.
      READ TABLE <grid> INDEX r ASSIGNING <row>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DO m TIMES.
        c = sy-index.
        READ TABLE <row> INDEX c ASSIGNING <cell>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        ASSIGN <cell> TO <ival> CASTING.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        v = <ival>.
        IF v < min_val.
          min_val = v.
          min_r = r.
          min_c = c.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.
    ENDDO.

    cur_r = min_r.
    cur_c = min_c.
    cur_val = min_val.

    APPEND cur_val TO rt_path.
    IF k = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO ( k - 1 ) TIMES.
      best_val = 2147483647.
      best_r = cur_r.
      best_c = cur_c.

      nr = cur_r - 1.
      nc = cur_c.
      IF nr >= 1.
        READ TABLE <grid> INDEX nr ASSIGNING <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE <row> INDEX nc ASSIGNING <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            ASSIGN <cell> TO <ival> CASTING.
            IF sy-subrc = 0.
              v = <ival>.
              IF v < best_val.
                best_val = v.
                best_r = nr.
                best_c = nc.
              ENDIF.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      nr = cur_r + 1.
      nc = cur_c.
      IF nr <= n.
        READ TABLE <grid> INDEX nr ASSIGNING <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE <row> INDEX nc ASSIGNING <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            ASSIGN <cell> TO <ival> CASTING.
            IF sy-subrc = 0.
              v = <ival>.
              IF v < best_val.
                best_val = v.
                best_r = nr.
                best_c = nc.
              ENDIF.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      nr = cur_r.
      nc = cur_c - 1.
      IF nc >= 1.
        READ TABLE <grid> INDEX nr ASSIGNING <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE <row> INDEX nc ASSIGNING <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            ASSIGN <cell> TO <ival> CASTING.
            IF sy-subrc = 0.
              v = <ival>.
              IF v < best_val.
                best_val = v.
                best_r = nr.
                best_c = nc.
              ENDIF.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      nr = cur_r.
      nc = cur_c + 1.
      IF nc <= m.
        READ TABLE <grid> INDEX nr ASSIGNING <row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          READ TABLE <row> INDEX nc ASSIGNING <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            ASSIGN <cell> TO <ival> CASTING.
            IF sy-subrc = 0.
              v = <ival>.
              IF v < best_val.
                best_val = v.
                best_r = nr.
                best_c = nc.
              ENDIF.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      cur_r = best_r.
      cur_c = best_c.
      cur_val = best_val.
      APPEND cur_val TO rt_path.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid          TYPE any TABLE
        capacity      TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <row_any> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <cell>    TYPE any.

    DATA: sum_row TYPE i,
          need    TYPE i.

    DATA lr_tabdescr TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.

    result = 0.

    IF capacity <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TRY.
        lr_tabdescr ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( grid ).
      CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_descr_no_object.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    LOOP AT grid ASSIGNING <row_any>.
      sum_row = 0.

      IF <row_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          DATA(lr_row_descr) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <row_any> ).
          IF lr_row_descr->kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>kind_table.
            CONTINUE.
          ENDIF.
        CATCH cx_sy_descr_no_object.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      ASSIGN <row_any> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<row_tab>) CASTING TYPE any TABLE.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT <row_tab> ASSIGNING <cell>.
        IF <cell> IS NOT INITIAL.
          sum_row = sum_row + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF sum_row > 0.
        need = ( sum_row + capacity - 1 ) DIV capacity.
        result = result + need.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC .

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE any
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    rv_count = 0.

    DATA(lv_cap) = capacity.
    IF lv_cap <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TRY.
        DATA(lo_grid_descr) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( grid ).
        IF lo_grid_descr IS INITIAL OR lo_grid_descr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_table.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lo_grid_tab) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( lo_grid_descr ).
        DATA(lo_row_descr) = lo_grid_tab->get_table_line_type( ).
        IF lo_row_descr IS INITIAL OR lo_row_descr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_table.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lo_row_tab) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( lo_row_descr ).

        DATA lr_grid TYPE REF TO data.
        GET REFERENCE OF grid INTO lr_grid.

        FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                       <row>  TYPE ANY TABLE,
                       <cell> TYPE any.

        ASSIGN lr_grid->* TO <grid>.
        IF <grid> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        LOOP AT <grid> ASSIGNING <row>.
          DATA(lv_units) = 0.

          LOOP AT <row> ASSIGNING <cell>.
            IF <cell> IS NOT INITIAL AND <cell> <> 0.
              lv_units = lv_units + 1.
            ENDIF.
          ENDLOOP.

          IF lv_units > 0.
            rv_count = rv_count + ( ( lv_units + lv_cap - 1 ) / lv_cap ).
          ENDIF.
        ENDLOOP.

      CATCH cx_root.
        rv_count = 0.
    ENDTRY.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: ty_int_row  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY,
           ty_int_grid TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int_row WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE ty_int_grid
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_times) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    DATA: lv_ones  TYPE i,
          lv_trips TYPE i.

    rv_times = 0.

    IF capacity <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT grid INTO DATA(lt_row).
      lv_ones = 0.
      LOOP AT lt_row INTO DATA(lv_cell).
        IF lv_cell <> 0.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF lv_ones > 0.
        lv_trips = ( lv_ones + capacity - 1 ) DIV capacity.
        rv_times = rv_times + lv_trips.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE any
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    rv_count = 0.
    IF capacity <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lo_grid_desc) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( grid ).
    IF lo_grid_desc->kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>kind_table.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid_tab> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <row>      TYPE any,
                   <row_tab>  TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <cell>     TYPE any.

    ASSIGN grid TO <grid_tab>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <grid_tab> ASSIGNING <row>.
      DATA(lv_units) = 0.

      DATA(lo_row_desc) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <row> ).
      IF lo_row_desc->kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>kind_table.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN <row> TO <row_tab>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT <row_tab> ASSIGNING <cell>.
        TRY.
            IF <cell> = 1.
              lv_units = lv_units + 1.
            ENDIF.
          CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error cx_sy_dyn_call_illegal_type cx_sy_no_handler.
            RETURN.
        ENDTRY.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF lv_units > 0.
        rv_count = rv_count + ( ( lv_units + capacity - 1 ) DIV capacity ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid                TYPE ANY TABLE
        capacity            TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_lowerings) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    rv_lowerings = 0.

    IF capacity <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ls_row>  TYPE any,
                   <lv_cell> TYPE any.

    DATA: lr_row_descr   TYPE REF TO cl_abap_typedescr,
          lr_cell_descr  TYPE REF TO cl_abap_typedescr,
          lv_water_in_row TYPE i,
          lv_cell_i       TYPE i,
          lv_str          TYPE string.

    LOOP AT grid ASSIGNING <ls_row>.
      lv_water_in_row = 0.

      lr_row_descr = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <ls_row> ).

      IF lr_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_table.
        FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_row> TYPE ANY TABLE.
        ASSIGN <ls_row> TO <lt_row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          LOOP AT <lt_row> ASSIGNING <lv_cell>.
            lv_cell_i = 0.

            TRY.
                lr_cell_descr = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <lv_cell> ).
              CATCH cx_root.
                CLEAR lr_cell_descr.
            ENDTRY.

            IF lr_cell_descr IS BOUND
               AND ( lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int1
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int2
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int8
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_num
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_packed
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_float
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_decfloat16
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_decfloat34
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_char
                  OR lr_cell_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_string ).

              TRY.
                  lv_cell_i = CONV i( <lv_cell> ).
                CATCH cx_root.
                  lv_cell_i = 0.
              ENDTRY.

            ELSE.
              TRY.
                  lv_str = CONV string( <lv_cell> ).
                  IF lv_str = '1'.
                    lv_cell_i = 1.
                  ELSE.
                    lv_cell_i = 0.
                  ENDIF.
                CATCH cx_root.
                  lv_cell_i = 0.
              ENDTRY.
            ENDIF.

            IF lv_cell_i = 1.
              lv_water_in_row = lv_water_in_row + 1.
            ENDIF.
          ENDLOOP.
        ENDIF.

      ELSEIF lr_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_string
          OR lr_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_char.

        TRY.
            lv_str = CONV string( <ls_row> ).
          CATCH cx_root.
            CLEAR lv_str.
        ENDTRY.

        DATA(lv_len) = strlen( lv_str ).
        DO lv_len TIMES.
          IF lv_str+sy-index(1) = '1'.
            lv_water_in_row = lv_water_in_row + 1.
          ENDIF.
        ENDDO.

      ELSE.
        lv_water_in_row = 0.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_water_in_row > 0.
        rv_lowerings = rv_lowerings + ( lv_water_in_row DIV capacity ).
        IF ( lv_water_in_row MOD capacity ) <> 0.
          rv_lowerings = rv_lowerings + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE ANY
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    rv_count = 0.
    IF capacity <= 0 OR grid IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lo_grid_desc) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( grid ).
    IF lo_grid_desc IS INITIAL OR lo_grid_desc->kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>kind_table.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lo_grid_tab) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( lo_grid_desc ).
    DATA(lo_row_desc) = lo_grid_tab->get_table_line_type( ).
    IF lo_row_desc IS INITIAL OR lo_row_desc->kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>kind_table.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lo_row_tab) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( lo_row_desc ).
    DATA(lo_cell_desc) = lo_row_tab->get_table_line_type( ).

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_grid> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <lt_row>  TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <lv_cell> TYPE any.

    ASSIGN grid TO <lt_grid>.
    IF <lt_grid> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <lt_grid> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_row_any>).
      ASSIGN <ls_row_any> TO <lt_row>.
      IF <lt_row> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_ones) = 0.
      LOOP AT <lt_row> ASSIGNING <lv_cell>.
        TRY.
            CASE lo_cell_desc->kind.
              WHEN cl_abap_typedescr=>kind_elem.
                IF <lv_cell> = 1 OR <lv_cell> = '1'.
                  lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
                ENDIF.
              WHEN OTHERS.
            ENDCASE.
          CATCH cx_root.
        ENDTRY.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF lv_ones > 0.
        rv_count = rv_count + ( ( lv_ones + capacity - 1 ) DIV capacity ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE any
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    rv_count = 0.
    IF capacity <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lr_descr TYPE REF TO cl_abap_typedescr.

    TRY.
        lr_descr = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( grid ).
      CATCH cx_root.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lr_descr IS INITIAL OR lr_descr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_table.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lr_tabdescr) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( lr_descr ).
    DATA(lr_rowdescr) = lr_tabdescr->get_table_line_type( ).

    IF lr_rowdescr IS INITIAL OR lr_rowdescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_table.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lr_rowtabdescr TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr.
    lr_rowtabdescr ?= lr_rowdescr.
    IF lr_rowtabdescr IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lr_celldescr TYPE REF TO cl_abap_typedescr.
    lr_celldescr = lr_rowtabdescr->get_table_line_type( ).
    IF lr_celldescr IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int
       AND lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int1
       AND lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int2
       AND lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_num
       AND lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_p
       AND lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_f
       AND lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_string
       AND lr_celldescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_char.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <grid> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <row>  TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <cell> TYPE any.

    ASSIGN grid TO <grid>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA: lv_ones TYPE i,
          lv_full TYPE i,
          lv_rest TYPE i.

    LOOP AT <grid> ASSIGNING <row>.
      lv_ones = 0.
      LOOP AT <row> ASSIGNING <cell>.
        DATA(lv_i) = 0.
        TRY.
            lv_i = CONV i( <cell> ).
          CATCH cx_root.
            lv_i = 0.
        ENDTRY.
        IF lv_i <> 0.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF lv_ones > 0.
        lv_full = lv_ones DIV capacity.
        lv_rest = lv_ones MOD capacity.
        rv_count = rv_count + lv_full.
        IF lv_rest > 0.
          rv_count = rv_count + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE ANY TABLE
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <row>  TYPE any,
                   <cell> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_ones TYPE i.

    rv_count = 0.

    IF capacity <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT grid ASSIGNING <row>.
      lv_ones = 0.

      LOOP AT <row> ASSIGNING <cell>.
        IF <cell> IS NOT INITIAL.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF lv_ones > 0.
        rv_count = rv_count + ( ( lv_ones + capacity - 1 ) DIV capacity ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_times) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <row>  TYPE any,
                   <cell> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_cap TYPE i,
          lv_ones TYPE i.

    rv_times = 0.
    lv_cap = capacity.
    IF lv_cap <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT grid ASSIGNING <row>.
      TRY.
          DATA(lo_descr) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <row> ).
        CATCH cx_root.
          CLEAR lo_descr.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lo_descr IS BOUND AND lo_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_table.
        FIELD-SYMBOLS <itab_row> TYPE ANY TABLE.
        ASSIGN <row> TO <itab_row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          LOOP AT <itab_row> ASSIGNING <cell>.
            IF <cell> IS NOT INITIAL.
              rv_times = rv_times + 1.
            ENDIF.
          ENDLOOP.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        lv_ones = 0.
        DO.
          ASSIGN COMPONENT sy-index OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <cell>.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          IF <cell> IS NOT INITIAL.
            lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
          ENDIF.
        ENDDO.

        rv_times = rv_times + lv_ones.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_times = ( rv_times + lv_cap - 1 ) DIV lv_cap.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS max_fill
      IMPORTING
        grid     TYPE ANY TABLE
        capacity TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_fill IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD max_fill.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <row>  TYPE any,
                   <cell> TYPE any.

    DATA: lr_row     TYPE REF TO data,
          lr_cell    TYPE REF TO data,
          lo_row_td  TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr,
          lo_cell_td TYPE REF TO cl_abap_tabledescr,
          lv_row_sum TYPE i,
          lv_cell_i  TYPE i.

    rv_count = 0.
    IF capacity <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT grid ASSIGNING <row>.
      lv_row_sum = 0.

      lr_row = REF #( <row> ).

      TRY.
          lo_row_td ?= cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data_ref( lr_row ).
        CATCH cx_root.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lo_row_td IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_lines) = lo_row_td->lines( lr_row ).
      DO lv_lines TIMES.
        lr_cell = lo_row_td->get_ref( EXPORTING index = sy-index table_ref = lr_row ).
        ASSIGN lr_cell->* TO <cell>.
        CLEAR lv_cell_i.
        TRY.
            lv_cell_i = <cell>.
          CATCH cx_root.
            lv_cell_i = 0.
        ENDTRY.
        IF lv_cell_i <> 0.
          lv_row_sum = lv_row_sum + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      IF lv_row_sum > 0.
        rv_count = rv_count + ( ( lv_row_sum + capacity - 1 ) DIV capacity ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_route_analysis DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    INTERFACES if_serializable_object.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_route_revenue,
             cityfrom      TYPE spfli-cityfrom,
             cityto        TYPE spfli-cityto,
             total_revenue TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 2,
           END OF ty_route_revenue,
           tt_route_revenue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_route_revenue WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS get_route_profitability
      RETURNING VALUE(rt_route_revenue) TYPE tt_route_revenue.

  PROTECTED SECTION.
  PRIVATE SECTION.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_route_analysis IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_route_profitability.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_join,
             cityfrom TYPE spfli-cityfrom,
             cityto   TYPE spfli-cityto,
             price    TYPE sflight-price,
             seatsocc TYPE sflight-seatsocc,
           END OF ty_join.

    DATA lt_join TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_join WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_agg  TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_route_revenue WITH UNIQUE KEY cityfrom cityto.

    DATA lv_revenue TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 2.

    SELECT
      p~cityfrom,
      p~cityto,
      f~price,
      f~seatsocc
      FROM spfli AS p
      INNER JOIN sflight AS f
        ON f~carrid = p~carrid
       AND f~connid = p~connid
      INTO TABLE @lt_join.

    LOOP AT lt_join ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<j>).
      CLEAR lv_revenue.
      lv_revenue = <j>-price * <j>-seatsocc.

      ASSIGN lt_agg[ cityfrom = <j>-cityfrom cityto = <j>-cityto ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<a>).
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        <a>-total_revenue = <a>-total_revenue + lv_revenue.
      ELSE.
        INSERT VALUE ty_route_revenue(
          cityfrom      = <j>-cityfrom
          cityto        = <j>-cityto
          total_revenue = lv_revenue
        ) INTO TABLE lt_agg.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_route_revenue = VALUE tt_route_revenue( FOR a IN lt_agg ( a ) ).
    SORT rt_route_revenue BY total_revenue DESCENDING cityfrom ASCENDING cityto ASCENDING.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_employees IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_emp_wo_subords.
    DATA lt_master TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_emp_master WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_org    TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_org_struct WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_sup    TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_org_struct-supervisor_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    SELECT employee_id, name
      FROM ('ZEMP_MASTER')
      INTO TABLE @lt_master.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_org.

    lt_sup = VALUE #( FOR r IN lt_org ( r-supervisor_id ) ).

    LOOP AT lt_master ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<m>).
      READ TABLE lt_sup WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <m>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        APPEND CONV string( <m>-name ) TO rt_employee_names.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_org_management_chain DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_employee_id TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_structure,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_employee_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_employee_id,
           END OF ty_structure.
    TYPES ty_structure_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_structure WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        employee_id TYPE ty_employee_id
      RETURNING
        VALUE(supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_org_management_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    DATA lt_all TYPE ty_structure_tab.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM zorg_structure
      INTO TABLE @lt_all.

    DATA lt_chain TYPE stringtab.
    DATA lv_current TYPE ty_employee_id.
    lv_current = employee_id.

    DATA lt_visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    WHILE abap_true = abap_true.
      READ TABLE lt_visited WITH TABLE KEY table_line = CONV string( lv_current ) TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT CONV string( lv_current ) INTO TABLE lt_visited.

      READ TABLE lt_all WITH KEY employee_id = lv_current ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_rel>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <ls_rel>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND CONV string( <ls_rel>-supervisor_id ) TO lt_chain.
      lv_current = <ls_rel>-supervisor_id.
    ENDWHILE.

    supervisor_ids = lt_chain.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_management_chain DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        employee_id TYPE char20
      RETURNING
        VALUE(supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_management_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    supervisor_ids = VALUE stringtab( ).

    DATA: lv_current_employee TYPE char20,
          lv_supervisor       TYPE char20.

    lv_current_employee = employee_id.

    DATA lt_visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF char20 WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    WHILE lv_current_employee IS NOT INITIAL.
      CLEAR lv_supervisor.

      SELECT SINGLE supervisor_id
        FROM zorg_structure
        WHERE ( employee_id = @lv_current_employee )
        INTO @lv_supervisor.

      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_supervisor IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF line_exists( lt_visited[ table_line = lv_supervisor ] ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT lv_supervisor INTO TABLE lt_visited.
      APPEND lv_supervisor TO supervisor_ids.

      lv_current_employee = lv_supervisor.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             employee_id   TYPE char20,
             supervisor_id TYPE char20,
           END OF ty_edge,
           ty_edge_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY,
           ty_edge_hash TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_edge WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        employee_id TYPE char20
      RETURNING
        VALUE(supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_management_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    supervisor_ids = VALUE stringtab( ).

    DATA current_employee_id TYPE char20.
    DATA lv_supervisor_id    TYPE char20.
    current_employee_id = employee_id.

    DATA lt_edges TYPE ty_edge_tab.
    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM zorg_structure
      INTO TABLE @lt_edges.

    DATA lt_by_employee TYPE ty_edge_hash.
    lt_by_employee = lt_edges.

    DATA lt_visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF char20 WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    WHILE current_employee_id IS NOT INITIAL.
      IF line_exists( lt_visited[ table_line = current_employee_id ] ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT current_employee_id INTO TABLE lt_visited.

      READ TABLE lt_by_employee WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = current_employee_id INTO DATA(ls_edge).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR ls_edge-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_supervisor_id = ls_edge-supervisor_id.
      APPEND CONV string( lv_supervisor_id ) TO supervisor_ids.

      IF lv_supervisor_id = current_employee_id.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      current_employee_id = lv_supervisor_id.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_management_chain DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_zorg_structure,
             employee_id   TYPE char20,
             supervisor_id TYPE char20,
           END OF ty_zorg_structure.

    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        employee_id TYPE char20
      RETURNING
        VALUE(supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_management_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    supervisor_ids = VALUE stringtab( ).

    DATA: current_employee TYPE char20,
          next_supervisor  TYPE char20.

    current_employee = employee_id.

    DATA visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF char20 WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    WHILE current_employee IS NOT INITIAL.
      READ TABLE visited WITH TABLE KEY table_line = current_employee TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT current_employee INTO TABLE visited.

      CLEAR next_supervisor.
      SELECT SINGLE supervisor_id
        FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
        WHERE employee_id = @current_employee
        INTO @next_supervisor.

      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR next_supervisor IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND CONV string( next_supervisor ) TO supervisor_ids.

      IF next_supervisor = current_employee.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      current_employee = next_supervisor.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      CLEAR lv_next_supervisor.

CLASS zcl_zorg_mgmt_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    supervisor_ids = VALUE stringtab( ).

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_rel,
             employee_id   TYPE char20,
             supervisor_id TYPE char20,
           END OF ty_rel.
    TYPES ty_rel_tab TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_rel WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    DATA lt_rel TYPE ty_rel_tab.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_rel.

    DATA lv_current_employee TYPE char20.
    DATA lv_supervisor TYPE char20.

    lv_current_employee = employee_id.

    DATA lt_visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF char20 WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    DO.
      IF lv_current_employee IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_visited WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_current_employee TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT lv_current_employee INTO TABLE lt_visited.

      READ TABLE lt_rel WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = lv_current_employee INTO DATA(ls_rel).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR ls_rel-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_supervisor = ls_rel-supervisor_id.
      APPEND lv_supervisor TO supervisor_ids.
      lv_current_employee = lv_supervisor.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
