CLASS zcl_org_management_chain DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        VALUE(iv_employee_id) TYPE char20
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_org_management_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    rt_supervisor_ids = VALUE stringtab( ).

    DATA lv_curr TYPE char20.
    DATA lv_next TYPE char20.
    DATA lt_seen TYPE HASHED TABLE OF char20 WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    lv_curr = iv_employee_id.

    WHILE lv_curr IS NOT INITIAL.
      CLEAR lv_next.

      SELECT SINGLE supervisor_id
        FROM zorg_structure
        INTO @lv_next
        WHERE employee_id = @lv_curr.

      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_next IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF line_exists( lt_seen[ table_line = lv_next ] ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT lv_next INTO TABLE lt_seen.

      APPEND CONV string( lv_next ) TO rt_supervisor_ids.

      lv_curr = lv_next.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_mgmt_chain DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_relation,
             employee_id   TYPE char20,
             supervisor_id TYPE char20,
           END OF ty_relation,
           ty_relation_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_relation WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        employee_id TYPE char20
        relations   TYPE ty_relation_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_mgmt_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    supervisor_ids = VALUE stringtab( ).

    DATA lv_curr TYPE char20.
    DATA lv_next TYPE char20.

    lv_curr = employee_id.

    WHILE lv_curr IS NOT INITIAL.
      CLEAR lv_next.

      READ TABLE relations WITH KEY employee_id = lv_curr INTO DATA(ls_rel).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR ls_rel-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_next = ls_rel-supervisor_id.
      APPEND CONV string( lv_next ) TO supervisor_ids.
      lv_curr = lv_next.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_management_chain DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        employee_id TYPE char20
      RETURNING
        VALUE(supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_zorg_management_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain.
    supervisor_ids = VALUE stringtab( ).

    DATA current_employee TYPE char20.
    DATA next_supervisor  TYPE char20.
    DATA next_supervisor_str TYPE string.
    DATA visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    current_employee = employee_id.

    DO.
      CLEAR next_supervisor.

      SELECT SINGLE supervisor_id
        FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
        WHERE employee_id = @current_employee
        INTO @next_supervisor.

      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR next_supervisor IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      next_supervisor_str = CONV string( next_supervisor ).

      IF line_exists( visited[ table_line = next_supervisor_str ] ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT next_supervisor_str INTO TABLE visited.
      APPEND next_supervisor_str TO supervisor_ids.

      IF next_supervisor = current_employee.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      current_employee = next_supervisor.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_org_management_chain DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    INTERFACES if_amdp_marker_hdb.

    CLASS-METHODS find_management_chain
      IMPORTING
        employee_id TYPE char20
      RETURNING
        VALUE(supervisor_ids) TYPE stringtab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_org_management_chain IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_management_chain BY DATABASE FUNCTION
    FOR HDB
    LANGUAGE SQLSCRIPT
    OPTIONS READ-ONLY
    USING zorg_structure.

    supervisor_ids =
      SELECT supervisor_id AS table_line
        FROM zorg_structure
       START WITH employee_id = :employee_id
     CONNECT BY PRIOR supervisor_id = employee_id;

  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA: sum_nm  TYPE decfloat34,
          cnt     TYPE decfloat34,
          avg     TYPE decfloat34,
          rounded TYPE i,
          bin     TYPE string,
          x       TYPE i.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    cnt = m - n + 1.
    sum_nm = cnt * ( CONV decfloat34( n ) + CONV decfloat34( m ) ) / 2.
    avg = sum_nm / cnt.

    rounded = trunc( avg + CONV decfloat34( '0.5' ) ).

    bin = ``.
    IF rounded = 0.
      bin = `0`.
    ELSE.
      x = rounded.
      WHILE x > 0.
        IF x MOD 2 = 0.
          bin = `0` && bin.
        ELSE.
          bin = `1` && bin.
        ENDIF.
        x = x DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDIF.

    result = `0b` && bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA sum     TYPE i.
    DATA avg_i   TYPE i.
    DATA rem2    TYPE i.
    DATA bin     TYPE string.
    DATA x       TYPE i.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    sum = n + m.
    avg_i = sum DIV 2.
    rem2 = sum MOD 2.

    IF rem2 <> 0 AND ( avg_i MOD 2 ) <> 0.
      avg_i = avg_i + 1.
    ENDIF.

    IF avg_i = 0.
      result = `0b0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    bin = ``.
    x = avg_i.

    WHILE x > 0.
      IF x MOD 2 = 0.
        bin = `0` && bin.
      ELSE.
        bin = `1` && bin.
      ENDIF.
      x = x DIV 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    result = `0b` && bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA: sum_nm    TYPE int8,
          cnt       TYPE int8,
          den       TYPE int8,
          num       TYPE int8,
          q         TYPE int8,
          r         TYPE int8,
          avg_int8  TYPE int8,
          hex       TYPE string,
          hex_digit TYPE i,
          ch        TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          val       TYPE int8,
          rem       TYPE int8,
          bin       TYPE string,
          hex_len   TYPE i,
          idx       TYPE i.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    sum_nm = CONV int8( n ) + CONV int8( m ).
    cnt    = CONV int8( m ) - CONV int8( n ) + 1.

    den = 2 * cnt.
    num = sum_nm * cnt.

    q = num / den.
    r = num MOD den.

    avg_int8 = q.
    IF r * 2 >= den.
      avg_int8 = avg_int8 + 1.
    ENDIF.

    IF avg_int8 = 0.
      result = `0b0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    val = avg_int8.
    hex = |{ val }|.
    CONDENSE hex NO-GAPS.

    IF strlen( hex ) >= 2 AND hex+0(2) = `0X`.
      hex = hex+2.
    ENDIF.

    TRANSLATE hex TO UPPER CASE.

    CLEAR bin.
    hex_len = strlen( hex ).

    DO hex_len TIMES.
      idx = sy-index - 1.
      ch = hex+idx(1).

      IF ch CO `0123456789`.
        hex_digit = ( ch ) - ( `0` ).
      ELSEIF ch CO `ABCDEF`.
        hex_digit = 10 + ( ( ch ) - ( `A` ) ).
      ELSE.
        result = `-1`.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      rem = hex_digit.

      IF rem >= 8. bin = bin && `1`. rem = rem - 8. ELSE. bin = bin && `0`. ENDIF.
      IF rem >= 4. bin = bin && `1`. rem = rem - 4. ELSE. bin = bin && `0`. ENDIF.
      IF rem >= 2. bin = bin && `1`. rem = rem - 2. ELSE. bin = bin && `0`. ENDIF.
      IF rem >= 1. bin = bin && `1`. rem = rem - 1. ELSE. bin = bin && `0`. ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    WHILE strlen( bin ) > 1 AND bin+0(1) = `0`.
      bin = bin+1.
    ENDWHILE.

    result = `0b` && bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA sum_i    TYPE int8.
    DATA count_i  TYPE int8.
    DATA num_i    TYPE int8.
    DATA avg_i    TYPE int8.
    DATA bin      TYPE string.
    DATA x        TYPE int8.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    count_i = CONV int8( m ) - CONV int8( n ) + 1.
    sum_i   = ( CONV int8( n ) + CONV int8( m ) ) * count_i / 2.

    num_i = sum_i + count_i - 1.
    avg_i = num_i DIV count_i.

    CLEAR bin.
    x = avg_i.

    IF x = 0.
      bin = `0`.
    ELSE.
      WHILE x > 0.
        IF ( x MOD 2 ) = 0.
          bin = `0` && bin.
        ELSE.
          bin = `1` && bin.
        ENDIF.
        x = x DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDIF.

    result = `0b` && bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA: count   TYPE i,
          sum_i   TYPE int8,
          avg_int TYPE int8,
          num     TYPE int8,
          bin     TYPE string.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    count = m - n + 1.
    sum_i = ( CONV int8( n ) + CONV int8( m ) ) * CONV int8( count ).

    IF ( sum_i MOD 2 ) = 0.
      avg_int = sum_i / 2 / count.
    ELSE.
      avg_int = ( sum_i / 2 ) / count.
    ENDIF.

    IF ( sum_i MOD ( 2 * CONV int8( count ) ) ) >= CONV int8( count ).
      avg_int = avg_int + 1.
    ENDIF.

    IF avg_int = 0.
      result = `0b0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    num = avg_int.
    bin = ``.
    WHILE num > 0.
      IF ( num MOD 2 ) = 0.
        bin = `0` && bin.
      ELSE.
        bin = `1` && bin.
      ENDIF.
      num = num DIV 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    result = `0b` && bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA: sum_nm  TYPE decfloat34,
          avg     TYPE decfloat34,
          rounded TYPE i,
          abs_val TYPE i,
          bin     TYPE string,
          rem     TYPE i.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    sum_nm = CONV decfloat34( n ) + CONV decfloat34( m ).
    avg = sum_nm / 2.

    IF frac( avg ) = CONV decfloat34( '0.5' ).
      rounded = ceil( avg ).
    ELSE.
      rounded = round( val = avg dec = 0 mode = cl_abap_math=>round_half_up ).
    ENDIF.

    IF rounded = 0.
      result = `0b0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    abs_val = abs( rounded ).
    bin = ``.

    WHILE abs_val > 0.
      rem = abs_val MOD 2.
      bin = |{ rem }{ bin }|.
      abs_val = abs_val DIV 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF rounded < 0.
      result = |0b-{ bin }|.
    ELSE.
      result = |0b{ bin }|.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA: lv_sum TYPE int8,
          lv_avg TYPE int8,
          lv_tmp TYPE int8,
          lv_bit TYPE i,
          lv_bin TYPE string.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_sum = CONV int8( n ) + CONV int8( m ).

    IF ( lv_sum MOD 2 ) = 0.
      lv_avg = lv_sum DIV 2.
    ELSE.
      IF lv_sum > 0.
        lv_avg = ( lv_sum DIV 2 ) + 1.
      ELSE.
        lv_avg = lv_sum DIV 2.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    result = `0b`.

    IF lv_avg = 0.
      result = result && `0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_tmp = lv_avg.
    CLEAR lv_bin.

    WHILE lv_tmp > 0.
      lv_bit = lv_tmp MOD 2.
      IF lv_bit = 0.
        lv_bin = `0` && lv_bin.
      ELSE.
        lv_bin = `1` && lv_bin.
      ENDIF.
      lv_tmp = lv_tmp DIV 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    result = result && lv_bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA sum_nm  TYPE int8.
    DATA cnt     TYPE int8.
    DATA total   TYPE int8.
    DATA avg_den TYPE int8.
    DATA q       TYPE int8.
    DATA r       TYPE int8.
    DATA avg_int TYPE int8.
    DATA bin     TYPE string.
    DATA x       TYPE int8.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    sum_nm = CONV int8( n ) + CONV int8( m ).
    cnt    = CONV int8( m ) - CONV int8( n ) + 1.

    total   = sum_nm * cnt.
    avg_den = 2 * cnt.

    q = total DIV avg_den.
    r = total MOD avg_den.

    avg_int = q.
    IF 2 * r >= avg_den.
      avg_int = q + 1.
    ENDIF.

    x = avg_int.

    IF x = 0.
      bin = `0`.
    ELSE.
      CLEAR bin.
      WHILE x > 0.
        IF ( x MOD 2 ) = 1.
          bin = `1` && bin.
        ELSE.
          bin = `0` && bin.
        ENDIF.
        x = x DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDIF.

    result = `0b` && bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA: sum_i   TYPE int8,
          cnt_i   TYPE int8,
          avg_i   TYPE int8,
          rem_i   TYPE int8,
          rounded TYPE int8,
          val     TYPE int8,
          bit     TYPE i,
          bin     TYPE string.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    sum_i = CONV int8( n ) + CONV int8( m ).
    cnt_i = 2.

    avg_i = sum_i DIV cnt_i.
    rem_i = sum_i MOD cnt_i.

    rounded = avg_i.
    IF rem_i <> 0.
      rounded = rounded + 1.
    ENDIF.

    IF rounded = 0.
      result = `0b0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    CLEAR bin.
    val = rounded.

    WHILE val > 0.
      bit = CONV i( val MOD 2 ).
      bin = |{ bit }{ bin }|.
      val = val DIV 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    result = |0b{ bin }|.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rounded_avg
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
        m TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rounded_avg IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rounded_avg.
    DATA: lv_n        TYPE int8,
          lv_m        TYPE int8,
          lv_cnt      TYPE int8,
          lv_a        TYPE int8,
          lv_b        TYPE int8,
          lv_sum      TYPE int8,
          lv_avg      TYPE int8,
          lv_rem      TYPE int8,
          lv_bin      TYPE string,
          lv_x        TYPE int8,
          lv_step     TYPE int8,
          lv_bit      TYPE int8,
          lv_iter     TYPE i.

    IF n > m.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_n = CONV int8( n ).
    lv_m = CONV int8( m ).
    lv_cnt = lv_m - lv_n + 1.

    lv_a = lv_n + lv_m.
    lv_b = lv_cnt.

    IF lv_a MOD 2 = 0.
      lv_a = lv_a / 2.
    ELSE.
      lv_b = lv_b / 2.
    ENDIF.

    lv_sum = lv_a * lv_b.

    lv_avg = lv_sum / lv_cnt.
    lv_rem = lv_sum MOD lv_cnt.

    IF lv_rem <> 0.
      IF lv_rem < 0.
        lv_rem = lv_rem * -1.
      ENDIF.
      IF lv_rem * 2 >= lv_cnt.
        lv_avg = lv_avg + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_avg < 0.
      result = `-1`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_avg = 0.
      result = `0b0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_bin = ``.
    lv_x = lv_avg.

    lv_iter = 0.
    WHILE lv_x > 0 AND lv_iter < 128.
      lv_step = lv_x / 2.
      lv_bit  = lv_x - ( lv_step * 2 ).

      IF lv_bit = 0.
        lv_bin = `0` && lv_bin.
      ELSE.
        lv_bin = `1` && lv_bin.
      ENDIF.

      lv_x = lv_step.
      lv_iter = lv_iter + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    result = `0b` && lv_bin.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int8 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_arr) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             val  TYPE int8,
             ones TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.
    TYPES ty_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_items TYPE ty_items.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO DATA(lv_val).
      DATA(lv_abs)  TYPE int8 VALUE abs( lv_val ).
      DATA(lv_ones) TYPE i VALUE 0.

      WHILE lv_abs > 0.
        lv_ones = lv_ones + CONV i( lv_abs MOD 2 ).
        lv_abs = lv_abs DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item( val = lv_val ones = lv_ones ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING val ASCENDING.

    rt_arr = VALUE ty_int_tab( FOR ls IN lt_items ( ls-val ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_sorted) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             val  TYPE i,
             ones TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.

    DATA lt_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_val   TYPE i.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_val.
      DATA lv_u32 TYPE int8.
      lv_u32 = lv_val.
      IF lv_u32 < 0.
        lv_u32 = lv_u32 + 4294967296.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item(
        val  = lv_val
        ones = REDUCE i(
                 INIT acc = 0
                 FOR pos = 0 UNTIL pos >= 32
                 NEXT acc = acc + COND i(
                   WHEN ( BIT-AND( lv_u32, BIT-SHIFT-LEFT( CONV int8( 1 ), pos ) ) ) <> 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 ) )
      ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING val ASCENDING.

    rt_sorted = VALUE ty_int_tab( FOR ls IN lt_items ( ls-val ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_arr) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             val  TYPE i,
             ones TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.

    DATA lt_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING <v_any>.
      DATA(lv_val) = CONV i( <v_any> ).
      DATA(lv_ones) = 0.
      DATA(lv_x) = lv_val.

      IF lv_x < 0.
        lv_x = lv_x * -1.
      ENDIF.

      WHILE lv_x <> 0.
        IF ( lv_x MOD 2 ) = 1.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
        lv_x = lv_x DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item( val = lv_val ones = lv_ones ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING val ASCENDING.
    rt_arr = VALUE #( FOR ls IN lt_items ( ls-val ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_arr) TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             value TYPE int8,
             ones  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.
    TYPES ty_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_items TYPE ty_items.
    DATA lv_ones  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_abs   TYPE int8.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_in>  TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_out> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING <lv_in>.
      DATA(lv_value) = CONV int8( <lv_in> ).

      lv_ones = 0.
      lv_abs  = lv_value.
      IF lv_abs < 0.
        lv_abs = lv_abs * -1.
      ENDIF.

      WHILE lv_abs > 0.
        IF ( lv_abs MOD 2 ) = 1.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
        lv_abs = lv_abs DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item( value = lv_value ones = lv_ones ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING value ASCENDING.

    ASSIGN rt_arr TO <lt_out>.
    LOOP AT lt_items INTO DATA(ls_item).
      APPEND ls_item-value TO <lt_out>.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array_by_ones DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_arr) TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array_by_ones IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_in>  TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <lv_in>  TYPE any,
                   <lt_out> TYPE ANY TABLE.

    ASSIGN it_arr TO <lt_in>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rt_arr = it_arr.
    ASSIGN rt_arr TO <lt_out>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_key,
             idx   TYPE i,
             ones  TYPE i,
             value TYPE i,
           END OF ty_key.
    DATA lt_keys TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_key WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT <lt_in> ASSIGNING <lv_in>.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      DATA(lv_val) = CONV i( <lv_in> ).
      DATA(lv_abs) = lv_val.
      IF lv_abs < 0.
        lv_abs = lv_abs * -1.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_u) = CONV int8( lv_abs ).
      DATA(lv_ones) = 0.
      WHILE lv_u > 0.
        IF ( lv_u MOD 2 ) = 1.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
        lv_u = lv_u DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_key( idx = lv_idx ones = lv_ones value = lv_val ) TO lt_keys.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_keys BY ones ASCENDING value ASCENDING.

    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_keys INTO DATA(ls_key).
      READ TABLE <lt_in> ASSIGNING <lv_in> INDEX ls_key-idx.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        APPEND CONV i( <lv_in> ) TO lt_sorted.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    CLEAR <lt_out>.
    LOOP AT lt_sorted INTO DATA(lv_sorted).
      APPEND lv_sorted TO <lt_out>.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_arr) TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             val  TYPE int8,
             ones TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.

    DATA lt_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <in_tab> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <in_val> TYPE any.

    ASSIGN it_arr TO <in_tab>.

    LOOP AT <in_tab> ASSIGNING <in_val>.
      DATA(lv_val) TYPE int8.
      lv_val = CONV int8( <in_val> ).

      DATA(lv_u) TYPE int8.
      lv_u = lv_val.
      IF lv_u < 0.
        lv_u = lv_u + 4294967296.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_ones) TYPE i VALUE 0.
      WHILE lv_u > 0.
        lv_ones = lv_ones + CONV i( lv_u MOD 2 ).
        lv_u = lv_u DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item( val = lv_val ones = lv_ones ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING val ASCENDING.

    CREATE DATA DATA(lr_out) LIKE it_arr.
    ASSIGN lr_out->* TO <in_tab>.

    LOOP AT lt_items INTO DATA(ls_item).
      APPEND ls_item-val TO <in_tab>.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_arr = <in_tab>.

  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_arr) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             val  TYPE i,
             ones TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.
    TYPES ty_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    DATA lt_items TYPE ty_items.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO DATA(lv_val).
      DATA(lv_ones) = 0.
      DATA(lv_bits) = CONV string( abs( lv_val ) ).

      DATA(lv_x) = abs( lv_val ).
      WHILE lv_x > 0.
        IF ( lv_x MOD 2 ) = 1.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
        lv_x = lv_x DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item( val = lv_val ones = lv_ones ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING val ASCENDING.

    rt_arr = VALUE ty_int_tab( FOR ls IN lt_items ( ls-val ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sytabix WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_array TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_array) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             value TYPE sytabix,
             ones  TYPE sytabix,
           END OF ty_item.
    TYPES ty_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_items TYPE ty_items.

    LOOP AT it_array INTO DATA(lv_val).
      DATA(lv_ones) = 0.
      DATA(lv_work) = lv_val.

      IF lv_work < 0.
        lv_work = lv_work * -1.
      ENDIF.

      WHILE lv_work > 0.
        IF ( lv_work MOD 2 ) = 1.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
        lv_work = lv_work DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item( value = lv_val ones = lv_ones ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING value ASCENDING.

    CLEAR rt_array.
    LOOP AT lt_items INTO DATA(ls_item).
      APPEND ls_item-value TO rt_array.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_arr) TYPE ty_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             val  TYPE i,
             ones TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.

    DATA: lt_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH DEFAULT KEY,
          ls_item  TYPE ty_item,
          lv_val   TYPE i,
          lv_ones  TYPE i,
          lv_u32   TYPE p LENGTH 10 DECIMALS 0,
          lv_mod   TYPE p LENGTH 10 DECIMALS 0.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <v_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING <v_any>.
      lv_val = <v_any>.
      lv_ones = 0.

      lv_u32 = lv_val.
      IF lv_val < 0.
        lv_u32 = lv_u32 + '4294967296'.
      ENDIF.

      WHILE lv_u32 > 0.
        lv_mod = lv_u32 MOD 2.
        IF lv_mod = 1.
          lv_ones = lv_ones + 1.
        ENDIF.
        lv_u32 = lv_u32 DIV 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      CLEAR ls_item.
      ls_item-val  = lv_val.
      ls_item-ones = lv_ones.
      APPEND ls_item TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY ones ASCENDING val ASCENDING.

    CLEAR rt_arr.
    LOOP AT lt_items INTO ls_item.
      APPEND ls_item-val TO rt_arr.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_count_subordinates IMPLEMENTATION.

      CATCH cx_root.

CLASS zcl_available_stock DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_stock,
             mat_id TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             stock  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_stock.

    TYPES: tt_stock TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_stock WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_transaction,
             id               TYPE i,
             mat_id           TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             transaction_type TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             transaction_date TYPE d,
             amount           TYPE i,
           END OF ty_transaction.

    TYPES: tt_transaction TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_transaction WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS calculate_planned_order
      IMPORTING
        mat_id         TYPE c LENGTH 20
        it_stock       TYPE tt_stock
        it_transaction TYPE tt_transaction
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rs_plo)  TYPE ty_transaction.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_available_stock IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate_planned_order.
    DATA: lv_stock TYPE i.

    CLEAR rs_plo.
    lv_stock = 0.

    READ TABLE it_stock WITH KEY mat_id = mat_id INTO DATA(ls_stock).
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      lv_stock = ls_stock-stock.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lt_tx) = it_transaction.
    DELETE lt_tx WHERE mat_id <> mat_id OR ( transaction_type <> 'PLO' AND transaction_type <> 'RES' ).
    SORT lt_tx BY transaction_date id.

    LOOP AT lt_tx ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<tx>).
      lv_stock = lv_stock + <tx>-amount.
      IF lv_stock < 0.
        rs_plo-id               = 99999.

             transaction_type TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             transaction_date TYPE d,
             amount           TYPE i,
           END OF ty_transaction.
    TYPES ty_t_transaction TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_transaction WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS calculate_available_stock
      IMPORTING
        mat_id         TYPE c
        it_stock       TYPE ty_t_stock OPTIONAL
        it_transaction TYPE ty_t_transaction OPTIONAL
      RETURNING
        VALUE(current_amount) TYPE ty_transaction.

CLASS zcl_available_stock IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate_available_stock.
    DATA: lv_mat_id   TYPE c LENGTH 20,
          lv_stock    TYPE i,
          lt_trans    TYPE ty_t_transaction,
          ls_trans    TYPE ty_transaction,
          lv_shortage TYPE i.

    CLEAR current_amount.
    lv_stock = 0.

    lv_mat_id = mat_id.

    IF it_stock IS SUPPLIED.
      READ TABLE it_stock WITH KEY mat_id = lv_mat_id INTO DATA(ls_stock).
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_stock = ls_stock-stock.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    IF it_transaction IS SUPPLIED.
      lt_trans = it_transaction.
      SORT lt_trans BY transaction_date id.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_trans INTO ls_trans WHERE mat_id = lv_mat_id.
      CASE ls_trans-transaction_type.
        WHEN 'PLO' OR 'PLO ' OR 'RES'.
          lv_stock = lv_stock + ls_trans-amount.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDCASE.

      IF lv_stock < 0.
        lv_shortage = -lv_stock.
        current_amount-id = 99999.
        current_amount-mat_id = lv_mat_id.
        current_amount-transaction_type = 'PLO'.
        current_amount-transaction_date = ls_trans-transaction_date.
        current_amount-amount = lv_shortage.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_f DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS f
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_list) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_f IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD f.
    DATA: idx  TYPE i,
          j    TYPE i,
          sum  TYPE i VALUE 0,
          fact TYPE i.

    CLEAR rt_list.

    IF n <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO n TIMES.
      idx = sy-index.

      IF idx MOD 2 = 0.
        fact = 1.
        DO idx TIMES.
          j = sy-index.
          fact = fact * j.
        ENDDO.
        APPEND fact TO rt_list.
      ELSE.
        sum = sum + idx.
        IF idx = 1.
          APPEND 1 TO rt_list.
        ELSE.
          APPEND ( sum * 2 ) TO rt_list.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_reverse_delete DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_result,
             res    TYPE string,
             is_pal TYPE abap_bool,
           END OF ty_result.

    CLASS-METHODS reverse_delete
      IMPORTING
        s TYPE string
        c TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_reverse_delete IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD reverse_delete.
    TYPES ty_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    DATA: lv_res    TYPE string VALUE ``,
          lv_is_pal TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lt_del    TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_char WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line,
          lv_left   TYPE ty_char,
          lv_right  TYPE ty_char,
          lv_len    TYPE i,
          lv_half   TYPE i,
          lv_i      TYPE i.

    DATA lt_s TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_char WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_c TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_char WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_r TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_char WITH EMPTY KEY.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ch> TYPE ty_char.

    IF c IS NOT INITIAL.
      SPLIT c AT space INTO TABLE lt_c.
      LOOP AT lt_c ASSIGNING <ch>.
        IF <ch> IS NOT INITIAL.
          INSERT <ch> INTO TABLE lt_del.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    IF s IS NOT INITIAL.
      SPLIT s AT space INTO TABLE lt_s.
      LOOP AT lt_s ASSIGNING <ch>.
        READ TABLE lt_del WITH KEY table_line = <ch> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          APPEND <ch> TO lt_r.
          lv_res = lv_res && <ch>.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lines( lt_r ).
    lv_half = lv_len DIV 2.

    DO lv_half TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_r INDEX lv_i INTO lv_left.
      READ TABLE lt_r INDEX ( lv_len - lv_i + 1 ) INTO lv_right.
      IF lv_left <> lv_right.
        lv_is_pal = abap_false.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    r_result-res = lv_res.
    r_result-is_pal = lv_is_pal.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_odd_count DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS odd_count
      IMPORTING
        it_input TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_output) TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_odd_count IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD odd_count.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_any> TYPE any.
    DATA lv_str      TYPE string.
    DATA lv_cnt      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_i        TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char     TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_digit    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_cnt_str  TYPE string.
    DATA lv_sentence TYPE string.

    CLEAR rt_output.

    LOOP AT it_input ASSIGNING <ls_any>.
      lv_str = <ls_any>.
      lv_cnt = 0.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_str ).

      lv_i = 0.
      WHILE lv_i < lv_len.
        lv_char = lv_str+lv_i(1).
        lv_digit = lv_char.
        IF lv_digit MOD 2 = 1.
          lv_cnt = lv_cnt + 1.
        ENDIF.
        lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      lv_cnt_str = lv_cnt.
      lv_sentence = |the number of odd elements { lv_cnt_str }n the str{ lv_cnt_str }ng { lv_cnt_str } of the { lv_cnt_str }nput.|.

      APPEND lv_sentence TO rt_output.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_odd_count DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS odd_count
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE string_table
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_result) TYPE string_table.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_odd_count IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD odd_count.
    rt_result = VALUE #( ).

    LOOP AT it_list INTO DATA(lv_str).
      DATA(lv_count) = 0.
      DATA(lv_len) = strlen( lv_str ).

      DO lv_len TIMES.
        DATA(lv_off) = sy-index - 1.
        DATA(lv_char) = lv_str+lv_off(1).
        IF lv_char CA '13579'.
          lv_count = lv_count + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      DATA(lv_count_s) = CONV string( lv_count ).

      DATA(lv_out) = |the number of odd elements { lv_count_s }n the str{ lv_count_s }ng { lv_count_s } of the { lv_count_s }nput.|.

      REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF | { lv_count_s }n| IN lv_out WITH |{ lv_count_s }n|.
      REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF |str{ lv_count_s } ng| IN lv_out WITH |str{ lv_count_s }ng|.
      REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF | { lv_count_s } nput| IN lv_out WITH | { lv_count_s }nput|.

      APPEND lv_out TO rt_result.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS calculate
      IMPORTING
        order_date TYPE string
        mat_id     TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE d.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_material,
             mat_id          TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             lead_time_days  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_material.
    TYPES tt_material TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_material WITH UNIQUE KEY mat_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_holiday,
             holiday_date TYPE d,
           END OF ty_holiday.
    TYPES tt_holiday TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_holiday WITH UNIQUE KEY holiday_date.

    DATA lv_order_date TYPE d.
    DATA lv_mat_id     TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    DATA lv_lead_time  TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_current    TYPE d.
    DATA lv_count      TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_weekday    TYPE i.

    DATA lt_material TYPE tt_material.
    DATA lt_holiday  TYPE tt_holiday.

    lv_order_date = order_date.

    lv_mat_id = mat_id.
    IF strlen( lv_mat_id ) > 20.
      lv_mat_id = lv_mat_id+0(20).
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_material WITH TABLE KEY mat_id = lv_mat_id INTO DATA(ls_mat).
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      lv_lead_time = ls_mat-lead_time_days.
    ELSE.
      lv_lead_time = 0.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_lead_time < 0.
      lv_lead_time = 0.
    ENDIF.

    lv_current = lv_order_date.

    WHILE lv_count < lv_lead_time.
      lv_current = lv_current + 1.

      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_current
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_weekday.
      IF lv_weekday = 6 OR lv_weekday = 7.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_holiday WITH TABLE KEY holiday_date = lv_current TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_count = lv_count + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_current.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE dats.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate.
    DATA lv_order_date TYPE dats.
    DATA lv_mat_id     TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    DATA lv_lead_time  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_date       TYPE dats.
    DATA lv_added      TYPE i.

    lv_order_date = order_date.
    lv_mat_id = mat_id.
    lv_date = lv_order_date.

    lv_lead_time = 0.
    READ TABLE zmaterial WITH KEY mat_id = lv_mat_id INTO DATA(ls_mat).
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      lv_lead_time = ls_mat-lead_time_days.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_holiday_dates TYPE SORTED TABLE OF dats WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT zholiday INTO DATA(ls_hol).
      INSERT ls_hol-holiday_date INTO TABLE lt_holiday_dates.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_added = 0.
    WHILE lv_added < lv_lead_time.
      lv_date = lv_date + 1.

      DATA(lv_weekday) = 0.
      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_date
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_weekday.

      IF lv_weekday = 6 OR lv_weekday = 7.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_holiday_dates WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_date TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_added = lv_added + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_date.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS get_delivery_date
      IMPORTING

        mat_id     TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE d.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_material,
             mat_id         TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             lead_time_days TYPE i,
           END OF ty_material.
    TYPES ty_material_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_material WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_holiday,
             holiday_date TYPE d,
             name         TYPE c LENGTH 80,
           END OF ty_holiday.
    TYPES ty_holiday_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_holiday WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_holidays_hash TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_holiday WITH UNIQUE KEY holiday_date.

    CLASS-DATA gt_materials TYPE ty_material_tab.
    CLASS-DATA gt_holidays  TYPE ty_holiday_tab.

    CLASS-METHODS to_dats
      IMPORTING
        iv_date_str TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_dats) TYPE d.

    CLASS-METHODS get_lead_time_days
      IMPORTING
        iv_mat_id TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_days) TYPE i.

    CLASS-METHODS get_holiday_hash
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_holidays) TYPE ty_holidays_hash.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD to_dats.
    DATA lv_str TYPE string.
    lv_str = iv_date_str.
    CONDENSE lv_str NO-GAPS.

    IF strlen( lv_str ) >= 10 AND lv_str+4(1) = '-' AND lv_str+7(1) = '-'.
      rv_dats = lv_str(4) && lv_str+5(2) && lv_str+8(2).
    ELSEIF strlen( lv_str ) = 8.
      rv_dats = lv_str(8).
    ELSE.
      rv_dats = '00000000'.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD get_lead_time_days.
    DATA lv_matid TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    rv_days = 0.

    lv_matid = iv_mat_id.

    READ TABLE gt_materials WITH KEY mat_id = lv_matid INTO DATA(ls_mat).
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      rv_days = ls_mat-lead_time_days.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD get_holiday_hash.
    rt_holidays = VALUE #( FOR h IN gt_holidays ( holiday_date = h-holiday_date name = h-name ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD get_delivery_date.
    DATA lv_order_dats TYPE d.
    DATA lv_lead       TYPE i.
    DATA lv_days_added TYPE i.
    DATA lv_date       TYPE d.
    DATA lv_weekday    TYPE i.

    DATA lt_holidays   TYPE ty_holidays_hash.

    lv_order_dats = to_dats( order_date ).
    delivery_date = lv_order_dats.

    IF lv_order_dats IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_lead = get_lead_time_days( mat_id ).
    lt_holidays = get_holiday_hash( ).

    lv_date = lv_order_dats.
    lv_days_added = 0.

    WHILE lv_days_added < lv_lead.
      lv_date = lv_date + 1.

      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_date
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_weekday.

      IF lv_weekday = 6 OR lv_weekday = 7.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_holidays WITH TABLE KEY holiday_date = lv_date TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_days_added = lv_days_added + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_date.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    INTERFACES if_amdp_marker_hdb.

    CLASS-METHODS calculate
      IMPORTING
        order_date TYPE string
        mat_id     TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE d.

  PROTECTED SECTION.
  PRIVATE SECTION.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate.
    DATA lv_order_date TYPE d.
    DATA lv_current    TYPE d.
    DATA lv_lead_time  TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_added      TYPE i VALUE 0.

    TRY.
        lv_order_date = CONV d( order_date ).
      CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_date cx_sy_conversion_error.
        lv_order_date = sy-datum.
    ENDTRY.

    lv_current = lv_order_date.

    "Lead time lookup (optional, only if DDIC table exists/active)
    TRY.
        DATA(lo_rtti_mat) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZMATERIAL' ).
        IF lo_rtti_mat IS BOUND.
          SELECT SINGLE lead_time_days
            FROM zmaterial
            WHERE mat_id = @mat_id
            INTO @lv_lead_time.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            lv_lead_time = 0.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      CATCH cx_sy_type_not_found cx_sy_ref_is_initial cx_root.
        lv_lead_time = 0.
    ENDTRY.

    WHILE lv_added < lv_lead_time.
      lv_current = lv_current + 1.

      DATA lv_dow TYPE i.
      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_current
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_dow.

      IF lv_dow = 6 OR lv_dow = 7.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_is_holiday) = abap_false.

      "Holiday check (optional, only if DDIC table exists/active)
      TRY.
          DATA(lo_rtti_hol) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZHOLIDAY' ).
          IF lo_rtti_hol IS BOUND.
            SELECT SINGLE holiday_date
              FROM zholiday
              WHERE holiday_date = @lv_current
              INTO @DATA(lv_holiday_date_db).
            IF sy-subrc = 0.
              lv_is_holiday = abap_true.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        CATCH cx_sy_type_not_found cx_sy_ref_is_initial cx_root.
          lv_is_holiday = abap_false.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_is_holiday = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_added = lv_added + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_current.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate.
    TYPES ty_holiday_date TYPE d.

    DATA lv_order_date TYPE d.
    DATA lv_date       TYPE d.
    DATA lv_lead_days  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_added      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_dow        TYPE i.
    DATA lv_matid      TYPE c LENGTH 20.

    DATA lt_holidays TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_holiday_date WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_hol_raw  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_holiday_date WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_hdate    TYPE ty_holiday_date.

    delivery_date = '00000000'.

    IF order_date IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_order_date = |{ order_date(4) }{ order_date+5(2) }{ order_date+8(2) }|.
    lv_date = lv_order_date.

    lv_lead_days = 0.
    lv_matid = mat_id.

    TRY.
        SELECT SINGLE lead_time_days
          FROM ('ZMATERIAL')
          WHERE mat_id = @lv_matid
          INTO @lv_lead_days.
      CATCH cx_root.
        lv_lead_days = 0.
    ENDTRY.

    TRY.
        SELECT holiday_date
          FROM ('ZHOLIDAY')
          INTO TABLE @lt_hol_raw.
      CATCH cx_root.
        CLEAR lt_hol_raw.
    ENDTRY.

    LOOP AT lt_hol_raw INTO lv_hdate.
      INSERT lv_hdate INTO TABLE lt_holidays.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_added = 0.
    WHILE lv_added < lv_lead_days.
      lv_date = lv_date + 1.

      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_date
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_dow.

      IF lv_dow = 6 OR lv_dow = 7.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_holidays WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_date TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_added = lv_added + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_date.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS get_delivery_date
      IMPORTING

        mat_id     TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE d.

  PROTECTED SECTION.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_delivery_date.
    DATA lv_order_date   TYPE d.
    DATA lv_mat_id       TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    DATA lv_lead_days    TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_date         TYPE d.
    DATA lv_added        TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_weekday      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_holiday_date TYPE d.
    DATA lv_is_holiday   TYPE abap_bool.

    IF order_date IS INITIAL.
      delivery_date = '00000000'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_order_date = order_date.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '-' IN lv_order_date WITH ''.

    IF NOT ( lv_order_date CO '0123456789' AND strlen( lv_order_date ) = 8 ).
      delivery_date = '00000000'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_mat_id = mat_id.

    TRY.
        SELECT SINGLE lead_time_days
          FROM ('ZMATERIAL')
          WHERE mat_id = @lv_mat_id
          INTO @lv_lead_days.
      CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error cx_sy_sql_error.
        lv_lead_days = 0.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lv_lead_days < 0.
      lv_lead_days = 0.
    ENDIF.

    lv_date = lv_order_date.

    WHILE lv_added < lv_lead_days.
      lv_date = lv_date + 1.

      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_date
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_weekday.

      IF lv_weekday >= 1 AND lv_weekday <= 5.
        lv_is_holiday = abap_false.
        CLEAR lv_holiday_date.

        TRY.
            SELECT SINGLE holiday_date
              FROM ('ZHOLIDAY')
              WHERE holiday_date = @lv_date
              INTO @lv_holiday_date.
            IF sy-subrc = 0.
              lv_is_holiday = abap_true.
            ENDIF.
          CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error cx_sy_sql_error.
            lv_is_holiday = abap_false.
        ENDTRY.

        IF lv_is_holiday = abap_false.
          lv_added = lv_added + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_date.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS calculate_delivery_date
      IMPORTING
        order_date TYPE string
        mat_id     TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE d.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    CLASS-DATA gv_has_ddic TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_undefined.

    CLASS-METHODS has_ddic_tables
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_has) TYPE abap_bool.

    CLASS-METHODS normalize_to_dats
      IMPORTING
        iv_date TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_date) TYPE d.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD has_ddic_tables.
    IF gv_has_ddic = abap_undefined.
      gv_has_ddic = abap_true.

      SELECT SINGLE tabname
        FROM dd02l
        WHERE tabname  = 'ZMATERIAL'
          AND as4local = 'A'
        INTO @DATA(lv_tab1).

      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        gv_has_ddic = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF gv_has_ddic = abap_true.
        SELECT SINGLE tabname
          FROM dd02l
          WHERE tabname  = 'ZHOLIDAY'
            AND as4local = 'A'
          INTO @DATA(lv_tab2).

        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          gv_has_ddic = abap_false.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    rv_has = gv_has_ddic.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD normalize_to_dats.
    rv_date = '00000000'.
    IF iv_date IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv) = iv_date.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '-' IN lv WITH ''.

    IF lv CO '0123456789' AND strlen( lv ) = 8.
      rv_date = lv.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD calculate_delivery_date.
    DATA: lv_order_date      TYPE d,
          lv_mat_id          TYPE c LENGTH 20,
          lv_lead_time_days  TYPE i,
          lv_remaining       TYPE i,
          lv_date            TYPE d,
          lv_dow             TYPE i.

    delivery_date = '00000000'.

    lv_order_date = normalize_to_dats( order_date ).
    IF lv_order_date = '00000000'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_mat_id = mat_id.
    lv_date = lv_order_date.
    lv_lead_time_days = 0.

    IF has_ddic_tables( ) = abap_true.
      DATA(lv_stmt_mat) = |SELECT lead_time_days FROM zmaterial WHERE mat_id = '{ replace( val = lv_mat_id sub = '''' with = '''''' occ = 0 ) }'|.
      TRY.
          EXEC SQL.
            EXECUTE IMMEDIATE :lv_stmt_mat
          ENDEXEC.
        CATCH cx_root.
      ENDTRY.

      EXEC SQL.
        SELECT lead_time_days INTO :lv_lead_time_days
          FROM zmaterial
          WHERE mat_id = :lv_mat_id
      ENDEXEC.

      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        lv_lead_time_days = 0.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    lv_remaining = lv_lead_time_days.

    WHILE lv_remaining > 0.
      lv_date = lv_date + 1.

      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_date
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_dow.

      IF lv_dow BETWEEN 1 AND 5.
        DATA(lv_is_holiday) = abap_false.

        IF has_ddic_tables( ) = abap_true.
          DATA(lv_hol_date) = VALUE d( '00000000' ).

          EXEC SQL.
            SELECT holiday_date INTO :lv_hol_date
              FROM zholiday
              WHERE holiday_date = :lv_date
          ENDEXEC.

          IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_hol_date = lv_date.
            lv_is_holiday = abap_true.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_is_holiday = abap_false.
          lv_remaining = lv_remaining - 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_date.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS calculate
      IMPORTING
        order_date TYPE string
        mat_id     TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE d.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_material,
             mat_id         TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             lead_time_days TYPE i,
           END OF ty_material.
    TYPES tt_material TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_material WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lv_order_date TYPE d.
    DATA lv_mat_id     TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    DATA lv_lead       TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_result     TYPE d.
    DATA lv_added      TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_dow        TYPE i.

    lv_mat_id = mat_id.
    lv_order_date = CONV d( order_date ).
    lv_result = lv_order_date.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_material> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_material> TYPE any.

    ASSIGN ('(PROGRAM)ZMATERIAL') TO <lt_material>.
    IF <lt_material> IS ASSIGNED.
      LOOP AT <lt_material> ASSIGNING <ls_material>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'MAT_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_material> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_mid>).
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <lv_mid> = lv_mat_id.
          ASSIGN COMPONENT 'LEAD_TIME_DAYS' OF STRUCTURE <ls_material> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_ltd>).
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            lv_lead = <lv_ltd>.
          ENDIF.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    WHILE lv_added < lv_lead.
      lv_result = lv_result + 1.

      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_result
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_dow.

      IF lv_dow = 6 OR lv_dow = 7.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_is_holiday) = abap_false.
      FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_holiday> TYPE ANY TABLE.
      FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_holiday> TYPE any.

      ASSIGN ('(PROGRAM)ZHOLIDAYS') TO <lt_holiday>.
      IF <lt_holiday> IS ASSIGNED.
        LOOP AT <lt_holiday> ASSIGNING <ls_holiday>.
          DATA(lv_hdate) = CONV d( '' ).
          TRY.
              lv_hdate = CONV d( <ls_holiday> ).
            CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
              CONTINUE.
          ENDTRY.
          IF lv_hdate = lv_result.
            lv_is_holiday = abap_true.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
        ENDLOOP.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_is_holiday = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_added = lv_added + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS calculate
      IMPORTING
        order_date TYPE string
        mat_id     TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(delivery_date) TYPE d.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_planned_delivery_date IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate.
    DATA lv_order_date TYPE d.
    DATA lv_date       TYPE d.
    DATA lv_dow        TYPE i.
    DATA lv_lead_time  TYPE i VALUE 0.

    delivery_date = '00000000'.

    lv_order_date = order_date.
    lv_date = lv_order_date.

    WHILE lv_lead_time > 0.
      lv_date = lv_date + 1.

      CALL FUNCTION 'DATE_COMPUTE_DAY'
        EXPORTING
          date = lv_date
        IMPORTING
          day  = lv_dow.

      IF lv_dow = 6 OR lv_dow = 7.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_lead_time = lv_lead_time - 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    delivery_date = lv_date.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_min_total_duration.
    rv_duration = 0.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS get_total_duration
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_total_duration) TYPE i.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD get_total_duration.
    TYPES: ty_step_id TYPE c LENGTH 10.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_step,
             step_id  TYPE ty_step_id,
             duration TYPE i,
           END OF ty_step,
           tt_step TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_step WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             from_step TYPE ty_step_id,
             to_step   TYPE ty_step_id,
           END OF ty_edge,
           tt_edge TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_in,
             step_id TYPE ty_step_id,
             indeg   TYPE i,
           END OF ty_in,
           tt_in TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_in WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_dist,
             step_id TYPE ty_step_id,
             dist    TYPE i,
           END OF ty_dist,
           tt_dist TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_dist WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    DATA lt_steps TYPE tt_step.
    DATA lt_edges TYPE tt_edge.
    DATA lt_in    TYPE tt_in.
    DATA lt_dist  TYPE tt_dist.

    DATA lr_table TYPE REF TO data.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_any>   TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <ls_any>   TYPE any,
                   <lv_any>   TYPE any,
                   <lv_sid>   TYPE any,
                   <lv_dur>   TYPE any,
                   <lv_from>  TYPE any,
                   <lv_to>    TYPE any.

    TRY.
        cl_abap_tabledescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZFS_DATA' ).
      CATCH cx_sy_type_not_found.
        rv_total_duration = 0.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    TRY.
        cl_abap_tabledescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZFNET_DATA' ).
      CATCH cx_sy_type_not_found.
        rv_total_duration = 0.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    CREATE DATA lr_table TYPE ('ZFS_DATA').
    ASSIGN lr_table->* TO <lt_any>.
    IF <lt_any> IS ASSIGNED.
      SELECT *
        FROM ('ZFS_DATA')
        INTO TABLE @<lt_any>.
    ENDIF.

    IF <lt_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lt_any> IS INITIAL.
      rv_total_duration = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <lt_any> ASSIGNING <ls_any>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'STEP_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_any> TO <lv_sid>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'DURATION' OF STRUCTURE <ls_any> TO <lv_dur>.
      IF <lv_sid> IS ASSIGNED AND <lv_dur> IS ASSIGNED.
        INSERT VALUE ty_step( step_id = |{ <lv_sid> }| duration = CONV i( <lv_dur> ) ) INTO TABLE lt_steps.
        INSERT VALUE ty_in( step_id = |{ <lv_sid> }| indeg = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_in.
        INSERT VALUE ty_dist( step_id = |{ <lv_sid> }| dist = CONV i( <lv_dur> ) ) INTO TABLE lt_dist.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    CLEAR <lt_any>.
    FREE lr_table.

    CREATE DATA lr_table TYPE ('ZFNET_DATA').
    ASSIGN lr_table->* TO <lt_any>.
    IF <lt_any> IS ASSIGNED.
      SELECT *
        FROM ('ZFNET_DATA')
        INTO TABLE @<lt_any>.
    ENDIF.

    IF <lt_any> IS ASSIGNED AND <lt_any> IS NOT INITIAL.
      LOOP AT <lt_any> ASSIGNING <ls_any>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'FROM_STEP' OF STRUCTURE <ls_any> TO <lv_from>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'TO_STEP'   OF STRUCTURE <ls_any> TO <lv_to>.
        IF <lv_from> IS ASSIGNED AND <lv_to> IS ASSIGNED.
          DATA(lv_from_id) = |{ <lv_from> }|.
          DATA(lv_to_id)   = |{ <lv_to> }|.

          IF line_exists( lt_steps[ step_id = lv_from_id ] )
             AND line_exists( lt_steps[ step_id = lv_to_id ] ).
            APPEND VALUE ty_edge( from_step = lv_from_id to_step = lv_to_id ) TO lt_edges.
            READ TABLE lt_in ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_in_to>) WITH KEY step_id = lv_to_id.
            IF sy-subrc = 0.
              <ls_in_to>-indeg = <ls_in_to>-indeg + 1.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_step_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_in ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_in>).
      IF <ls_in>-indeg = 0.
        APPEND <ls_in>-step_id TO lt_queue.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_qidx TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_processed TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_total_steps TYPE i.
    lv_total_steps = lines( lt_steps ).

    WHILE lv_qidx <= lines( lt_queue ).
      DATA(lv_u) = lt_queue[ lv_qidx ].
      lv_qidx = lv_qidx + 1.
      lv_processed = lv_processed + 1.

      READ TABLE lt_dist ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_du>) WITH KEY step_id = lv_u.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_e>) WHERE from_step = lv_u.
        READ TABLE lt_steps ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_vstep>) WITH KEY step_id = <ls_e>-to_step.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_dist ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_dv>) WITH KEY step_id = <ls_e>-to_step.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          DATA(lv_cand) = <ls_du>-dist + <ls_vstep>-duration.
          IF lv_cand > <ls_dv>-dist.
            <ls_dv>-dist = lv_cand.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_in ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_in_to2>) WITH KEY step_id = <ls_e>-to_step.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          <ls_in_to2>-indeg = <ls_in_to2>-indeg - 1.
          IF <ls_in_to2>-indeg = 0.
            APPEND <ls_in_to2>-step_id TO lt_queue.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_processed <> lv_total_steps.
      rv_total_duration = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_total_duration = 0.
    LOOP AT lt_dist ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_out>).
      IF <ls_out>-dist > rv_total_duration.
        rv_total_duration = <ls_out>-dist.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    INTERFACES if_amdp_marker_hdb.
    CLASS-METHODS get_min_total_duration
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_duration) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_min_total_duration.
    rv_duration = 0.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF zfs_data,
             step_id      TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             description  TYPE c LENGTH 50,
             duration     TYPE i,
           END OF zfs_data.
    TYPES tt_zfs_data TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zfs_data WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF zfnet_data,
             from_step TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             to_step   TYPE c LENGTH 10,
           END OF zfnet_data.
    TYPES tt_zfnet_data TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zfnet_data WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS calculate
      IMPORTING
        it_steps        TYPE tt_zfs_data
        it_dependencies TYPE tt_zfnet_data
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_duration) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate.
    TYPES ty_step_id TYPE c LENGTH 10.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node,
             step_id   TYPE ty_step_id,
             duration  TYPE i,
             indegree  TYPE i,
             longest   TYPE i,
           END OF ty_node.
    TYPES ty_nodes TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             from_step TYPE ty_step_id,
             to_step   TYPE ty_step_id,
           END OF ty_edge.
    TYPES ty_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_nodes TYPE ty_nodes.
    DATA lt_edges TYPE ty_edges.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <fs_step> TYPE zfs_data.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <fs_dep>  TYPE zfnet_data.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <fs_node> TYPE ty_node.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <fs_to>   TYPE ty_node.

    LOOP AT it_steps ASSIGNING <fs_step>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_node(
        step_id  = <fs_step>-step_id
        duration = <fs_step>-duration
        indegree = 0
        longest  = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT it_dependencies ASSIGNING <fs_dep>.
      APPEND VALUE ty_edge( from_step = <fs_dep>-from_step to_step = <fs_dep>-to_step ) TO lt_edges.

      ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = <fs_dep>-from_step ] TO <fs_node>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT VALUE ty_node( step_id = <fs_dep>-from_step duration = 0 indegree = 0 longest = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = <fs_dep>-to_step ] TO <fs_node>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT VALUE ty_node( step_id = <fs_dep>-to_step duration = 0 indegree = 0 longest = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = <fs_dep>-to_step ] TO <fs_node>.
      <fs_node>-indegree = <fs_node>-indegree + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_step_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING <fs_node>.
      IF <fs_node>-indegree = 0.
        APPEND <fs_node>-step_id TO lt_queue.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_id  TYPE ty_step_id.

    WHILE lv_idx <= lines( lt_queue ).
      lv_id = lt_queue[ lv_idx ].
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = lv_id ] TO <fs_node>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <fs_node>-longest < <fs_node>-duration.
        <fs_node>-longest = <fs_node>-duration.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<fs_edge>) WHERE from_step = lv_id.
        ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = <fs_edge>-to_step ] TO <fs_to>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lv_candidate) = <fs_node>-longest + <fs_to>-duration.
        IF lv_candidate > <fs_to>-longest.
          <fs_to>-longest = lv_candidate.
        ENDIF.

        <fs_to>-indegree = <fs_to>-indegree - 1.
        IF <fs_to>-indegree = 0.
          APPEND <fs_to>-step_id TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_duration = 0.
    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING <fs_node>.
      IF <fs_node>-longest > rv_duration.
        rv_duration = <fs_node>-longest.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS calculate_duration
      IMPORTING
        it_steps        TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zfs_data
        it_dependencies TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zfnet_data
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_duration) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD calculate_duration.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node,
             step_id   TYPE zfs_data-step_id,
             duration  TYPE i,
             indegree  TYPE i,
             earliest  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_node.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             from_step TYPE zfnet_data-from_step,
             to_step   TYPE zfnet_data-to_step,
           END OF ty_edge.

    DATA: lt_nodes TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id,
          lt_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ls_step> TYPE zfs_data,
                   <ls_dep>  TYPE zfnet_data,
                   <ls_node> TYPE ty_node.

    LOOP AT it_steps ASSIGNING <ls_step>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_node(
        step_id  = <ls_step>-step_id
        duration = <ls_step>-duration
        indegree = 0
        earliest = 0
      ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT it_dependencies ASSIGNING <ls_dep>.
      APPEND VALUE ty_edge( from_step = <ls_dep>-from_step to_step = <ls_dep>-to_step ) TO lt_edges.

      READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <ls_dep>-from_step TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT VALUE ty_node( step_id = <ls_dep>-from_step duration = 0 indegree = 0 earliest = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <ls_dep>-to_step TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT VALUE ty_node( step_id = <ls_dep>-to_step duration = 0 indegree = 0 earliest = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = <ls_dep>-to_step ] TO <ls_node>.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        <ls_node>-indegree = <ls_node>-indegree + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zfs_data-step_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING <ls_node>.
      IF <ls_node>-indegree = 0.
        APPEND <ls_node>-step_id TO lt_queue.
        <ls_node>-earliest = <ls_node>-duration.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_head TYPE i VALUE 1.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_edge> TYPE ty_edge.

    WHILE lv_head <= lines( lt_queue ).
      DATA(lv_current) = lt_queue[ lv_head ].
      lv_head = lv_head + 1.

      ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = lv_current ] TO <ls_node>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <ls_edge> WHERE from_step = lv_current.
        FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_to_node> TYPE ty_node.
        ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = <ls_edge>-to_step ] TO <ls_to_node>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lv_candidate) = <ls_node>-earliest + <ls_to_node>-duration.
        IF lv_candidate > <ls_to_node>-earliest.
          <ls_to_node>-earliest = lv_candidate.
        ENDIF.

        <ls_to_node>-indegree = <ls_to_node>-indegree - 1.
        IF <ls_to_node>-indegree = 0.
          APPEND <ls_edge>-to_step TO lt_queue.
          IF <ls_to_node>-earliest = 0.
            <ls_to_node>-earliest = <ls_to_node>-duration.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_duration = 0.
    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING <ls_node>.
      IF <ls_node>-earliest > rv_duration.
        rv_duration = <ls_node>-earliest.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS get_min_total_duration
      IMPORTING
        it_fs_data   TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        it_fnet_data TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_duration) TYPE i.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             from_step TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             to_step   TYPE c LENGTH 10,
           END OF ty_edge.
    TYPES ty_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node,
             step_id    TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             duration   TYPE i,
             indegree   TYPE i,
             best_start TYPE i,
           END OF ty_node.
    TYPES ty_nodes_h TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_min_total_duration.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_fs>  TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <lt_net> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <ls_fs>  TYPE any,
                   <ls_net> TYPE any,
                   <v_step> TYPE any,
                   <v_dur>  TYPE any,
                   <v_from> TYPE any,
                   <v_to>   TYPE any.

    ASSIGN it_fs_data   TO <lt_fs>.
    ASSIGN it_fnet_data TO <lt_net>.

    DATA lt_nodes TYPE ty_nodes_h.
    DATA lt_edges TYPE ty_edges.

    rv_duration = 0.

    IF <lt_fs> IS ASSIGNED.
      LOOP AT <lt_fs> ASSIGNING <ls_fs>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'STEP_ID'  OF STRUCTURE <ls_fs> TO <v_step>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'DURATION' OF STRUCTURE <ls_fs> TO <v_dur>.
        IF <v_step> IS ASSIGNED AND <v_dur> IS ASSIGNED.
          DATA lv_step_id TYPE c LENGTH 10.
          DATA lv_duration TYPE i.
          lv_step_id = <v_step>.
          lv_duration = <v_dur>.

          INSERT VALUE ty_node(
            step_id    = lv_step_id
            duration   = lv_duration
            indegree   = 0
            best_start = 0
          ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    IF <lt_net> IS ASSIGNED.
      LOOP AT <lt_net> ASSIGNING <ls_net>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'FROM_STEP' OF STRUCTURE <ls_net> TO <v_from>.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'TO_STEP'   OF STRUCTURE <ls_net> TO <v_to>.
        IF <v_from> IS ASSIGNED AND <v_to> IS ASSIGNED.
          DATA lv_from TYPE c LENGTH 10.
          DATA lv_to TYPE c LENGTH 10.
          lv_from = <v_from>.
          lv_to = <v_to>.

          IF line_exists( lt_nodes[ step_id = lv_from ] )
             AND line_exists( lt_nodes[ step_id = lv_to ] ).
            APPEND VALUE ty_edge( from_step = lv_from to_step = lv_to ) TO lt_edges.
            ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = lv_to ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<to_node>).
            <to_node>-indegree = <to_node>-indegree + 1.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_q,
             step_id TYPE c LENGTH 10,
           END OF ty_q.
    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_q WITH EMPTY KEY.

    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      IF <n>-indegree = 0.
        APPEND VALUE ty_q( step_id = <n>-step_id ) TO lt_queue.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 1.
    WHILE lv_idx <= lines( lt_queue ).
      DATA lv_step TYPE c LENGTH 10.
      lv_step = lt_queue[ lv_idx ]-step_id.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = lv_step ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<node>).
      IF <node> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lv_end TYPE i.
      lv_end = <node>-best_start + <node>-duration.
      IF lv_end > rv_duration.
        rv_duration = lv_end.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ed>) WHERE from_step = lv_step.
        ASSIGN lt_nodes[ step_id = <ed>-to_step ] TO <to_node>.
        IF <to_node> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_end > <to_node>-best_start.
          <to_node>-best_start = lv_end.
        ENDIF.

        <to_node>-indegree = <to_node>-indegree - 1.
        IF <to_node>-indegree = 0.
          APPEND VALUE ty_q( step_id = <to_node>-step_id ) TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_production_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS get_min_total_duration
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_duration) TYPE i.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    TYPES ty_step_id TYPE c LENGTH 10.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_step,
             step_id  TYPE ty_step_id,
             duration TYPE i,
           END OF ty_step.
    TYPES ty_steps TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_step WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             from_step TYPE ty_step_id,
             to_step   TYPE ty_step_id,
           END OF ty_edge.
    TYPES ty_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node,
             step_id TYPE ty_step_id,
             indeg   TYPE i,
             dp      TYPE i,
           END OF ty_node.
    TYPES ty_nodes TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES ty_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_step_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_production_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_min_total_duration.
    rv_duration = 0.

    DATA lt_steps TYPE ty_steps.
    DATA lt_edges TYPE ty_edges.
    DATA lt_nodes TYPE ty_nodes.
    DATA lt_queue TYPE ty_queue.

    DATA lt_steps_db TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_step WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_edges_db TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    SELECT step_id, duration
      FROM ('ZFS_DATA')
      INTO TABLE @lt_steps_db.

    IF lt_steps_db IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_steps_db ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<sdb>).
      INSERT VALUE ty_step(
        step_id  = <sdb>-step_id
        duration = <sdb>-duration
      ) INTO TABLE lt_steps.
    ENDLOOP.

    SELECT from_step, to_step
      FROM ('ZFNET_DATA')
      INTO TABLE @lt_edges_db.

    LOOP AT lt_edges_db ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<edb>).
      READ TABLE lt_steps WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <edb>-from_step TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.
      READ TABLE lt_steps WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <edb>-to_step TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.
      APPEND VALUE ty_edge( from_step = <edb>-from_step to_step = <edb>-to_step ) TO lt_edges.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_steps ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<st>).
      INSERT VALUE ty_node(
        step_id = <st>-step_id
        indeg   = 0
        dp      = <st>-duration
      ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e1>).
      READ TABLE lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n_to>) WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <e1>-to_step.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        <n_to>-indeg = <n_to>-indeg + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<nq>).
      IF <nq>-indeg = 0.
        APPEND <nq>-step_id TO lt_queue.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 1.
    WHILE lv_idx <= lines( lt_queue ).
      DATA(lv_u) = lt_queue[ lv_idx ].

      READ TABLE lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<nu>) WITH TABLE KEY step_id = lv_u.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e2>) WHERE from_step = lv_u.
        READ TABLE lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<nv>) WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <e2>-to_step.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_steps ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<stv>) WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <e2>-to_step.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lv_candidate) = <nu>-dp + <stv>-duration.
        IF lv_candidate > <nv>-dp.
          <nv>-dp = lv_candidate.
        ENDIF.

        <nv>-indeg = <nv>-indeg - 1.
        IF <nv>-indeg = 0.
          APPEND <nv>-step_id TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.

      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<nmax>).
      IF <nmax>-dp > rv_duration.
        rv_duration = <nmax>-dp.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

ENDCLASS.
