CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_step_id TYPE c LENGTH 10.

    CLASS-METHODS get_min_total_duration
      IMPORTING
        it_steps        TYPE ANY TABLE
        it_dependencies TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_total_duration) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.


CLASS zcl_prod_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_min_total_duration.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_step_h,
             step_id  TYPE ty_step_id,
             duration TYPE i,
           END OF ty_step_h.
    TYPES ty_t_step_h TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_step_h WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_indeg,
             step_id TYPE ty_step_id,
             indeg   TYPE i,
           END OF ty_indeg.
    TYPES ty_t_indeg TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_indeg WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_dist,
             step_id TYPE ty_step_id,
             dist    TYPE i,
           END OF ty_dist.
    TYPES ty_t_dist TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_dist WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES ty_t_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_step_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_steps_h TYPE ty_t_step_h.
    DATA lt_indeg   TYPE ty_t_indeg.
    DATA lt_dist    TYPE ty_t_dist.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <steps> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <deps>  TYPE ANY TABLE.

    ASSIGN it_steps        TO <steps>.
    ASSIGN it_dependencies TO <deps>.

    IF <steps> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR lines( <steps> ) = 0.
      rv_total_duration = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <steps> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<s>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'STEP_ID' OF STRUCTURE <s> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<sid>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'DURATION' OF STRUCTURE <s> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<dur>).
      IF <sid> IS ASSIGNED AND <dur> IS ASSIGNED.
        INSERT VALUE ty_step_h(
          step_id  = CONV ty_step_id( <sid> )
          duration = CONV i( <dur> )
        ) INTO TABLE lt_steps_h.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lt_steps_h IS INITIAL.
      rv_total_duration = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_steps_h ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<st>).
      INSERT VALUE ty_indeg( step_id = <st>-step_id indeg = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_indeg.
      INSERT VALUE ty_dist( step_id = <st>-step_id dist = <st>-duration ) INTO TABLE lt_dist.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF <deps> IS ASSIGNED AND lines( <deps> ) > 0.
      LOOP AT <deps> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e>).
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'TO_STEP' OF STRUCTURE <e> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<to>).
        IF <to> IS ASSIGNED.
          ASSIGN lt_indeg[ step_id = CONV ty_step_id( <to> ) ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<ind>).
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            <ind>-indeg = <ind>-indeg + 1.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_queue TYPE ty_t_queue.
    LOOP AT lt_indeg ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<inq>).
      IF <inq>-indeg = 0.
        APPEND <inq>-step_id TO lt_queue.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 1.
    WHILE lv_idx <= lines( lt_queue ).
      DATA(lv_u) = lt_queue[ lv_idx ].
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      ASSIGN lt_dist[ step_id = lv_u ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<du>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <deps> IS ASSIGNED AND lines( <deps> ) > 0.
        LOOP AT <deps> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ed>).
          ASSIGN COMPONENT 'FROM_STEP' OF STRUCTURE <ed> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<from>).
          ASSIGN COMPONENT 'TO_STEP'   OF STRUCTURE <ed> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<to2>).
          IF <from> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <to2> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
            CONTINUE.
          ENDIF.
          IF CONV ty_step_id( <from> ) <> lv_u.
            CONTINUE.
          ENDIF.

          DATA(lv_v) = CONV ty_step_id( <to2> ).

          ASSIGN lt_steps_h[ step_id = lv_v ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<sv>).
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            CONTINUE.
          ENDIF.

          ASSIGN lt_dist[ step_id = lv_v ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<dv>).
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            DATA(lv_new) = <du>-dist + <sv>-duration.
            IF lv_new > <dv>-dist.
              <dv>-dist = lv_new.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.

          ASSIGN lt_indeg[ step_id = lv_v ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<indv>).
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            <indv>-indeg = <indv>-indeg - 1.
            IF <indv>-indeg = 0.
              APPEND <indv>-step_id TO lt_queue.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.
        ENDLOOP.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_total_duration = 0.
    LOOP AT lt_dist ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<d>).
      IF <d>-dist > rv_total_duration.
        rv_total_duration = <d>-dist.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_production_critical_path DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    INTERFACES if_oo_adt_classrun.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF zfs_data,
             step_id     TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             description TYPE c LENGTH 50,
             duration    TYPE i,
           END OF zfs_data.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF zfnet_data,
             from_step TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             to_step   TYPE c LENGTH 10,
           END OF zfnet_data.

    CLASS-METHODS get_min_total_duration
      IMPORTING
        it_steps        TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        it_dependencies TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_duration) TYPE i.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    TYPES ty_step_id TYPE c LENGTH 10.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node,
             step_id  TYPE ty_step_id,
             duration TYPE i,
             indegree TYPE i,
           END OF ty_node.
    TYPES ty_nodes TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_adj,
             from_step TYPE ty_step_id,
             to_step   TYPE ty_step_id,
           END OF ty_adj.
    TYPES ty_adj_tab TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_adj WITH NON-UNIQUE KEY from_step.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_dist,
             step_id TYPE ty_step_id,
             dist    TYPE i,
           END OF ty_dist.
    TYPES ty_dist_tab TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_dist WITH UNIQUE KEY step_id.

    TYPES ty_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_step_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_production_critical_path IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD get_min_total_duration.
    rv_duration = 0.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_steps> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <lt_deps>  TYPE ANY TABLE.

    ASSIGN it_steps        TO <lt_steps>.
    ASSIGN it_dependencies TO <lt_deps>.

    IF <lt_steps> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lt_steps> IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_nodes TYPE ty_nodes.

    LOOP AT <lt_steps> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_any_step>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'STEP_ID' OF STRUCTURE <ls_any_step> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_step_id_any>).
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'DURATION' OF STRUCTURE <ls_any_step> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_duration_any>).

      IF <lv_step_id_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lv_duration_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_step_id) = CONV ty_step_id( <lv_step_id_any> ).
      DATA(lv_duration) = CONV i( <lv_duration_any> ).

      INSERT VALUE ty_node(
        step_id  = lv_step_id
        duration = lv_duration
        indegree = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lt_nodes IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_adj TYPE ty_adj_tab.

    IF <lt_deps> IS ASSIGNED AND <lt_deps> IS NOT INITIAL.
      LOOP AT <lt_deps> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_any_dep>).
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'FROM_STEP' OF STRUCTURE <ls_any_dep> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_from_any>).
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'TO_STEP'   OF STRUCTURE <ls_any_dep> TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_to_any>).

        IF <lv_from_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <lv_to_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lv_from) = CONV ty_step_id( <lv_from_any> ).
        DATA(lv_to)   = CONV ty_step_id( <lv_to_any> ).

        READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY step_id = lv_from TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.
        READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY step_id = lv_to TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        INSERT VALUE ty_adj( from_step = lv_from to_step = lv_to ) INTO TABLE lt_adj.

        READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY step_id = lv_to ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n_to>).
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          <n_to>-indegree = <n_to>-indegree + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_dist TYPE ty_dist_tab.
    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      INSERT VALUE ty_dist( step_id = <n>-step_id dist = <n>-duration ) INTO TABLE lt_dist.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_queue TYPE ty_queue.
    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING <n>.
      IF <n>-indegree = 0.
        APPEND <n>-step_id TO lt_queue.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_processed TYPE i VALUE 0.

    WHILE lt_queue IS NOT INITIAL.
      READ TABLE lt_queue INDEX 1 INTO DATA(lv_u).
      DELETE lt_queue INDEX 1.

      lv_processed = lv_processed + 1.

      READ TABLE lt_dist WITH TABLE KEY step_id = lv_u ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<du>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      LOOP AT lt_adj ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<a>) WHERE from_step = lv_u.
        READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <a>-to_step ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n_v>).
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_dist WITH TABLE KEY step_id = <a>-to_step ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<dv>).
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lv_candidate) = <du>-dist + <n_v>-duration.
        IF lv_candidate > <dv>-dist.
          <dv>-dist = lv_candidate.
        ENDIF.

        <n_v>-indegree = <n_v>-indegree - 1.
        IF <n_v>-indegree = 0.
          APPEND <n_v>-step_id TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_processed <> lines( lt_nodes ).
      rv_duration = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_dist ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<d>).
      IF <d>-dist > rv_duration.
        rv_duration = <d>-dist.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD if_oo_adt_classrun~main.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_flight_search DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_flight_result,
             carrname   TYPE scarr-carrname,
             cityfrom   TYPE spfli-cityfrom,
             cityto     TYPE spfli-cityto,
             fltime     TYPE spfli-fltime,
             free_seats TYPE sflight-seatsmax,
           END OF ty_flight_result,
           tt_flight_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_flight_result WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS get_available_flights
      IMPORTING
        origin_city      TYPE char20
        destination_city TYPE char20
        flight_date      TYPE dats
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_result) TYPE tt_flight_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_flight_search IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_available_flights.
    SELECT
      c~carrname                                 AS carrname,
      p~cityfrom                                 AS cityfrom,
      p~cityto                                   AS cityto,
      p~fltime                                   AS fltime,
      CAST( ( f~seatsmax - f~seatsocc ) AS INT4 ) AS free_seats
      FROM sflight AS f
      INNER JOIN spfli AS p
        ON  p~carrid = f~carrid
        AND p~connid = f~connid
      INNER JOIN scarr AS c
        ON c~carrid = f~carrid
      WHERE p~cityfrom = @origin_city
        AND p~cityto   = @destination_city
        AND f~fldate   = @flight_date
        AND ( f~seatsmax - f~seatsocc ) > 0
      INTO TABLE @rt_result.

    SORT rt_result BY carrname cityfrom cityto fltime free_seats DESCENDING.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      WHERE f~fldate   = @flight_date
        AND p~cityfrom = @origin_city
        AND p~cityto   = @destination_city
        AND f~seatsmax > f~seatsocc
      INTO TABLE @rt_result.
  ENDMETHOD.

        flight_date      TYPE dats
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_result) TYPE tt_string.

CLASS zcl_flight_search IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_available_flights.
    SELECT
      concat_with_space(
        concat_with_space(
          concat_with_space(
            concat_with_space(
              carr~carrname,
              con~cityfrom,
              1 ),
            con~cityto,
            1 ),
          CAST( con~fltime AS abap.char(10) ),
          1 ),
        CAST( flt~seatsmax - flt~seatsocc AS abap.char(10) ),
        1 ) AS line
      FROM sflight AS flt
      INNER JOIN spfli AS con
        ON con~carrid = flt~carrid
       AND con~connid = flt~connid
      INNER JOIN scarr AS carr
        ON carr~carrid = flt~carrid
      WHERE con~cityfrom = @origin_city
        AND con~cityto   = @destination_city
        AND flt~fldate   = @flight_date
        AND flt~seatsmax > flt~seatsocc
      INTO TABLE @rt_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_factorial DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.

    CLASS-METHODS special_factorial
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_factorial IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD special_factorial.
    DATA res  TYPE ty_result VALUE '1'.
    DATA fact TYPE ty_result VALUE '1'.
    DATA i    TYPE i.

    IF n <= 0.
      result = CONV ty_result( 0 ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO n TIMES.
      i = sy-index.
      fact = fact * CONV ty_result( i ).
      res  = res  * fact.
    ENDDO.

    result = res.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_histogram DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS histogram
      IMPORTING
        test          TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_histogram IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD histogram.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_count,
             letter TYPE c LENGTH 1,
             count  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_count.

    DATA lt_tokens TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_counts TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_count WITH UNIQUE KEY letter.
    DATA ls_count  TYPE ty_count.
    DATA lv_token  TYPE string.
    DATA lv_letter TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_max    TYPE i VALUE 0.

    DATA lt_max_letters TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF c WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
    DATA lv_json TYPE string.
    DATA lv_first TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    SPLIT test AT space INTO TABLE lt_tokens.

    LOOP AT lt_tokens INTO lv_token.
      IF lv_token IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_letter = lv_token+0(1).

      READ TABLE lt_counts WITH TABLE KEY letter = lv_letter INTO ls_count.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        ls_count-count = ls_count-count + 1.
        MODIFY TABLE lt_counts FROM ls_count.
      ELSE.
        ls_count-letter = lv_letter.
        ls_count-count  = 1.
        INSERT ls_count INTO TABLE lt_counts.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_counts INTO ls_count.
      IF ls_count-count > lv_max.
        lv_max = ls_count-count.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_max = 0.
      result = ``.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_counts INTO ls_count.
      IF ls_count-count = lv_max.
        APPEND ls_count-letter TO lt_max_letters.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_max_letters.

    lv_json = '{'.
    LOOP AT lt_max_letters INTO lv_letter.
      IF lv_first = abap_false.
        lv_json = lv_json && ','.
      ENDIF.
      lv_json = lv_json && |"{ lv_letter }":{ lv_max }|.
      lv_first = abap_false.
    ENDLOOP.
    lv_json = lv_json && '}'.

    result = lv_json.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_by_length DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab    TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int    WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_string_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS by_length
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_names) TYPE ty_string_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_by_length IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD by_length.
    DATA lt_digits TYPE ty_int_tab.
    DATA lv_n      TYPE int.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_n WHERE lv_n BETWEEN 1 AND 9.
      APPEND lv_n TO lt_digits.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_digits ASCENDING.

    DATA(lv_lines) = lines( lt_digits ).

    DO lv_lines TIMES.
      READ TABLE lt_digits INTO lv_n INDEX ( lv_lines - sy-index + 1 ).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CASE lv_n.
        WHEN 1. APPEND `One`   TO rt_names.
        WHEN 2. APPEND `Two`   TO rt_names.
        WHEN 3. APPEND `Three` TO rt_names.
        WHEN 4. APPEND `Four`  TO rt_names.
        WHEN 5. APPEND `Five`  TO rt_names.
        WHEN 6. APPEND `Six`   TO rt_names.
        WHEN 7. APPEND `Seven` TO rt_names.
        WHEN 8. APPEND `Eight` TO rt_names.
        WHEN 9. APPEND `Nine`  TO rt_names.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_by_length DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

CLASS zcl_by_length IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD by_length.

        WHEN 3. APPEND `Three` TO rt_names.

CLASS zcl_by_length DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_string_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS by_length
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_names) TYPE ty_string_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_by_length IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD by_length.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    DATA lt_filtered TYPE SORTED TABLE OF i WITH NON-UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT it_arr ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      TRY.
          DATA(lv_num) = CONV i( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_num BETWEEN 1 AND 9.
        INSERT lv_num INTO TABLE lt_filtered.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA(lv_lines) = lines( lt_filtered ).

    DO lv_lines TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx) = lv_lines - sy-index + 1.
      DATA(lv_val) = lt_filtered[ lv_idx ].

      DATA(lv_name) = SWITCH string(
        lv_val
        WHEN 1 THEN `One`
        WHEN 2 THEN `Two`
        WHEN 3 THEN `Three`
        WHEN 4 THEN `Four`
        WHEN 5 THEN `Five`
        WHEN 6 THEN `Six`
        WHEN 7 THEN `Seven`
        WHEN 8 THEN `Eight`
        WHEN 9 THEN `Nine`
        ELSE `` ).

      IF lv_name IS NOT INITIAL.
        APPEND lv_name TO rt_names.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_by_length DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS by_length
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_names) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_by_length IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD by_length.
    DATA lt_digits TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
    DATA lv_digit  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_lines  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx    TYPE i.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_digit WHERE ( table_line BETWEEN 1 AND 9 ).
      APPEND lv_digit TO lt_digits.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_digits ASCENDING.

    lv_lines = lines( lt_digits ).
    DO lv_lines TIMES.
      lv_idx = lv_lines - sy-index + 1.
      READ TABLE lt_digits INDEX lv_idx INTO lv_digit.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CASE lv_digit.
        WHEN 1. APPEND `One`   TO rt_names.
        WHEN 2. APPEND `Two`   TO rt_names.
        WHEN 3. APPEND `Three` TO rt_names.
        WHEN 4. APPEND `Four`  TO rt_names.
        WHEN 5. APPEND `Five`  TO rt_names.
        WHEN 6. APPEND `Six`   TO rt_names.
        WHEN 7. APPEND `Seven` TO rt_names.
        WHEN 8. APPEND `Eight` TO rt_names.
        WHEN 9. APPEND `Nine`  TO rt_names.
        WHEN OTHERS.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.

        it_x TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_result) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

CLASS zcl_unique_digits IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD unique_digits.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE any.

    DATA lv_orig  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_num   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_digit TYPE i.
    DATA lv_ok    TYPE abap_bool.

    rt_result = VALUE #( ).

    LOOP AT it_x ASSIGNING <n>.
      lv_orig = <n>.
      IF lv_orig <= 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_num = lv_orig.
      lv_ok  = abap_true.

      WHILE lv_num > 0.
        lv_digit = lv_num MOD 10.
        IF ( lv_digit MOD 2 ) = 0.
          lv_ok = abap_false.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
        lv_num = lv_num DIV 10.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF lv_ok = abap_true.
        INSERT lv_orig INTO TABLE rt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT rt_result BY table_line ASCENDING.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_unique_digits IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD unique_digits.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_num> TYPE any.

    DATA lt_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.
    DATA lv_num_i  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_str    TYPE string.
    DATA lv_ok     TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_idx    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char   TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_digit  TYPE i.

    CLEAR lt_result.

    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <lv_num>.
      TRY.
          lv_num_i = <lv_num>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_str = |{ lv_num_i }|.
      lv_ok = abap_true.

      DO strlen( lv_str ) TIMES.
        lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
        lv_char = lv_str+lv_idx(1).
        lv_digit = lv_char.
        IF lv_digit MOD 2 = 0.
          lv_ok = abap_false.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      IF lv_ok = abap_true.
        APPEND lv_num_i TO lt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_result ASCENDING.
    rt_numbers = lt_result.

    TYPES ty_numbers TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_number WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    CLASS-METHODS unique_digits
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_number WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_numbers) TYPE ty_numbers.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_unique_digits IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD unique_digits.
    DATA lt_result TYPE ty_numbers.
    DATA lv_num    TYPE ty_number.
    DATA lv_value  TYPE ty_number.
    DATA lv_digit  TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_ok     TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_len    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx    TYPE i.

    LOOP AT it_numbers INTO lv_num.
      lv_ok = abap_true.

      IF lv_num IS INITIAL.
        lv_ok = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_value = lv_num.
        SHIFT lv_value LEFT DELETING LEADING '0'.
        IF lv_value IS INITIAL.
          lv_ok = abap_false.
        ELSE.
          lv_len = strlen( lv_value ).
          lv_idx = 0.
          WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
            lv_digit = lv_value+lv_idx(1).
            IF lv_digit CA '02468'.
              lv_ok = abap_false.
              EXIT.
            ENDIF.
            lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
          ENDWHILE.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_ok = abap_true.
        INSERT lv_num INTO TABLE lt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_numbers = lt_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_unique_digits IMPLEMENTATION.

    DATA lv_str      TYPE string.
    DATA lv_len      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char     TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_has_even TYPE abap_bool.

    LOOP AT it_numbers INTO lv_num.
      lv_str = |{ lv_num }|.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_str ).
      lv_has_even = abap_false.

      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
        lv_char = lv_str+lv_idx(1).
        CASE lv_char.
          WHEN '0' OR '2' OR '4' OR '6' OR '8'.
            lv_has_even = abap_true.
            EXIT.
        ENDCASE.
      ENDDO.

      IF lv_has_even = abap_false.
        INSERT lv_num INTO TABLE lt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_numbers = VALUE ty_t_num_std( FOR n IN lt_result ( n ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.

      RETURNING

CLASS zcl_unique_digits IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD unique_digits.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <num> TYPE any.
    DATA lt_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.
    DATA lv_num    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_str    TYPE string.
    DATA lv_len    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char   TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_digit  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_ok     TYPE abap_bool.

    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <num>.
      TRY.
          lv_num = <num>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_num <= 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_str = |{ lv_num }|.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_str ).
      lv_ok = abap_true.

      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
        lv_char = lv_str+lv_idx(1).

        TRY.
            lv_digit = lv_char.
          CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
            lv_ok = abap_false.
            EXIT.
        ENDTRY.

        IF ( lv_digit MOD 2 ) = 0.
          lv_ok = abap_false.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      IF lv_ok = abap_true.
        APPEND lv_num TO lt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_result ASCENDING.

    rt_numbers = VALUE #( FOR lv_num IN lt_result ( lv_num ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_unique_digits DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS unique_digits
      IMPORTING
        it_x TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_result) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_unique_digits IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD unique_digits.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_x> TYPE any.
    DATA lv_i TYPE i.
    DATA lv_s TYPE string.
    DATA lv_ok TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_ch TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_pos TYPE i.

    LOOP AT it_x ASSIGNING <lv_x>.
      TRY.
          lv_i = <lv_x>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_i <= 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_s = |{ lv_i }|.
      lv_ok = abap_true.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_s ).

      lv_pos = 0.
      WHILE lv_pos < lv_len.
        lv_ch = lv_s+lv_pos(1).
        CASE lv_ch.
          WHEN '0' OR '2' OR '4' OR '6' OR '8'.
            lv_ok = abap_false.
            EXIT.
        ENDCASE.
        lv_pos = lv_pos + 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF lv_ok = abap_true.
        APPEND lv_i TO rt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT rt_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_exchange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS exchange
      IMPORTING
        lst1 TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        lst2 TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.

CLASS zcl_exchange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD exchange.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <t1> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <t2> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <v1> TYPE any,
                   <v2> TYPE any.

    ASSIGN lst1 TO <t1>.
    ASSIGN lst2 TO <t2>.

    DATA lv_odd_in_lst1 TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_even_in_lst2 TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_num TYPE i.

    LOOP AT <t1> ASSIGNING <v1>.
      lv_num = CONV i( <v1> ).
      IF lv_num MOD 2 <> 0.
        lv_odd_in_lst1 = lv_odd_in_lst1 + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT <t2> ASSIGNING <v2>.
      lv_num = CONV i( <v2> ).
      IF lv_num MOD 2 = 0.
        lv_even_in_lst2 = lv_even_in_lst2 + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_even_in_lst2 >= lv_odd_in_lst1.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
    ELSE.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

    IF lv_available_even >= lv_needed_even.

             name        TYPE c LENGTH 50,
           END OF ty_customer.

CLASS zcl_customer_search IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_by_pattern.
    DATA: lv_input   TYPE string,
          lv_pattern TYPE string.

      FROM zcustomer

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    TYPES: ty_id TYPE char20.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_rel,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_rel.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_parent,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_parent.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_child,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_child.

    rv_valid = abap_false.

    DATA lt_rel TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_rel WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lo_desc TYPE REF TO cl_abap_typedescr.
    TRY.
        lo_desc = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZORG_STRUCTURE' ).
      CATCH cx_sy_descr_no_object.
        RETURN.
      CATCH cx_sy_ref_is_initial.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_rel.

    IF lt_rel IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_employees   TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_supervisors TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_all_nodes   TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT lt_rel ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<r>).
      INSERT <r>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_employees.
      INSERT <r>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_supervisors.
      INSERT <r>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_all_nodes.
      INSERT <r>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_all_nodes.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_ceos TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT lt_supervisors ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<sup>).
      READ TABLE lt_employees WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <sup> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT <sup> INTO TABLE lt_ceos.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_ceos ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo) = lt_ceos[ 1 ].

    DATA lt_parent TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_parent WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.
    LOOP AT lt_rel ASSIGNING <r>.
      READ TABLE lt_parent WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <r>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT VALUE ty_parent( employee_id = <r>-employee_id supervisor_id = <r>-supervisor_id ) INTO TABLE lt_parent.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_children TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_child WITH UNIQUE KEY supervisor_id employee_id.
    LOOP AT lt_rel ASSIGNING <r>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_child( supervisor_id = <r>-supervisor_id employee_id = <r>-employee_id ) INTO TABLE lt_children.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_state TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    LOOP AT lt_all_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<node>).
      INSERT |0:{ <node> }| INTO TABLE lt_state.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_all_nodes ASSIGNING <node>.
      READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY table_line = |0:{ <node> }| TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lt_stack TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
      APPEND <node> TO lt_stack.

      WHILE lt_stack IS NOT INITIAL.
        DATA(lv_cur) = lt_stack[ lines( lt_stack ) ].

        READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY table_line = |2:{ lv_cur }| TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          DELETE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ).
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY table_line = |1:{ lv_cur }| TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          DELETE TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY table_line = |0:{ lv_cur }|.
          INSERT |1:{ lv_cur }| INTO TABLE lt_state.
        ELSE.
          DELETE TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY table_line = |1:{ lv_cur }|.
          INSERT |2:{ lv_cur }| INTO TABLE lt_state.
          DELETE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ).
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_parent WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = lv_cur INTO DATA(ls_p).
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          DATA(lv_next) = ls_p-supervisor_id.

          READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY table_line = |1:{ lv_next }| TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.

          READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY table_line = |2:{ lv_next }| TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            APPEND lv_next TO lt_stack.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_reached TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_queue   TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

    INSERT lv_ceo INTO TABLE lt_reached.
    APPEND lv_ceo TO lt_queue.

    WHILE lt_queue IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA(lv_q) = lt_queue[ 1 ].
      DELETE lt_queue INDEX 1.

      LOOP AT lt_children INTO DATA(ls_child) WHERE supervisor_id = lv_q.
        READ TABLE lt_reached WITH TABLE KEY table_line = ls_child-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          INSERT ls_child-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_reached.
          APPEND ls_child-employee_id TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_reached ) <> lines( lt_all_nodes ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_valid = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_is_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    rv_is_valid = abap_false.

    TYPES: ty_id TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_edge.

    DATA lt_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lr_tab TYPE REF TO data.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_any> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.

    TRY.
        cl_abap_tabledescr=>create(
          p_line_type = cl_abap_structdescr=>create(
            VALUE abap_component_tab(
              ( name = 'EMPLOYEE_ID'   type = cl_abap_elemdescr=>get_c( 20 ) )
              ( name = 'SUPERVISOR_ID' type = cl_abap_elemdescr=>get_c( 20 ) ) ) ) )->get_table_line_type( ).
      CATCH cx_root.
    ENDTRY.

    CREATE DATA lr_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge.
    ASSIGN lr_tab->* TO <lt_any>.

    DATA(lv_sql) = |SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id FROM ZORG_STRUCTURE|.
    TRY.
        cl_sql_statement=>execute_query( lv_sql )->set_param_table( <lt_any> ).
      CATCH cx_root.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    lt_edges = <lt_any>.

    IF lt_edges IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_employee_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_supervisor_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e>).
      IF <e>-employee_id IS INITIAL OR <e>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_employee_ids.
      INSERT <e>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_supervisor_ids.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_all_ids TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    lt_all_ids = CORRESPONDING #( lt_employee_ids ).
    LOOP AT lt_supervisor_ids ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<sid>).
      INSERT <sid> INTO TABLE lt_all_ids.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_ceos TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    LOOP AT lt_all_ids ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<id>).
      READ TABLE lt_employee_ids WITH KEY table_line = <id> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        APPEND <id> TO lt_ceos.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_ceos ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo) = lt_ceos[ 1 ].

    DATA lt_emp_to_sup TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_edge WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.
    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_edge( employee_id = <e>-employee_id supervisor_id = <e>-supervisor_id ) INTO TABLE lt_emp_to_sup.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF <e>-employee_id = <e>-supervisor_id.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node_state,
             id    TYPE ty_id,
             state TYPE i,
           END OF ty_node_state.
    TYPES ty_state_tab TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node_state WITH UNIQUE KEY id.

    CONSTANTS: c_unvisited TYPE i VALUE 0,
               c_visiting  TYPE i VALUE 1,
               c_visited   TYPE i VALUE 2.

    DATA lt_state TYPE ty_state_tab.
    LOOP AT lt_all_ids ASSIGNING <id>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_node_state( id = <id> state = c_unvisited ) INTO TABLE lt_state.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_stack TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_cur TYPE ty_id.
    DATA lv_next TYPE ty_id.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <st>  TYPE ty_node_state,
                   <map> TYPE ty_edge.

    LOOP AT lt_all_ids ASSIGNING <id>.
      READ TABLE lt_state ASSIGNING <st> WITH KEY id = <id>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <st>-state <> c_unvisited.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lt_stack.
      lv_cur = <id>.

      WHILE abap_true = abap_true.
        READ TABLE lt_state ASSIGNING <st> WITH KEY id = lv_cur.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        IF <st>-state = c_visiting.
          RETURN.
        ELSEIF <st>-state = c_visited.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        <st>-state = c_visiting.
        APPEND lv_cur TO lt_stack.

        READ TABLE lt_emp_to_sup ASSIGNING <map> WITH KEY employee_id = lv_cur.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          lv_next = <map>-supervisor_id.
          READ TABLE lt_state TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS WITH KEY id = lv_next.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_cur = lv_next.
          CONTINUE.
        ELSE.
          IF lv_cur <> lv_ceo.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.

      LOOP AT lt_stack INTO DATA(lv_mark).
        READ TABLE lt_state ASSIGNING <st> WITH KEY id = lv_mark.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        <st>-state = c_visited.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_is_valid = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF zorg_structure,
             employee_id   TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             supervisor_id TYPE c LENGTH 20,
           END OF zorg_structure.
    TYPES tt_zorg_structure TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zorg_structure WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_valid) TYPE abap_bool.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    TYPES ty_id TYPE c LENGTH 20.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_edge.
    TYPES tt_edge TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node,
             id         TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor TYPE ty_id,
             in_degree  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_node.
    TYPES tt_node TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY id.

    DATA lt_edges TYPE tt_edge.

    TRY.
        SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
          FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
          INTO TABLE @lt_edges.
      CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error cx_sy_open_sql_db.
        rv_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lt_edges IS INITIAL.
      rv_valid = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_nodes TYPE tt_node.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e>).
      IF <e>-employee_id IS INITIAL OR <e>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        rv_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF <e>-employee_id = <e>-supervisor_id.
        rv_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY id = <e>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT VALUE ty_node( id = <e>-employee_id ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY id = <e>-supervisor_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT VALUE ty_node( id = <e>-supervisor_id ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY id = <e>-employee_id INTO DATA(ls_emp).
      IF ls_emp-supervisor IS INITIAL.
        ls_emp-supervisor = <e>-supervisor_id.
        MODIFY TABLE lt_nodes FROM ls_emp.
      ELSEIF ls_emp-supervisor <> <e>-supervisor_id.
        rv_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      READ TABLE lt_nodes WITH TABLE KEY id = <e>-supervisor_id INTO DATA(ls_sup).
      ls_sup-in_degree = ls_sup-in_degree + 1.
      MODIFY TABLE lt_nodes FROM ls_sup.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_ceo_count TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_ceo_id TYPE ty_id.

    LOOP AT lt_nodes INTO DATA(ls_node).
      IF ls_node-in_degree = 0.
        lv_ceo_count = lv_ceo_count + 1.
        lv_ceo_id = ls_node-id.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_ceo_count <> 1.
      rv_valid = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    APPEND lv_ceo_id TO lt_queue.
    INSERT lv_ceo_id INTO TABLE lt_visited.

    WHILE lt_queue IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA(lv_cur) = lt_queue[ 1 ].
      DELETE lt_queue INDEX 1.

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e> WHERE supervisor_id = lv_cur.
        READ TABLE lt_visited WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <e>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          rv_valid = abap_false.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_visited.
        APPEND <e>-employee_id TO lt_queue.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_visited ) <> lines( lt_nodes ).
      rv_valid = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_valid = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_is_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.


CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    rv_is_valid = abap_false.

    TRY.
        cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZORG_STRUCTURE' ).
      CATCH cx_sy_descr_no_object.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    TYPES ty_empid TYPE c LENGTH 20.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_rel,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_empid,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_empid,
           END OF ty_rel.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_state,
             id    TYPE ty_empid,
             state TYPE c LENGTH 1,
           END OF ty_state.

    DATA lt_rel TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_rel WITH EMPTY KEY.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_rel.

    IF lt_rel IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_emp_to_sup  TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_rel   WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.
    DATA lt_employees   TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_supervisors TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT lt_rel ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<r>).
      IF <r>-employee_id IS INITIAL OR <r>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT <r>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_employees.
      INSERT <r>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_supervisors.

      READ TABLE lt_emp_to_sup WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <r>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT VALUE ty_rel(
        employee_id   = <r>-employee_id
        supervisor_id = <r>-supervisor_id
      ) INTO TABLE lt_emp_to_sup.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_ceo_candidates TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT lt_supervisors ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<sup>).
      READ TABLE lt_employees WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <sup> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        INSERT <sup> INTO TABLE lt_ceo_candidates.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_ceo_candidates ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo) = lt_ceo_candidates[ 1 ].

    DATA lt_all_nodes TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    lt_all_nodes = lt_employees.
    LOOP AT lt_supervisors ASSIGNING <sup>.
      INSERT <sup> INTO TABLE lt_all_nodes.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_children TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_rel WITH UNIQUE KEY supervisor_id employee_id.
    LOOP AT lt_rel ASSIGNING <r>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_rel( supervisor_id = <r>-supervisor_id employee_id = <r>-employee_id ) INTO TABLE lt_children.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_queue   TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_empid WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_visited TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_empid WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    APPEND lv_ceo TO lt_queue.
    INSERT lv_ceo INTO TABLE lt_visited.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 0.
    WHILE lv_idx < lines( lt_queue ).
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      DATA lv_curr TYPE ty_empid.
      lv_curr = lt_queue[ lv_idx ].

      LOOP AT lt_children ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<c>) USING KEY primary_key WHERE supervisor_id = lv_curr.
        READ TABLE lt_visited WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <c>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          INSERT <c>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_visited.
          APPEND <c>-employee_id TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_visited ) <> lines( lt_all_nodes ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_state TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_state WITH UNIQUE KEY id.
    LOOP AT lt_all_nodes INTO DATA(lv_node).
      INSERT VALUE ty_state( id = lv_node state = '0' ) INTO TABLE lt_state.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA(lv_cycle) = abap_false.

    LOOP AT lt_all_nodes INTO lv_node.
      READ TABLE lt_state ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<st>) WITH TABLE KEY id = lv_node.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <st>-state <> '0'.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lt_stack TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_empid WITH EMPTY KEY.
      APPEND lv_node TO lt_stack.

      WHILE lt_stack IS NOT INITIAL AND lv_cycle = abap_false.
        DATA(lv_top) = lt_stack[ lines( lt_stack ) ].

        READ TABLE lt_state ASSIGNING <st> WITH TABLE KEY id = lv_top.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          DELETE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ).
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        IF <st>-state = '0'.
          <st>-state = '1'.
        ENDIF.

        DATA(lv_pushed_child) = abap_false.
        LOOP AT lt_children ASSIGNING <c> USING KEY primary_key WHERE supervisor_id = lv_top.
          DATA(lv_child) = <c>-employee_id.

          READ TABLE lt_state ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<st_child>) WITH TABLE KEY id = lv_child.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            CONTINUE.
          ENDIF.

          IF <st_child>-state = '1'.
            lv_cycle = abap_true.
            EXIT.
          ELSEIF <st_child>-state = '0'.
            APPEND lv_child TO lt_stack.
            lv_pushed_child = abap_true.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
        ENDLOOP.

        IF lv_cycle = abap_true.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_pushed_child = abap_false.
          <st>-state = '2'.
          DELETE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ).
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF lv_cycle = abap_true.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_is_valid = xsdbool( lv_cycle = abap_false ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_is_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    rv_is_valid = abap_false.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             employee_id   TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             supervisor_id TYPE c LENGTH 20,
           END OF ty_edge.

    TYPES: ty_employee_id TYPE c LENGTH 20.
    TYPES: ty_set         TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_employee_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_state,
             employee_id TYPE ty_employee_id,
             state       TYPE i,
           END OF ty_state.
    TYPES: ty_state_map TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_state WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    DATA lt_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge.

    TRY.
        SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
          FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
          INTO TABLE @lt_edges.
      CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error cx_sy_open_sql_db.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lt_edges IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_all_employees TYPE ty_set.
    DATA lt_has_manager   TYPE ty_set.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e>).
      IF <e>-employee_id IS INITIAL OR <e>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_all_employees.
      INSERT <e>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_all_employees.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      IF line_exists( lt_has_manager[ table_line = <e>-employee_id ] ).
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_has_manager.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_ceos TYPE ty_set.
    lt_ceos = lt_all_employees.
    LOOP AT lt_has_manager ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<hm>).
      DELETE TABLE lt_ceos FROM <hm>.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_ceos ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_ceo) = VALUE ty_employee_id( ).
    LOOP AT lt_ceos ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ceo>).
      lv_ceo = <ceo>.
      EXIT.
    ENDLOOP.
    IF lv_ceo IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_reachable TYPE ty_set.
    DATA lt_stack TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_employee_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

    APPEND lv_ceo TO lt_stack.
    INSERT lv_ceo INTO TABLE lt_reachable.

    WHILE lt_stack IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA(lv_curr) = lt_stack[ lines( lt_stack ) ].
      DELETE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ).

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e> WHERE supervisor_id = lv_curr.
        IF NOT line_exists( lt_reachable[ table_line = <e>-employee_id ] ).
          INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_reachable.
          APPEND <e>-employee_id TO lt_stack.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_reachable ) <> lines( lt_all_employees ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_state TYPE ty_state_map.
    LOOP AT lt_all_employees ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<emp>).
      INSERT VALUE ty_state( employee_id = <emp> state = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_state.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_all_employees ASSIGNING <emp>.
      READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <emp> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<s>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <s>-state <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lt_node_stack TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_employee_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
      DATA lt_idx_stack  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

      APPEND <emp> TO lt_node_stack.
      APPEND 0 TO lt_idx_stack.

      WHILE lt_node_stack IS NOT INITIAL.
        DATA(lv_node) = lt_node_stack[ lines( lt_node_stack ) ].
        DATA(lv_idx)  = lt_idx_stack[ lines( lt_idx_stack ) ].

        READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = lv_node ASSIGNING <s>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        IF <s>-state = 0.
          <s>-state = 1.
        ENDIF.

        DATA lt_children TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_employee_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
        LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e> WHERE supervisor_id = lv_node.
          APPEND <e>-employee_id TO lt_children.
        ENDLOOP.

        IF lv_idx < lines( lt_children ).
          DATA(lv_child) = lt_children[ lv_idx + 1 ].

          lt_idx_stack[ lines( lt_idx_stack ) ] = lv_idx + 1.

          READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = lv_child ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<cs>).
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.

          IF <cs>-state = 1.
            RETURN.
          ELSEIF <cs>-state = 0.
            APPEND lv_child TO lt_node_stack.
            APPEND 0 TO lt_idx_stack.
          ENDIF.
        ELSE.
          <s>-state = 2.
          DELETE lt_node_stack INDEX lines( lt_node_stack ).
          DELETE lt_idx_stack  INDEX lines( lt_idx_stack ).
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_is_valid = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    TYPES ty_id TYPE c LENGTH 20.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_edge.
    TYPES ty_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_state,
             employee_id TYPE ty_id,
             state       TYPE i,
           END OF ty_state.
    TYPES ty_states TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_state WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_node,
             employee_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_node.
    TYPES ty_nodes TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_manager,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_id,
           END OF ty_manager.
    TYPES ty_managers TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_manager WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_stack_item,
             employee_id TYPE ty_id,
             idx         TYPE i,
           END OF ty_stack_item.
    TYPES ty_stack TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_stack_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    rv_valid = abap_false.

    DATA lt_edges TYPE ty_edges.

    TRY.
        DATA(lo_tab) = cl_abap_tabledescr=>describe_by_name( 'ZORG_STRUCTURE' ).
      CATCH cx_sy_descr_no_object.
        RETURN.
      CATCH cx_sy_descr_no_name.
        RETURN.
      CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
      FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
      INTO TABLE @lt_edges.

    DATA lt_nodes TYPE ty_nodes.
    DATA lt_managers TYPE ty_managers.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<e>).
      IF <e>-employee_id IS INITIAL OR <e>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT VALUE ty_node( employee_id = <e>-employee_id ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.
      INSERT VALUE ty_node( employee_id = <e>-supervisor_id ) INTO TABLE lt_nodes.

      READ TABLE lt_managers WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <e>-employee_id ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<m>).
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        IF <m>-supervisor_id <> <e>-supervisor_id.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        INSERT VALUE ty_manager( employee_id = <e>-employee_id supervisor_id = <e>-supervisor_id ) INTO TABLE lt_managers.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lt_nodes IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_ceo TYPE ty_id.
    CLEAR lv_ceo.

    LOOP AT lt_nodes ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      READ TABLE lt_managers WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <n>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        IF lv_ceo IS INITIAL.
          lv_ceo = <n>-employee_id.
        ELSE.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_ceo IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_states TYPE ty_states.
    lt_states = VALUE #( FOR n IN lt_nodes ( employee_id = n-employee_id state = 0 ) ).

    DATA lt_adj TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_edge WITH NON-UNIQUE KEY supervisor_id employee_id.
    lt_adj = CORRESPONDING #( lt_edges ).

    DATA lt_stack TYPE ty_stack.

    LOOP AT lt_nodes INTO DATA(ls_node).
      READ TABLE lt_states WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = ls_node-employee_id ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<st0>).
      IF <st0>-state <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lt_stack.
      APPEND VALUE ty_stack_item( employee_id = ls_node-employee_id idx = 0 ) TO lt_stack.

      WHILE lines( lt_stack ) > 0.
        DATA(lv_top_idx) = lines( lt_stack ).
        ASSIGN lt_stack[ lv_top_idx ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<top>).

        READ TABLE lt_states WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <top>-employee_id ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<st>).
        IF <st>-state = 0.
          <st>-state = 1.
        ENDIF.

        DATA lt_children TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
        LOOP AT lt_adj INTO DATA(ls_adj) WHERE supervisor_id = <top>-employee_id.
          APPEND ls_adj-employee_id TO lt_children.
        ENDLOOP.

        IF <top>-idx >= lines( lt_children ).
          <st>-state = 2.
          DELETE lt_stack INDEX lv_top_idx.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        <top>-idx = <top>-idx + 1.
        DATA(lv_child) = lt_children[ <top>-idx ].

        READ TABLE lt_states WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = lv_child ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<stc>).
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        IF <stc>-state = 1.
          RETURN.
        ELSEIF <stc>-state = 0.
          APPEND VALUE ty_stack_item( employee_id = lv_child idx = 0 ) TO lt_stack.
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lt_reached TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_node WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.
    INSERT VALUE ty_node( employee_id = lv_ceo ) INTO TABLE lt_reached.

    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    APPEND lv_ceo TO lt_queue.

    WHILE lines( lt_queue ) > 0.
      DATA(lv_cur) = lt_queue[ 1 ].
      DELETE lt_queue INDEX 1.

      LOOP AT lt_adj INTO DATA(ls_adj2) WHERE supervisor_id = lv_cur.
        READ TABLE lt_reached WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = ls_adj2-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          INSERT VALUE ty_node( employee_id = ls_adj2-employee_id ) INTO TABLE lt_reached.
          APPEND ls_adj2-employee_id TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_reached ) <> lines( lt_nodes ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_valid = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: ty_employee_id   TYPE c LENGTH 20,
           ty_supervisor_id TYPE c LENGTH 20,
           BEGIN OF zorg_structure,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_employee_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_supervisor_id,
           END OF zorg_structure.

    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_is_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_edge,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_employee_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_supervisor_id,
           END OF ty_edge.
    TYPES ty_edges TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_edge WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_sup,
             employee_id   TYPE ty_employee_id,
             supervisor_id TYPE ty_supervisor_id,
           END OF ty_sup.
    TYPES ty_sup_map TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_sup WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_indeg,
             employee_id TYPE ty_employee_id,
             indegree    TYPE i,
           END OF ty_indeg.
    TYPES ty_indeg_map TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_indeg WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    TYPES ty_id_set TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_employee_id WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_state,
             employee_id TYPE ty_employee_id,
             state       TYPE i,
           END OF ty_state.
    TYPES ty_state_map TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_state WITH UNIQUE KEY employee_id.

    CONSTANTS: c_unvisited TYPE i VALUE 0,
               c_visiting  TYPE i VALUE 1,
               c_done      TYPE i VALUE 2.

    DATA lt_edges TYPE ty_edges.
    DATA lt_employees TYPE ty_id_set.
    DATA lt_supervisors TYPE ty_id_set.
    DATA lt_all TYPE ty_id_set.
    DATA lt_sup_map TYPE ty_sup_map.
    DATA lt_indeg TYPE ty_indeg_map.
    DATA lt_state TYPE ty_state_map.
    DATA lt_stack TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_employee_id WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_reachable TYPE ty_id_set.
    DATA lt_queue TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_employee_id WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lv_ceo_count TYPE i.
    DATA lv_ceo TYPE ty_employee_id.
    DATA lv_cycle TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
    DATA lv_node TYPE ty_employee_id.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <e>   TYPE ty_edge,
                   <sid> TYPE ty_employee_id,
                   <id>  TYPE ty_employee_id,
                   <sup> TYPE ty_sup,
                   <in>  TYPE ty_indeg,
                   <st>  TYPE ty_state,
                   <st2> TYPE ty_state,
                   <cur> TYPE ty_employee_id.

    rv_is_valid = abap_false.

    TRY.
        SELECT employee_id, supervisor_id
          FROM ('ZORG_STRUCTURE')
          INTO TABLE @lt_edges.
      CATCH cx_sy_dynamic_osql_error cx_sy_open_sql_db.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lt_edges IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      IF <e>-employee_id IS INITIAL OR <e>-supervisor_id IS INITIAL.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_employees.
      INSERT <e>-supervisor_id INTO TABLE lt_supervisors.
    ENDLOOP.

    lt_all = lt_employees.
    LOOP AT lt_supervisors ASSIGNING <sid>.
      INSERT <sid> INTO TABLE lt_all.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      READ TABLE lt_sup_map WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <e>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      INSERT VALUE ty_sup( employee_id = <e>-employee_id supervisor_id = <e>-supervisor_id ) INTO TABLE lt_sup_map.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_all ASSIGNING <id>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_indeg( employee_id = <id> indegree = 0 ) INTO TABLE lt_indeg.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e>.
      READ TABLE lt_indeg WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <e>-employee_id ASSIGNING <in>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      <in>-indegree = <in>-indegree + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    CLEAR lv_ceo_count.
    CLEAR lv_ceo.

    LOOP AT lt_indeg ASSIGNING <in>.
      IF <in>-indegree = 0.
        lv_ceo_count = lv_ceo_count + 1.
        lv_ceo = <in>-employee_id.
        IF lv_ceo_count > 1.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_ceo_count <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF line_exists( lt_sup_map[ employee_id = lv_ceo ] ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_all ASSIGNING <id>.
      INSERT VALUE ty_state( employee_id = <id> state = c_unvisited ) INTO TABLE lt_state.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_cycle = abap_false.

    LOOP AT lt_all ASSIGNING <id>.
      READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <id> ASSIGNING <st>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <st>-state <> c_unvisited.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lt_stack.
      APPEND <id> TO lt_stack.

      WHILE lt_stack IS NOT INITIAL AND lv_cycle = abap_false.
        READ TABLE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ) ASSIGNING <cur>.
        READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <cur> ASSIGNING <st>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          lv_cycle = abap_true.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        IF <st>-state = c_unvisited.
          <st>-state = c_visiting.

          READ TABLE lt_sup_map WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <cur> ASSIGNING <sup>.
          IF sy-subrc = 0.
            READ TABLE lt_state WITH TABLE KEY employee_id = <sup>-supervisor_id ASSIGNING <st2>.
            IF sy-subrc <> 0.
              lv_cycle = abap_true.
              EXIT.
            ENDIF.

            IF <st2>-state = c_visiting.
              lv_cycle = abap_true.
              EXIT.
            ELSEIF <st2>-state = c_unvisited.
              APPEND <sup>-supervisor_id TO lt_stack.
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.

        ELSEIF <st>-state = c_visiting.
          <st>-state = c_done.
          DELETE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ).
        ELSE.
          DELETE lt_stack INDEX lines( lt_stack ).
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF lv_cycle = abap_true.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    INSERT lv_ceo INTO TABLE lt_reachable.
    APPEND lv_ceo TO lt_queue.

    lv_idx = 0.
    WHILE lv_idx < lines( lt_queue ).
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      lv_node = lt_queue[ lv_idx ].

      LOOP AT lt_edges ASSIGNING <e> WHERE supervisor_id = lv_node.
        READ TABLE lt_reachable WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <e>-employee_id TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          INSERT <e>-employee_id INTO TABLE lt_reachable.
          APPEND <e>-employee_id TO lt_queue.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_reachable ) <> lines( lt_all ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_is_valid = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_valid_hierarchy
      RETURNING VALUE(rv_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_hierarchy_utils IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_valid_hierarchy.
    rv_valid = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num TYPE i.
    TYPES ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_xs) TYPE ty_num_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    rt_xs = VALUE #( ).

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <xs> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    ASSIGN xs TO <xs>.

    DATA(lv_lines) = lines( <xs> ).
    IF lv_lines <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <c> TYPE any.
    DATA(lv_val) TYPE ty_num.

    DO lv_lines - 1 TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx) = sy-index + 1.
      ASSIGN <xs>[ lv_idx ] TO <c>.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_val = <c> * sy-index.
        APPEND lv_val TO rt_xs.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_t_int TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_derivative) TYPE ty_t_int.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    rt_derivative = VALUE #( ).

    DATA(lv_lines) = lines( xs ).
    IF lv_lines <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <x> TYPE any.
    DATA(lv_idx) = 0.

    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <x>.
      IF lv_idx = 0.
        lv_idx = 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.
      APPEND CONV i( <x> ) * ( lv_idx ) TO rt_derivative.
      lv_idx += 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE string_table
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_derivative) TYPE string_table.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    DATA lv_idx   TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_coeff TYPE string.
    DATA lv_val   TYPE f.

    rt_derivative = VALUE #( ).

    LOOP AT xs INTO lv_coeff FROM 2.
      lv_val = lv_coeff.
      lv_val = lv_val * lv_idx.
      APPEND |{ lv_val }| TO rt_derivative.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_xs) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    rt_xs = VALUE #( ).

    IF lines( xs ) <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<x>) FROM 2.
      DATA(lv_index) = sy-tabix - 1.
      APPEND <x> * lv_index TO rt_xs.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_t_coeff TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs            TYPE ty_t_coeff
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_t_coeff.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    DATA lv_index TYPE i.
    DATA lv_coeff TYPE i.

    result = VALUE #( ).

    lv_index = 0.
    LOOP AT xs INTO lv_coeff.
      IF lv_index > 0.
        APPEND lv_coeff * lv_index TO result.
      ENDIF.
      lv_index = lv_index + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_xs) TYPE ty_num_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    rt_xs = VALUE #( ).
    DATA idx TYPE i VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<c>).
      IF idx > 0.
        APPEND <c> * idx TO rt_xs.
      ENDIF.
      idx = idx + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs            TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    result = VALUE #( ).

    DATA idx TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_i TYPE i.

    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<c>).
      idx = idx + 1.
      IF idx = 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = CONV i( <c> ) * ( idx - 1 ).
      APPEND lv_i TO result.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs            TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int4 WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int4 WITH EMPTY KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_polynomial_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    DATA lv_idx  TYPE int4.
    DATA lv_coef TYPE int4.

    CLEAR result.

    LOOP AT xs INTO lv_coef.
      lv_idx = sy-tabix - 1.
      IF lv_idx > 0.
        APPEND lv_coef * lv_idx TO result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS derivative
      IMPORTING
        xs            TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_derivative IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD derivative.
    result = VALUE ty_int_tab( ).

    DATA(lv_lines) = lines( xs ).
    IF lv_lines <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_lines - 1 TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx) = sy-index + 1.
      APPEND xs[ lv_idx ] * sy-index TO result.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt_rotate DEFINITION PUBLIC FINAL CREATE PUBLIC.
  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encrypt
      IMPORTING
        iv_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt_rotate IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encrypt.
    DATA: lv_in   TYPE string,
          lv_len  TYPE i,
          lv_out  TYPE string,
          lv_idx  TYPE i,
          lv_c    TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_code TYPE i.

    lv_in  = iv_text.
    lv_len = strlen( lv_in ).
    CLEAR lv_out.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c   = lv_in+lv_idx(1).
      lv_code = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccpi( lv_c ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 65 AND 90.
        lv_code = ( ( lv_code - 65 + 4 ) MOD 26 ) + 65.
        lv_c = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccpi( lv_code ).
      ELSEIF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_code = ( ( lv_code - 97 + 4 ) MOD 26 ) + 97.
        lv_c = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccpi( lv_code ).
      ENDIF.

      CONCATENATE lv_out lv_c INTO lv_out IN CHARACTER MODE.
    ENDDO.

    rv_text = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encrypt
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encrypt.
    DATA: lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_off   TYPE i,
          lv_c     TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_code  TYPE i,
          lv_shift TYPE i,
          lv_out   TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).
    r_text = ``.
    lv_shift = 4.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_off = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = i_text+lv_off(1).

      lv_code = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( lv_c ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_code = ( ( lv_code - 97 + lv_shift ) MOD 26 ) + 97.
        lv_out = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( lv_code ).
        r_text = r_text && lv_out.
      ELSEIF lv_code BETWEEN 65 AND 90.
        lv_code = ( ( lv_code - 65 + lv_shift ) MOD 26 ) + 65.
        lv_out = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( lv_code ).
        r_text = r_text && lv_out.
      ELSE.
        r_text = r_text && lv_c.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encrypt
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encrypt.
    DATA: lv_len    TYPE i,
          lv_idx    TYPE i,
          lv_out    TYPE string,
          lv_c      TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_code   TYPE i,
          lv_shift  TYPE i VALUE 4,
          lv_result TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).
    lv_idx = 0.

    WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
      lv_c = substring( val = i_text off = lv_idx len = 1 ).
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      lv_code = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccpi( lv_c ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_code = 97 + ( ( lv_code - 97 + lv_shift ) MOD 26 ).
        lv_result = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccpi( lv_code ).
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_result.
      ELSEIF lv_code BETWEEN 65 AND 90.
        lv_code = 65 + ( ( lv_code - 65 + lv_shift ) MOD 26 ).
        lv_result = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccpi( lv_code ).
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_result.
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_c.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    r_text = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encrypt
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encrypt.
    DATA: lv_len  TYPE i,
          lv_out  TYPE string,
          lv_char TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_code TYPE i,
          lv_base TYPE i,
          lv_pos  TYPE i,
          lv_new  TYPE i,
          lv_uc   TYPE i,
          lv_x    TYPE x LENGTH 2.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_char = i_text+sy-index(1).
      lv_code = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( lv_char ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 65 AND 90.
        lv_base = 65.
        lv_pos  = lv_code - lv_base.
        lv_new  = ( lv_pos + 4 ) MOD 26.
        lv_uc   = lv_base + lv_new.

        lv_x = lv_uc.
        lv_out = lv_out && cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( lv_x ).
      ELSEIF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_base = 97.
        lv_pos  = lv_code - lv_base.
        lv_new  = ( lv_pos + 4 ) MOD 26.
        lv_uc   = lv_base + lv_new.

        lv_x = lv_uc.
        lv_out = lv_out && cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( lv_x ).
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_char.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    r_text = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encrypt
      IMPORTING
        s             TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encrypt.
    CONSTANTS: lc_lower TYPE string VALUE 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz',
               lc_upper TYPE string VALUE 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'.

    DATA: lv_input TYPE string,
          lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_out   TYPE string,
          lv_c     TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_pos   TYPE i,
          lv_idx   TYPE i.

    lv_input = s.
    lv_len = strlen( lv_input ).
    CLEAR lv_out.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = lv_input+lv_idx(1).

      FIND lv_c IN lc_lower MATCH OFFSET lv_pos.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_pos = ( lv_pos + 4 ) MOD 26.
        lv_c = lc_lower+lv_pos(1).
      ELSE.
        FIND lv_c IN lc_upper MATCH OFFSET lv_pos.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          lv_pos = ( lv_pos + 4 ) MOD 26.
          lv_c = lc_upper+lv_pos(1).
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      CONCATENATE lv_out lv_c INTO lv_out IN CHARACTER MODE.
    ENDDO.

    result = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encrypt
      IMPORTING
        !iv_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encrypt.
    DATA: lv_len    TYPE i,
          lv_pos    TYPE i,
          lv_char   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_alpha  TYPE string VALUE 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz',
          lv_idx    TYPE i,
          lv_newidx TYPE i.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_text ).
    CLEAR rv_text.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_pos = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = iv_text+lv_pos(1).

      FIND lv_char IN lv_alpha MATCH OFFSET lv_idx.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_newidx = ( lv_idx + 4 ) MOD 26.
        rv_text = rv_text && lv_alpha+lv_newidx(1).
      ELSE.
        rv_text = rv_text && lv_char.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encrypt
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encrypt IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encrypt.
    DATA lv_len     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char    TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_code    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_shifted TYPE i.
    DATA lv_out     TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    r_text = ``.
    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = i_text+lv_idx(1).

      lv_code = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( CONV string( lv_char ) ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_shifted = ( ( lv_code - 97 + 4 ) MOD 26 ) + 97.
        lv_out = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( CONV string( cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( lv_shifted ) ) ).
        lv_out = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( lv_shifted ).
        r_text = r_text && lv_out.
      ELSEIF lv_code BETWEEN 65 AND 90.
        lv_shifted = ( ( lv_code - 65 + 4 ) MOD 26 ) + 65.
        lv_out = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( lv_shifted ).
        r_text = r_text && lv_out.
      ELSE.
        r_text = r_text && lv_char.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      IMPORTING

      RETURNING

CLASS zcl_string_to_md5 IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD string_to_md5.
    IF text IS INITIAL.
      CLEAR result.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA: lv_xstr  TYPE xstring,
          lv_hashx TYPE xstring.

    lv_xstr = cl_abap_codepage=>convert_to( source = text ).

    TRY.
        cl_abap_message_digest=>calculate_hash_for_raw(
          EXPORTING
            if_algorithm = 'MD5'
            if_data      = lv_xstr
          IMPORTING
            ef_hashx     = lv_hashx ).
      CATCH cx_abap_message_digest.
        CLEAR result.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    result = lv_hashx.
    TRANSLATE result TO LOWER CASE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_md5)  TYPE string.

CLASS zcl_string_to_md5 IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD string_to_md5.
    rv_md5 = ''.
    IF iv_text IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_xstr     TYPE xstring.
    DATA lv_md5_raw  TYPE xstring.

    lv_xstr = cl_abap_codepage=>convert_to( source = iv_text ).

    CALL FUNCTION 'MD5_CALCULATE_HASH_FOR_RAW'
      EXPORTING
        data = lv_xstr
      IMPORTING
        hash = lv_md5_raw.

    rv_md5 = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>create( encoding = 'HEX' )->convert( lv_md5_raw ).
    rv_md5 = to_lower( rv_md5 ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.
