CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_array        TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sytabix WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_array) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sytabix WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    rt_array = it_array.

    IF lines( rt_array ) <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_first) TYPE sytabix.
    DATA(lv_last)  TYPE sytabix.
    DATA(lv_sum)   TYPE sytabix.

    READ TABLE rt_array INDEX 1 INTO lv_first.
    READ TABLE rt_array INDEX lines( rt_array ) INTO lv_last.

    lv_sum = lv_first + lv_last.

    SORT rt_array ASCENDING.

    IF lv_sum MOD 2 = 0.
      DATA lt_desc TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sytabix WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
      DATA(lv_lines) = lines( rt_array ).
      DO lv_lines TIMES.
        APPEND rt_array[ lv_lines - sy-index + 1 ] TO lt_desc.
      ENDDO.
      rt_array = lt_desc.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sort_array
      IMPORTING
        it_array TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_array) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sort_array IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sort_array.
    rt_array = it_array.

    DATA(lv_lines) = lines( rt_array ).
    IF lv_lines <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_first) TYPE syindex.
    DATA(lv_last)  TYPE syindex.

    READ TABLE rt_array INDEX 1 INTO lv_first.
    READ TABLE rt_array INDEX lv_lines INTO lv_last.

    IF ( lv_first + lv_last ) MOD 2 = 1.
      SORT rt_array ASCENDING.
    ELSE.
      SORT rt_array DESCENDING.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_multiply_prime
      IMPORTING
        !a TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_multiply_prime.
    r_result = abap_false.

    IF a <= 1 OR a >= 100.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA count TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA n TYPE i.
    n = a.

    DATA d TYPE i VALUE 2.

    WHILE d * d <= n AND count < 3.
      IF n MOD d = 0.
        n = n / d.
        count = count + 1.
      ELSE.
        d = d + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF n > 1.
      count = count + 1.
    ENDIF.

    IF count = 3.
      r_result = abap_true.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_multiply_prime
      IMPORTING
        a TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_multiply_prime.
    DATA lv_n     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_count TYPE i.
    DATA lv_p     TYPE i.

    rv_result = abap_false.

    IF a < 2 OR a >= 100.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_n = a.
    lv_count = 0.
    lv_p = 2.

    WHILE lv_p * lv_p <= lv_n.
      WHILE lv_n MOD lv_p = 0.
        lv_n = lv_n / lv_p.
        lv_count = lv_count + 1.
        IF lv_count > 3.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.
      lv_p = lv_p + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_n > 1.
      lv_count = lv_count + 1.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_count = 3.
      rv_result = abap_true.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_multiply_prime
      IMPORTING
        a TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_multiply_prime.
    rv_result = abap_false.

    IF a < 2 OR a >= 100.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_primes TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DO 97 TIMES.
      DATA(lv_n) = sy-index + 2.
      DATA(lv_is_prime) = abap_true.

      IF lv_n > 2 AND lv_n MOD 2 = 0.
        lv_is_prime = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        DATA(lv_d) = 3.
        WHILE lv_d * lv_d <= lv_n.
          IF lv_n MOD lv_d = 0.
            lv_is_prime = abap_false.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          lv_d = lv_d + 2.
        ENDWHILE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_n = 2.
        lv_is_prime = abap_true.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_is_prime = abap_true.
        APPEND lv_n TO lt_primes.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    LOOP AT lt_primes INTO DATA(p1).
      LOOP AT lt_primes INTO DATA(p2).
        LOOP AT lt_primes INTO DATA(p3).
          IF p1 * p2 * p3 = a.
            rv_result = abap_true.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
        ENDLOOP.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_multiply_prime
      IMPORTING
        a TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_multiply_prime) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_multiply_prime.
    DATA lt_primes TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_n TYPE i.
    DATA lv_d TYPE i.
    DATA lv_is_prime TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_p1 TYPE i.
    DATA lv_p2 TYPE i.
    DATA lv_p3 TYPE i.
    DATA lv_prod12 TYPE i.

    rv_is_multiply_prime = abap_false.

    DO 99 TIMES.
      lv_n = sy-index.
      lv_is_prime = abap_true.

      IF lv_n < 2.
        lv_is_prime = abap_false.
      ELSEIF lv_n = 2 OR lv_n = 3.
        lv_is_prime = abap_true.
      ELSEIF lv_n MOD 2 = 0.
        lv_is_prime = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_d = 3.
        WHILE lv_d * lv_d <= lv_n.
          IF lv_n MOD lv_d = 0.
            lv_is_prime = abap_false.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          lv_d = lv_d + 2.
        ENDWHILE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_is_prime = abap_true.
        APPEND lv_n TO lt_primes.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    LOOP AT lt_primes INTO lv_p1.
      LOOP AT lt_primes INTO lv_p2.
        lv_prod12 = lv_p1 * lv_p2.
        IF lv_prod12 = 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.
        IF a MOD lv_prod12 <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        lv_p3 = a / lv_prod12.

        READ TABLE lt_primes WITH KEY table_line = lv_p3 TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          rv_is_multiply_prime = abap_true.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDLOOP.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_multiply_prime
      IMPORTING
        a TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_multiply_prime IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_multiply_prime.
    r_result = abap_false.

    IF a < 2 OR a >= 100.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA x TYPE i.
    DATA y TYPE i.
    DATA z TYPE i.

    DO a - 1 TIMES.
      x = sy-index + 1.
      IF x < 2 OR a MOD x <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA px TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.
      DATA dx TYPE i VALUE 2.
      WHILE dx * dx <= x.
        IF x MOD dx = 0.
          px = abap_false.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
        dx = dx + 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      IF px = abap_false.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DO a - 1 TIMES.
        y = sy-index + 1.
        IF y < 2 OR ( a / x ) MOD y <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA py TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.
        DATA dy TYPE i VALUE 2.
        WHILE dy * dy <= y.
          IF y MOD dy = 0.
            py = abap_false.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          dy = dy + 1.
        ENDWHILE.
        IF py = abap_false.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        z = a / ( x * y ).
        IF z < 2.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        IF x * y * z <> a.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.

        DATA pz TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.
        DATA dz TYPE i VALUE 2.
        WHILE dz * dz <= z.
          IF z MOD dz = 0.
            pz = abap_false.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          dz = dz + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        IF pz = abap_true.
          r_result = abap_true.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_operator TYPE c LENGTH 2.
    TYPES ty_operator_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_operator WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_operand_tab  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        it_operator TYPE ty_operator_tab
        it_operand  TYPE ty_operand_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA lv_opcnt TYPE i.
    DATA lv_vacnt TYPE i.

    DATA lv_res TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_tmp TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_a   TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_b   TYPE decfloat34.

    DATA lv_exp_i TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <op> TYPE ty_operator.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <iv> TYPE i.

    lv_opcnt = lines( it_operator ).
    lv_vacnt = lines( it_operand ).

    IF lv_vacnt < 2 OR lv_opcnt < 1 OR lv_opcnt <> lv_vacnt - 1.
      rv_result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE it_operand INDEX 1 ASSIGNING <iv>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_res = <iv>.

    DO lv_opcnt TIMES.
      READ TABLE it_operator INDEX sy-index ASSIGNING <op>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_result = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE it_operand INDEX sy-index + 1 ASSIGNING <iv>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_result = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_b = <iv>.

      CASE <op>.
        WHEN '+'.
          lv_res = lv_res + lv_b.
        WHEN '-'.
          lv_res = lv_res - lv_b.
        WHEN '*'.
          lv_res = lv_res * lv_b.
        WHEN '//' .
          IF lv_b = 0.
            rv_result = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_tmp = lv_res / lv_b.
          lv_res = floor( lv_tmp ).
        WHEN '**'.
          lv_a = lv_res.
          lv_res = 1.
          lv_exp_i = trunc( lv_b ).
          IF lv_exp_i < 0.
            rv_result = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          DO lv_exp_i TIMES.
            lv_res = lv_res * lv_a.
          ENDDO.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          rv_result = 0.
          RETURN.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDDO.

    rv_result = trunc( lv_res ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_t_int TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_op    TYPE c LENGTH 2.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        operator TYPE string_table
        operand  TYPE ty_t_int
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_token,
             kind TYPE c LENGTH 1,
             op   TYPE zcl_do_algebra=>ty_op,
             val  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_token.
    TYPES ty_t_token TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_token WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lt_tokens TYPE ty_t_token.
    DATA ls_token  TYPE ty_token.

    DATA lv_curr   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_next   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_tmp    TYPE i.

    DATA lt_vals   TYPE ty_t_int.
    DATA lt_ops    TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF zcl_do_algebra=>ty_op WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lv_left   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_right  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_do_op  TYPE zcl_do_algebra=>ty_op.
    DATA lv_op     TYPE zcl_do_algebra=>ty_op.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <oper> TYPE string.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <opnd> TYPE i.

    IF lines( operand ) < 2 OR lines( operator ) < 1 OR lines( operator ) <> lines( operand ) - 1.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE operand INDEX 1 INTO lv_curr.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    CLEAR lt_tokens.
    CLEAR ls_token.
    ls_token-kind = 'N'.
    ls_token-val  = lv_curr.
    APPEND ls_token TO lt_tokens.

    DO lines( operator ) TIMES.
      READ TABLE operator INDEX sy-index ASSIGNING <oper>.
      READ TABLE operand  INDEX sy-index + 1 ASSIGNING <opnd>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <oper> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <opnd> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        result = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF <oper> = '**'.
        lv_next = <opnd>.
        lv_tmp = 1.
        IF lv_next = 0.
          lv_tmp = 1.
        ELSE.
          DO lv_next TIMES.
            lv_tmp = lv_tmp * lv_curr.
          ENDDO.
        ENDIF.
        lv_curr = lv_tmp.

        READ TABLE lt_tokens INDEX lines( lt_tokens ) INTO ls_token.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND ls_token-kind = 'N'.
          ls_token-val = lv_curr.
          MODIFY lt_tokens FROM ls_token INDEX lines( lt_tokens ).
        ENDIF.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR ls_token.
      ls_token-kind = 'O'.

      CLEAR lv_op.
      IF <oper> = '//' .
        lv_op = 'DV'.
      ELSEIF <oper> = '+'.
        lv_op = '+'.
      ELSEIF <oper> = '-'.
        lv_op = '-'.
      ELSEIF <oper> = '*'.
        lv_op = '*'.
      ELSE.
        result = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      ls_token-op = lv_op.
      APPEND ls_token TO lt_tokens.

      lv_curr = <opnd>.
      CLEAR ls_token.
      ls_token-kind = 'N'.
      ls_token-val  = lv_curr.
      APPEND ls_token TO lt_tokens.
    ENDDO.

    CLEAR lt_vals.
    CLEAR lt_ops.

    LOOP AT lt_tokens INTO ls_token.
      IF ls_token-kind = 'N'.
        APPEND ls_token-val TO lt_vals.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_op = ls_token-op.

      WHILE lines( lt_ops ) > 0.
        READ TABLE lt_ops INDEX lines( lt_ops ) INTO lv_do_op.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        IF ( lv_do_op = '*' OR lv_do_op = 'DV' ) AND ( lv_op = '+' OR lv_op = '-' ).
        ELSEIF ( lv_do_op = '*' OR lv_do_op = 'DV' ) AND ( lv_op = '*' OR lv_op = 'DV' ).
        ELSEIF ( lv_do_op = '+' OR lv_do_op = '-' ) AND ( lv_op = '+' OR lv_op = '-' ).
        ELSE.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ) INTO lv_right.
        DELETE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ).
        READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ) INTO lv_left.
        DELETE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ).

        CASE lv_do_op.
          WHEN '+'.
            lv_tmp = lv_left + lv_right.
          WHEN '-'.
            lv_tmp = lv_left - lv_right.
          WHEN '*'.
            lv_tmp = lv_left * lv_right.
          WHEN 'DV'.
            IF lv_right = 0.
              lv_tmp = 0.
            ELSE.
              lv_tmp = lv_left DIV lv_right.
            ENDIF.
          WHEN OTHERS.
            lv_tmp = 0.
        ENDCASE.

        APPEND lv_tmp TO lt_vals.
        DELETE lt_ops INDEX lines( lt_ops ).
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND lv_op TO lt_ops.
    ENDLOOP.

    WHILE lines( lt_ops ) > 0.
      READ TABLE lt_ops INDEX lines( lt_ops ) INTO lv_do_op.
      DELETE lt_ops INDEX lines( lt_ops ).

      READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ) INTO lv_right.
      DELETE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ).
      READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ) INTO lv_left.
      DELETE lt_vals INDEX lines( lt_vals ).

      CASE lv_do_op.
        WHEN '+'.
          lv_tmp = lv_left + lv_right.
        WHEN '-'.
          lv_tmp = lv_left - lv_right.
        WHEN '*'.
          lv_tmp = lv_left * lv_right.
        WHEN 'DV'.
          IF lv_right = 0.
            lv_tmp = 0.
          ELSE.
            lv_tmp = lv_left DIV lv_right.
          ENDIF.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          lv_tmp = 0.
      ENDCASE.

      APPEND lv_tmp TO lt_vals.
    ENDWHILE.

    READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX 1 INTO result.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      result = 0.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_operator,
             op TYPE c LENGTH 2,
           END OF ty_operator.
    TYPES tt_operator TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_operator WITH DEFAULT KEY.
    TYPES tt_operand  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        it_operator TYPE tt_operator
        it_operand  TYPE tt_operand
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE int8.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA lv_len_op   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len_va   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_prec_new TYPE i.
    DATA lv_prec_top TYPE i.
    DATA lv_reduce   TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_top_op   TYPE c LENGTH 2.
    DATA lv_op2      TYPE c LENGTH 2.

    DATA lt_stack_val TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_stack_op  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_operator WITH EMPTY KEY.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <op>  TYPE ty_operator.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <val> TYPE i.

    DATA lv_new_val TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_rhs     TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_lhs     TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_res     TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_rhs2    TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_lhs2    TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_res2    TYPE decfloat34.

    rv_result = 0.

    lv_len_op = lines( it_operator ).
    lv_len_va = lines( it_operand ).

    IF lv_len_va < 2 OR lv_len_op < 1 OR lv_len_op <> lv_len_va - 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    ASSIGN it_operand[ 1 ] TO <val>.
    APPEND CONV decfloat34( <val> ) TO lt_stack_val.

    DO lv_len_op TIMES.
      ASSIGN it_operator[ sy-index ] TO <op>.
      ASSIGN it_operand[ sy-index + 1 ] TO <val>.

      lv_new_val = CONV decfloat34( <val> ).

      lv_prec_new = 0.
      CASE <op>-op.
        WHEN '+' OR '-'.
          lv_prec_new = 1.
        WHEN '*' OR '//' .
          lv_prec_new = 2.
        WHEN '**'.
          lv_prec_new = 3.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          RETURN.
      ENDCASE.

      WHILE lines( lt_stack_op ) > 0.
        lv_top_op = lt_stack_op[ lines( lt_stack_op ) ]-op.

        lv_prec_top = 0.
        CASE lv_top_op.
          WHEN '+' OR '-'.
            lv_prec_top = 1.
          WHEN '*' OR '//' .
            lv_prec_top = 2.
          WHEN '**'.
            lv_prec_top = 3.
        ENDCASE.

        lv_reduce = abap_false.
        IF lv_prec_top > lv_prec_new.
          lv_reduce = abap_true.
        ELSEIF lv_prec_top = lv_prec_new AND <op>-op <> '**'.
          lv_reduce = abap_true.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_reduce = abap_false.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        lv_rhs = lt_stack_val[ lines( lt_stack_val ) ].
        DELETE lt_stack_val INDEX lines( lt_stack_val ).

        lv_lhs = lt_stack_val[ lines( lt_stack_val ) ].
        DELETE lt_stack_val INDEX lines( lt_stack_val ).

        DELETE lt_stack_op INDEX lines( lt_stack_op ).

        lv_res = CONV decfloat34( 0 ).

        CASE lv_top_op.
          WHEN '+'.
            lv_res = lv_lhs + lv_rhs.
          WHEN '-'.
            lv_res = lv_lhs - lv_rhs.
          WHEN '*'.
            lv_res = lv_lhs * lv_rhs.
          WHEN '//' .
            IF lv_rhs = 0.
              RETURN.
            ENDIF.
            lv_res = floor( lv_lhs / lv_rhs ).
          WHEN '**'.
            lv_res = ipow( base = lv_lhs exp = lv_rhs ).
          WHEN OTHERS.
            RETURN.
        ENDCASE.

        APPEND lv_res TO lt_stack_val.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_operator( op = <op>-op ) TO lt_stack_op.
      APPEND lv_new_val TO lt_stack_val.
    ENDDO.

    WHILE lines( lt_stack_op ) > 0.
      lv_rhs2 = lt_stack_val[ lines( lt_stack_val ) ].
      DELETE lt_stack_val INDEX lines( lt_stack_val ).

      lv_lhs2 = lt_stack_val[ lines( lt_stack_val ) ].
      DELETE lt_stack_val INDEX lines( lt_stack_val ).

      lv_op2 = lt_stack_op[ lines( lt_stack_op ) ]-op.
      DELETE lt_stack_op INDEX lines( lt_stack_op ).

      lv_res2 = CONV decfloat34( 0 ).

      CASE lv_op2.
        WHEN '+'.
          lv_res2 = lv_lhs2 + lv_rhs2.
        WHEN '-'.
          lv_res2 = lv_lhs2 - lv_rhs2.
        WHEN '*'.
          lv_res2 = lv_lhs2 * lv_rhs2.
        WHEN '//' .
          IF lv_rhs2 = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_res2 = floor( lv_lhs2 / lv_rhs2 ).
        WHEN '**'.
          lv_res2 = ipow( base = lv_lhs2 exp = lv_rhs2 ).
        WHEN OTHERS.
          RETURN.
      ENDCASE.

      APPEND lv_res2 TO lt_stack_val.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lines( lt_stack_val ) <> 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_result = lt_stack_val[ 1 ].
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC .

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_operator     TYPE c LENGTH 2.
    TYPES ty_operator_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_operator WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_int_tab      TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int4 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        operator TYPE ty_operator_tab
        operand  TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE int8.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA lv_vals TYPE int4.
    DATA lt_ops  TYPE ty_operator_tab.
    DATA lt_vals TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int8 WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_idx  TYPE int4.

    lv_vals = lines( operand ).
    rv_result = 0.

    IF lv_vals = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_vals = 1.
      rv_result = operand[ 1 ].
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lt_ops = operator.
    LOOP AT operand ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<opnd>).
      APPEND <opnd> TO lt_vals.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_idx = 1.
    WHILE lv_idx <= lines( lt_ops ).
      DATA lv_op TYPE ty_operator.
      lv_op = lt_ops[ lv_idx ].

      IF lv_op = '**'.
        DATA lv_left  TYPE int8.
        DATA lv_right TYPE int8.
        DATA lv_pow   TYPE int8.

        lv_left  = lt_vals[ lv_idx ].
        lv_right = lt_vals[ lv_idx + 1 ].

        lv_pow = 1.
        IF lv_right = 0.
          lv_pow = 1.
        ELSE.
          DO lv_right TIMES.
            lv_pow = lv_pow * lv_left.
          ENDDO.
        ENDIF.

        lt_vals[ lv_idx ] = lv_pow.
        DELETE lt_vals INDEX lv_idx + 1.
        DELETE lt_ops  INDEX lv_idx.
      ELSE.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    lv_idx = 1.
    WHILE lv_idx <= lines( lt_ops ).
      DATA lv_op2 TYPE ty_operator.
      lv_op2 = lt_ops[ lv_idx ].

      IF lv_op2 = '*' OR lv_op2 = '//' .
        DATA lv_a   TYPE int8.
        DATA lv_b   TYPE int8.
        DATA lv_res TYPE int8.

        lv_a = lt_vals[ lv_idx ].
        lv_b = lt_vals[ lv_idx + 1 ].

        IF lv_op2 = '*'.
          lv_res = lv_a * lv_b.
        ELSE.
          IF lv_b = 0.
            lv_res = 0.
          ELSE.
            lv_res = lv_a DIV lv_b.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.

        lt_vals[ lv_idx ] = lv_res.
        DELETE lt_vals INDEX lv_idx + 1.
        DELETE lt_ops  INDEX lv_idx.
      ELSE.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = lt_vals[ 1 ].
    DO lines( lt_ops ) TIMES.
      DATA lv_i   TYPE int4.
      DATA lv_op3 TYPE ty_operator.
      DATA lv_v   TYPE int8.

      lv_i = sy-index.
      lv_op3 = lt_ops[ lv_i ].
      lv_v = lt_vals[ lv_i + 1 ].

      IF lv_op3 = '+'.
        rv_result = rv_result + lv_v.
      ELSEIF lv_op3 = '-'.
        rv_result = rv_result - lv_v.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_op TYPE c LENGTH 2.
    TYPES ty_t_operator TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_op WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_t_operand  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        operator TYPE ty_t_operator
        operand  TYPE ty_t_operand
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA lv_acc     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_operand TYPE i.
    DATA lv_op      TYPE ty_op.
    DATA lv_base    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_pow     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx     TYPE i.

    rv_result = 0.

    IF lines( operand ) < 2 OR lines( operator ) < 1 OR lines( operator ) <> lines( operand ) - 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE operand INDEX 1 INTO lv_acc.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lines( operator ) TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index.

      READ TABLE operator INDEX lv_idx INTO lv_op.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE operand INDEX lv_idx + 1 INTO lv_operand.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      CASE lv_op.
        WHEN '+'.
          lv_acc = lv_acc + lv_operand.
        WHEN '-'.
          lv_acc = lv_acc - lv_operand.
        WHEN '*'.
          lv_acc = lv_acc * lv_operand.
        WHEN '//' .
          IF lv_operand = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_acc = lv_acc DIV lv_operand.
        WHEN '**'.
          IF lv_operand < 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_base = lv_acc.
          lv_pow  = 1.
          DO lv_operand TIMES.
            lv_pow = lv_pow * lv_base.
          ENDDO.
          lv_acc = lv_pow.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          RETURN.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDDO.

    rv_result = lv_acc.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_operator   TYPE c LENGTH 2.
    TYPES ty_t_operator TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_operator WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_t_operand  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int8 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        operator TYPE ty_t_operator
        operand  TYPE ty_t_operand
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE decfloat34.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA lt_ops TYPE ty_t_operator.
    DATA lt_val TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    lt_ops = operator.
    LOOP AT operand ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      APPEND CONV decfloat34( <n> ) TO lt_val.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_val ) < 2 OR lines( lt_ops ) <> lines( lt_val ) - 1.
      rv_result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
    DATA lv_ops_count TYPE i.

    lv_idx = 1.
    lv_ops_count = lines( lt_ops ).

    WHILE lv_idx <= lv_ops_count.
      READ TABLE lt_ops INDEX lv_idx INTO DATA(lv_op).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_op = '**'.
        READ TABLE lt_val INDEX lv_idx INTO DATA(lv_left).
        READ TABLE lt_val INDEX lv_idx + 1 INTO DATA(lv_right).
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          rv_result = 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        DATA lv_res TYPE decfloat34.
        DATA lv_exp TYPE int8.

        lv_res = 1.
        lv_exp = CONV int8( lv_right ).

        IF lv_right <> CONV decfloat34( lv_exp ) OR lv_exp < 0.
          rv_result = 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        DO lv_exp TIMES.
          lv_res = lv_res * lv_left.
        ENDDO.

        DELETE lt_val INDEX lv_idx + 1.
        MODIFY lt_val INDEX lv_idx FROM lv_res.

        DELETE lt_ops INDEX lv_idx.
        lv_ops_count = lv_ops_count - 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    lv_idx = 1.
    lv_ops_count = lines( lt_ops ).

    WHILE lv_idx <= lv_ops_count.
      READ TABLE lt_ops INDEX lv_idx INTO DATA(lv_op2).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_op2 = '*' OR lv_op2 = '//' .
        READ TABLE lt_val INDEX lv_idx INTO DATA(lv_a).
        READ TABLE lt_val INDEX lv_idx + 1 INTO DATA(lv_b).
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          rv_result = 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        DATA lv_r2 TYPE decfloat34.
        lv_r2 = 0.

        IF lv_op2 = '*'.
          lv_r2 = lv_a * lv_b.
        ELSE.
          IF lv_b = 0.
            rv_result = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_r2 = floor( lv_a / lv_b ).
        ENDIF.

        DELETE lt_val INDEX lv_idx + 1.
        MODIFY lt_val INDEX lv_idx FROM lv_r2.

        DELETE lt_ops INDEX lv_idx.
        lv_ops_count = lv_ops_count - 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    READ TABLE lt_val INDEX 1 INTO rv_result.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_ops INTO DATA(lv_op3).
      READ TABLE lt_val INDEX sy-tabix + 1 INTO DATA(lv_next).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_result = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      CASE lv_op3.
        WHEN '+'.
          rv_result = rv_result + lv_next.
        WHEN '-'.
          rv_result = rv_result - lv_next.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          rv_result = 0.
          RETURN.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        operator TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH DEFAULT KEY
        operand  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA: lv_acc  TYPE i,
          lv_i    TYPE i,
          lv_j    TYPE i,
          lv_k    TYPE i,
          lv_ops  TYPE i,
          lv_op   TYPE string,
          lv_op2  TYPE string,
          lv_sign TYPE string,
          lv_num  TYPE i,
          lv_rhs  TYPE i,
          lv_term TYPE i,
          lv_pow  TYPE i.

    READ TABLE operand INDEX 1 INTO lv_acc.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_ops = lines( operator ).
    lv_i = 1.

    WHILE lv_i <= lv_ops.
      READ TABLE operator INDEX lv_i INTO lv_op.
      READ TABLE operand  INDEX lv_i + 1 INTO lv_num.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      CASE lv_op.
        WHEN '+' OR '-'.
          lv_sign = lv_op.
          lv_term = lv_num.

          lv_j = lv_i + 1.
          WHILE lv_j <= lv_ops.
            READ TABLE operator INDEX lv_j INTO lv_op2.
            IF sy-subrc <> 0.
              EXIT.
            ENDIF.

            IF lv_op2 <> '*' AND lv_op2 <> '//' AND lv_op2 <> '/' AND lv_op2 <> '**'.
              EXIT.
            ENDIF.

            READ TABLE operand INDEX lv_j + 1 INTO lv_rhs.
            IF sy-subrc <> 0.
              EXIT.
            ENDIF.

            CASE lv_op2.
              WHEN '**'.
                IF lv_rhs = 0.
                  lv_pow = 1.
                ELSE.
                  lv_pow = lv_term.
                  lv_k = 1.
                  WHILE lv_k < lv_rhs.
                    lv_pow = lv_pow * lv_term.
                    lv_k = lv_k + 1.
                  ENDWHILE.
                ENDIF.
                lv_term = lv_pow.
              WHEN '*'.
                lv_term = lv_term * lv_rhs.
              WHEN '//' OR '/'.
                IF lv_rhs = 0.
                  rv_result = 0.
                  RETURN.
                ENDIF.
                lv_term = lv_term DIV lv_rhs.
            ENDCASE.

            lv_j = lv_j + 1.
          ENDWHILE.

          IF lv_sign = '+'.
            lv_acc = lv_acc + lv_term.
          ELSE.
            lv_acc = lv_acc - lv_term.
          ENDIF.

          lv_i = lv_j.

        WHEN '*'.
          lv_acc = lv_acc * lv_num.
          lv_i = lv_i + 1.

        WHEN '//' OR '/'.
          IF lv_num = 0.
            rv_result = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_acc = lv_acc DIV lv_num.
          lv_i = lv_i + 1.

        WHEN '**'.
          IF lv_num = 0.
            lv_pow = 1.
          ELSE.
            lv_pow = lv_acc.
            lv_k = 1.
            WHILE lv_k < lv_num.
              lv_pow = lv_pow * lv_acc.
              lv_k = lv_k + 1.
            ENDWHILE.
          ENDIF.
          lv_acc = lv_pow.
          lv_i = lv_i + 1.

        WHEN OTHERS.
          lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = lv_acc.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int TYPE int8.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        operator TYPE string_table
        operand  TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE ty_int.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA: lv_acc     TYPE ty_int,
          lv_current TYPE ty_int,
          lv_next    TYPE ty_int,
          lv_op      TYPE string.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <op> TYPE string,
                   <n>  TYPE ty_int.

    READ TABLE operand INDEX 1 ASSIGNING <n>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_acc = <n>.
    lv_current = <n>.

    DO lines( operator ) TIMES.
      ASSIGN operator[ sy-index ] TO <op>.
      READ TABLE operand INDEX sy-index + 1 ASSIGNING <n>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_next = <n>.
      lv_op = <op>.

      CASE lv_op.
        WHEN '**'.
          lv_current = ipow( base = lv_current exp = lv_next ).
          lv_acc = lv_current.
        WHEN '*'.
          lv_current = lv_current * lv_next.
          lv_acc = lv_current.
        WHEN '//' .
          IF lv_next = 0.
            rv_result = 0.
            RETURN.
          ENDIF.
          lv_current = lv_current DIV lv_next.
          lv_acc = lv_current.
        WHEN '+'.
          lv_acc = lv_acc + lv_next.
          lv_current = lv_acc.
        WHEN '-'.
          lv_acc = lv_acc - lv_next.
          lv_current = lv_acc.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          rv_result = 0.
          RETURN.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDDO.

    rv_result = lv_acc.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_operator_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_operand_tab  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int4   WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS do_algebra
      IMPORTING
        operator TYPE ty_operator_tab
        operand  TYPE ty_operand_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE decfloat34.

  PROTECTED SECTION.
  PRIVATE SECTION.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_do_algebra IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD do_algebra.
    DATA lt_opnd TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_oper TYPE ty_operator_tab.

    LOOP AT operand ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<i>).
      APPEND CONV decfloat34( <i> ) TO lt_opnd.
    ENDLOOP.
    lt_oper = operator.

    DATA lv_count_oper TYPE int4.
    DATA lv_count_opnd TYPE int4.
    lv_count_oper = lines( lt_oper ).
    lv_count_opnd = lines( lt_opnd ).

    IF lv_count_opnd < 2 OR lv_count_oper < 1 OR lv_count_oper <> lv_count_opnd - 1.
      rv_result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_index TYPE int4.

    DATA lt_vals TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lt_ops  TYPE ty_operator_tab.

    APPEND lt_opnd[ 1 ] TO lt_vals.

    DATA lv_last TYPE int4.

    DO lv_count_oper TIMES.
      lv_index = sy-index.
      DATA(lv_op)  = lt_oper[ lv_index ].
      DATA(lv_rhs) = lt_opnd[ lv_index + 1 ].

      IF lv_op = '**'.
        lv_last = lines( lt_vals ).
        READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lv_last INTO DATA(lv_base).
        DELETE lt_vals INDEX lv_last.
        APPEND ipow( base = lv_base exp = lv_rhs ) TO lt_vals.
      ELSEIF lv_op = '*'.
        lv_last = lines( lt_vals ).
        READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lv_last INTO DATA(lv_lhs_m).
        DELETE lt_vals INDEX lv_last.
        APPEND ( lv_lhs_m * lv_rhs ) TO lt_vals.
      ELSEIF lv_op = '//' .
        lv_last = lines( lt_vals ).
        READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lv_last INTO DATA(lv_lhs_d).
        DELETE lt_vals INDEX lv_last.
        IF lv_rhs = 0.
          rv_result = 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        APPEND floor( lv_lhs_d / lv_rhs ) TO lt_vals.
      ELSE.
        APPEND lv_op  TO lt_ops.
        APPEND lv_rhs TO lt_vals.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX 1 INTO rv_result.

    DATA lv_ops_cnt TYPE int4.
    lv_ops_cnt = lines( lt_ops ).

    DO lv_ops_cnt TIMES.
      lv_index = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_ops  INDEX lv_index     INTO DATA(lv_o).
      READ TABLE lt_vals INDEX lv_index + 1 INTO DATA(lv_v).

      IF lv_o = '+'.
        rv_result = rv_result + lv_v.
      ELSEIF lv_o = '-'.
        rv_result = rv_result - lv_v.
      ELSE.
        rv_result = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sorted_list_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_t_string TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_s_item,
             word TYPE string,
             len  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_s_item.
    TYPES ty_t_item TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_s_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS sorted_list_sum
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_list) TYPE ty_t_string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sorted_list_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sorted_list_sum.
    DATA lt_items TYPE ty_t_item.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.
    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      DATA(lv_word) = CONV string( <lv_any> ).
      DATA(lv_len)  = strlen( lv_word ).
      IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0.
        APPEND VALUE ty_s_item( word = lv_word len = lv_len ) TO lt_items.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY len ASCENDING word ASCENDING.

    rt_list = VALUE ty_t_string( FOR ls IN lt_items ( ls-word ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_total_match DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS total_match
      IMPORTING
        lst1 TYPE string_table
        lst2 TYPE string_table
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_result) TYPE string_table.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_total_match IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD total_match.
    DATA lv_len1 TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len2 TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <s1> TYPE string.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <s2> TYPE string.

    CLEAR: lv_len1, lv_len2.

    LOOP AT lst1 ASSIGNING <s1>.
      lv_len1 = lv_len1 + strlen( <s1> ).
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lst2 ASSIGNING <s2>.
      lv_len2 = lv_len2 + strlen( <s2> ).
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_len1 LE lv_len2.
      rt_result = lst1.
    ELSE.
      rt_result = lst2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_palindrome DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_palindrome
      IMPORTING
        text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_palindrome) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_palindrome IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_palindrome.
    DATA: lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_idx   TYPE i,
          lv_left  TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_right TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_text  TYPE csequence.

    lv_text = text.
    lv_len = strlen( lv_text ).
    rv_is_palindrome = abap_true.

    DO lv_len DIV 2 TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.

      lv_left  = lv_text+lv_idx(1).
      lv_right = lv_text+( lv_len - 1 - lv_idx )(1).

      IF lv_left <> lv_right.
        rv_is_palindrome = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int TYPE int4.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int WITH NON-UNIQUE SORTED KEY sk COMPONENTS table_line.

    CLASS-METHODS strange_sort_list
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_list) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int WITH EMPTY KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD strange_sort_list.
    rt_list = VALUE #( ).

    IF it_list IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int WITH EMPTY KEY.
    lt_sorted = it_list.
    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    DATA lv_low TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_high TYPE i VALUE lines( lt_sorted ).
    DATA lv_take_low TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    WHILE lv_low <= lv_high.
      IF lv_take_low = abap_true.
        APPEND lt_sorted[ lv_low ] TO rt_list.
        lv_low = lv_low + 1.
        lv_take_low = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        APPEND lt_sorted[ lv_high ] TO rt_list.
        lv_high = lv_high - 1.
        lv_take_low = abap_true.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH NON-UNIQUE SORTED KEY sk COMPONENTS table_line.

    CLASS-METHODS strange_sort_list
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD strange_sort_list.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE ty_int_tab.
    DATA lv_min TYPE i.
    DATA lv_max TYPE i.
    DATA lv_pick_min TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.
    DATA lv_lines TYPE i.

    strange_sort_list = VALUE ty_int_tab( ).
    lt_sorted = it_list.

    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    WHILE lines( lt_sorted ) > 0.
      IF lv_pick_min = abap_true.
        READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 1 INTO lv_min.
        APPEND lv_min TO strange_sort_list.
        DELETE lt_sorted INDEX 1.
        lv_pick_min = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_lines = lines( lt_sorted ).
        READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_lines INTO lv_max.
        APPEND lv_max TO strange_sort_list.
        DELETE lt_sorted INDEX lv_lines.
        lv_pick_min = abap_true.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH NON-UNIQUE SORTED KEY sk COMPONENTS table_line.

    CLASS-METHODS strange_sort_list
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_list) TYPE ty_int_tab.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD strange_sort_list.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE ty_int_tab.
    lt_sorted = it_list.
    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    rt_list = VALUE ty_int_tab( ).

    DATA lv_left TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_right TYPE i.
    lv_right = lines( lt_sorted ).

    DATA lv_take_min TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    WHILE lv_left <= lv_right.
      IF lv_take_min = abap_true.
        APPEND lt_sorted[ lv_left ] TO rt_list.
        lv_left = lv_left + 1.
        lv_take_min = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        APPEND lt_sorted[ lv_right ] TO rt_list.
        lv_right = lv_right - 1.
        lv_take_min = abap_true.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH NON-UNIQUE SORTED KEY sk COMPONENTS table_line.

    CLASS-METHODS strange_sort_list
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_list) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strange_sort_list IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD strange_sort_list.
    rt_list = VALUE ty_int_tab( ).

    IF it_list IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_sorted TYPE ty_int_tab.
    lt_sorted = it_list.
    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    DATA lv_left  TYPE syindex VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_right TYPE syindex.
    lv_right = lines( lt_sorted ).

    WHILE lv_left <= lv_right.
      APPEND lt_sorted[ lv_left ] TO rt_list.
      lv_left = lv_left + 1.

      IF lv_left <= lv_right.
        APPEND lt_sorted[ lv_right ] TO rt_list.
        lv_right = lv_right - 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES tt_values TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS common
      IMPORTING
        l1 TYPE tt_values
        l2 TYPE tt_values
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_common) TYPE tt_values.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD common.
    TYPES tt_set TYPE SORTED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    DATA lt_set1   TYPE tt_set.
    DATA lt_set2   TYPE tt_set.
    DATA lt_common TYPE tt_set.

    LOOP AT l1 ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<l1>).
      INSERT <l1> INTO TABLE lt_set1.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT l2 ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<l2>).
      INSERT <l2> INTO TABLE lt_set2.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_set1 ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<v>).
      READ TABLE lt_set2 WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <v> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        INSERT <v> INTO TABLE lt_common.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_common = lt_common.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS common
      IMPORTING
        l1 TYPE ANY TABLE
        l2 TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_common) TYPE ty_list.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD common.
    DATA lt_set2   TYPE HASHED TABLE OF i WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_result TYPE SORTED TABLE OF i WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v>  TYPE any.
    DATA lv_i TYPE i.

    LOOP AT l2 ASSIGNING <v>.
      lv_i = CONV i( <v> ).
      INSERT lv_i INTO TABLE lt_set2.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT l1 ASSIGNING <v>.
      lv_i = CONV i( <v> ).
      READ TABLE lt_set2 WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_i TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        INSERT lv_i INTO TABLE lt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_common = lt_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS common
      IMPORTING
        l1 TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        l2 TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_common) TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD common.
    DATA lt_l2_sorted TYPE SORTED TABLE OF i WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_result    TYPE SORTED TABLE OF i WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    LOOP AT l2 ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv2>).
      INSERT CONV i( <lv2> ) INTO TABLE lt_l2_sorted.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT l1 ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv1>).
      DATA(lv_i) = CONV i( <lv1> ).
      READ TABLE lt_l2_sorted WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_i TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        INSERT lv_i INTO TABLE lt_result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_common = lt_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int     TYPE i.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS common
      IMPORTING
        l1 TYPE ty_int_tab
        l2 TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_common) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_common IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD common.
    DATA lt_set1       TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_int WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_set2       TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_int WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt_common_set TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_int WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v> TYPE ty_int.

    LOOP AT l1 ASSIGNING <v>.
      INSERT <v> INTO TABLE lt_set1.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT l2 ASSIGNING <v>.
      INSERT <v> INTO TABLE lt_set2.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_set1 ASSIGNING <v>.
      READ TABLE lt_set2 WITH TABLE KEY table_line = <v> TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        INSERT <v> INTO TABLE lt_common_set.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_common = lt_common_set.
    SORT rt_common ASCENDING.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_find_max DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_string_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_max
      IMPORTING
        it_words TYPE ty_string_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_word) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_max IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_max.
    DATA: lv_best_unique TYPE i VALUE -1,
          lv_unique      TYPE i,
          lv_len         TYPE i,
          lv_char        TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_word        TYPE string.

    DATA lt_chars TYPE HASHED TABLE OF c WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    CLEAR rv_word.

    LOOP AT it_words INTO lv_word.
      CLEAR lt_chars.

      lv_len = strlen( lv_word ).

      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_char = lv_word+sy-index-1(1).
        INSERT lv_char INTO TABLE lt_chars.
      ENDDO.

      lv_unique = lines( lt_chars ).

      IF lv_unique > lv_best_unique.
        lv_best_unique = lv_unique.
        rv_word = lv_word.
      ELSEIF lv_unique = lv_best_unique.
        IF rv_word IS INITIAL OR lv_word < rv_word.
          rv_word = lv_word.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  FINAL

CLASS zcl_find_max IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD find_max.
    DATA lv_best_word  TYPE string.
    DATA lv_best_count TYPE i VALUE -1.
    DATA lv_word       TYPE string.

    LOOP AT it_words INTO lv_word.
      DATA lt_seen TYPE ty_char_set.
      DATA(lv_len) = strlen( lv_word ).
      DATA lv_char TYPE ty_char.

      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_char = lv_word+sy-index(1).
        INSERT lv_char INTO TABLE lt_seen.
      ENDDO.

      DATA(lv_count) = lines( lt_seen ).

      IF lv_count > lv_best_count OR ( lv_count = lv_best_count AND ( lv_best_word IS INITIAL OR lv_word < lv_best_word ) ).
        lv_best_count = lv_count.
        lv_best_word  = lv_word.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_word = lv_best_word.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_circular_shift DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS circular_shift
      IMPORTING
        VALUE(iv_x)     TYPE string
        VALUE(iv_shift) TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_circular_shift IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD circular_shift.
    DATA: lv_digits TYPE string,
          lv_len    TYPE i,
          lv_shift  TYPE i,
          lv_pos    TYPE i,
          lv_char   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_part1  TYPE string,
          lv_part2  TYPE string.

    lv_digits = iv_x.
    CONDENSE lv_digits NO-GAPS.

    IF lv_digits IS INITIAL.
      rv_result = ``.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_digits(1) = `-`.
      lv_digits = lv_digits+1.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = strlen( lv_digits ).

    IF lv_len <= 1 OR iv_shift <= 0.
      rv_result = lv_digits.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF iv_shift > lv_len.
      rv_result = ``.
      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_pos = lv_len - sy-index.
        lv_char = lv_digits+lv_pos(1).
        rv_result = rv_result && lv_char.
      ENDDO.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_shift = iv_shift MOD lv_len.

    IF lv_shift = 0.
      rv_result = lv_digits.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_pos = lv_len - lv_shift.
    lv_part1 = lv_digits+lv_pos(lv_shift).
    lv_part2 = lv_digits(lv_pos).
    rv_result = lv_part1 && lv_part2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_circular_shift DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS circular_shift
      IMPORTING
        x     TYPE i
        shift TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_circular_shift IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD circular_shift.
    DATA: lv_str    TYPE string,
          lv_len    TYPE i,
          lv_shift  TYPE i,
          lv_idx    TYPE i,
          lv_off    TYPE i,
          lv_left   TYPE string,
          lv_right  TYPE string.

    lv_str = |{ x }|.
    CONDENSE lv_str NO-GAPS.

    lv_len = strlen( lv_str ).
    lv_shift = shift.

    IF lv_len <= 0.
      rv_result = ''.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_shift < 0.
      lv_shift = lv_shift * -1.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_shift > lv_len.
      rv_result = ''.
      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_idx = lv_len - sy-index.
        rv_result = rv_result && lv_str+lv_idx(1).
      ENDDO.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_shift = lv_shift MOD lv_len.

    IF lv_shift = 0.
      rv_result = lv_str.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_off = lv_len - lv_shift.

    lv_left  = lv_str(lv_off).
    lv_right = lv_str+lv_off(lv_shift).

    rv_result = lv_right && lv_left.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_smallest_change DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_line,
             value TYPE string,
           END OF ty_line,
           ty_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_line WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS smallest_change
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE ty_arr
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_changes) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_smallest_change IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD smallest_change.
    DATA: lv_len       TYPE i,
          lv_left_idx  TYPE i,
          lv_right_idx TYPE i,
          ls_left      TYPE ty_line,
          ls_right     TYPE ty_line.

    lv_len = lines( it_arr ).
    rv_changes = 0.

    IF lv_len <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len DIV 2 TIMES.
      lv_left_idx = sy-index.
      lv_right_idx = lv_len - sy-index + 1.

      READ TABLE it_arr INDEX lv_left_idx INTO ls_left.
      READ TABLE it_arr INDEX lv_right_idx INTO ls_right.

      IF ls_left-value <> ls_right-value.
        rv_changes = rv_changes + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_smallest_change DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS smallest_change
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_changes) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_smallest_change IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD smallest_change.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lv_any> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_i     TYPE i,
          lv_j     TYPE i,
          lv_left  TYPE string,
          lv_right TYPE string.

    rv_changes = 0.

    lv_len = lines( it_arr ).
    IF lv_len <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_i = 1.
    lv_j = lv_len.

    WHILE lv_i < lv_j.
      CLEAR lv_left.
      CLEAR lv_right.

      ASSIGN it_arr[ lv_i ] TO <lv_any>.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_left = |{ <lv_any> }|.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN it_arr[ lv_j ] TO <lv_any>.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_right = |{ <lv_any> }|.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_left <> lv_right.
        rv_changes = rv_changes + 1.
      ENDIF.

      lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      lv_j = lv_j - 1.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fruit_distribution DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS fruit_distribution
      IMPORTING
        s TYPE string
        n TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_mangoes) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fruit_distribution IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD fruit_distribution.
    DATA lv_sum     TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_numstr  TYPE string.
    DATA lv_rest    TYPE string.
    DATA lv_offset  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_length  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_start   TYPE i.

    lv_rest = s.

    DO 2 TIMES.
      CLEAR lv_numstr.
      FIND FIRST OCCURRENCE OF PCRE '\d+' IN lv_rest SUBMATCHES lv_numstr.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_numstr IS INITIAL.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sum = lv_sum + CONV i( lv_numstr ).

      lv_offset = sy-fdpos.
      lv_length = strlen( lv_numstr ).
      lv_start = lv_offset + lv_length.

      IF lv_start >= strlen( lv_rest ).
        CLEAR lv_rest.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_rest = lv_rest+lv_start.
    ENDDO.

    r_mangoes = n - lv_sum.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fruit_distribution DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS fruit_distribution
      IMPORTING
        s TYPE string
        n TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_mango) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fruit_distribution IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD fruit_distribution.
    DATA: lv_apples  TYPE i VALUE 0,
          lv_oranges TYPE i VALUE 0.

    DATA: lt_tokens TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY,
          lv_tok    TYPE string,
          lv_idx    TYPE i,
          lv_num    TYPE i.

    SPLIT s AT space INTO TABLE lt_tokens.

    LOOP AT lt_tokens INTO lv_tok.
      lv_idx = sy-tabix.

      lv_num = 0.
      IF lv_tok CO '0123456789' AND lv_tok IS NOT INITIAL.
        lv_num = lv_tok.
      ELSE.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_tokens INDEX lv_idx + 1 INTO DATA(lv_next).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      TRANSLATE lv_next TO LOWER CASE.

      IF lv_next CP 'apple*'.
        lv_apples = lv_num.
      ELSEIF lv_next CP 'orange*'.
        lv_oranges = lv_num.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    r_mango = n - lv_apples - lv_oranges.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rolling_max DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS rolling_max
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_max) TYPE int4_table.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rolling_max IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD rolling_max.
    DATA lv_current_max TYPE i.
    DATA lv_initialized TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      DATA(lv_number) = CONV i( <lv_any> ).

      IF lv_initialized = abap_false.
        lv_current_max = lv_number.
        lv_initialized = abap_true.
      ELSEIF lv_number > lv_current_max.
        lv_current_max = lv_number.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND lv_current_max TO rt_max.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_rolling_max DEFINITION

CLASS zcl_digit_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD digit_sum.
    r_sum = 0.

    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_pos TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c   TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_len = strlen( i_s ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_pos = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = i_s+lv_pos(1).

      IF lv_c CO 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'.
        r_sum = r_sum + ( 65 + ( sy-fdpos ) ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

          lv_pos  TYPE i,
          lv_char TYPE c LENGTH 1,

    rv_sum = 0.
    lv_len = strlen( iv_text ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_pos  = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = iv_text+lv_pos(1).

CLASS zcl_digit_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL

      IMPORTING
        i_string TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_sum) TYPE i.

CLASS zcl_digit_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD digit_sum.
    r_sum = 0.

    DATA lv_len  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_len = strlen( i_string ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = substring( val = i_string off = lv_idx len = 1 ).

      CASE lv_char.
        WHEN 'A'. r_sum = r_sum + 65.
        WHEN 'B'. r_sum = r_sum + 66.
        WHEN 'C'. r_sum = r_sum + 67.
        WHEN 'D'. r_sum = r_sum + 68.
        WHEN 'E'. r_sum = r_sum + 69.
        WHEN 'F'. r_sum = r_sum + 70.
        WHEN 'G'. r_sum = r_sum + 71.
        WHEN 'H'. r_sum = r_sum + 72.
        WHEN 'I'. r_sum = r_sum + 73.
        WHEN 'J'. r_sum = r_sum + 74.
        WHEN 'K'. r_sum = r_sum + 75.
        WHEN 'L'. r_sum = r_sum + 76.
        WHEN 'M'. r_sum = r_sum + 77.
        WHEN 'N'. r_sum = r_sum + 78.
        WHEN 'O'. r_sum = r_sum + 79.
        WHEN 'P'. r_sum = r_sum + 80.
        WHEN 'Q'. r_sum = r_sum + 81.
        WHEN 'R'. r_sum = r_sum + 82.
        WHEN 'S'. r_sum = r_sum + 83.
        WHEN 'T'. r_sum = r_sum + 84.
        WHEN 'U'. r_sum = r_sum + 85.
        WHEN 'V'. r_sum = r_sum + 86.
        WHEN 'W'. r_sum = r_sum + 87.
        WHEN 'X'. r_sum = r_sum + 88.
        WHEN 'Y'. r_sum = r_sum + 89.
        WHEN 'Z'. r_sum = r_sum + 90.
        WHEN OTHERS.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_will_it_fly DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS will_it_fly
      IMPORTING
        q TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        w TYPE integer
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_will_it_fly IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD will_it_fly.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <q> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    ASSIGN q TO <q>.

    DATA lv_sum TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0 VALUE '0'.
    LOOP AT <q> ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<line>).
      lv_sum = lv_sum + CONV p( <line> ).
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_sum > w.
      rv_result = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    lv_len = lines( <q> ).

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 1.

    WHILE lv_idx <= lv_len / 2.
      READ TABLE <q> INDEX lv_idx ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<left>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE <q> INDEX ( lv_len - lv_idx + 1 ) ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<right>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF CONV string( <left> ) <> CONV string( <right> ).
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zwill_it_fly DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL

    TYPES ty_q TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sytabix WITH DEFAULT KEY.

      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zwill_it_fly IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD will_it_fly.
    DATA lv_sum TYPE sytabix VALUE 0.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v> TYPE sytabix.
    LOOP AT q ASSIGNING <v>.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + <v>.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_sum > w.
      rv_result = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_len TYPE sytabix.
    lv_len = lines( q ).

    IF lv_len <= 1.
      rv_result = abap_true.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_result = abap_true.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <a> TYPE sytabix,
                   <b> TYPE sytabix.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE sytabix.
    DO lv_len DIV 2 TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index.
      READ TABLE q INDEX lv_idx ASSIGNING <a>.
      READ TABLE q INDEX ( lv_len - lv_idx + 1 ) ASSIGNING <b>.
      IF <a> <> <b>.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zwill_it_fly DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL

  PUBLIC SECTION.

        iv_w TYPE c
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_ok) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zwill_it_fly IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD will_it_fly.
    rv_ok = abap_false.

    DATA lv_w TYPE i.
    lv_w = iv_w.

    DATA lv_sum TYPE i VALUE 0.
    LOOP AT it_q ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<v_raw>).
      DATA lv_v TYPE i.
      lv_v = <v_raw>.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + lv_v.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_sum > lv_w.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    lv_len = lines( it_q ).

    IF lv_len <= 1.
      rv_ok = abap_true.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len DIV 2 TIMES.
      READ TABLE it_q INDEX sy-index ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<l>).
      READ TABLE it_q INDEX ( lv_len - sy-index + 1 ) ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<r>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <l> <> <r>.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    rv_ok = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zwill_it_fly DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS will_it_fly
      IMPORTING
        q             TYPE any
        w             TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zwill_it_fly IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD will_it_fly.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <tab> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    ASSIGN q TO <tab>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      result = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_sum TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0 VALUE 0.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <line> TYPE any.
    LOOP AT <tab> ASSIGNING <line>.
      TRY.
          lv_sum = lv_sum + CONV p( <line> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          result = abap_false.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_sum > w.
      result = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_len) = lines( <tab> ).
    IF lv_len <= 1.
      result = abap_true.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_half) = lv_len / 2.

    result = abap_true.
    DO lv_half TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx_left)  = sy-index.
      DATA(lv_idx_right) = lv_len - sy-index + 1.

      READ TABLE <tab> INDEX lv_idx_left ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<l>).
      READ TABLE <tab> INDEX lv_idx_right ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<r>).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_left)  TYPE string.
      DATA(lv_right) TYPE string.

      TRY.
          lv_left  = CONV string( <l> ).
          lv_right = CONV string( <r> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          result = abap_false.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_left <> lv_right.
        result = abap_false.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_will_it_fly DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS will_it_fly
      IMPORTING
        q TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        w TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_will_it_fly IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD will_it_fly.
    DATA lv_sum TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0 VALUE '0'.
    DATA lv_n   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_i   TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v> TYPE any.
    LOOP AT q ASSIGNING <v>.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + CONV p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0( <v> ).
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_sum > w.
      rv_result = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_n = lines( q ).

    rv_result = abap_true.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <a> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <b> TYPE any.

    lv_i = 1.
    WHILE lv_i <= lv_n / 2.
      READ TABLE q INDEX lv_i ASSIGNING <a>.
      READ TABLE q INDEX ( lv_n - lv_i + 1 ) ASSIGNING <b>.
      IF <a> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <b> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF CONV string( <a> ) <> CONV string( <b> ).
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 1.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_monotonic DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS monotonic
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_monotonic) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_monotonic IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD monotonic.
    DATA lv_lines TYPE i.
    DATA lv_prev TYPE string.
    DATA lv_has_prev TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_direction TYPE i.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE string.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <any> TYPE any.

    lv_lines = lines( it_values ).
    IF lv_lines <= 2.
      rv_is_monotonic = abap_true.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_has_prev = abap_false.
    lv_direction = 0.

    LOOP AT it_values ASSIGNING <any>.
      lv_curr = <any>.

      IF lv_has_prev = abap_false.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        lv_has_prev = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_curr > lv_prev.
        IF lv_direction = -1.
          rv_is_monotonic = abap_false.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        lv_direction = 1.
      ELSEIF lv_curr < lv_prev.
        IF lv_direction = 1.
          rv_is_monotonic = abap_false.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        lv_direction = -1.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_is_monotonic = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_monotonic DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS monotonic
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_monotonic) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_monotonic IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD monotonic.
    DATA lv_count TYPE i.
    DATA lv_inc   TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_dec   TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_prev  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_curr  TYPE i.

    lv_count = lines( it_list ).

    IF lv_count <= 2.
      rv_is_monotonic = abap_true.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_inc = abap_true.
    lv_dec = abap_true.

    READ TABLE it_list INDEX 1 INTO lv_prev.

    DO lv_count - 1 TIMES.
      READ TABLE it_list INDEX sy-index + 1 INTO lv_curr.

      IF lv_curr > lv_prev.
        lv_dec = abap_false.
      ELSEIF lv_curr < lv_prev.
        lv_inc = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_inc = abap_false AND lv_dec = abap_false.
        rv_is_monotonic = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDDO.

    IF lv_inc = abap_true OR lv_dec = abap_true.
      rv_is_monotonic = abap_true.
    ELSE.
      rv_is_monotonic = abap_false.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_monotonic DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS monotonic
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int4 WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_monotonic) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_monotonic IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD monotonic.
    DATA: lv_prev     TYPE int4,
          lv_curr     TYPE int4,
          lv_inc      TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_dec      TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_has_prev TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    rv_is_monotonic = abap_true.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO lv_curr.
      IF lv_has_prev = abap_false.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        lv_has_prev = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_curr > lv_prev.
        lv_dec = abap_false.
      ELSEIF lv_curr < lv_prev.
        lv_inc = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_inc = abap_false AND lv_dec = abap_false.
        rv_is_monotonic = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_monotonic DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS monotonic

      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_monotonic) TYPE abap_bool.

CLASS zcl_monotonic IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD monotonic.
    DATA: lv_prev  TYPE int4,
          lv_curr  TYPE int4,
          lv_inc   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_dec   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_first TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO lv_curr.
      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        lv_first = abap_false.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_curr < lv_prev.
        lv_inc = abap_false.
      ELSEIF lv_curr > lv_prev.
        lv_dec = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_inc = abap_false AND lv_dec = abap_false.
        rv_is_monotonic = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_is_monotonic = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_monotonic IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD monotonic.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ls_any> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_prev TYPE string,
          lv_curr TYPE string,
          lv_dir  TYPE i,
          lv_inited TYPE abap_bool.

    lv_dir = 0.
    lv_inited = abap_false.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <ls_any>.
      lv_curr = |{ <ls_any> }|.

      IF lv_inited = abap_false.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        lv_inited = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_curr > lv_prev.
        IF lv_dir = -1.
          rv_result = abap_false.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        lv_dir = 1.
      ELSEIF lv_curr < lv_prev.
        IF lv_dir = 1.
          rv_result = abap_false.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        lv_dir = -1.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.

CLASS zcl_monotonic IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD monotonic.
    rv_is_monotonic = abap_true.

    IF lines( it_list ) <= 2.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <cur>  TYPE any.

      ELSEIF <cur> < <prev>.
        lv_nondec = abap_true.

      IF lv_nondec = abap_true AND lv_noninc = abap_true.
        rv_is_monotonic = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zpairs_sum_to_zero IMPLEMENTATION.

    rv_true = abap_false.

    DATA lt_seen TYPE HASHED TABLE OF i WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lv_val  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_neg  TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      lv_val = CONV i( <lv_any> ).

      lv_neg = lv_val * -1.
      READ TABLE lt_seen WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_neg TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        rv_true = abap_true.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      INSERT lv_val INTO TABLE lt_seen.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_pairs_sum_to_zero IMPLEMENTATION.

          lv_x_i = <lv_x>.
