CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS compute
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum_digits) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compute.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE any.

    DATA lv_max_prime TYPE i.
    lv_max_prime = -1.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <n>.
      DATA lv_n TYPE i.
      TRY.
          lv_n = <n>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_n <= 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_n = 2 OR lv_n = 3.
        IF lv_n > lv_max_prime.
          lv_max_prime = lv_n.
        ENDIF.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_n MOD 2 = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lv_is_prime TYPE abap_bool.
      lv_is_prime = abap_true.

      DATA lv_d TYPE i.
      lv_d = 3.

      WHILE lv_d * lv_d <= lv_n.
        IF lv_n MOD lv_d = 0.
          lv_is_prime = abap_false.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
        lv_d = lv_d + 2.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF lv_is_prime = abap_true AND lv_n > lv_max_prime.
        lv_max_prime = lv_n.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_max_prime < 0.
      rv_sum_digits = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_x TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sum TYPE i.
    lv_x = lv_max_prime.
    lv_sum = 0.

    WHILE lv_x > 0.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + lv_x MOD 10.
      lv_x = lv_x DIV 10.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_sum_digits = lv_sum.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS solve
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD solve.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lv_any> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_max_prime TYPE i VALUE -1,
          lv_n         TYPE i,
          lv_i         TYPE i,
          lv_is_prime  TYPE abap_bool,
          lv_limit     TYPE i,
          lv_s         TYPE string,
          lv_len       TYPE i,
          lv_pos       TYPE i,
          lv_char      TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      TRY.
          lv_n = CONV i( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_n < 2.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_n = 2 OR lv_n = 3.
        lv_is_prime = abap_true.
      ELSEIF lv_n MOD 2 = 0.
        lv_is_prime = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_is_prime = abap_true.

        lv_limit = 0.
        WHILE ( lv_limit + 1 ) * ( lv_limit + 1 ) <= lv_n.
          lv_limit = lv_limit + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        lv_i = 3.
        WHILE lv_i <= lv_limit.
          IF lv_n MOD lv_i = 0.
            lv_is_prime = abap_false.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          lv_i = lv_i + 2.
        ENDWHILE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_is_prime = abap_true AND lv_n > lv_max_prime.
        lv_max_prime = lv_n.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_max_prime < 2.
      rv_sum = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_s = |{ lv_max_prime }|.
    lv_len = strlen( lv_s ).
    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_pos = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = lv_s+lv_pos(1).
      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_char - '0' ).
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num TYPE int8.
    TYPES ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS solve
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE ty_num.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD solve.
    DATA lv_max_prime TYPE ty_num VALUE -1.
    DATA lv_n         TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_i         TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_is_prime  TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_work      TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_digit     TYPE ty_num.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO lv_n.
      IF lv_n <= 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_n = 2 OR lv_n = 3.
        lv_is_prime = abap_true.
      ELSEIF lv_n MOD 2 = 0.
        lv_is_prime = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_is_prime = abap_true.
        lv_i = 3.
        WHILE lv_i > 0 AND lv_i * lv_i <= lv_n.
          IF lv_n MOD lv_i = 0.
            lv_is_prime = abap_false.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          lv_i = lv_i + 2.
        ENDWHILE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_is_prime = abap_true AND lv_n > lv_max_prime.
        lv_max_prime = lv_n.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_sum = 0.
    IF lv_max_prime < 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_work = lv_max_prime.
    WHILE lv_work > 0.
      lv_digit = lv_work MOD 10.
      rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_digit.
      lv_work = lv_work DIV 10.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.
    TYPES ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS get_digit_sum_of_largest_prime
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE ty_num.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_largest_prime_digit_sum IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_digit_sum_of_largest_prime.
    rv_sum = 0.

    DATA lv_max_prime TYPE ty_num VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_is_prime  TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_i         TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_limit     TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_val       TYPE ty_num.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE ty_num.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <n>.
      IF <n> <= 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_is_prime = abap_true.

      IF <n> = 2 OR <n> = 3.
        lv_is_prime = abap_true.
      ELSEIF ( <n> MOD 2 ) = 0 OR ( <n> MOD 3 ) = 0.
        lv_is_prime = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        lv_i = 5.
        lv_limit = 1.

        WHILE lv_limit * lv_limit < <n>.
          lv_limit = lv_limit + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        WHILE lv_i <= lv_limit.
          IF ( <n> MOD lv_i ) = 0 OR ( <n> MOD ( lv_i + 2 ) ) = 0.
            lv_is_prime = abap_false.
            EXIT.
          ENDIF.
          lv_i = lv_i + 6.
        ENDWHILE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_is_prime = abap_true AND <n> > lv_max_prime.
        lv_max_prime = <n>.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_val = lv_max_prime.
    WHILE lv_val > 0.
      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_val MOD 10 ).
      lv_val = lv_val DIV 10.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_happy DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_happy
      IMPORTING
        iv_s TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_happy) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_happy IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_happy.
    DATA: lv_len TYPE i,
          lv_i   TYPE i,
          lv_a   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_b   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_c   TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_s ).

    IF lv_len < 3.
      rv_is_happy = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_is_happy = abap_true.

    lv_i = 0.
    WHILE lv_i <= lv_len - 3.
      lv_a = iv_s+lv_i(1).
      lv_b = iv_s+(lv_i + 1)(1).
      lv_c = iv_s+(lv_i + 2)(1).

      IF lv_a = lv_b OR lv_a = lv_c OR lv_b = lv_c.
        rv_is_happy = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_i = lv_i + 1.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_happy DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_happy
      IMPORTING
        VALUE(iv_s) TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_happy) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_happy IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_happy.
    DATA: lv_len TYPE i,
          lv_i   TYPE i,
          lv_o2  TYPE i,
          lv_o3  TYPE i,
          lv_a   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_b   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_c   TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    rv_is_happy = abap_false.
    lv_len = strlen( iv_s ).

    IF lv_len < 3.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len - 2 TIMES.
      lv_i  = sy-index - 1.
      lv_o2 = lv_i + 1.
      lv_o3 = lv_i + 2.

      lv_a = iv_s+lv_i(1).
      lv_b = iv_s+lv_o2(1).
      lv_c = iv_s+lv_o3(1).

      IF lv_a = lv_b OR lv_a = lv_c OR lv_b = lv_c.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    rv_is_happy = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_happy DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_happy
      IMPORTING
        VALUE(iv_s) TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_happy) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_happy IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_happy.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    lv_len = strlen( iv_s ).

    IF lv_len < 3.
      rv_is_happy = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_chars TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF c LENGTH 1 WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      APPEND iv_s+0(1) TO lt_chars.
      SHIFT iv_s BY 1 PLACES LEFT.
    ENDDO.

    DO lv_len - 2 TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index.
      DATA(lv_c1) = lt_chars[ lv_idx ].
      DATA(lv_c2) = lt_chars[ lv_idx + 1 ].
      DATA(lv_c3) = lt_chars[ lv_idx + 2 ].

      IF lv_c1 = lv_c2 OR lv_c1 = lv_c3 OR lv_c2 = lv_c3.
        rv_is_happy = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    rv_is_happy = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS znumerical_letter_grade DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_string_tab TYPE string_table.

    CLASS-METHODS numerical_letter_grade
      IMPORTING
        it_grades TYPE ty_string_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_letters) TYPE ty_string_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS znumerical_letter_grade IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD numerical_letter_grade.
    DATA lv_grade_str TYPE string.
    DATA lv_grade_num TYPE string.
    DATA lv_letter    TYPE string.

    CLEAR rt_letters.

    LOOP AT it_grades INTO lv_grade_str.
      lv_grade_num = lv_grade_str.
      TRANSLATE lv_grade_num USING ',.'.

      IF lv_grade_num = '4.0' OR lv_grade_num = '4.00' OR lv_grade_num = '4'.
        lv_letter = 'A+'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '3.7'.
        lv_letter = 'A'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '3.3'.
        lv_letter = 'A-'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '3.0'.
        lv_letter = 'B+'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '2.7'.
        lv_letter = 'B'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '2.3'.
        lv_letter = 'B-'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '2.0'.
        lv_letter = 'C+'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '1.7'.
        lv_letter = 'C'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '1.3'.
        lv_letter = 'C-'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '1.0'.
        lv_letter = 'D+'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '0.7'.
        lv_letter = 'D'.
      ELSEIF lv_grade_num > '0.0'.
        lv_letter = 'D-'.
      ELSE.
        lv_letter = 'E'.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND lv_letter TO rt_letters.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS znumerical_letter_grade IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD numerical_letter_grade.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <g> TYPE ty_grade_any.
    DATA lv_gpa TYPE p LENGTH 4 DECIMALS 1.
    DATA lv_letter TYPE string.

    LOOP AT it_grades ASSIGNING <g>.
      CLEAR lv_gpa.
      TRY.
          lv_gpa = CONV #( <g> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          lv_gpa = '0.0'.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_gpa = '4.0'.
        lv_letter = |A+|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '3.7'.
        lv_letter = |A|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '3.3'.
        lv_letter = |A-|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '3.0'.
        lv_letter = |B+|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '2.7'.
        lv_letter = |B|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '2.3'.
        lv_letter = |B-|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '2.0'.
        lv_letter = |C+|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '1.7'.
        lv_letter = |C|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '1.3'.
        lv_letter = |C-|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '1.0'.
        lv_letter = |D+|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '0.7'.
        lv_letter = |D|.
      ELSEIF lv_gpa > '0.0'.
        lv_letter = |D-|.
      ELSE.
        lv_letter = |E|.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND lv_letter TO rt_letter_grades.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS znumerical_letter_grade IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD numerical_letter_grade.
    LOOP AT it_grades ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<g>).
      DATA(lv_gpa) TYPE ty_gpa.
      lv_gpa = <g>.

      DATA(lv_letter) = COND string(
        WHEN lv_gpa = '4.00' THEN 'A+'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '3.70' THEN 'A'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '3.30' THEN 'A-'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '3.00' THEN 'B+'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '2.70' THEN 'B'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '2.30' THEN 'B-'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '2.00' THEN 'C+'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '1.70' THEN 'C'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '1.30' THEN 'C-'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '1.00' THEN 'D+'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '0.70' THEN 'D'
        WHEN lv_gpa > '0.00' THEN 'D-'
        ELSE 'E' ).

      APPEND lv_letter TO rt_letters.
    ENDLOOP.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS check_dict_case
      IMPORTING
        it_dict TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD check_dict_case.
    rv_result = abap_false.

    IF it_dict IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ls_any> TYPE any,
                   <lv_key> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_all_lower TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_all_upper TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true,
          lv_has_any   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false,
          lv_key_str   TYPE string,
          lv_lower     TYPE string,
          lv_upper     TYPE string.

    LOOP AT it_dict ASSIGNING <ls_any>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'KEY' OF STRUCTURE <ls_any> TO <lv_key>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lo_tdescr) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <lv_key> ).

      IF lo_tdescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_string
         AND lo_tdescr->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_char.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_key_str = |{ <lv_key> }|.
      lv_key_str = condense( lv_key_str ).

      IF lv_key_str IS INITIAL.
        lv_all_lower = abap_false.
        lv_all_upper = abap_false.
        lv_has_any   = abap_true.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key_str CO '0123456789'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_has_any = abap_true.

      lv_lower = to_lower( lv_key_str ).
      lv_upper = to_upper( lv_key_str ).

      IF lv_key_str <> lv_lower.
        lv_all_lower = abap_false.
      ENDIF.
      IF lv_key_str <> lv_upper.
        lv_all_upper = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_all_lower = abap_false AND lv_all_upper = abap_false.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_has_any = abap_true AND ( lv_all_lower = abap_true OR lv_all_upper = abap_true ).
      rv_result = abap_true.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS check_dict_case
      IMPORTING
        it_keys TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD check_dict_case.
    DATA lv_all_lower TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_all_upper TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_key       TYPE string.

    rv_result = abap_false.

    IF it_keys IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_all_lower = abap_true.
    lv_all_upper = abap_true.

    LOOP AT it_keys ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<row>).
      CLEAR lv_key.
      TRY.
          lv_key = CONV string( <row> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          rv_result = abap_false.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_key IS INITIAL.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key <> to_lower( lv_key ).
        lv_all_lower = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key <> to_upper( lv_key ).
        lv_all_upper = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_all_lower = abap_false AND lv_all_upper = abap_false.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_all_lower = abap_true OR lv_all_upper = abap_true.
      rv_result = abap_true.
    ELSE.
      rv_result = abap_false.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS check
      IMPORTING
        it_dict TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_valid) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD check.
    rv_is_valid = abap_false.

    IF it_dict IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_all_lower TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.
    DATA lv_all_upper TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_row>      TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_key_any>  TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_key_cseq> TYPE csequence.

    LOOP AT it_dict ASSIGNING <ls_row>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE <ls_row> TO <lv_key_any>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_is_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      ASSIGN <lv_key_any> TO <lv_key_cseq>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_is_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_key) = |{ <lv_key_cseq> }|.
      IF lv_key IS INITIAL.
        rv_is_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key <> to_lower( lv_key ).
        lv_all_lower = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key <> to_upper( lv_key ).
        lv_all_upper = abap_false.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_all_lower = abap_false AND lv_all_upper = abap_false.
        rv_is_valid = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_is_valid = xsdbool( lv_all_lower = abap_true OR lv_all_upper = abap_true ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case DEFINITION

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD check_dict_case.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ls_row> TYPE any,
                   <lv_key> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_all_lower TYPE char1,
          lv_all_upper TYPE char1,
          lv_key_str   TYPE string,
          lo_desc      TYPE REF TO cl_abap_typedescr.

    rv_ok = space.

    IF it_dict IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_all_lower = 'X'.
    lv_all_upper = 'X'.

    LOOP AT it_dict ASSIGNING <ls_row>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'KEY' OF STRUCTURE <ls_row> TO <lv_key>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_ok = space.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lo_desc = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <lv_key> ).
      IF lo_desc->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_string
         AND lo_desc->type_kind <> cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_char.
        rv_ok = space.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          lv_key_str = CONV string( <lv_key> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          rv_ok = space.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_key_str IS INITIAL.
        rv_ok = space.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key_str <> to_lower( lv_key_str ).
        lv_all_lower = space.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key_str <> to_upper( lv_key_str ).
        lv_all_upper = space.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_all_lower = space AND lv_all_upper = space.
        rv_ok = space.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_all_lower = 'X' OR lv_all_upper = 'X'.
      rv_ok = 'X'.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS check_dict_case
      IMPORTING
        it_pairs TYPE any
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_check_dict_case IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD check_dict_case.
    DATA: lv_has_lower TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false,
          lv_has_upper TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_pairs> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <ls_pair>  TYPE any,
                   <lv_key>   TYPE any.

    rv_result = abap_false.

    ASSIGN it_pairs TO <lt_pairs>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF <lt_pairs> IS INITIAL.
      rv_result = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <lt_pairs> ASSIGNING <ls_pair>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 'KEY' OF STRUCTURE <ls_pair> TO <lv_key>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 'key' OF STRUCTURE <ls_pair> TO <lv_key>.
      ENDIF.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_key_str) TYPE string.
      TRY.
          lv_key_str = CONV string( <lv_key> ).
        CATCH cx_root.
          rv_result = abap_false.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_key_str IS INITIAL.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_lower) TYPE string.
      DATA(lv_upper) TYPE string.

      lv_lower = to_lower( lv_key_str ).
      lv_upper = to_upper( lv_key_str ).

      IF lv_key_str <> lv_lower AND lv_key_str <> lv_upper.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_key_str = lv_lower AND lv_key_str <> lv_upper.
        lv_has_lower = abap_true.
      ELSEIF lv_key_str = lv_upper AND lv_key_str <> lv_lower.
        lv_has_upper = abap_true.
      ELSE.
        IF lv_has_lower = abap_true OR lv_has_upper = abap_true.
          rv_result = abap_false.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_has_lower = abap_true AND lv_has_upper = abap_true.
        rv_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF ( lv_has_lower = abap_true AND lv_has_upper = abap_false )
       OR ( lv_has_lower = abap_false AND lv_has_upper = abap_true ).
      rv_result = abap_true.
    ELSE.
      rv_result = abap_false.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_incr_list DEFINITION

CLASS zcl_incr_list DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS incr_list
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_list) TYPE REF TO data.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_incr_list IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD incr_list.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_out> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_in>  TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_out> TYPE any.

    DATA lr_out TYPE REF TO data.
    CREATE DATA lr_out LIKE STANDARD TABLE OF line of it_list.
    ASSIGN lr_out->* TO <lt_out>.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_in>.
      APPEND INITIAL LINE TO <lt_out> ASSIGNING <lv_out>.
      TRY.
          <lv_out> = CONV i( <lv_in> ) + 1.
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          <lv_out> = <lv_in>.
      ENDTRY.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_list = lr_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zincr_list DEFINITION
  PUBLIC

  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

      IMPORTING

      RETURNING

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

CLASS zincr_list DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS incr_list
      IMPORTING

      RETURNING
        VALUE(rr_list) TYPE REF TO data.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zincr_list IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD incr_list.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_in>     TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <lv_in>     TYPE any,
                   <lt_out>    TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <lv_out>    TYPE any,
                   <ls_new>    TYPE any.

    ASSIGN it_list TO <lt_in>.

    CREATE DATA rr_list LIKE it_list.
    ASSIGN rr_list->* TO <lt_out>.

    LOOP AT <lt_in> ASSIGNING <lv_in>.
      CREATE DATA DATA(lr_line) LIKE LINE OF <lt_out>.
      ASSIGN lr_line->* TO <ls_new>.
      TRY.
          <ls_new> = <lv_in> + 1.
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_error cx_sy_arithmetic_error cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          <ls_new> = <lv_in>.
      ENDTRY.
      INSERT <ls_new> INTO TABLE <lt_out>.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS mean_absolute_deviation
      IMPORTING
        numbers        TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF fltp WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result)  TYPE fltp.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.
    DATA sum  TYPE fltp VALUE '0'.
    DATA mean TYPE fltp VALUE '0'.
    DATA mad  TYPE fltp VALUE '0'.
    DATA cnt  TYPE i VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      sum = sum + <n>.
      cnt = cnt + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF cnt = 0.
      result = '0'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    mean = sum / cnt.

    LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      mad = mad + abs( <n> - mean ).
    ENDLOOP.

    result = mad / cnt.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_number TYPE p DECIMALS 8.
    TYPES ty_t_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_number WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS mean_absolute_deviation
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE ty_t_numbers
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_mad) TYPE ty_number.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.
    rv_mad = 0.

    DATA(lv_count) = lines( it_numbers ).
    IF lv_count = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_sum) TYPE p DECIMALS 8 VALUE 0.
    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      lv_sum = lv_sum + <n>.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA(lv_mean) TYPE p DECIMALS 8.
    lv_mean = lv_sum / lv_count.

    DATA(lv_abs_sum) TYPE p DECIMALS 8 VALUE 0.
    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      DATA(lv_diff) TYPE p DECIMALS 8.
      lv_diff = <n> - lv_mean.
      IF lv_diff < 0.
        lv_diff = -lv_diff.
      ENDIF.
      lv_abs_sum = lv_abs_sum + lv_diff.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_mad = lv_abs_sum / lv_count.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS mean_absolute_deviation
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF FLOAT
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_mad) TYPE FLOAT.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.
    DATA lv_sum     TYPE FLOAT.
    DATA lv_abs_sum TYPE FLOAT.
    DATA lv_mean    TYPE FLOAT.
    DATA lv_num     TYPE FLOAT.
    DATA lv_diff    TYPE FLOAT.
    DATA lv_count   TYPE i.

    CLEAR: rv_mad, lv_sum, lv_abs_sum, lv_mean.

    lv_count = lines( it_numbers ).
    IF lv_count = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT it_numbers INTO lv_num.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + lv_num.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_mean = lv_sum / lv_count.

    LOOP AT it_numbers INTO lv_num.
      lv_diff = lv_num - lv_mean.
      IF lv_diff < 0.
        lv_diff = lv_diff * -1.
      ENDIF.
      lv_abs_sum = lv_abs_sum + lv_diff.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_mad = lv_abs_sum / lv_count.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS mean_absolute_deviation
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.
    DATA count   TYPE i.
    DATA sum     TYPE f.
    DATA mean    TYPE f.
    DATA mad_sum TYPE f.
    DATA value_f TYPE f.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE any.

    count = lines( numbers ).
    IF count = 0.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    CLEAR sum.
    LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      TRY.
          value_f = <n>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          value_f = 0.
      ENDTRY.
      sum = sum + value_f.
    ENDLOOP.

    mean = sum / count.

    CLEAR mad_sum.
    LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      TRY.
          value_f = <n>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          value_f = 0.
      ENDTRY.
      mad_sum = mad_sum + abs( value_f - mean ).
    ENDLOOP.

    result = mad_sum / count.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.

          lv_mean  TYPE p DECIMALS 15,

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.

          lv_mean TYPE ty_num VALUE '0',
          lv_mad  TYPE ty_num VALUE '0',
          lv_abs  TYPE ty_num VALUE '0',

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS mean_absolute_deviation
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_mad) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.
    DATA lv_count   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sum     TYPE f.
    DATA lv_mean    TYPE f.
    DATA lv_abs_sum TYPE f.
    DATA lv_value   TYPE f.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE any.

    lv_count = lines( it_numbers ).
    IF lv_count = 0.
      rv_mad = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_sum = 0.
    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      TRY.
          lv_value = CONV f( <n> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          lv_value = 0.
      ENDTRY.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + lv_value.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_mean = lv_sum / lv_count.

    lv_abs_sum = 0.
    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      TRY.
          lv_value = CONV f( <n> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          lv_value = 0.
      ENDTRY.
      lv_abs_sum = lv_abs_sum + abs( lv_value - lv_mean ).
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_mad = lv_abs_sum / lv_count.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS mean_absolute_deviation
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_mad) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_sum   TYPE decfloat34 VALUE '0',
          lv_mean  TYPE decfloat34 VALUE '0',
          lv_mad   TYPE decfloat34 VALUE '0',
          lv_val   TYPE decfloat34 VALUE '0',
          lv_count TYPE i VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      TRY.
          lv_val = CONV decfloat34( <n> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_error cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + lv_val.
      lv_count = lv_count + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_count = 0.
      rv_mad = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_mean = lv_sum / CONV decfloat34( lv_count ).

    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      TRY.
          lv_val = CONV decfloat34( <n> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_error cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.
      lv_mad = lv_mad + abs( lv_val - lv_mean ).
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_mad = lv_mad / CONV decfloat34( lv_count ).

    rv_mad = CONV f( lv_mad ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_number TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 7.
    TYPES ty_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_number WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS mean_absolute_deviation
      IMPORTING
        numbers        TYPE ty_numbers
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result)  TYPE ty_number.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_mean_absolute_deviation IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD mean_absolute_deviation.
    DATA sum   TYPE ty_number VALUE '0'.
    DATA count TYPE i VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<n>).
      sum = sum + <n>.
      count = count + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF count = 0.
      result = '0'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA mean TYPE ty_number.
    mean = sum / count.

    DATA mad_sum TYPE ty_number VALUE '0'.
    LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      DATA diff TYPE ty_number.
      diff = <n> - mean.
      IF diff < 0.
        diff = -diff.
      ENDIF.
      mad_sum = mad_sum + diff.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = mad_sum / count.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_triples_sum_to_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS triples_sum_to_zero
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_triples_sum_to_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD triples_sum_to_zero.
    rv_result = abap_false.

    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    lt_sorted = VALUE #( FOR <x> IN it_list ( CONV i( <x> ) ) ).
    SORT lt_sorted.

    DATA(lv_n) = lines( lt_sorted ).
    IF lv_n < 3.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <a> TYPE i.

    DATA lv_i TYPE i.
    DATA lv_l TYPE i.
    DATA lv_r TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sum TYPE i.
    DATA lv_left TYPE i.
    DATA lv_right TYPE i.

    DO lv_n - 2 TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_i ASSIGNING <a>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_l = lv_i + 1.
      lv_r = lv_n.

      WHILE lv_l < lv_r.
        READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_l INTO lv_left.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_r INTO lv_right.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        lv_sum = <a> + lv_left + lv_right.

        IF lv_sum = 0.
          rv_result = abap_true.
          RETURN.
        ELSEIF lv_sum < 0.
          lv_l = lv_l + 1.
        ELSE.
          lv_r = lv_r - 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_triples_sum_to_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS triples_sum_to_zero
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_triples_sum_to_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD triples_sum_to_zero.
    rv_result = abap_false.

    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      APPEND CONV i( <lv_any> ) TO lt_sorted.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA lv_n TYPE i.
    lv_n = lines( lt_sorted ).
    IF lv_n < 3.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SORT lt_sorted.

    DATA lv_i TYPE i.
    DATA lv_l TYPE i.
    DATA lv_r TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sum TYPE i.

    DO lv_n - 2 TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.

      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_i INTO lv_a.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_i > 1.
        DATA lv_prev TYPE i.
        READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_i - 1 INTO lv_prev.
        IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_prev = lv_a.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      lv_l = lv_i + 1.
      lv_r = lv_n.

      WHILE lv_l < lv_r.
        DATA lv_b TYPE i.
        DATA lv_c TYPE i.

        READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_l INTO lv_b.
        READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_r INTO lv_c.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        lv_sum = lv_a + lv_b + lv_c.

        IF lv_sum = 0.
          rv_result = abap_true.
          RETURN.
        ELSEIF lv_sum < 0.
          lv_l = lv_l + 1.
        ELSE.
          lv_r = lv_r - 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_parse_nested_parens IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD parse_nested_parens.
    DATA lt_groups TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_group  TYPE string.
    DATA lv_depth  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_max    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c      TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_idx    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_out    TYPE string.

    SPLIT paren_string AT space INTO TABLE lt_groups.

    LOOP AT lt_groups INTO lv_group.
      IF lv_group IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR: lv_depth, lv_max.

      lv_len = strlen( lv_group ).
      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
        lv_c = lv_group+lv_idx(1).

        IF lv_c = '('.
          lv_depth = lv_depth + 1.
          IF lv_depth > lv_max.
            lv_max = lv_depth.
          ENDIF.
        ELSEIF lv_c = ')'.
          IF lv_depth > 0.
            lv_depth = lv_depth - 1.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      IF lv_out IS INITIAL.
        lv_out = |{ lv_max }|.
      ELSE.
        lv_out = |{ lv_out } { lv_max }|.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_depths = lv_out.

  FINAL

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS parse_nested_parens
      IMPORTING
        i_paren_string TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_levels) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_parse_nested_parens IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD parse_nested_parens.
    DATA lt_groups TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_group  TYPE string.

    DATA lv_depth   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_max     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char    TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_invalid TYPE abap_bool.

    SPLIT i_paren_string AT space INTO TABLE lt_groups.

    LOOP AT lt_groups INTO lv_group.
      IF lv_group IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_depth = 0.
      lv_max = 0.
      lv_invalid = abap_false.

      DO strlen( lv_group ) TIMES.
        lv_char = lv_group+sy-index(1).

        CASE lv_char.
          WHEN '('.
            lv_depth = lv_depth + 1.
            IF lv_depth > lv_max.
              lv_max = lv_depth.
            ENDIF.
          WHEN ')'.
            lv_depth = lv_depth - 1.
            IF lv_depth < 0.
              lv_invalid = abap_true.
              EXIT.
            ENDIF.
          WHEN OTHERS.
            lv_invalid = abap_true.
            EXIT.
        ENDCASE.
      ENDDO.

      IF lv_invalid = abap_true OR lv_depth <> 0.
        APPEND 0 TO rt_levels.
      ELSE.
        APPEND lv_max TO rt_levels.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_same_chars DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS same_chars
      IMPORTING
        s0 TYPE string
        s1 TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_same) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_same_chars IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD same_chars.
    DATA lt0 TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt1 TYPE HASHED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lv_char TYPE string.
    DATA lv_i TYPE i.

    rv_same = abap_true.

    DO strlen( s0 ) TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = s0+lv_i(1).
      TRANSLATE lv_char TO LOWER CASE.
      INSERT lv_char INTO TABLE lt0.
    ENDDO.

    DO strlen( s1 ) TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = s1+lv_i(1).
      TRANSLATE lv_char TO LOWER CASE.
      INSERT lv_char INTO TABLE lt1.
    ENDDO.

    IF lines( lt0 ) <> lines( lt1 ).
      rv_same = abap_false.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt0 INTO lv_char.
      READ TABLE lt1 WITH TABLE KEY table_line = lv_char TRANSPORTING NO FIELDS.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_same = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_same_chars DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS same_chars
      IMPORTING
        s0 TYPE string
        s1 TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_same_chars IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD same_chars.
    DATA lt0 TYPE SORTED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lt1 TYPE SORTED TABLE OF string WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lv_str TYPE string.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_off TYPE i.

    CLEAR lt0.
    lv_len = strlen( s0 ).
    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_off = sy-index - 1.
      lv_str = s0+lv_off(1).
      INSERT lv_str INTO TABLE lt0.
    ENDDO.

    CLEAR lt1.
    lv_len = strlen( s1 ).
    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_off = sy-index - 1.
      lv_str = s1+lv_off(1).
      INSERT lv_str INTO TABLE lt1.
    ENDDO.

    IF lt0 = lt1.
      r_result = abap_true.
    ELSE.
      r_result = abap_false.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF n = 1.
      rv_count = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_pow10_nm1 = 1.
    DO ( n - 1 ) TIMES.
      lv_pow10_nm1 = lv_pow10_nm1 * 10.
    ENDDO.

    lv_total = 9 * lv_pow10_nm1.

    lv_count_s = lv_pow10_nm1.
    lv_count_e = lv_pow10_nm1.

    lv_both = 1.

    rv_count = lv_count_s + lv_count_e - lv_both.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_starts_one_ends DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.

      IMPORTING

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_starts_one_ends IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD starts_one_ends.
    DATA lv_pow10_n_minus_1 TYPE decfloat34.

    rv_count = 0.

    IF n <= 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_pow10_n_minus_1 = 1.
    IF n > 1.
      DO n - 1 TIMES.
        lv_pow10_n_minus_1 = lv_pow10_n_minus_1 * 10.
      ENDDO.
    ENDIF.

    rv_count = 18 * lv_pow10_n_minus_1 / 10.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_starts_one_ends DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_starts_one_ends IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD starts_one_ends.
    DATA: pow10_n1 TYPE ty_result,
          pow10_n2 TYPE ty_result.

    IF n <= 0.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF n = 1.
      result = 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    pow10_n1 = 1.
    DO ( n - 1 ) TIMES.
      pow10_n1 = pow10_n1 * 10.
    ENDDO.

    pow10_n2 = 1.

CLASS zcl_count_up_to DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_t_primes TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS count_up_to
      IMPORTING
        iv_n TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_primes) TYPE ty_t_primes.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_count_up_to IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD count_up_to.
    rt_primes = VALUE ty_t_primes( ).

    IF iv_n <= 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_is_prime TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF abap_bool WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_p TYPE i.
    DATA lv_m TYPE i.
    DATA lv_x TYPE i.

    lt_is_prime = VALUE #( FOR lv_x = 1 THEN lv_x + 1 UNTIL lv_x >= iv_n ( abap_true ) ).

    lt_is_prime[ 1 ] = abap_false.
    IF iv_n > 1.
      lt_is_prime[ 2 ] = abap_false.
    ENDIF.

    lv_p = 2.
    WHILE lv_p * lv_p < iv_n.
      IF lt_is_prime[ lv_p + 1 ] = abap_true.
        lv_m = lv_p * lv_p.
        WHILE lv_m < iv_n.
          lt_is_prime[ lv_m + 1 ] = abap_false.
          lv_m = lv_m + lv_p.
        ENDWHILE.
      ENDIF.
      lv_p = lv_p + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    DO iv_n TIMES.
      lv_p = sy-index - 1.
      IF lv_p >= 2 AND lv_p < iv_n AND lt_is_prime[ lv_p + 1 ] = abap_true.
        APPEND lv_p TO rt_primes.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fix_spaces DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS fix_spaces
      IMPORTING
        iv_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fix_spaces IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD fix_spaces.
    DATA lv_len     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_run     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char    TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_out_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_needed  TYPE i.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_text ).

    IF lv_len = 0.
      rv_text = ``.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_out_len = 0.
    lv_idx = 0.
    WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
      lv_char = iv_text+lv_idx(1).
      IF lv_char = space.
        lv_run = 1.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        WHILE lv_idx < lv_len AND iv_text+lv_idx(1) = space.
          lv_run = lv_run + 1.
          lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        ENDWHILE.
        IF lv_run > 2.
          lv_out_len = lv_out_len + 1.
        ELSE.
          lv_out_len = lv_out_len + lv_run.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        lv_out_len = lv_out_len + 1.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_text = repeat( val = ` ` occ = lv_out_len ).

    lv_idx = 0.
    DATA lv_out_pos TYPE i.
    lv_out_pos = 0.

    WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
      lv_char = iv_text+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_char = space.
        lv_run = 1.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        WHILE lv_idx < lv_len AND iv_text+lv_idx(1) = space.
          lv_run = lv_run + 1.
          lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        IF lv_run > 2.
          rv_text+lv_out_pos(1) = `-`.
          lv_out_pos = lv_out_pos + 1.
        ELSEIF lv_run = 2.
          rv_text+lv_out_pos(2) = `__`.
          lv_out_pos = lv_out_pos + 2.
        ELSE.
          rv_text+lv_out_pos(1) = `_`.
          lv_out_pos = lv_out_pos + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        rv_text+lv_out_pos(1) = lv_char.
        lv_out_pos = lv_out_pos + 1.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fix_spaces DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS fix_spaces
      IMPORTING
        text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fix_spaces IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD fix_spaces.
    DATA: lv_in       TYPE string,
          lv_out      TYPE string,
          lv_len      TYPE i,
          lv_idx      TYPE i,
          lv_j        TYPE i,
          lv_run      TYPE i,
          lv_has_trpl TYPE abap_bool.

    lv_in = text.
    lv_len = strlen( lv_in ).
    lv_idx = 0.
    CLEAR lv_out.
    lv_has_trpl = abap_false.

    WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
      IF lv_in+lv_idx(1) = space.
        lv_j = lv_idx + 1.
        WHILE lv_j < lv_len AND lv_in+lv_j(1) = space.
          lv_j = lv_j + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        lv_run = lv_j - lv_idx.

        IF lv_run >= 3.
          lv_has_trpl = abap_true.
          lv_out = lv_out && `-`.
        ELSEIF lv_run = 2.
          lv_out = lv_out && `__`.
        ELSE.
          lv_out = lv_out && `_`.
        ENDIF.

        lv_idx = lv_j.
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_in+lv_idx(1).
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_has_trpl = abap_true.
      REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF `__` IN lv_out WITH `_`.
    ENDIF.

    result = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fix_spaces DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS fix_spaces
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_fix_spaces IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD fix_spaces.
    DATA lv_in   TYPE string.
    DATA lv_out  TYPE string.
    DATA lv_len  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_run  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_in = i_text.
    lv_len = strlen( lv_in ).

    lv_idx = 0.
    WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
      lv_char = lv_in+lv_idx(1).
      IF lv_char = space.
        lv_run = 1.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        WHILE lv_idx < lv_len AND lv_in+lv_idx(1) = space.
          lv_run = lv_run + 1.
          lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        IF lv_run > 2.
          lv_out = lv_out && `-`.
        ELSEIF lv_run = 2.
          lv_out = lv_out && `__`.
        ELSE.
          lv_out = lv_out && `_`.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_char.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_len > 0 AND lv_in+0(1) = space AND strlen( lv_out ) > 0.
      WHILE lv_out+0(1) = `_`.
        lv_out = lv_out+1.
        IF strlen( lv_out ) = 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDWHILE.
      lv_out = `-` && lv_out.
    ENDIF.

    r_text = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_search DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS search
      IMPORTING
        it_list        TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int8 WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_best) TYPE int8.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_search IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD search.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_freq,
             val   TYPE int8,
             count TYPE int8,
           END OF ty_freq.

    DATA lt_freq TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_freq WITH UNIQUE KEY val.
    DATA ls_freq TYPE ty_freq.

    rv_best = -1.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO DATA(lv_val).
      READ TABLE lt_freq INTO ls_freq WITH TABLE KEY val = lv_val.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        ls_freq-count = ls_freq-count + 1.
        MODIFY lt_freq FROM ls_freq.
      ELSE.
        ls_freq-val = lv_val.
        ls_freq-count = 1.
        INSERT ls_freq INTO TABLE lt_freq.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_freq INTO ls_freq.
      IF ls_freq-val > 0 AND ls_freq-count >= ls_freq-val AND ls_freq-val > rv_best.
        rv_best = ls_freq-val.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_search DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS search
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE i.

CLASS zcl_search IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD search.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_count,
             value TYPE i,
             freq  TYPE i,
           END OF ty_count.
    TYPES ty_counts TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_count WITH UNIQUE KEY value.

    DATA lt_counts TYPE ty_counts.
    DATA ls_count  TYPE ty_count.
    DATA lv_value  TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      TRY.
          lv_value = CONV i( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      READ TABLE lt_counts INTO ls_count WITH TABLE KEY value = lv_value.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        ls_count-freq = ls_count-freq + 1.
        MODIFY TABLE lt_counts FROM ls_count.
      ELSE.
        ls_count-value = lv_value.
        ls_count-freq  = 1.
        INSERT ls_count INTO TABLE lt_counts.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_result = -1.

    LOOP AT lt_counts INTO ls_count.
      IF ls_count-value > 0
         AND ls_count-freq >= ls_count-value
         AND ls_count-value > rv_result.
        rv_result = ls_count-value.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_search_frequency DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC .

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int TYPE n LENGTH 10.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_int WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS search
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_search_frequency IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD search.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_count,
             value TYPE ty_int,
             cnt   TYPE i,
           END OF ty_count.

    DATA lt_count TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_count WITH UNIQUE KEY value.

    rv_result = `-1`.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO DATA(lv_val).
      READ TABLE lt_count ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<c>) WITH TABLE KEY value = lv_val.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        <c>-cnt = <c>-cnt + 1.
      ELSE.
        INSERT VALUE ty_count( value = lv_val cnt = 1 ) INTO TABLE lt_count.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_count INTO DATA(ls_count).
      DATA(lv_value_i) = CONV i( ls_count-value ).
      IF lv_value_i > 0 AND ls_count-cnt >= lv_value_i.
        DATA(lv_best_i) = COND i( WHEN rv_result = `-1` THEN -1 ELSE CONV i( rv_result ) ).
        IF lv_value_i > lv_best_i.
          rv_result = |{ lv_value_i }|.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_search DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

    CLASS-METHODS search
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE i.

CLASS zcl_search IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD search.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_freq,
             val   TYPE i,
             count TYPE i,
           END OF ty_freq.
    TYPES ty_freq_tab TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_freq WITH UNIQUE KEY val.

    DATA lt_freq TYPE ty_freq_tab.
    DATA ls_freq TYPE ty_freq.
    DATA lv_s    TYPE string.
    DATA lv_x    TYPE i.

    rv_result = -1.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO lv_s.
      TRY.
          lv_x = lv_s.
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_x <= 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE lt_freq INTO ls_freq WITH TABLE KEY val = lv_x.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        ls_freq-count = ls_freq-count + 1.
        MODIFY TABLE lt_freq FROM ls_freq.
      ELSE.
        CLEAR ls_freq.
        ls_freq-val = lv_x.
        ls_freq-count = 1.
        INSERT ls_freq INTO TABLE lt_freq.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT lt_freq INTO ls_freq.
      IF ls_freq-count >= ls_freq-val AND ls_freq-val > rv_result.
        rv_result = ls_freq-val.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

      IMPORTING

      RETURNING

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD anti_shuffle.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_token,
             is_space TYPE abap_bool,
             value    TYPE string,
           END OF ty_token.

    DATA lt_tokens TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_token WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA(lv_len) = strlen( i_text ).
    DATA lv_i TYPE i VALUE 0.

    WHILE lv_i < lv_len.
      DATA(lv_ch) = i_text+lv_i(1).

      IF lv_ch = ` `.
        DATA lv_j TYPE i VALUE lv_i.
        WHILE lv_j < lv_len AND i_text+lv_j(1) = ` `.
          lv_j = lv_j + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        DATA(lv_space_len) = lv_j - lv_i.
        APPEND VALUE ty_token(
                 is_space = abap_true
                 value    = repeat( val = ` ` occ = lv_space_len ) ) TO lt_tokens.

        lv_i = lv_j.
      ELSE.
        DATA lv_k TYPE i VALUE lv_i.
        WHILE lv_k < lv_len AND i_text+lv_k(1) <> ` `.
          lv_k = lv_k + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        DATA(lv_word_len) = lv_k - lv_i.

        DATA(lv_word) TYPE string.
        lv_word = i_text.
        SHIFT lv_word LEFT BY lv_i PLACES.
        lv_word = lv_word(lv_word_len).

        APPEND VALUE ty_token(
                 is_space = abap_false
                 value    = lv_word ) TO lt_tokens.

        lv_i = lv_k.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    LOOP AT lt_tokens ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<t>).
      IF <t>-is_space = abap_true.
        r_text = r_text && <t>-value.
      ELSE.
        DATA lt_chars TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
        DATA(lv_wlen) = strlen( <t>-value ).

        DO lv_wlen TIMES.
          APPEND <t>-value+( sy-index - 1 )(1) TO lt_chars.
        ENDDO.

        SORT lt_chars BY table_line ASCENDING.

        DATA(lv_sorted) = ``.
        LOOP AT lt_chars ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<c>).
          lv_sorted = lv_sorted && <c>.
        ENDLOOP.

        r_text = r_text && lv_sorted.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS anti_shuffle
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD anti_shuffle.
    TYPES: tt_char TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF c WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.

    DATA: len    TYPE i,
          pos    TYPE i,
          start  TYPE i,
          wlen   TYPE i,
          ch     TYPE c,
          word   TYPE string,
          sorted TYPE string,
          chars  TYPE tt_char,
          c1     TYPE c,
          idx    TYPE i.

    r_text = ``.

    len = strlen( i_text ).
    pos = 0.

    WHILE pos < len.
      ch = i_text+pos(1).

      IF ch = space.
        r_text = r_text && space.
        pos = pos + 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      start = pos.

      WHILE pos < len AND i_text+pos(1) <> space.
        pos = pos + 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      wlen = pos - start.
      word = i_text+start(wlen).

      CLEAR chars.
      DO strlen( word ) TIMES.
        idx = sy-index - 1.
        APPEND word+idx(1) TO chars.
      ENDDO.

      SORT chars ASCENDING.

      sorted = ``.
      LOOP AT chars INTO c1.
        sorted = sorted && c1.
      ENDLOOP.

      r_text = r_text && sorted.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS anti_shuffle
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD anti_shuffle.
    r_text = ``.

    DATA len TYPE i.
    len = strlen( i_text ).

    DATA current TYPE string VALUE ``.
    DATA pos TYPE i VALUE 0.

    DATA codepoint TYPE i.
    DATA one_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    WHILE pos < len.
      DATA(ch) = i_text+pos(1).

      IF ch = ` `.
        IF current IS NOT INITIAL.
          DATA(sorted) = ``.
          DATA(cur_len) = strlen( current ).

          DATA cps TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.

          DO cur_len TIMES.
            DATA(idx) = sy-index - 1.
            DATA(c2) = current+idx(1).
            codepoint = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( c2 ).
            APPEND codepoint TO cps.
          ENDDO.

          SORT cps ASCENDING.

          LOOP AT cps INTO codepoint.
            one_char = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( uccp = codepoint ).
            sorted = sorted && one_char.
          ENDLOOP.

          r_text = r_text && sorted.
          current = ``.
        ENDIF.

        r_text = r_text && ` `.
      ELSE.
        current = current && ch.
      ENDIF.

      pos = pos + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF current IS NOT INITIAL.
      DATA(sorted2) = ``.
      DATA(cur_len2) = strlen( current ).

      DATA cps2 TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.

      DO cur_len2 TIMES.
        DATA(idx2) = sy-index - 1.
        DATA(c3) = current+idx2(1).
        codepoint = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( c3 ).
        APPEND codepoint TO cps2.
      ENDDO.

      SORT cps2 ASCENDING.

      LOOP AT cps2 INTO codepoint.
        one_char = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( uccp = codepoint ).
        sorted2 = sorted2 && one_char.
      ENDLOOP.

      r_text = r_text && sorted2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS anti_shuffle
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD anti_shuffle.
    TYPES ty_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    TYPES ty_char_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_char WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char TYPE ty_char.
    DATA lv_token TYPE string.
    DATA lv_tlen TYPE i.
    DATA lv_pos TYPE i.
    DATA lt_chars TYPE ty_char_tab.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).
    lv_idx = 0.
    r_text = ``.

    WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
      lv_char = i_text+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_char = space.
        r_text = r_text && space.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lv_token.

      WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
        lv_char = i_text+lv_idx(1).
        IF lv_char = space.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
        lv_token = lv_token && lv_char.
        lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF lv_token IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lt_chars.
      lv_tlen = strlen( lv_token ).
      lv_pos = 0.
      WHILE lv_pos < lv_tlen.
        APPEND lv_token+lv_pos(1) TO lt_chars.
        lv_pos = lv_pos + 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      SORT lt_chars ASCENDING.

      CLEAR lv_token.
      LOOP AT lt_chars INTO lv_char.
        lv_token = lv_token && lv_char.
      ENDLOOP.

      r_text = r_text && lv_token.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS anti_shuffle
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD anti_shuffle.
    TYPES ty_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    TYPES ty_t_char TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_char WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    DATA: lv_len TYPE i,
          lv_pos TYPE i,
          lv_c1  TYPE ty_char.

    DATA: lt_runs        TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY,
          lt_is_space    TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF abap_bool WITH EMPTY KEY,
          lv_run         TYPE string,
          lv_curr_is_sp  TYPE abap_bool,
          lv_prev_is_sp  TYPE abap_bool.

    DATA: lv_part     TYPE string,
          lv_is_space TYPE abap_bool,
          lv_idx      TYPE sy-tabix.

    r_text = ``.
    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).
    IF lv_len = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_pos = 0.
    lv_run = ``.

    lv_c1 = i_text+0(1).
    lv_prev_is_sp = xsdbool( lv_c1 = ` ` ).

    WHILE lv_pos < lv_len.
      lv_c1 = i_text+lv_pos(1).
      lv_curr_is_sp = xsdbool( lv_c1 = ` ` ).

      IF lv_curr_is_sp = lv_prev_is_sp.
        lv_run = lv_run && lv_c1.
      ELSE.
        APPEND lv_run TO lt_runs.
        APPEND lv_prev_is_sp TO lt_is_space.
        lv_run = lv_c1.
        lv_prev_is_sp = lv_curr_is_sp.
      ENDIF.

      lv_pos = lv_pos + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    APPEND lv_run TO lt_runs.
    APPEND lv_prev_is_sp TO lt_is_space.

    LOOP AT lt_runs INTO lv_part.
      lv_idx = sy-tabix.
      READ TABLE lt_is_space INDEX lv_idx INTO lv_is_space.

      IF lv_is_space = abap_true.
        r_text = r_text && lv_part.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lt_chars TYPE ty_t_char.
      CLEAR lt_chars.

      DATA(lv_work) = lv_part.
      DATA(lv_plen) = strlen( lv_work ).
      DO lv_plen TIMES.
        lv_c1 = lv_work+0(1).
        SHIFT lv_work LEFT BY 1 PLACES.
        APPEND lv_c1 TO lt_chars.
      ENDDO.

      SORT lt_chars.

      DATA(lv_sorted) = ``.
      LOOP AT lt_chars INTO lv_c1.
        lv_sorted = lv_sorted && lv_c1.
      ENDLOOP.

      r_text = r_text && lv_sorted.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS anti_shuffle
      IMPORTING
        VALUE(iv_text) TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_anti_shuffle IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD anti_shuffle.
    TYPES: ty_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    TYPES: ty_t_chars TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_char WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    DATA: lv_len        TYPE i,
          lv_i          TYPE i,
          lv_char       TYPE ty_char,
          lv_token       TYPE string,
          lv_token_len   TYPE i,
          lv_sorted      TYPE string,
          lt_chars       TYPE ty_t_chars,
          lv_c           TYPE ty_char.

    rv_text = ``.
    lv_len = strlen( iv_text ).

    lv_i = 0.
    WHILE lv_i < lv_len.
      lv_char = iv_text+lv_i(1).

      IF lv_char CA `ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789`.
        CLEAR lv_token.
        WHILE lv_i < lv_len AND iv_text+lv_i(1) CA `ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789`.
          lv_token = lv_token && iv_text+lv_i(1).
          lv_i = lv_i + 1.
        ENDWHILE.

        CLEAR lt_chars.
        lv_token_len = strlen( lv_token ).
        DO lv_token_len TIMES.
          lv_c = substring( val = lv_token off = sy-index - 1 len = 1 ).
          APPEND lv_c TO lt_chars.
        ENDDO.

        SORT lt_chars ASCENDING.

        CLEAR lv_sorted.
        LOOP AT lt_chars INTO lv_c.
          lv_sorted = lv_sorted && lv_c.
        ENDLOOP.

        rv_text = rv_text && lv_sorted.
      ELSE.
        rv_text = rv_text && lv_char.
        lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_sum TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.

    CLASS-METHODS double_the_difference
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE ty_sum.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD double_the_difference.
    rv_sum = 0.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_any> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_any> TYPE ANY TABLE.

    ASSIGN it_list TO <lt_any>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <lt_any> ASSIGNING <ls_any>.
      ASSIGN <ls_any> TO <lv_any>.

      DATA(lv_is_int)   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
      DATA(lv_is_neg)   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
      DATA(lv_is_odd)   TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
      DATA(lv_int8)     TYPE int8.
      DATA(lv_as_text)  TYPE string.

      CASE cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <lv_any> )->type_kind.
        WHEN cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int
          OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int1
          OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int2
          OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int8.
          lv_is_int = abap_true.
          lv_int8   = <lv_any>.

        WHEN cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_num
          OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_char
          OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_string.
          lv_as_text = CONV string( <lv_any> ).
          CONDENSE lv_as_text NO-GAPS.
          IF lv_as_text IS NOT INITIAL.
            FIND PCRE '^[+-]?\d+$' IN lv_as_text MATCH COUNT DATA(lv_match).
            IF lv_match > 0.
              lv_is_int = abap_true.
              lv_int8   = CONV int8( lv_as_text ).
            ENDIF.
          ENDIF.

        WHEN OTHERS.
      ENDCASE.

      IF lv_is_int = abap_false.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_int8 < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_int8 MOD 2 ) <> 0.
        rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_int8 * lv_int8.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS double_the_difference
      IMPORTING
        it_list       TYPE any table
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD double_the_difference.
    DATA lv_i TYPE i.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      CLEAR lv_i.

      TRY.
          lv_i = <lv_any>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error cx_sy_arithmetic_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_i < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_i MOD 2 = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_i * lv_i ).
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num     TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8.
    TYPES ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_sum     TYPE p LENGTH 31 DECIMALS 0.

      RETURNING

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD double_the_difference.

    LOOP AT it_values INTO DATA(lv_num).
      IF lv_num < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_int) TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.
      lv_int = lv_num.

      IF lv_int <> lv_num.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_int MOD 2 ) = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_int * lv_int ).

  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: ty_num     TYPE f,
           ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS double_the_difference
      IMPORTING
        it_list       TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD double_the_difference.
    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<v>).
      IF <v> < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_trunc) TYPE f.
      lv_trunc = trunc( <v> ).

      IF lv_trunc <> <v>.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_i) TYPE i.
      lv_i = lv_trunc.

      IF lv_i MOD 2 = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_trunc * lv_trunc ).
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8.
    TYPES ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_sum TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.

    CLASS-METHODS double_the_difference
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE ty_sum.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD double_the_difference.
    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<v>).
      IF <v> < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_int) TYPE int8.
      DATA(lv_tmp) TYPE ty_num.

      TRY.
          lv_int = EXACT #( <v> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow cx_sy_arithmetic_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_tmp = lv_int.
      IF lv_tmp <> <v>.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_int MOD 2 ) <> 0.
        DATA(lv_sq) TYPE int8.
        lv_sq = lv_int * lv_int.
        rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_sq.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS double_the_difference
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD double_the_difference.
    DATA lv_int TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sq  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_num TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 6.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v> TYPE any.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <v>.
      TRY.
          lv_num = <v>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_num < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_int = lv_num.

      IF CONV #( lv_int ) <> lv_num.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_int MOD 2 = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sq = lv_int * lv_int.
      rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_sq.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS double_the_difference
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE int8.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_double_the_difference IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD double_the_difference.
    DATA: lv_int8 TYPE int8,
          lv_f    TYPE f,
          lv_tr   TYPE f,
          lv_diff TYPE f,
          lv_xstr TYPE xstring.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lv_any> TYPE any.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      CLEAR: lv_f, lv_int8, lv_tr, lv_diff, lv_xstr.

      TRY.
          lv_xstr = cl_abap_container_utilities=>fill_container_c( im_value = <lv_any> ).
          cl_abap_container_utilities=>read_container_c(
            EXPORTING
              im_container = lv_xstr
            IMPORTING
              ex_value     = lv_f ).
        CATCH cx_root.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_f < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_tr = trunc( lv_f ).
      lv_diff = abs( lv_f - lv_tr ).
      IF lv_diff > 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          lv_int8 = CONV int8( lv_tr ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_overflow cx_sy_arithmetic_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_int8 MOD 2 = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_int8 * lv_int8 ).
        CATCH cx_sy_arithmetic_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_order_by_points DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS order_by_points
      IMPORTING
        nums TYPE ty_nums
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_nums.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_order_by_points IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD order_by_points.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             idx TYPE i,
             num TYPE i,
             sum TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.

    DATA lt_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH DEFAULT KEY.
    DATA ls_item  TYPE ty_item.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_num TYPE i.

    LOOP AT nums INTO lv_num.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      ls_item-idx = lv_idx.
      ls_item-num = lv_num.
      ls_item-sum = abs( lv_num ).

      APPEND ls_item TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY sum ASCENDING idx ASCENDING.

    result = VALUE ty_nums( FOR wa IN lt_items ( wa-num ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_order_by_points DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS order_by_points
      IMPORTING
        it_nums TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_nums) TYPE ty_int_tab.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_order_by_points IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD order_by_points.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             idx  TYPE i,
             num  TYPE i,
             sumd TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.

    DATA: lt_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY,
          ls_item  TYPE ty_item,
          lv_idx   TYPE i,
          lv_num   TYPE i,
          lv_abs   TYPE i,
          lv_str   TYPE string,
          lv_sum   TYPE i,
          lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_pos   TYPE i,
          lv_char  TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    rt_nums = VALUE #( ).

    IF it_nums IS INITIAL.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_idx = 0.

    LOOP AT it_nums INTO lv_num.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      lv_abs = lv_num.
      IF lv_abs < 0.
        lv_abs = 0 - lv_abs.
      ENDIF.

      lv_str = |{ lv_abs }|.
      lv_sum = 0.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_str ).

      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_pos = sy-index - 1.
        lv_char = lv_str+lv_pos(1).
        lv_sum = lv_sum + ( lv_char - '0' ).
      ENDDO.

      CLEAR ls_item.
      ls_item-idx  = lv_idx.
      ls_item-num  = lv_num.
      ls_item-sumd = lv_sum.
      APPEND ls_item TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY sumd ASCENDING idx ASCENDING.

    LOOP AT lt_items INTO ls_item.
      APPEND ls_item-num TO rt_nums.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_order_by_points IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD order_by_points.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_nums> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <ls_num>  TYPE any.

    ASSIGN it_nums TO <lt_nums>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_item,
             idx    TYPE sy-tabix,
             num    TYPE i,
             points TYPE i,
           END OF ty_item.
    DATA lt_items TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_item WITH EMPTY KEY.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE sy-tabix VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT <lt_nums> ASSIGNING <ls_num>.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.

      DATA(lv_num) = CONV i( <ls_num> ).

      DATA lv_abs TYPE i.
      lv_abs = lv_num.
      IF lv_abs < 0.
        lv_abs = 0 - lv_abs.
      ENDIF.

      DATA lv_points TYPE i VALUE 0.
      DATA lv_work   TYPE i.
      lv_work = lv_abs.

      WHILE lv_work > 0.
        lv_points = lv_points + ( lv_work MOD 10 ).
        lv_work = lv_work DIV 10.
      ENDWHILE.

      APPEND VALUE ty_item( idx = lv_idx num = lv_num points = lv_points ) TO lt_items.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_items BY points ASCENDING idx ASCENDING.

    DATA lr_out TYPE REF TO data.
    CREATE DATA lr_out LIKE it_nums.
    ASSIGN lr_out->* TO <lt_nums>.

    CLEAR <lt_nums>.
    LOOP AT lt_items INTO DATA(ls_item).
      APPEND ls_item-num TO <lt_nums>.
    ENDLOOP.

    rt_nums = <lt_nums>.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encode
      IMPORTING
        message       TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encode.
    DATA lv_out TYPE string.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_off TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c   TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_out = ``.
    lv_len = strlen( message ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_off = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = message+lv_off(1).

      IF lv_c CO `abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz`.
        CASE lv_c.
          WHEN `a`. lv_c = `c`.
          WHEN `e`. lv_c = `g`.
          WHEN `i`. lv_c = `k`.
          WHEN `o`. lv_c = `q`.
          WHEN `u`. lv_c = `w`.
          WHEN OTHERS.
        ENDCASE.
      ELSEIF lv_c CO `ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ`.
        TRANSLATE lv_c TO LOWER CASE.
        CASE lv_c.
          WHEN `a`. lv_c = `C`.
          WHEN `e`. lv_c = `G`.
          WHEN `i`. lv_c = `K`.
          WHEN `o`. lv_c = `Q`.
          WHEN `u`. lv_c = `W`.
          WHEN OTHERS.
        ENDCASE.
      ENDIF.

      CONCATENATE lv_out lv_c INTO lv_out IN CHARACTER MODE.
    ENDDO.

    result = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encode
      IMPORTING
        iv_message TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_encoded) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encode.
    DATA: lv_len      TYPE i,
          lv_idx      TYPE i,
          lv_char     TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_lower    TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_work     TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_is_upper TYPE abap_bool.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_message ).
    CLEAR rv_encoded.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = iv_message+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_char CA ` `.
        rv_encoded = rv_encoded && lv_char.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_work = lv_char.
      TRANSLATE lv_work TO LOWER CASE.
      lv_is_upper = xsdbool( lv_char <> lv_work ).

      lv_lower = lv_work.
      CASE lv_lower.
        WHEN `a`. lv_lower = `c`.
        WHEN `e`. lv_lower = `g`.
        WHEN `i`. lv_lower = `k`.
        WHEN `o`. lv_lower = `q`.
        WHEN `u`. lv_lower = `w`.
      ENDCASE.

      lv_work = lv_lower.

      IF lv_is_upper = abap_true.
        TRANSLATE lv_work TO LOWER CASE.
      ELSE.
        TRANSLATE lv_work TO UPPER CASE.
      ENDIF.

      rv_encoded = rv_encoded && lv_work.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encode
      IMPORTING
        message       TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encode.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_i   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c   TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_out TYPE string.

    DATA lv_is_upper TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_is_lower TYPE abap_bool.
    DATA lv_lower    TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_rep      TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_out = ``.
    lv_len = strlen( message ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = message+lv_i(1).

      IF lv_c = ` `.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_c.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_is_upper = abap_false.
      lv_is_lower = abap_false.

      IF lv_c CA 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'.
        lv_is_upper = abap_true.
      ELSEIF lv_c CA 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'.
        lv_is_lower = abap_true.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_is_upper = abap_true OR lv_is_lower = abap_true.
        lv_lower = lv_c.
        TRANSLATE lv_lower TO LOWER CASE.

        CASE lv_lower.
          WHEN 'a'.
            lv_rep = 'c'.
          WHEN 'e'.
            lv_rep = 'g'.
          WHEN 'i'.
            lv_rep = 'k'.
          WHEN 'o'.
            lv_rep = 'q'.
          WHEN 'u'.
            lv_rep = 'w'.
          WHEN OTHERS.
            lv_rep = lv_lower.
        ENDCASE.

        IF lv_is_upper = abap_true.
          TRANSLATE lv_rep TO LOWER CASE.
        ELSE.
          TRANSLATE lv_rep TO UPPER CASE.
        ENDIF.

        lv_out = lv_out && lv_rep.
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_c.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    result = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode_message DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encode
      IMPORTING
        iv_message TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_encoded) TYPE string.
