CLASS zcl_encode_message IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encode.
    DATA: lv_len  TYPE i,
          lv_pos  TYPE i,
          lv_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_message ).
    rv_encoded = ``.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_pos = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = iv_message+lv_pos(1).

      CASE lv_char.
        WHEN `a`. lv_char = `C`.
        WHEN `e`. lv_char = `G`.
        WHEN `i`. lv_char = `K`.
        WHEN `o`. lv_char = `Q`.
        WHEN `u`. lv_char = `W`.
        WHEN `A`. lv_char = `c`.
        WHEN `E`. lv_char = `g`.
        WHEN `I`. lv_char = `k`.
        WHEN `O`. lv_char = `q`.
        WHEN `U`. lv_char = `w`.
        WHEN OTHERS.
          IF lv_char CO `abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz`.
            TRANSLATE lv_char TO UPPER CASE.
          ELSEIF lv_char CO `ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ`.
            TRANSLATE lv_char TO LOWER CASE.
          ENDIF.
      ENDCASE.

      rv_encoded = rv_encoded && lv_char.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode_message DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS encode
      IMPORTING
        i_message TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_encode_message IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD encode.
    DATA: lv_len TYPE i,
          lv_out TYPE string,
          lv_c   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_u   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_idx TYPE i.

    lv_len = strlen( i_message ).
    CLEAR lv_out.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = i_message+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_c CO 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'.
        lv_u = lv_c.
        TRANSLATE lv_u TO UPPER CASE.
      ELSEIF lv_c CO 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'.
        lv_u = lv_c.
        TRANSLATE lv_u TO LOWER CASE.
      ELSE.
        lv_u = lv_c.
      ENDIF.

      CASE lv_u.
        WHEN 'a'. lv_u = 'c'.
        WHEN 'e'. lv_u = 'g'.
        WHEN 'i'. lv_u = 'k'.
        WHEN 'o'. lv_u = 'q'.
        WHEN 'u'. lv_u = 'w'.
        WHEN 'A'. lv_u = 'C'.
        WHEN 'E'. lv_u = 'G'.
        WHEN 'I'. lv_u = 'K'.
        WHEN 'O'. lv_u = 'Q'.
        WHEN 'U'. lv_u = 'W'.
        WHEN OTHERS.
      ENDCASE.

      lv_out = lv_out && lv_u.
    ENDDO.

    r_result = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_get_row IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_row.

    CLEAR rt_coords.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <rows> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <row>  TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <val>  TYPE any.

    ASSIGN lst TO <rows>.
    IF <rows> IS NOT ASSIGNED.

        IF <val> IS ASSIGNED AND <val> = x.

CLASS zcl_get_row IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_row.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <matrix> TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <row>    TYPE ANY TABLE,
                   <val>    TYPE any.

    ASSIGN lst TO <matrix>.
    IF <matrix> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_row TYPE i VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT <matrix> ASSIGNING <row>.
      DATA lv_col TYPE i VALUE 0.
      DATA lv_idx TYPE i.

      DO.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT sy-index OF STRUCTURE <row> TO <val>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.

        lv_idx = sy-index - 1.

        TRY.
            IF CONV i( <val> ) = x.
              APPEND VALUE ty_coordinate( row = lv_row col = lv_idx ) TO result.
            ENDIF.
          CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
        ENDTRY.
      ENDDO.

      lv_row = lv_row + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT result BY row ASCENDING col DESCENDING.
  ENDMETHOD.

             row TYPE i,

CLASS zcl_get_row IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_row.
    DATA: lv_row_idx TYPE i,
          lv_col_idx TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ls_row> TYPE any,
                   <ls_val> TYPE any.

    CLEAR rt_coords.

    lv_row_idx = 0.
    LOOP AT lst ASSIGNING <ls_row>.
      lv_col_idx = 0.

      DATA(lo_row_descr) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <ls_row> ).

      IF lo_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_table.
        DATA(lo_tab_descr) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( lo_row_descr ).
        DATA(lo_line_descr) = lo_tab_descr->get_table_line_type( ).

        FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_row> TYPE ANY TABLE.
        ASSIGN <ls_row> TO <lt_row>.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          LOOP AT <lt_row> ASSIGNING <ls_val>.
            DATA(lo_val_descr) = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <ls_val> ).
            IF lo_val_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int
            OR lo_val_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int1
            OR lo_val_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int2
            OR lo_val_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int8.
              IF <ls_val> = x.
                APPEND VALUE ty_coord( row = lv_row_idx col = lv_col_idx ) TO rt_coords.
              ENDIF.
            ENDIF.
            lv_col_idx += 1.
          ENDLOOP.
        ENDIF.
      ELSEIF lo_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int
          OR lo_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int1
          OR lo_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int2
          OR lo_row_descr->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int8.
        IF <ls_row> = x.
          APPEND VALUE ty_coord( row = lv_row_idx col = 0 ) TO rt_coords.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      lv_row_idx += 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT rt_coords BY row ASCENDING col DESCENDING.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS process
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.

  PROTECTED SECTION.
  PRIVATE SECTION.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    CONSTANTS lc_alpha TYPE string VALUE 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'.

    DATA(lv_len) = strlen( i_text ).
    r_text = ``.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx) = sy-index - 1.
      DATA(lv_ch)  = i_text+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_ch CO lc_alpha.
        DATA(lv_pos) = find( val = lc_alpha sub = lv_ch ).
        IF lv_pos >= 0.
          DATA(lv_new_pos) = ( lv_pos + 21 ) MOD 26.
          r_text = r_text && lc_alpha+lv_new_pos(1).
        ELSE.
          r_text = r_text && lv_ch.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        r_text = r_text && lv_ch.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS process
      IMPORTING
        i_text TYPE string OPTIONAL
        i_mode TYPE c OPTIONAL
      PREFERRED PARAMETER i_text
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA lv_len   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char  TYPE c.
    DATA lv_code  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_base  TYPE i VALUE 97.
    DATA lv_off   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_shift TYPE i.

    IF i_mode IS INITIAL.
      r_text = i_text.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    CASE i_mode.
      WHEN 'E' OR 'e'.
        lv_shift = 5.
      WHEN 'D' OR 'd'.
        lv_shift = -5.
      WHEN OTHERS.
        r_text = i_text.
        RETURN.
    ENDCASE.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).
    CLEAR r_text.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = i_text+lv_idx(1).

      lv_code = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( lv_char ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_off = lv_code - lv_base.
        lv_off = ( lv_off + lv_shift ) MOD 26.
        IF lv_off < 0.
          lv_off = lv_off + 26.
        ENDIF.
        lv_code = lv_base + lv_off.
        r_text = r_text && cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccpi( lv_code ).
      ELSE.
        r_text = r_text && lv_char.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

CLASS zcl_shift_codec IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA lv_len      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_out      TYPE string.
    DATA lv_pos      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_ch       TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_a        TYPE i VALUE 97.
    DATA lv_code     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_shift    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_new_code TYPE i.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).

    CASE i_mode.
      WHEN 'E'.
        lv_shift = 5.
      WHEN 'D'.
        lv_shift = 21.
      WHEN OTHERS.
        lv_shift = 0.
    ENDCASE.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_pos = sy-index - 1.
      lv_ch  = i_text+lv_pos(1).

      lv_code = CONV i( lv_ch ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN lv_a AND lv_a + 25 AND lv_shift <> 0.
        lv_new_code = ( ( lv_code - lv_a + lv_shift ) MOD 26 ) + lv_a.
        lv_out = lv_out && CONV c( lv_new_code ).
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_ch.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    r_text = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS process
      IMPORTING
        iv_text TYPE string
        iv_mode TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_text) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA: lv_shift TYPE i,
          lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_idx   TYPE i,
          lv_code  TYPE i,
          lv_base  TYPE i VALUE 97,
          lv_off   TYPE i,
          lv_in    TYPE string,
          lv_char  TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    rv_text = ''.

    IF iv_mode = 'ENCODE'.
      lv_shift = 5.
    ELSEIF iv_mode = 'DECODE'.
      lv_shift = -5.
    ELSE.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_text ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx  = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = iv_text+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_char CO 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'.
        lv_code = cl_abap_char_utilities=>char_to_num( lv_char ) - cl_abap_char_utilities=>char_to_num( 'a' ).
        lv_code = ( lv_code + lv_shift ) MOD 26.
        IF lv_code LT 0.
          lv_code = lv_code + 26.
        ENDIF.
        lv_char = cl_abap_char_utilities=>num_to_char( lv_code + cl_abap_char_utilities=>char_to_num( 'a' ) ).
        rv_text = rv_text && lv_char.
      ELSE.
        rv_text = rv_text && lv_char.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA: lv_len     TYPE i,
          lv_i       TYPE i,
          lv_ch       TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_char_out TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_code     TYPE i,
          lv_base     TYPE i,
          lv_shift    TYPE i,
          lv_code_u   TYPE sychar02,
          lv_mode     TYPE string.

    IF i_mode IS INITIAL.
      lv_mode = 'ENCODE'.
    ELSE.
      lv_mode = i_mode.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len  = strlen( i_text ).
    lv_base = 97.

    IF to_upper( lv_mode ) = 'DECODE'.
      lv_shift = -5.
    ELSE.
      lv_shift = 5.
    ENDIF.

    r_text = ``.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index - 1.
      lv_ch = i_text+lv_i(1).
      lv_code = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( lv_ch ).

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_code = ( ( lv_code - lv_base + lv_shift ) MOD 26 + 26 ) MOD 26 + lv_base.
        lv_code_u = lv_code.
        lv_char_out = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( char = lv_code_u ).
        r_text = r_text && lv_char_out.
      ELSE.
        r_text = r_text && lv_ch.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

      RETURNING

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA lv_len    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_i      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c1     TYPE string.
    DATA lv_code   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_base   TYPE i VALUE 97.
    DATA lv_shift  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_x      TYPE x LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_out    TYPE xstring.

    rv_text = ``.

    IF iv_mode = 'DECODE'.
      lv_shift = -5.
    ELSE.
      lv_shift = 5.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_text ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c1 = iv_text+lv_i(1).

      lv_out = cl_abap_codepage=>convert_to( source = lv_c1 ).
      lv_x = lv_out(1).
      lv_code = lv_x.

      IF lv_code BETWEEN 97 AND 122.
        lv_code = ( ( lv_code - lv_base + lv_shift ) MOD 26 ).
        IF lv_code < 0.
          lv_code = lv_code + 26.
        ENDIF.
        lv_code = lv_code + lv_base.

        lv_x = lv_code.
        lv_out = lv_x.
        rv_text = rv_text && cl_abap_codepage=>convert_from( source = lv_out ).
      ELSE.
        rv_text = rv_text && lv_c1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS process
      IMPORTING
        i_text   TYPE string
        i_decode TYPE abap_bool DEFAULT abap_false
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_text) TYPE string.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA: lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_idx   TYPE i,
          lv_in    TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_out   TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_ord   TYPE i,
          lv_a     TYPE i VALUE 97,
          lv_shift TYPE i.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).
    CLEAR r_text.

    IF i_decode = abap_true.
      lv_shift = -5.
    ELSE.
      lv_shift = 5.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_in = i_text+lv_idx(1).
      lv_ord = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccpi( lv_in ).

      IF lv_ord GE 97 AND lv_ord LE 122.
        lv_ord = lv_ord - lv_a.
        lv_ord = lv_ord + lv_shift.
        lv_ord = lv_ord MOD 26.
        IF lv_ord LT 0.
          lv_ord = lv_ord + 26.
        ENDIF.
        lv_ord = lv_ord + lv_a.
        lv_out = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccpi( lv_ord ).
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_in.
      ENDIF.

      CONCATENATE r_text lv_out INTO r_text IN CHARACTER MODE.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA lv_len   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_i     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c     TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_cp    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a     TYPE i VALUE 97.
    DATA lv_z     TYPE i VALUE 122.
    DATA lv_shift TYPE i.
    DATA lv_base  TYPE i.

    rv_text = ``.
    lv_len = strlen( iv_text ).

    IF iv_mode = `E`.
      lv_shift = 5.
    ELSEIF iv_mode = `D`.
      lv_shift = -5.
    ELSE.
      rv_text = iv_text.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = iv_text+lv_i(1).

      lv_cp = cl_abap_conv_in_ce=>uccp( lv_c ).

      IF lv_cp BETWEEN lv_a AND lv_z.
        lv_base = lv_cp - lv_a.
        lv_base = ( lv_base + lv_shift ) MOD 26.
        IF lv_base < 0.
          lv_base = lv_base + 26.
        ENDIF.
        lv_cp = lv_base + lv_a.
        lv_c = cl_abap_conv_out_ce=>uccp( CONV n( lv_cp ) ).
      ENDIF.

      rv_text = rv_text && lv_c.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_shift_codec IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD decode_shift.
    CONSTANTS lc_alpha TYPE string VALUE 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'.

    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
    DATA lv_pos TYPE i.
    DATA lv_out TYPE string.
    DATA lv_ch  TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    lv_len = strlen( i_s ).
    lv_out = ``.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_ch  = i_s+lv_idx(1).

      FIND lv_ch IN lc_alpha MATCH OFFSET lv_pos.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_pos = lv_pos - 5.
        IF lv_pos < 0.
          lv_pos = lv_pos + 26.
        ENDIF.
        lv_out = lv_out && lc_alpha+lv_pos(1).
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_ch.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    r_s = lv_out.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_shift_cipher IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
    DATA lv_out TYPE string.
    DATA lv_ch TYPE c.
    DATA lv_pos TYPE i.
    DATA lv_shift TYPE i.
    DATA lv_new_pos TYPE i.

    lv_len = strlen( i_text ).
    lv_out = ``.

    IF i_mode = 'E'.
      lv_shift = 5.
    ELSEIF i_mode = 'D'.
      lv_shift = 21.
    ELSE.
      r_text = i_text.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_ch = i_text+lv_idx(1).

      FIND lv_ch IN 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz' MATCH OFFSET lv_pos.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_new_pos = ( lv_pos + lv_shift ) MOD 26.
        lv_out = lv_out && 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'+lv_new_pos(1).
      ELSE.
        lv_out = lv_out && lv_ch.

CLASS zcl_has_close_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES tt_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES ty_p TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 7.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_num,
             v TYPE ty_p,
           END OF ty_num.
    TYPES tt_num TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS has_close_elements
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers   TYPE tt_numbers
        iv_threshold TYPE ty_p
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_has_close) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_has_close_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD has_close_elements.
    DATA lt_numbers TYPE tt_num.
    DATA ls_num     TYPE ty_num.

    LOOP AT it_numbers INTO DATA(lv_str).
      TRY.
          ls_num-v = CONV ty_p( lv_str ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.
      APPEND ls_num TO lt_numbers.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_numbers BY v ASCENDING.

    rv_has_close = abap_false.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE ty_p.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE ty_p.
    DATA lv_diff TYPE ty_p.

    LOOP AT lt_numbers INTO ls_num.
      lv_curr = ls_num-v.
      IF sy-tabix > 1.
        lv_diff = lv_curr - lv_prev.
        IF lv_diff < 0.
          lv_diff = -lv_diff.
        ENDIF.
        IF lv_diff < iv_threshold.
          rv_has_close = abap_true.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  PUBLIC
  FINAL

      IMPORTING

CLASS zcl_has_close_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD has_close_elements.
    rv_has_close = abap_false.

    DATA lt_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH NON-UNIQUE SORTED KEY sk COMPONENTS table_line.
    DATA lv_token TYPE string.
    DATA lv_work  TYPE string.

    lv_work = numbers.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '[' IN lv_work WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF ']' IN lv_work WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF space IN lv_work WITH ''.

    SPLIT lv_work AT ',' INTO TABLE DATA(lt_tokens).

    LOOP AT lt_tokens INTO lv_token.
      IF lv_token IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.
      TRY.
          APPEND CONV decfloat34( lv_token ) TO lt_numbers.
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lines( lt_numbers ) < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SORT lt_numbers BY table_line.

    DATA lv_prev  TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_first TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    LOOP AT lt_numbers INTO DATA(lv_curr).
      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        lv_first = abap_false.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ) < threshold.
        rv_has_close = abap_true.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_bored DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_bored
      IMPORTING
        !iv_s TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_bored IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_bored.
    DATA: lv_text TYPE string,
          lt_sent TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY,
          lv_sent TYPE string,
          lv_trim TYPE string,
          lv_first TYPE string,
          lv_dummy TYPE string.

    rv_count = 0.

    lv_text = iv_s.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF cl_abap_char_utilities=>cr_lf IN lv_text WITH space.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF cl_abap_char_utilities=>newline IN lv_text WITH space.

    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '?' IN lv_text WITH '.'.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '!' IN lv_text WITH '.'.

    SPLIT lv_text AT '.' INTO TABLE lt_sent.

    LOOP AT lt_sent INTO lv_sent.
      lv_trim = lv_sent.
      SHIFT lv_trim LEFT DELETING LEADING space.
      SHIFT lv_trim LEFT DELETING LEADING cl_abap_char_utilities=>horizontal_tab.

      IF lv_trim IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lv_first.
      CLEAR lv_dummy.
      SPLIT lv_trim AT space INTO lv_first lv_dummy.
      IF lv_first = 'I'.
        rv_count = rv_count + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      IF ( lv_idx MOD 2 ) = 0 AND ( <lv_val> MOD 2 ) = 0.

CLASS zcl_strongest_extension DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS strongest_extension
      IMPORTING
        class_name  TYPE string
        extensions  TYPE string_table
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strongest_extension IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD strongest_extension.
    DATA: lv_best_ext      TYPE string,
          lv_best_strength TYPE i VALUE -2147483648,
          lv_strength      TYPE i,
          lv_cap           TYPE i,
          lv_sm            TYPE i,
          lv_len           TYPE i,
          lv_idx           TYPE i,
          lv_char_c        TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    LOOP AT extensions INTO DATA(lv_ext).
      lv_cap = 0.
      lv_sm  = 0.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_ext ).

      DO lv_len TIMES.
        lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
        lv_char_c = lv_ext+lv_idx(1).

        IF lv_char_c CO 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'.
          lv_cap = lv_cap + 1.
        ELSEIF lv_char_c CO 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'.
          lv_sm = lv_sm + 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      lv_strength = lv_cap - lv_sm.

      IF lv_strength > lv_best_strength.
        lv_best_strength = lv_strength.
        lv_best_ext = lv_ext.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = |{ class_name }.{ lv_best_ext }|.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strongest_extension DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS strongest_extension
      IMPORTING
        class_name TYPE string
        extensions TYPE string_table
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_strongest_extension IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD strongest_extension.
    DATA best_ext TYPE string.
    DATA best_strength TYPE i VALUE -2147483648.

    LOOP AT extensions INTO DATA(ext).
      DATA cap TYPE i VALUE 0.
      DATA sm  TYPE i VALUE 0.

      DATA len TYPE i.
      len = strlen( ext ).

      DATA pos TYPE i VALUE 0.
      WHILE pos < len.
        DATA ch TYPE c LENGTH 1.
        ch = ext+pos(1).

        IF ch CO 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ'.
          cap = cap + 1.
        ELSEIF ch CO 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'.
          sm = sm + 1.
        ENDIF.

        pos = pos + 1.
      ENDWHILE.

      DATA strength TYPE i.
      strength = cap - sm.

      IF best_ext IS INITIAL OR strength > best_strength.
        best_strength = strength.
        best_ext = ext.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = |{ class_name }.{ best_ext }|.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_triples DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC .

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS get_max_triples
      IMPORTING
        n TYPE i
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE int8.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_max_triples IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD get_max_triples.
    DATA: lv_i   TYPE i,
          lv_mod TYPE i,
          lv_c0  TYPE int8,
          lv_c1  TYPE int8,
          lv_c2  TYPE int8.

    rv_count = 0.
    IF n < 3.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_c0 = 0.
    lv_c1 = 0.
    lv_c2 = 0.

    DO n TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.
      lv_mod = ( lv_i * lv_i - lv_i + 1 ) MOD 3.
      IF lv_mod < 0.
        lv_mod = lv_mod + 3.
      ENDIF.

      CASE lv_mod.
        WHEN 0.
          lv_c0 = lv_c0 + 1.
        WHEN 1.
          lv_c1 = lv_c1 + 1.
        WHEN 2.
          lv_c2 = lv_c2 + 1.
      ENDCASE.
    ENDDO.

    rv_count = ( lv_c0 * ( lv_c0 - 1 ) * ( lv_c0 - 2 ) ) DIV 6
            + ( lv_c1 * ( lv_c1 - 1 ) * ( lv_c1 - 2 ) ) DIV 6
            + ( lv_c2 * ( lv_c2 - 1 ) * ( lv_c2 - 2 ) ) DIV 6
            + lv_c0 * lv_c1 * lv_c2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS specialfilter
      IMPORTING
        nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD specialfilter.
    rv_count = 0.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT nums ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      DATA(lv_str) = |{ <lv_any> }|.

      CONDENSE lv_str NO-GAPS.
      IF lv_str IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_str CP '-*'.
        SHIFT lv_str LEFT BY 1 PLACES.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_str IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_str CA '.' OR lv_str CA ','.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_len) = strlen( lv_str ).
      IF lv_len <= 2.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      FIND FIRST OCCURRENCE OF PCRE '[^0-9]' IN lv_str.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_first_c) = lv_str+0(1).
      DATA(lv_last_c)  = lv_str+( lv_len - 1 )(1).

      IF ( lv_first_c = '1' OR lv_first_c = '3' OR lv_first_c = '5' OR lv_first_c = '7' OR lv_first_c = '9' )
         AND ( lv_last_c = '1' OR lv_last_c = '3' OR lv_last_c = '5' OR lv_last_c = '7' OR lv_last_c = '9' ).
        rv_count = rv_count + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num TYPE int8.
    TYPES ty_nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS special_filter
      IMPORTING
        nums TYPE ty_nums
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_num.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD special_filter.
    DATA lv_num   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_abs   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_str   TYPE string.
    DATA lv_len   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_first TYPE i.
    DATA lv_last  TYPE i.

    result = 0.

    LOOP AT nums INTO lv_num.
      IF lv_num <= 10.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_abs = abs( lv_num ).
      lv_str = |{ lv_abs }|.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_str ).

      IF lv_len <= 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_first = lv_str+0(1).
      lv_last  = lv_str+( lv_len - 1 )(1).

      IF ( lv_first MOD 2 = 1 ) AND ( lv_last MOD 2 = 1 ).
        result = result + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_special_filter DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS special_filter

      RETURNING

CLASS zcl_special_filter IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD special_filter.
    DATA lv_str   TYPE string.
    DATA lv_len   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_off   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_first TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_last  TYPE c LENGTH 1.

    rv_count = 0.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT nums ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      TRY.
          DATA(lv_num) = CONV i( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_num <= 10 OR lv_num < 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_str = |{ lv_num }|.
      lv_len = strlen( lv_str ).
      IF lv_len = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_first = lv_str(1).
      lv_off = lv_len - 1.
      lv_last = lv_str+lv_off(1).

      IF lv_first CA '13579' AND lv_last CA '13579'.
        rv_count = rv_count + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

CLASS zcl_special_filter IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD special_filter.
    DATA lv_str     TYPE string.
    DATA lv_work    TYPE string.
    DATA lv_val     TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.
    DATA lv_len     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_first_c TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_last_c  TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_off     TYPE i.

    rv_count = 0.

    LOOP AT nums INTO lv_str.
      lv_work = lv_str.

      REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '-' IN lv_work WITH ''.
      CONDENSE lv_work NO-GAPS.

      IF lv_work IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lv_val.
      TRY.
          lv_val = lv_work.
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_val <= 10.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_len = strlen( lv_work ).
      IF lv_len <= 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_first_c = lv_work+0(1).

      lv_off = lv_len - 1.
      lv_last_c = lv_work+lv_off(1).

      IF ( lv_first_c CA '13579' ) AND ( lv_last_c CA '13579' ).
        rv_count = rv_count + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD special_filter.
    DATA count TYPE i VALUE 0.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT nums ASSIGNING <n_any>.
      DATA n TYPE i.
      TRY.
          n = CONV i( <n_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF n <= 10.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA s TYPE string.
      s = |{ n }|.

      DATA first_c TYPE c LENGTH 1.
      DATA last_c  TYPE c LENGTH 1.

      first_c = s+0(1).
      last_c  = s+strlen( s )-1(1).

      IF ( first_c CA '13579' ) AND ( last_c CA '13579' ).
        count = count + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = count.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_special_filter DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS special_filter
      IMPORTING
        nums TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD special_filter.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE any.
    DATA n_i TYPE i.

    result = 0.

    LOOP AT nums ASSIGNING <n>.
      n_i = <n>.

      IF n_i <= 10.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(last_digit) = n_i MOD 10.
      IF last_digit < 0.
        last_digit = -last_digit.
      ENDIF.
      IF last_digit MOD 2 = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(first_digit) = n_i.
      IF first_digit < 0.
        first_digit = -first_digit.
      ENDIF.
      WHILE first_digit >= 10.
        first_digit = first_digit DIV 10.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF first_digit MOD 2 = 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      result = result + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num     TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 0.

    CLASS-METHODS special_filter
      IMPORTING
        it_nums TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_count) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_special_filter IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD special_filter.
    DATA lv_n     TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_abs   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_first TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_last  TYPE ty_num.

    rv_count = 0.

    LOOP AT it_nums INTO lv_n.
      IF lv_n <= 10.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_abs = lv_n.
      IF lv_abs < 0.
        lv_abs = lv_abs * -1.
      ENDIF.

      lv_last = lv_abs MOD 10.

      lv_first = lv_abs.
      WHILE lv_first >= 10.
        lv_first = lv_first DIV 10.
      ENDWHILE.

      IF ( lv_first MOD 2 ) = 1 AND ( lv_last MOD 2 ) = 1.
        rv_count = rv_count + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      IF ( lv_first = '1' OR lv_first = '3' OR lv_first = '5' OR lv_first = '7' OR lv_first = '9' )
         AND
         ( lv_last  = '1' OR lv_last  = '3' OR lv_last  = '5' OR lv_last  = '7' OR lv_last  = '9' ).

CLASS zcl_compare DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int4 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS compare
      IMPORTING
        game  TYPE ANY TABLE
        guess TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_diff) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compare.
    rt_diff = VALUE #( ).

    DATA(lv_len_game)  = lines( game ).
    DATA(lv_len_guess) = lines( guess ).
    DATA(lv_len)       = COND int4( WHEN lv_len_game < lv_len_guess THEN lv_len_game ELSE lv_len_guess ).

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <g> TYPE any,
                   <q> TYPE any.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      ASSIGN game[ sy-index ]  TO <g>.
      ASSIGN guess[ sy-index ] TO <q>.
      APPEND abs( CONV int4( <g> ) - CONV int4( <q> ) ) TO rt_diff.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS compare
      IMPORTING
        game  TYPE ANY TABLE
        guess TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_diff) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compare.
    DATA lv_len_game  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len_guess TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx       TYPE sy-tabix.
    DATA lv_val_game  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_val_guess TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <g> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <q> TYPE any.

    lv_len_game  = lines( game ).
    lv_len_guess = lines( guess ).

    IF lv_len_game <> lv_len_guess.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT game ASSIGNING <g>.
      lv_idx = sy-tabix.

      READ TABLE guess ASSIGNING <q> INDEX lv_idx.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          lv_val_game  = CONV i( <g> ).
          lv_val_guess = CONV i( <q> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.

      APPEND abs( lv_val_game - lv_val_guess ) TO rt_diff.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS compare
      IMPORTING
        game  TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        guess TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compare.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <g> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <q> TYPE any.

    DATA lt_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.

    lv_len = lines( game ).
    IF lines( guess ) < lv_len.
      lv_len = lines( guess ).
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      ASSIGN game[ sy-index ]  TO <g>.
      ASSIGN guess[ sy-index ] TO <q>.

      DATA(lv_game)  = CONV i( <g> ).
      DATA(lv_guess) = CONV i( <q> ).

      APPEND abs( lv_guess - lv_game ) TO lt_result.
    ENDDO.

    result = lt_result.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS compare
      IMPORTING
        game  TYPE ANY TABLE
        guess TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_diff) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compare.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <g> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <h> TYPE any.

    DATA lv_len_game  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len_guess TYPE i.
    DATA idx          TYPE i.
    DATA lv_game_i    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_guess_i   TYPE i.

    lv_len_game  = lines( game ).
    lv_len_guess = lines( guess ).

    IF lv_len_game <> lv_len_guess.
      CLEAR rt_diff.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    CLEAR rt_diff.

    DO lv_len_game TIMES.
      idx = sy-index.

      ASSIGN game[ idx ] TO <g>.
      ASSIGN guess[ idx ] TO <h>.

      lv_game_i  = <g>.
      lv_guess_i = <h>.

      APPEND abs( lv_guess_i - lv_game_i ) TO rt_diff.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int4 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS compare
      IMPORTING
        game  TYPE ANY TABLE
        guess TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_diff) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compare.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <game_std>  TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <guess_std> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <g>         TYPE any,
                   <q>         TYPE any.

    ASSIGN game  TO <game_std>.
    ASSIGN guess TO <guess_std>.

    DATA(lv_len_game)  = lines( <game_std> ).
    DATA(lv_len_guess) = lines( <guess_std> ).

    DATA(lv_len) = lv_len_game.
    IF lv_len_guess < lv_len.
      lv_len = lv_len_guess.
    ENDIF.

    CLEAR rt_diff.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx) = sy-index.

      READ TABLE <game_std>  ASSIGNING <g> INDEX lv_idx.
      READ TABLE <guess_std> ASSIGNING <q> INDEX lv_idx.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <g> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <q> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      APPEND abs( CONV int4( <g> ) - CONV int4( <q> ) ) TO rt_diff.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare_results DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS compare
      IMPORTING
        game  TYPE ANY TABLE
        guess TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare_results IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compare.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <game_tab>  TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <guess_tab> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <g>         TYPE any,
                   <q>         TYPE any.

    DATA lv_len_game  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len_guess TYPE i.
    DATA lv_game_i    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_guess_i   TYPE i.

    ASSIGN game  TO <game_tab>.
    ASSIGN guess TO <guess_tab>.

    IF <game_tab> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <guess_tab> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      result = VALUE ty_result( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len_game  = lines( <game_tab> ).
    lv_len_guess = lines( <guess_tab> ).

    IF lv_len_game <> lv_len_guess.
      result = VALUE ty_result( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len_game TIMES.
      ASSIGN <game_tab>[ sy-index ] TO <g>.
      ASSIGN <guess_tab>[ sy-index ] TO <q>.

      TRY.
          lv_game_i  = CONV i( <g> ).
          lv_guess_i = CONV i( <q> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          lv_game_i  = 0.
          lv_guess_i = 0.
      ENDTRY.

      APPEND abs( lv_game_i - lv_guess_i ) TO result.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS compare
      IMPORTING
        game  TYPE ANY TABLE
        guess TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_diff) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_compare IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD compare.
    DATA(lv_lines_game)  TYPE i.
    DATA(lv_lines_guess) TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <game_line>  TYPE any,
                   <guess_line> TYPE any.

    lv_lines_game  = lines( game ).
    lv_lines_guess = lines( guess ).

    IF lv_lines_game = 0 OR lv_lines_guess = 0 OR lv_lines_game <> lv_lines_guess.
      rt_diff = VALUE ty_result( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_lines_game TIMES.
      ASSIGN game[ sy-index ] TO <game_line>.
      ASSIGN guess[ sy-index ] TO <guess_line>.
      APPEND abs( CONV i( <guess_line> ) - CONV i( <game_line> ) ) TO rt_diff.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS next_smallest
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE int.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD next_smallest.
    CLEAR rv_result.

    IF lines( it_list ) < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA: lv_min1 TYPE int,
          lv_min2 TYPE int,
          lv_set1 TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false,
          lv_set2 TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<v>).
      IF lv_set1 = abap_false.
        lv_min1 = <v>.
        lv_set1 = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <v> < lv_min1.
        IF lv_set2 = abap_false OR lv_min1 < lv_min2.
          lv_min2 = lv_min1.
          lv_set2 = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
        lv_min1 = <v>.
      ELSEIF <v> > lv_min1.
        IF lv_set2 = abap_false OR <v> < lv_min2.
          lv_min2 = <v>.
          lv_set2 = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_set2 = abap_true.
      rv_result = lv_min2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS next_smallest
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syst_int4 WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE syst_int4.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD next_smallest.
    DATA lv_min      TYPE syst_int4.
    DATA lv_min2     TYPE syst_int4.
    DATA lv_has_min  TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
    DATA lv_has_min2 TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_val>).
      IF lv_has_min = abap_false.
        lv_min = <lv_val>.
        lv_has_min = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <lv_val> < lv_min.
        lv_min2 = lv_min.
        lv_has_min2 = abap_true.
        lv_min = <lv_val>.
      ELSEIF <lv_val> > lv_min.
        IF lv_has_min2 = abap_false OR <lv_val> < lv_min2.
          lv_min2 = <lv_val>.
          lv_has_min2 = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_has_min2 = abap_true.
      rv_result = lv_min2.
    ELSE.
      CLEAR rv_result.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS next_smallest
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_value) TYPE REF TO data.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD next_smallest.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_int> TYPE i.

    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.
    lt_sorted = it_list.
    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE i.
    DATA lv_prev_set TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    LOOP AT lt_sorted ASSIGNING <lv_int>.
      IF lv_prev_set = abap_false.
        lv_prev = <lv_int>.
        lv_prev_set = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <lv_int> <> lv_prev.
        DATA lr_result TYPE REF TO i.
        CREATE DATA lr_result.
        lr_result->* = <lv_int>.
        rv_value = lr_result.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    CLEAR rv_value.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS next_smallest
      IMPORTING

      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE int8.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD next_smallest.
    rv_result = 0.

    DATA: lv_min1     TYPE int8,
          lv_min2     TYPE int8,
          lv_has_min1 TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false,
          lv_has_min2 TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO DATA(lv_val).
      IF lv_has_min1 = abap_false.
        lv_min1 = lv_val.
        lv_has_min1 = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_val < lv_min1.
        lv_min2 = lv_min1.
        lv_has_min2 = abap_true.
        lv_min1 = lv_val.
      ELSEIF lv_val > lv_min1.
        IF lv_has_min2 = abap_false OR lv_val < lv_min2.
          lv_min2 = lv_val.
          lv_has_min2 = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_has_min2 = abap_false.
      CLEAR rv_result.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    rv_result = lv_min2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

      RETURNING

CLASS zcl_next_smallest IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD next_smallest.
    CLEAR rv_second.

    IF lines( it_list ) < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_unique TYPE SORTED TABLE OF syindex WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    lt_unique = VALUE #( FOR <v> IN it_list ( <v> ) ).

    IF lines( lt_unique ) < 2.
      CLEAR rv_second.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT lt_unique INTO DATA(lv_val).
      IF sy-tabix = 2.
        rv_second = lv_val.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS next_smallest
      IMPORTING
        it_list         TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_value) TYPE syindex.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_next_smallest IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD next_smallest.
    DATA: lv_min        TYPE syindex,
          lv_second     TYPE syindex,
          lv_has_min    TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false,
          lv_has_second TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    CLEAR rv_value.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <n> TYPE syindex.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <n>.
      IF lv_has_min = abap_false.
        lv_min = <n>.
        lv_has_min = abap_true.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <n> < lv_min.
        lv_second = lv_min.
        lv_has_second = abap_true.
        lv_min = <n>.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <n> > lv_min.
        IF lv_has_second = abap_false OR <n> < lv_second.
          lv_second = <n>.
          lv_has_second = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_has_second = abap_true.
      rv_value = lv_second.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS median
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_median) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD median.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_any> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
    DATA lv_value  TYPE f.
    DATA lv_count  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_mid    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a      TYPE f.
    DATA lv_b      TYPE f.

    ASSIGN it_values TO <lt_any>.
    LOOP AT <lt_any> ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      lv_value = <lv_any>.
      APPEND lv_value TO lt_sorted.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    lv_count = lines( lt_sorted ).
    IF lv_count = 0.
      rv_median = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_count MOD 2 = 1.
      lv_mid = ( lv_count + 1 ) / 2.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_mid INTO rv_median.
    ELSE.
      lv_mid = lv_count / 2.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_mid INTO lv_a.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_mid + 1 INTO lv_b.
      rv_median = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS median
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_median) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD median.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_count  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx1   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx2   TYPE i.

    lt_sorted = it_values.
    SORT lt_sorted BY table_line.

    lv_count = lines( lt_sorted ).
    IF lv_count = 0.
      rv_median = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_count MOD 2 = 1.
      lv_idx1 = ( lv_count + 1 ) / 2.
      rv_median = lt_sorted[ lv_idx1 ].
    ELSE.
      lv_idx1 = lv_count / 2.
      lv_idx2 = lv_idx1 + 1.
      rv_median = ( lt_sorted[ lv_idx1 ] + lt_sorted[ lv_idx2 ] ) / 2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_t_values TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS median
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE ty_t_values
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_median) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD median.
    DATA lt_num TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8 WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_num TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_mid TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a   TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8.
    DATA lv_b   TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8.
    DATA lv_med TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8.

    LOOP AT it_values ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<s>).
      lv_num = CONV #( <s> ).
      APPEND lv_num TO lt_num.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_num.

    lv_len = lines( lt_num ).
    IF lv_len = 0.
      rv_median = `0`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_mid = lv_len DIV 2.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 1.
      lv_med = lt_num[ lv_mid + 1 ].
    ELSE.
      lv_a = lt_num[ lv_mid ].
      lv_b = lt_num[ lv_mid + 1 ].
      lv_med = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.
    ENDIF.

    rv_median = |{ lv_med DECIMALS = 8 SIGN = LEFT }|.
    SHIFT rv_median RIGHT DELETING TRAILING space.
    SHIFT rv_median LEFT DELETING LEADING space.

    IF rv_median CS `.`.
      WHILE rv_median CP `*0`.
        IF rv_median+strlen( rv_median )-1(1) <> `0`.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
        rv_median = rv_median( strlen( rv_median ) - 1 ).
      ENDWHILE.
      IF rv_median+strlen( rv_median )-1(1) = `.`.
        rv_median = rv_median( strlen( rv_median ) - 1 ).
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_t_values TYPE SORTED TABLE OF f WITH NON-UNIQUE KEY table_line.

    CLASS-METHODS median
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE ty_t_values
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_median) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD median.
    DATA lt_values TYPE ty_t_values.
    DATA lv_count  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_mid    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_v1     TYPE f.
    DATA lv_v2     TYPE f.

    lt_values = it_values.

    lv_count = lines( lt_values ).
    IF lv_count = 0.
      rv_median = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_count MOD 2 = 1.
      lv_mid = ( lv_count + 1 ) / 2.
      rv_median = lt_values[ lv_mid ].
    ELSE.
      lv_mid = lv_count / 2.
      lv_v1 = lt_values[ lv_mid ].
      lv_v2 = lt_values[ lv_mid + 1 ].
      rv_median = ( lv_v1 + lv_v2 ) / 2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_value TYPE p LENGTH 8 DECIMALS 2.
    TYPES ty_values TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_value WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS median
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE ty_values
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_median) TYPE ty_value.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD median.
    DATA lt_values TYPE ty_values.
    DATA lv_n TYPE i.
    DATA lv_mid TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a TYPE ty_value.
    DATA lv_b TYPE ty_value.

    IF it_values IS INITIAL.
      rv_median = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lt_values = it_values.
    SORT lt_values ASCENDING.

    lv_n = lines( lt_values ).
    lv_mid = lv_n DIV 2.

    IF lv_n MOD 2 = 1.
      READ TABLE lt_values INDEX ( lv_mid + 1 ) INTO rv_median.
    ELSE.
      READ TABLE lt_values INDEX lv_mid INTO lv_a.
      READ TABLE lt_values INDEX ( lv_mid + 1 ) INTO lv_b.
      rv_median = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS median
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_median) TYPE f.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD median.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_any> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    DATA lt_values TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.

    LOOP AT it_values ASSIGNING <ls_any>.
      ASSIGN <ls_any> TO <lv_any>.
      APPEND CONV f( <lv_any> ) TO lt_values.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_values ASCENDING.

    DATA(lv_count) = lines( lt_values ).
    IF lv_count = 0.
      rv_median = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_count MOD 2 = 1.
      READ TABLE lt_values INDEX ( lv_count DIV 2 + 1 ) INTO rv_median.
    ELSE.
      DATA(lv_left)  = lv_count DIV 2.
      DATA(lv_right) = lv_left + 1.
      DATA lv_v1 TYPE f.
      DATA lv_v2 TYPE f.

      READ TABLE lt_values INDEX lv_left INTO lv_v1.
      READ TABLE lt_values INDEX lv_right INTO lv_v2.

      rv_median = ( lv_v1 + lv_v2 ) / 2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num TYPE i.
    TYPES ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS median
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_median) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_median IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD median.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE ty_num_tab.
    DATA lv_n      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_mid    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_b      TYPE i.

    lt_sorted = it_values.
    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    lv_n = lines( lt_sorted ).
    IF lv_n = 0.
      rv_median = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_n MOD 2 = 1.
      lv_mid = ( lv_n + 1 ) DIV 2.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_mid INTO lv_a.
      rv_median = lv_a.
    ELSE.
      lv_mid = lv_n DIV 2.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_mid INTO lv_a.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_mid + 1 INTO lv_b.
      rv_median = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sales_pos_processor IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process_sales_positions.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_pos,
             zid       TYPE i,
             zname     TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             zarticle  TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             zcurrency TYPE c LENGTH 5,
             zrev      TYPE p LENGTH 13 DECIMALS 2,
           END OF ty_pos.
    TYPES tt_pos TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_pos WITH EMPTY KEY.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_aggr,
             zname     TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             zarticle  TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             zcurrency TYPE c LENGTH 5,
             zrev      TYPE p LENGTH 13 DECIMALS 2,
           END OF ty_aggr.
    TYPES tt_aggr TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_aggr WITH UNIQUE KEY zname zarticle zcurrency.

    DATA lt_pos  TYPE tt_pos.
    DATA lt_aggr TYPE tt_aggr.

    SELECT zid, zname, zarticle, zcurrency, zrev
      FROM ('ZSALES_POSITIONS')
      INTO TABLE @lt_pos.

    LOOP AT lt_pos ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_pos>).
      READ TABLE lt_aggr ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_aggr>)
        WITH KEY zname = <ls_pos>-zname
                 zarticle = <ls_pos>-zarticle
                 zcurrency = <ls_pos>-zcurrency.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        <ls_aggr>-zrev = <ls_aggr>-zrev + <ls_pos>-zrev.
      ELSE.
        INSERT VALUE ty_aggr(
          zname     = <ls_pos>-zname
          zarticle  = <ls_pos>-zarticle
          zcurrency = <ls_pos>-zcurrency
          zrev      = <ls_pos>-zrev
        ) INTO TABLE lt_aggr.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    DELETE FROM ('ZSALES_AGGR').

    IF lt_aggr IS NOT INITIAL.
      INSERT ('ZSALES_AGGR') FROM TABLE @lt_aggr.
    ENDIF.

    rv_updated = abap_true.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sales_position_aggr IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD process.

             zid       TYPE i,
             zname     TYPE c LENGTH 20,
             zarticle  TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             zcurrency TYPE c LENGTH 5,
             zrev      TYPE p LENGTH 13 DECIMALS 2,
           END OF ty_pos.

    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_aggr,

             zarticle  TYPE c LENGTH 10,
             zcurrency TYPE c LENGTH 5,
             zrev      TYPE p LENGTH 13 DECIMALS 2,

    DATA lv_aggr_tab TYPE tabname VALUE 'ZSALES_AGGR'.

    DATA lt_pos  TYPE ty_t_pos.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_pos>  TYPE ty_pos.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_aggr> TYPE ty_aggr.

    rv_affected = 0.

    SELECT zid, zname, zarticle, zcurrency, zrev
      FROM (lv_pos_tab)
      INTO TABLE @lt_pos.

    LOOP AT lt_pos ASSIGNING <ls_pos>.
      READ TABLE lt_aggr ASSIGNING <ls_aggr>
        WITH TABLE KEY zname = <ls_pos>-zname
                       zarticle = <ls_pos>-zarticle

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE any TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE any TABLE.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lt_numbers> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <lv_prev>    TYPE any,
                   <lv_curr>    TYPE any.

    ASSIGN numbers TO <lt_numbers>.
    IF <lt_numbers> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR lines( <lt_numbers> ) < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lo_tabdescr) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( numbers ) ).
    DATA(lo_linedescr) = lo_tabdescr->get_table_line_type( ).

    DATA lr_sorted TYPE REF TO data.
    CREATE DATA lr_sorted TYPE HANDLE lo_tabdescr.
    ASSIGN lr_sorted->* TO <lt_numbers>.
    <lt_numbers> = numbers.

    SORT <lt_numbers> ASCENDING.

    DATA lr_result TYPE REF TO data.
    DATA(lo_pairdescr) = cl_abap_tabledescr=>create( p_line_type = lo_linedescr p_table_kind = cl_abap_tabledescr=>tablekind_std ).
    CREATE DATA lr_result TYPE HANDLE lo_pairdescr.
    ASSIGN lr_result->* TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lt_result>).

    READ TABLE <lt_numbers> INDEX 1 ASSIGNING <lv_prev>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_min_diff TYPE f VALUE '1E308'.
    DATA lv_best_a_f TYPE f.
    DATA lv_best_b_f TYPE f.
    DATA lr_a TYPE REF TO data.
    DATA lr_b TYPE REF TO data.

    DO lines( <lt_numbers> ) - 1 TIMES.
      READ TABLE <lt_numbers> INDEX sy-index + 1 ASSIGNING <lv_curr>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_prev_f) = CONV f( <lv_prev> ).
      DATA(lv_curr_f) = CONV f( <lv_curr> ).
      DATA(lv_diff) = abs( lv_curr_f - lv_prev_f ).

      IF lv_diff < lv_min_diff.
        lv_min_diff = lv_diff.
        lv_best_a_f = lv_prev_f.
        lv_best_b_f = lv_curr_f.

        CREATE DATA lr_a TYPE HANDLE lo_linedescr.
        CREATE DATA lr_b TYPE HANDLE lo_linedescr.
        ASSIGN lr_a->* TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_a>).
        ASSIGN lr_b->* TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_b>).
        <lv_a> = <lv_prev>.
        <lv_b> = <lv_curr>.

        CLEAR <lt_result>.
        APPEND <lv_a> TO <lt_result>.
        APPEND <lv_b> TO <lt_result>.

        IF lv_min_diff = 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      <lv_prev> = <lv_curr>.
    ENDDO.

    result = <lt_result>.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF fltp
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF fltp.
    lt_sorted = numbers.
    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE fltp.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE fltp.
    DATA lv_best_a TYPE fltp.
    DATA lv_best_b TYPE fltp.
    DATA lv_diff TYPE fltp.
    DATA lv_min_diff TYPE fltp.

    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 1 INTO lv_prev.
    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 2 INTO lv_curr.

    lv_best_a = lv_prev.
    lv_best_b = lv_curr.
    lv_min_diff = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).

    LOOP AT lt_sorted INTO lv_curr FROM 2.
      lv_diff = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).
      IF lv_diff < lv_min_diff.
        lv_min_diff = lv_diff.
        lv_best_a = lv_prev.
        lv_best_b = lv_curr.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_best_a <= lv_best_b.
      result = |({ lv_best_a }, { lv_best_b })|.
    ELSE.
      result = |({ lv_best_b }, { lv_best_a })|.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE ty_numbers
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_numbers TYPE ty_numbers.
    lt_numbers = numbers.

    IF lines( lt_numbers ) < 2.
      result = ``.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SORT lt_numbers ASCENDING.

    DATA lv_best_diff TYPE f VALUE 9999999999999999999999999999999999999.0.
    DATA lv_a         TYPE f.
    DATA lv_b         TYPE f.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <x> TYPE f.

    LOOP AT lt_numbers ASSIGNING <x> FROM 1 TO lines( lt_numbers ) - 1.
      DATA(lv_idx) = sy-tabix.
      DATA(lv_curr) = <x>.
      READ TABLE lt_numbers INDEX lv_idx + 1 INTO DATA(lv_next).
      DATA(lv_diff) = abs( lv_next - lv_curr ).

      IF lv_diff < lv_best_diff.
        lv_best_diff = lv_diff.
        lv_a = lv_curr.
        lv_b = lv_next.
        IF lv_best_diff = 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_a <= lv_b.
      result = |({ lv_a }, { lv_b })|.
    ELSE.
      result = |({ lv_b }, { lv_a })|.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_number TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 6.
    TYPES ty_numbers TYPE SORTED TABLE OF ty_number WITH UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_pair,
             a TYPE ty_number,
             b TYPE ty_number,
           END OF ty_pair.

    CLASS-METHODS find
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_number WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rs_pair) TYPE ty_pair.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find.
    DATA lt_numbers TYPE ty_numbers.
    lt_numbers = VALUE #( FOR <n> IN it_numbers ( <n> ) ).

    IF lines( lt_numbers ) < 2.
      CLEAR rs_pair.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_best_diff TYPE ty_number.
    DATA lv_initialized TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n1> TYPE ty_number.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n2> TYPE ty_number.

    DATA lv_idx TYPE i VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_count TYPE i.
    lv_count = lines( lt_numbers ).

    WHILE lv_idx < lv_count.
      ASSIGN lt_numbers[ lv_idx ] TO <n1>.
      ASSIGN lt_numbers[ lv_idx + 1 ] TO <n2>.

      DATA(lv_diff) = <n2> - <n1>.
      IF lv_diff < 0.
        lv_diff = lv_diff * -1.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_initialized = abap_false OR lv_diff < lv_best_diff.
        rs_pair-a = <n1>.
        rs_pair-b = <n2>.
        lv_best_diff = lv_diff.
        lv_initialized = abap_true.
      ENDIF.

      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDWHILE.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF float
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF float WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
    lt_sorted = numbers.
    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE float.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE float.
    DATA lv_min_diff TYPE float.
    DATA lv_best_a TYPE float.
    DATA lv_best_b TYPE float.
    DATA lv_has_pair TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    LOOP AT lt_sorted INTO lv_curr.
      IF sy-tabix = 1.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      DATA(lv_diff) = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).

      IF lv_has_pair = abap_false OR lv_diff < lv_min_diff.
        lv_min_diff = lv_diff.
        lv_best_a = lv_prev.
        lv_best_b = lv_curr.
        lv_has_pair = abap_true.
        IF lv_min_diff = 0.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.

    result = |({ lv_best_a }, { lv_best_b })|.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.
    TYPES ty_result  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH NON-UNIQUE DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE ty_numbers.
    DATA lv_prev TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_diff TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_best_diff TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_a TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_b TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_first TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    TRY.
        LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
          APPEND CONV decfloat34( <lv_any> ) TO lt_sorted.
        ENDLOOP.
      CATCH cx_root.
        result = VALUE #( ).
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lines( lt_sorted ) < 2.
      result = VALUE #( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    LOOP AT lt_sorted INTO lv_curr.
      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        lv_first = abap_false.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_diff = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).

      IF lv_best_diff IS INITIAL OR lv_diff < lv_best_diff.
        lv_best_diff = lv_diff.
        lv_a = lv_prev.
        lv_b = lv_curr.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.

    IF lv_a <= lv_b.
      result = VALUE #( ( lv_a ) ( lv_b ) ).
    ELSE.
      result = VALUE #( ( lv_b ) ( lv_a ) ).
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_pair TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_pair) TYPE ty_pair.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_sorted  TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH NON-UNIQUE KEY table_line.
    DATA lv_min_diff TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_diff     TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_a        TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_b        TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_i        TYPE i.
    DATA lv_count    TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT numbers ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      APPEND CONV decfloat34( <lv_any> ) TO lt_sorted.
    ENDLOOP.

    SORT lt_sorted ASCENDING.

    lv_count = lines( lt_sorted ).
    IF lv_count < 2.
      rt_pair = VALUE #( ).
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 1 INTO lv_a.
    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 2 INTO lv_b.
    lv_min_diff = abs( lv_b - lv_a ).

    DO lv_count - 1 TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_i INTO lv_a.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_i + 1 INTO lv_b.
      lv_diff = abs( lv_b - lv_a ).
      IF lv_diff < lv_min_diff.
        lv_min_diff = lv_diff.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    DO lv_count - 1 TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_i INTO lv_a.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_i + 1 INTO lv_b.
      lv_diff = abs( lv_b - lv_a ).
      IF lv_diff = lv_min_diff.
        rt_pair = VALUE #( ( lv_a ) ( lv_b ) ).
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES tt_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH NON-UNIQUE SORTED KEY sk COMPONENTS table_line.
    TYPES BEGIN OF ts_pair.
    TYPES low  TYPE f.
    TYPES high TYPE f.
    TYPES END OF ts_pair.

    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE tt_numbers
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rs_pair) TYPE ts_pair.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE tt_numbers.
    DATA lv_prev   TYPE f.
    DATA lv_curr   TYPE f.
    DATA lv_diff   TYPE f.
    DATA lv_best   TYPE f.

    CLEAR rs_pair.

    lt_sorted = numbers.
    SORT lt_sorted BY table_line.

    IF lines( lt_sorted ) < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 1 INTO lv_prev.
    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 2 INTO lv_curr.

    lv_best = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).
    rs_pair-low = lv_prev.
    rs_pair-high = lv_curr.

    DO lines( lt_sorted ) - 1 TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx) = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_idx INTO lv_prev.
      READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX lv_idx + 1 INTO lv_curr.

      lv_diff = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).
      IF lv_diff < lv_best.
        lv_best = lv_diff.
        rs_pair-low = lv_prev.
        rs_pair-high = lv_curr.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE ty_numbers
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_numbers.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH DEFAULT KEY.
    lt_numbers = numbers.

    SORT lt_numbers BY table_line.

    IF lines( lt_numbers ) < 2.
      CLEAR result.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_numbers INDEX 1 INTO DATA(lv_prev).
    READ TABLE lt_numbers INDEX 2 INTO DATA(lv_curr).

    DATA(lv_best_i)    = 1.
    DATA(lv_best_diff) = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).

    DO lines( lt_numbers ) - 1 TIMES.
      DATA(lv_i) = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_numbers INDEX lv_i     INTO lv_prev.
      READ TABLE lt_numbers INDEX lv_i + 1 INTO lv_curr.

      DATA(lv_diff) = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).
      IF lv_diff < lv_best_diff.
        lv_best_diff = lv_diff.
        lv_best_i = lv_i.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    READ TABLE lt_numbers INDEX lv_best_i     INTO lv_prev.
    READ TABLE lt_numbers INDEX lv_best_i + 1 INTO lv_curr.

    result = VALUE ty_numbers( ( lv_prev ) ( lv_curr ) ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH DEFAULT KEY.
    CLASS-METHODS find_closest_elements
      IMPORTING
        numbers TYPE ty_numbers
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rt_pair) TYPE ty_numbers.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_find_closest_elements IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_closest_elements.
    DATA lt_sorted TYPE ty_numbers.
    DATA lv_prev   TYPE f.
    DATA lv_curr   TYPE f.
    DATA lv_diff   TYPE f.
    DATA lv_min    TYPE f.
    DATA lv_a      TYPE f.
    DATA lv_b      TYPE f.

    lt_sorted = numbers.
    SORT lt_sorted BY table_line.

    CLEAR rt_pair.

    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 1 INTO lv_prev.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    READ TABLE lt_sorted INDEX 2 INTO lv_curr.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_min = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).
    lv_a = lv_prev.
    lv_b = lv_curr.
    lv_prev = lv_curr.

    LOOP AT lt_sorted INTO lv_curr FROM 3.
      lv_diff = abs( lv_curr - lv_prev ).
      IF lv_diff < lv_min.
        lv_min = lv_diff.
        lv_a = lv_prev.
        lv_b = lv_curr.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.

    APPEND lv_a TO rt_pair.
    APPEND lv_b TO rt_pair.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE int.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    rv_index = -1.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE int.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE int.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_curr.
      IF sy-tabix > 1 AND lv_curr <= lv_prev.
        rv_index = sy-tabix - 1.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE syindex.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    DATA: lv_prev TYPE syindex,
          lv_curr TYPE syindex,
          lv_idx  TYPE syindex.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <lv_any> TYPE any.

    rv_index = -1.
    lv_idx = 0.

    LOOP AT arr ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      lv_curr = <lv_any>.
      IF lv_idx > 0.
        IF lv_curr <= lv_prev.
          rv_index = lv_idx.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_curr.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF integer WITH DEFAULT KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE integer.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    rv_index = -1.

    DATA lv_prev  TYPE integer.
    DATA lv_i     TYPE integer VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_first TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_true.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO DATA(lv_curr).
      IF lv_first = abap_true.
        lv_prev  = lv_curr.
        lv_first = abap_false.
      ELSE.
        IF lv_curr <= lv_prev.
          rv_index = lv_i.
        ENDIF.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    DATA: lv_lines TYPE i,
          lv_idx   TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <cur>  TYPE any,
                   <prev> TYPE any.

    rv_index = -1.

    DESCRIBE TABLE it_arr LINES lv_lines.
    IF lv_lines <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_lines - 1 TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index.

      READ TABLE it_arr INDEX lv_idx ASSIGNING <prev>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      READ TABLE it_arr INDEX lv_idx + 1 ASSIGNING <cur>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF <cur> <= <prev>.
        rv_index = lv_idx + 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int8 WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE int8.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    rv_index = -1.

    DATA(lv_lines) = lines( it_arr ).
    IF lv_lines < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_prev) = it_arr[ 1 ].

    DO lv_lines - 1 TIMES.
      DATA(lv_idx) = sy-index + 1.
      DATA(lv_curr) = it_arr[ lv_idx ].
      IF lv_curr <= lv_prev.
        rv_index = lv_idx.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS run
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF syindex WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE syindex.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD run.
    rv_index = -1.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE syindex.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE syindex.
    DATA lv_idx  TYPE sy-tabix.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_curr.
      lv_idx = sy-tabix.
      IF lv_idx = 1.
        lv_prev = lv_curr.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_curr <= lv_prev.
        rv_index = lv_idx - 1.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    DATA lv_prev TYPE i.
    DATA lv_curr TYPE i.

    rv_index = -1.

    IF lines( it_arr ) < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE it_arr INDEX 1 INTO lv_prev.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_curr FROM 2.
      IF lv_curr <= lv_prev.
        rv_index = sy-tabix - 1.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF sytabix WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE sytabix.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    rv_index = -1.

    DATA lv_lines TYPE sytabix.
    lv_lines = lines( it_arr ).
    IF lv_lines <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE sytabix.
    READ TABLE it_arr INDEX 1 INTO lv_prev.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_lines - 1 TIMES.
      DATA lv_idx TYPE sytabix.
      lv_idx = sy-index + 1.

      DATA lv_curr TYPE sytabix.
      READ TABLE it_arr INDEX lv_idx INTO lv_curr.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_curr <= lv_prev.
        rv_index = lv_idx.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_curr.
    ENDDO.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS can_arrange
      IMPORTING
        it_arr TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF int
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_index) TYPE int.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_can_arrange IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD can_arrange.
    rv_index = -1.

    DATA lv_prev TYPE int.
    DATA lv_val  TYPE int.
    DATA lv_idx  TYPE int.

    lv_idx = 0.

    LOOP AT it_arr INTO lv_val.
      IF lv_idx > 0 AND lv_val <= lv_prev.
        rv_index = lv_idx.
      ENDIF.
      lv_prev = lv_val.
      lv_idx = lv_idx + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_solution DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

    CLASS-METHODS solution
      IMPORTING
        lst TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF integer
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE integer.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_solution IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD solution.
    result = 0.
    DATA idx TYPE integer VALUE 0.

    LOOP AT lst INTO DATA(val).
      idx = idx + 1.
      IF idx MOD 2 = 0 AND val MOD 2 <> 0.
        result = result + val.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS solution
      IMPORTING
        lst TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_odd_sum_even_pos IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD solution.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v> TYPE any.
    DATA idx TYPE sy-tabix.
    DATA val TYPE i.

    result = 0.

    LOOP AT lst ASSIGNING <v>.
      idx = sy-tabix.
      val = <v>.
      IF idx MOD 2 = 0 AND val MOD 2 <> 0.
        result = result + val.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

CLASS zcl_odd_sum_even_pos DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS solution
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_odd_sum_even_pos IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD solution.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
    DATA lv_val TYPE i.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      lv_idx = sy-tabix - 1.
      TRY.
          lv_val = CONV i( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF ( lv_idx MOD 2 = 0 ) AND ( lv_val MOD 2 <> 0 ).
        rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_val.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_solution DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS solution
      IMPORTING
        lst TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_solution IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD solution.
    DATA idx TYPE i.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <n> TYPE any.

    result = 0.
    idx = 0.

    LOOP AT lst ASSIGNING <n>.
      idx = idx + 1.

      "even positions are 0-based (Python-style): 0,2,4,... => ABAP indices 1,3,5,...
      IF ( idx MOD 2 ) = 1.
        TRY.
            DATA(val) = CONV i( <n> ).
            IF ( val MOD 2 ) <> 0.
              result = result + val.
            ENDIF.
          CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
        ENDTRY.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_odd_sum_even_pos DEFINITION
  PUBLIC

  CREATE PUBLIC.

CLASS zcl_odd_sum_even_pos IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD solution.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_list> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_val>  TYPE any.

    DATA lv_pos TYPE i.
    DATA lv_num TYPE i.

    rv_sum = 0.
    lv_pos = 0.

    ASSIGN it_list TO <lt_list>.

    LOOP AT <lt_list> ASSIGNING <lv_val>.
      lv_pos = lv_pos + 1.

      IF lv_pos MOD 2 = 0.
        TRY.
            lv_num = <lv_val>.
          CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
            CONTINUE.
        ENDTRY.

        IF lv_num MOD 2 <> 0.
          rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_num.

      IF lv_idx MOD 2 = 0.
