CLASS zcl_filter_integers IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD filter_integers.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <ls_line> TYPE any,
                   <lv_val>  TYPE any.

    DATA(lo_tabdescr) = CAST cl_abap_tabledescr( cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( values ) ).
    DATA(lo_linedescr) = lo_tabdescr->get_table_line_type( ).

    LOOP AT values ASSIGNING <ls_line>.
      IF lo_linedescr->kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>kind_struct.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE <ls_line> TO <lv_val>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          CONTINUE.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        ASSIGN <ls_line> TO <lv_val>.
      ENDIF.

      IF cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <lv_val> )->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int.
        APPEND <lv_val> TO result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

    LOOP AT it_values ASSIGNING <ls_row>.
      UNASSIGN <lv_val>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE <ls_row> TO <lv_val>.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR <lv_val> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF cl_abap_datadescr=>describe_by_data( <lv_val> )->type_kind = cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int.
        APPEND <lv_val> TO rt_integers.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_filter_integers IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD filter_integers.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <ls_line> TYPE any.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_val>  TYPE any.

    DATA lv_trim   TYPE char255.
    DATA lv_sign   TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_digits TYPE char255.
    DATA lv_i      TYPE i.

    rt_integers = VALUE #( ).

    LOOP AT it_values ASSIGNING <ls_line>.
      ASSIGN <ls_line> TO <lv_val>.
      IF <lv_val> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      CLEAR lv_trim.
      TRY.
          lv_trim = <lv_val>.
        CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_no_number.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      CONDENSE lv_trim NO-GAPS.

      IF lv_trim IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sign = lv_trim(1).

      IF lv_sign = '+' OR lv_sign = '-'.
        lv_digits = lv_trim+1.
      ELSE.
        lv_digits = lv_trim.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_digits IS INITIAL.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_digits CO '0123456789'.
        TRY.
            lv_i = lv_trim.
            APPEND lv_i TO rt_integers.
          CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
        ENDTRY.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

  PUBLIC
  FINAL

      IMPORTING
        numbers       TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i
      RETURNING

CLASS zcl_remove_duplicates IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD remove_duplicates.
    TYPES: BEGIN OF ty_count,
             num TYPE i,
             cnt TYPE i,
           END OF ty_count.

    DATA lt_counts TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_count WITH UNIQUE KEY num.

    LOOP AT numbers INTO DATA(lv_num).
      ASSIGN lt_counts[ KEY primary_key COMPONENTS num = lv_num ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_count>).
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        <ls_count>-cnt = <ls_count>-cnt + 1.
      ELSE.
        INSERT VALUE ty_count( num = lv_num cnt = 1 ) INTO TABLE lt_counts.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.

    LOOP AT numbers INTO DATA(lv_num2).
      ASSIGN lt_counts[ KEY primary_key COMPONENTS num = lv_num2 ] TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<ls_count2>).
      IF sy-subrc = 0 AND <ls_count2>-cnt = 1.
        APPEND lv_num2 TO result.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_remove_duplicates IMPLEMENTATION.

    TYPES ty_count_htab TYPE HASHED TABLE OF ty_count WITH UNIQUE KEY number.

    DATA lt_counts TYPE ty_count_htab.
    DATA lv_n      TYPE i.

    LOOP AT it_numbers INTO lv_n.

    rt_numbers = VALUE ty_numbers( ).

      IF lt_counts[ number = lv_n ]-count = 1.

      ENDIF.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num TYPE f.

    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_x) TYPE ty_num.

  PRIVATE SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS poly
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        x  TYPE ty_num
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_y) TYPE ty_num.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD poly.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.
    DATA lv_i     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_pow   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_coeff TYPE ty_num.

    rv_y = 0.
    lv_i = 0.

    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      TRY.
          lv_coeff = CONV ty_num( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          lv_coeff = 0.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_pow = 1.
      DO lv_i TIMES.
        lv_pow = lv_pow * x.
      ENDDO.

      rv_y = rv_y + lv_coeff * lv_pow.
      lv_i = lv_i + 1.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.

  METHOD find_zero.
    DATA lv_n      TYPE i.
    DATA lv_deg    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_lead   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_a0     TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_scale  TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_abs    TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_bound  TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_left   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_right  TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_fl     TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_fr     TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_expand TYPE i.
    DATA lv_l      TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_r      TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_m      TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_fm     TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_eps    TYPE ty_num.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.
    DATA lv_tmp TYPE ty_num.

    rv_x = 0.

    lv_n = lines( xs ).
    IF lv_n = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_deg = lv_n - 1.

    READ TABLE xs INDEX lv_n ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    TRY.
        lv_lead = CONV ty_num( <lv_any> ).
      CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
        lv_lead = 0.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lv_lead = 0.
      DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
      lv_idx = lv_n.
      WHILE lv_idx > 0.
        READ TABLE xs INDEX lv_idx ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        TRY.
            lv_lead = CONV ty_num( <lv_any> ).
          CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
            lv_lead = 0.
        ENDTRY.
        IF lv_lead <> 0.
          lv_deg = lv_idx - 1.
          EXIT.
        ENDIF.
        lv_idx = lv_idx - 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      IF lv_lead = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_deg = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE xs INDEX 1 ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    TRY.
        lv_a0 = CONV ty_num( <lv_any> ).
      CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
        lv_a0 = 0.
    ENDTRY.
    IF lv_a0 = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_scale = 0.
    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      TRY.
          lv_tmp = CONV ty_num( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          lv_tmp = 0.
      ENDTRY.
      lv_abs = abs( lv_tmp ).
      IF lv_abs > lv_scale.
        lv_scale = lv_abs.
      ENDIF.
    ENDLOOP.
    IF lv_scale = 0 OR lv_lead = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_bound = 1 + ( lv_scale / abs( lv_lead ) ).
    IF lv_bound <= 0.
      lv_bound = 1.
    ENDIF.

    lv_left  = -lv_bound.
    lv_right =  lv_bound.

    lv_fl = poly( xs = xs x = lv_left ).
    lv_fr = poly( xs = xs x = lv_right ).

    lv_expand = 0.
    WHILE lv_fl * lv_fr > 0 AND lv_expand < 60.
      lv_bound = lv_bound * 2.
      lv_left  = -lv_bound.
      lv_right =  lv_bound.
      lv_fl = poly( xs = xs x = lv_left ).
      lv_fr = poly( xs = xs x = lv_right ).
      lv_expand = lv_expand + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_fl = 0.
      rv_x = lv_left.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    IF lv_fr = 0.
      rv_x = lv_right.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_fl * lv_fr > 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_l = lv_left.
    lv_r = lv_right.
    lv_eps = 1E-7.

    DO 300 TIMES.
      lv_m  = ( lv_l + lv_r ) / 2.
      lv_fm = poly( xs = xs x = lv_m ).

      IF abs( lv_fm ) <= lv_eps OR abs( lv_r - lv_l ) <= lv_eps.
        rv_x = lv_m.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_fl * lv_fm <= 0.
        lv_r  = lv_m.
        lv_fr = lv_fm.
      ELSE.
        lv_l  = lv_m.
        lv_fl = lv_fm.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    rv_x = ( lv_l + lv_r ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_x) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_zero.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <c_any> TYPE any.

    DATA lt_coeff TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH EMPTY KEY.
    DATA lv_c     TYPE decfloat34.

    DATA lv_n TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_b TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_fa TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_fb TYPE decfloat34.

    DATA lv_expand TYPE i.
    DATA lv_absdiff TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_mid TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_fm  TYPE decfloat34.

    DATA lv_pow TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_x   TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_eps TYPE decfloat34.

    DATA lv_sign_a TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sign_b TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sign_m TYPE i.

    DATA lv_max_expand TYPE i.
    DATA lv_max_iter   TYPE i.

    rv_x = 0.

    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <c_any>.
      TRY.
          lv_c = CONV decfloat34( <c_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.
      APPEND lv_c TO lt_coeff.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_n = lines( lt_coeff ).
    IF lv_n = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_n MOD 2 <> 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_n INTO lv_c.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR lv_c = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_a = CONV decfloat34( '-1' ).
    lv_b = CONV decfloat34( '1' ).

    lv_eps = CONV decfloat34( '1E-30' ).
    lv_max_expand = 200.
    lv_max_iter   = 400.
    lv_expand = 0.

    DEFINE eval_poly_into.
      lv_x = &1.
      &2 = CONV decfloat34( '0' ).
      lv_pow = CONV decfloat34( '1' ).
      LOOP AT lt_coeff INTO lv_c.
        &2 = &2 + ( lv_c * lv_pow ).
        lv_pow = lv_pow * lv_x.
      ENDLOOP.
    END-OF-DEFINITION.

    DEFINE sign_of.
      IF &1 > 0.
        &2 = 1.
      ELSEIF &1 < 0.
        &2 = -1.
      ELSE.
        &2 = 0.
      ENDIF.
    END-OF-DEFINITION.

    eval_poly_into lv_a lv_fa.
    eval_poly_into lv_b lv_fb.

    sign_of lv_fa lv_sign_a.
    sign_of lv_fb lv_sign_b.

    WHILE lv_sign_a = lv_sign_b AND lv_expand < lv_max_expand.
      lv_expand = lv_expand + 1.
      lv_a = lv_a * 2.
      lv_b = lv_b * 2.
      eval_poly_into lv_a lv_fa.
      eval_poly_into lv_b lv_fb.
      sign_of lv_fa lv_sign_a.
      sign_of lv_fb lv_sign_b.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_sign_a = 0.
      rv_x = lv_a.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    IF lv_sign_b = 0.
      rv_x = lv_b.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_sign_a = lv_sign_b.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_max_iter TIMES.
      lv_mid = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.
      eval_poly_into lv_mid lv_fm.
      sign_of lv_fm lv_sign_m.

      IF lv_sign_m = 0.
        rv_x = lv_mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_b >= lv_a.
        lv_absdiff = lv_b - lv_a.
      ELSE.
        lv_absdiff = lv_a - lv_b.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_absdiff <= lv_eps.
        rv_x = lv_mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_sign_m = lv_sign_a.
        lv_a = lv_mid.
        lv_fa = lv_fm.
        lv_sign_a = lv_sign_m.
      ELSE.
        lv_b = lv_mid.
        lv_fb = lv_fm.
        lv_sign_b = lv_sign_m.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    rv_x = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_coeffs TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF decfloat34 WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE ty_coeffs
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_x) TYPE f.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero IMPLEMENTATION.

  METHOD find_zero.
    DATA lv_n TYPE i.
    lv_n = lines( xs ).

    IF lv_n IS INITIAL OR lv_n MOD 2 <> 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lt_coeff TYPE ty_coeffs.
    lt_coeff = xs.

    DATA lv_last_idx TYPE i.
    lv_last_idx = lv_n.

    DATA lv_a_n TYPE decfloat34.

    WHILE lv_last_idx > 0.
      READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_last_idx INTO lv_a_n.
      IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_a_n <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      lv_last_idx = lv_last_idx - 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_last_idx = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_deg TYPE i.
    lv_deg = lv_last_idx - 1.

    DATA lv_lo TYPE f.
    DATA lv_hi TYPE f.
    DATA lv_flo TYPE f.
    DATA lv_fhi TYPE f.

    DATA lv_b TYPE f.
    lv_b = 1.

    DATA lv_abs_an TYPE f.
    lv_abs_an = abs( CONV f( lv_a_n ) ).

    DATA lv_i TYPE i.
    DATA lv_ai_df TYPE decfloat34.
    DATA lv_cand TYPE f.

    DO lv_deg TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.
      READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_i INTO lv_ai_df.
      IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_abs_an <> 0.
        lv_cand = 1 + abs( CONV f( lv_ai_df ) ) / lv_abs_an.
        IF lv_cand > lv_b.
          lv_b = lv_cand.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    lv_lo = 0 - lv_b.
    lv_hi = lv_b.

    DATA lv_k TYPE i.
    DATA lv_val TYPE f.
    DATA lv_ck TYPE f.
    DATA lv_ck_df TYPE decfloat34.

    lv_val = 0.
    lv_k = lv_deg + 1.
    WHILE lv_k >= 1.
      READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_k INTO lv_ck_df.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        lv_ck = 0.
      ELSE.
        lv_ck = CONV f( lv_ck_df ).
      ENDIF.
      lv_val = lv_val * lv_lo + lv_ck.
      lv_k = lv_k - 1.
    ENDWHILE.
    lv_flo = lv_val.

    lv_val = 0.
    lv_k = lv_deg + 1.
    WHILE lv_k >= 1.
      READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_k INTO lv_ck_df.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        lv_ck = 0.
      ELSE.
        lv_ck = CONV f( lv_ck_df ).
      ENDIF.
      lv_val = lv_val * lv_hi + lv_ck.
      lv_k = lv_k - 1.
    ENDWHILE.
    lv_fhi = lv_val.

    IF lv_flo = 0.
      rv_x = lv_lo.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    IF lv_fhi = 0.
      rv_x = lv_hi.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_iter TYPE i.
    lv_iter = 0.

    DATA lv_mid TYPE f.
    DATA lv_fmid TYPE f.
    DATA lv_tol TYPE f.
    lv_tol = '0.000000000001'.

    DATA lv_max_iter TYPE i.
    lv_max_iter = 200.

    IF lv_flo * lv_fhi > 0.
      DATA lv_scale TYPE f.
      lv_scale = 2.

      WHILE lv_iter < 60 AND lv_flo * lv_fhi > 0.
        lv_iter = lv_iter + 1.
        lv_lo = lv_lo * lv_scale.
        lv_hi = lv_hi * lv_scale.

        lv_val = 0.
        lv_k = lv_deg + 1.
        WHILE lv_k >= 1.
          READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_k INTO lv_ck_df.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            lv_ck = 0.
          ELSE.
            lv_ck = CONV f( lv_ck_df ).
          ENDIF.
          lv_val = lv_val * lv_lo + lv_ck.
          lv_k = lv_k - 1.
        ENDWHILE.
        lv_flo = lv_val.

        lv_val = 0.
        lv_k = lv_deg + 1.
        WHILE lv_k >= 1.
          READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_k INTO lv_ck_df.
          IF sy-subrc <> 0.
            lv_ck = 0.
          ELSE.
            lv_ck = CONV f( lv_ck_df ).
          ENDIF.
          lv_val = lv_val * lv_hi + lv_ck.
          lv_k = lv_k - 1.
        ENDWHILE.
        lv_fhi = lv_val.
      ENDWHILE.
    ENDIF.

    lv_iter = 0.
    WHILE lv_iter < lv_max_iter.
      lv_iter = lv_iter + 1.
      lv_mid = ( lv_lo + lv_hi ) / 2.

      lv_val = 0.
      lv_k = lv_deg + 1.
      WHILE lv_k >= 1.
        READ TABLE lt_coeff INDEX lv_k INTO lv_ck_df.
        IF sy-subrc <> 0.
          lv_ck = 0.
        ELSE.
          lv_ck = CONV f( lv_ck_df ).
        ENDIF.
        lv_val = lv_val * lv_mid + lv_ck.
        lv_k = lv_k - 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      lv_fmid = lv_val.

      IF lv_fmid = 0.
        rv_x = lv_mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF abs( lv_hi - lv_lo ) <= lv_tol * ( 1 + abs( lv_mid ) ).
        rv_x = lv_mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_flo * lv_fmid < 0.
        lv_hi = lv_mid.
        lv_fhi = lv_fmid.
      ELSE.
        lv_lo = lv_mid.
        lv_flo = lv_fmid.
      ENDIF.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_x = ( lv_lo + lv_hi ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.

ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_num    TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 8.
    TYPES ty_coeffs TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE ty_coeffs
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_x) TYPE ty_num.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_zero.
    DATA lv_n    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_low  TYPE ty_num VALUE -1.
    DATA lv_high TYPE ty_num VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_a    TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_b    TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_fa   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_fb   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_fm   TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_m    TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_p    TYPE ty_num.
    DATA lv_eps  TYPE ty_num VALUE '0.00000001'.
    DATA lv_i    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_iter TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <c> TYPE ty_num.

    lv_n = lines( xs ).
    IF lv_n = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_iter = 0.
    WHILE lv_iter < 200.
      lv_fa = 0.
      lv_p = 1.
      lv_i = 0.
      LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <c>.
        IF lv_i = 0.
          lv_fa = <c>.
        ELSE.
          lv_p = lv_p * lv_low.
          lv_fa = lv_fa + <c> * lv_p.
        ENDIF.
        lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      ENDLOOP.

      lv_fb = 0.
      lv_p = 1.
      lv_i = 0.
      LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <c>.
        IF lv_i = 0.
          lv_fb = <c>.
        ELSE.
          lv_p = lv_p * lv_high.
          lv_fb = lv_fb + <c> * lv_p.
        ENDIF.
        lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF lv_fa = 0.
        rv_x = lv_low.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF lv_fb = 0.
        rv_x = lv_high.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_fa < 0 AND lv_fb > 0 ) OR ( lv_fa > 0 AND lv_fb < 0 ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_low  = lv_low  * 2.
      lv_high = lv_high * 2.
      lv_iter = lv_iter + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    lv_a = lv_low.
    lv_b = lv_high.

    lv_fa = 0.
    lv_p = 1.
    lv_i = 0.
    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <c>.
      IF lv_i = 0.
        lv_fa = <c>.
      ELSE.
        lv_p = lv_p * lv_a.
        lv_fa = lv_fa + <c> * lv_p.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    lv_fb = 0.
    lv_p = 1.
    lv_i = 0.
    LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <c>.
      IF lv_i = 0.
        lv_fb = <c>.
        CONTINUE.
      ENDIF.
      lv_p = lv_p * lv_b.
      lv_fb = lv_fb + <c> * lv_p.
      lv_i = lv_i + 1.
    ENDLOOP.

    DO 200 TIMES.
      lv_m = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.

      lv_fm = 0.
      lv_p = 1.
      lv_i = 0.
      LOOP AT xs ASSIGNING <c>.
        IF lv_i = 0.
          lv_fm = <c>.
        ELSE.
          lv_p = lv_p * lv_m.
          lv_fm = lv_fm + <c> * lv_p.
        ENDIF.
        lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      ENDLOOP.

      IF abs( lv_fm ) < lv_eps OR abs( lv_b - lv_a ) < lv_eps.
        rv_x = lv_m.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_fa < 0 AND lv_fm > 0 ) OR ( lv_fa > 0 AND lv_fm < 0 ).
        lv_b  = lv_m.
        lv_fb = lv_fm.
      ELSE.
        lv_a  = lv_m.
        lv_fa = lv_fm.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    rv_x = ( lv_a + lv_b ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_coeff  TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 14.
    TYPES ty_coeffs TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_coeff WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_result TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 14.

    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs            TYPE ty_coeffs
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE ty_result.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_zero.
    DATA n TYPE i.
    n = lines( xs ).
    IF n = 0.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA idx TYPE i.
    DATA a_last TYPE ty_coeff.

    READ TABLE xs INDEX n INTO a_last.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR a_last = 0.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA eps TYPE ty_result VALUE '0.00000000000001'.

    DATA lo  TYPE ty_result VALUE -1.
    DATA hi  TYPE ty_result VALUE 1.
    DATA flo TYPE ty_result.
    DATA fhi TYPE ty_result.
    DATA fx  TYPE ty_result.
    DATA mid TYPE ty_result.
    DATA a   TYPE ty_coeff.

    flo = 0.
    DO n TIMES.
      idx = n - sy-index + 1.
      READ TABLE xs INDEX idx INTO a.
      flo = flo * lo + a.
    ENDDO.

    fhi = 0.
    DO n TIMES.
      idx = n - sy-index + 1.
      READ TABLE xs INDEX idx INTO a.
      fhi = fhi * hi + a.
    ENDDO.

    DATA iter TYPE i VALUE 0.
    WHILE flo * fhi > 0 AND iter < 200.
      iter = iter + 1.
      lo = lo * 2.
      hi = hi * 2.

      flo = 0.
      DO n TIMES.
        idx = n - sy-index + 1.
        READ TABLE xs INDEX idx INTO a.
        flo = flo * lo + a.
      ENDDO.

      fhi = 0.
      DO n TIMES.
        idx = n - sy-index + 1.
        READ TABLE xs INDEX idx INTO a.
        fhi = fhi * hi + a.
      ENDDO.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF flo = 0.
      result = lo.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    IF fhi = 0.
      result = hi.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    IF flo * fhi > 0.
      result = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO 200 TIMES.
      mid = ( lo + hi ) / 2.

      fx = 0.
      DO n TIMES.
        idx = n - sy-index + 1.
        READ TABLE xs INDEX idx INTO a.
        fx = fx * mid + a.
      ENDDO.

      IF fx = 0.
        result = mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF flo * fx < 0.
        hi = mid.
        fhi = fx.
      ELSE.
        lo = mid.
        flo = fx.
      ENDIF.

      IF abs( hi - lo ) <= eps.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    result = ( lo + hi ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_coeffs TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        it_coeffs      TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_root) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_zero.
    DATA lt_coeffs TYPE ty_coeffs.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_coeffs ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      APPEND CONV f( <lv_any> ) TO lt_coeffs.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA n TYPE i.
    n = lines( lt_coeffs ).

    IF n = 0 OR n MOD 2 <> 0.
      rv_root = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA a_n TYPE f.
    READ TABLE lt_coeffs INDEX n INTO a_n.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR a_n = 0.
      rv_root = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA sign_an TYPE i.
    sign_an = COND i( WHEN a_n > 0 THEN 1 ELSE -1 ).

    DATA x        TYPE f.
    DATA poly_val TYPE f.
    DATA coeff    TYPE f.
    DATA idx      TYPE i.

    DATA x0 TYPE f.
    DATA x1 TYPE f.
    DATA f0 TYPE f.
    DATA f1 TYPE f.

    DATA found TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    DO 801 TIMES.
      DATA k TYPE i.
      k = sy-index - 401.
      x = k.

      poly_val = 0.
      DO n TIMES.
        idx = n - sy-index + 1.
        READ TABLE lt_coeffs INDEX idx INTO coeff.
        poly_val = poly_val * x + coeff.
      ENDDO.

      IF poly_val = 0.
        rv_root = x.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF sign_an * poly_val < 0.
        x0 = x.
        f0 = poly_val.
        found = abap_true.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    IF found = abap_false.
      x0 = -1.
      poly_val = 0.
      DO n TIMES.
        idx = n - sy-index + 1.
        READ TABLE lt_coeffs INDEX idx INTO coeff.
        poly_val = poly_val * x0 + coeff.
      ENDDO.
      f0 = poly_val.
    ENDIF.

    x1 = x0.
    f1 = f0.

    DATA step  TYPE f VALUE 1.
    DATA tries TYPE i VALUE 0.

    WHILE sign_an * f1 < 0 AND tries < 2000.
      tries = tries + 1.
      x1 = x1 + step.

      poly_val = 0.
      DO n TIMES.
        idx = n - sy-index + 1.
        READ TABLE lt_coeffs INDEX idx INTO coeff.
        poly_val = poly_val * x1 + coeff.
      ENDDO.
      f1 = poly_val.

      IF f1 = 0.
        rv_root = x1.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      step = step * 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF sign_an * f1 < 0.
      rv_root = x0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lo  TYPE f.
    DATA hi  TYPE f.
    DATA flo TYPE f.
    DATA fhi TYPE f.

    lo = x0.
    hi = x1.
    flo = f0.
    fhi = f1.

    IF lo > hi.
      DATA tmp TYPE f.
      tmp = lo.  lo = hi.  hi = tmp.
      tmp = flo. flo = fhi. fhi = tmp.
    ENDIF.

    IF flo = 0.
      rv_root = lo.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    IF fhi = 0.
      rv_root = hi.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF flo * fhi > 0.
      rv_root = lo.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA mid  TYPE f.
    DATA fmid TYPE f.
    DATA eps  TYPE f VALUE '0.000000000001'.

    DO 200 TIMES.
      mid = ( lo + hi ) / 2.

      poly_val = 0.
      DO n TIMES.
        idx = n - sy-index + 1.
        READ TABLE lt_coeffs INDEX idx INTO coeff.
        poly_val = poly_val * mid + coeff.
      ENDDO.
      fmid = poly_val.

      IF fmid = 0.
        rv_root = mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF flo * fmid < 0.
        hi = mid.
        fhi = fmid.
      ELSE.
        lo = mid.
        flo = fmid.
      ENDIF.

      IF abs( hi - lo ) < eps.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    rv_root = ( lo + hi ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_coeff TYPE f.

    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_x) TYPE ty_coeff.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_zero.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_xs> TYPE STANDARD TABLE.
    ASSIGN xs TO <lt_xs>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_n TYPE i.
    lv_n = lines( <lt_xs> ).
    IF lv_n = 0 OR lv_n MOD 2 <> 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <c_any> TYPE any.

    DATA lv_has_pos TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
    DATA lv_has_neg TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
    DATA lv_lead TYPE ty_coeff VALUE 0.

    DATA lv_i TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c TYPE ty_coeff.

    DO lv_n TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index.
      READ TABLE <lt_xs> ASSIGNING <c_any> INDEX lv_i.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_x = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          lv_c = CONV ty_coeff( <c_any> ).
        CATCH cx_root.
          rv_x = 0.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_c > 0.
        lv_has_pos = abap_true.
      ELSEIF lv_c < 0.
        lv_has_neg = abap_true.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    lv_i = lv_n.
    WHILE lv_i >= 1.
      READ TABLE <lt_xs> ASSIGNING <c_any> INDEX lv_i.
      IF sy-subrc <> 0.
        rv_x = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          lv_lead = CONV ty_coeff( <c_any> ).
        CATCH cx_root.
          rv_x = 0.
          RETURN.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_lead <> 0.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i - 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_lead = 0 OR lv_has_pos <> abap_true OR lv_has_neg <> abap_true.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_eps TYPE ty_coeff VALUE '0.000000000001'.
    DATA lv_max_iter TYPE i VALUE 200.

    DATA lv_low TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_high TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_mid TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_flow TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_fhigh TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_fmid TYPE ty_coeff.

    DATA lv_tmp TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_eval_x TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_cc TYPE ty_coeff.

    DEFINE eval_poly.
      lv_eval_x = &1.
      lv_tmp = 0.
      lv_i = lv_n.
      WHILE lv_i >= 1.
        READ TABLE <lt_xs> ASSIGNING <c_any> INDEX lv_i.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          TRY.
              lv_cc = CONV ty_coeff( <c_any> ).
            CATCH cx_root.
              lv_cc = 0.
          ENDTRY.
        ELSE.
          lv_cc = 0.
        ENDIF.
        lv_tmp = lv_tmp * lv_eval_x + lv_cc.
        lv_i = lv_i - 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      &2 = lv_tmp.
    END-OF-DEFINITION.

    lv_low = -1.
    eval_poly lv_low lv_flow.
    IF lv_flow = 0.
      rv_x = lv_low.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_high = 1.
    eval_poly lv_high lv_fhigh.
    IF lv_fhigh = 0.
      rv_x = lv_high.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_scale_iter TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_prev_low TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_prev_high TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_prev_flow TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA lv_prev_fhigh TYPE ty_coeff.

    WHILE lv_flow * lv_fhigh > 0 AND lv_scale_iter < 200.
      lv_prev_low = lv_low.
      lv_prev_high = lv_high.
      lv_prev_flow = lv_flow.
      lv_prev_fhigh = lv_fhigh.

      lv_low = lv_low * 2.
      lv_high = lv_high * 2.

      eval_poly lv_low lv_flow.
      eval_poly lv_high lv_fhigh.

      IF lv_flow = 0.
        rv_x = lv_low.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF lv_fhigh = 0.
        rv_x = lv_high.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_low = lv_prev_low AND lv_high = lv_prev_high )
         OR ( lv_flow = lv_prev_flow AND lv_fhigh = lv_prev_fhigh ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      IF abs( lv_low ) > 1E6 OR abs( lv_high ) > 1E6.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_scale_iter = lv_scale_iter + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_flow * lv_fhigh > 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_iter TYPE i VALUE 0.
    WHILE lv_iter < lv_max_iter.
      lv_mid = ( lv_low + lv_high ) / 2.
      eval_poly lv_mid lv_fmid.

      IF lv_fmid = 0.
        rv_x = lv_mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF abs( lv_high - lv_low ) <= lv_eps * ( abs( lv_high ) + abs( lv_low ) + 1 ).
        rv_x = lv_mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF lv_flow * lv_fmid < 0.
        lv_high = lv_mid.
        lv_fhigh = lv_fmid.
      ELSE.
        lv_low = lv_mid.
        lv_flow = lv_fmid.
      ENDIF.

      lv_iter = lv_iter + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_x = ( lv_low + lv_high ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_coeff  TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 14.
    TYPES ty_coeffs TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_coeff WITH EMPTY KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs TYPE ty_coeffs
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_x) TYPE ty_coeff.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_zero.
    DATA lt_xs TYPE ty_coeffs.
    lt_xs = xs.

    DATA n TYPE i.
    n = lines( lt_xs ).

    IF n = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lc_eps TYPE ty_coeff VALUE '0.00000000000000000001'.
    DATA lc_tol TYPE ty_coeff VALUE '0.000000000000001'.
    DATA lc_max TYPE i VALUE 200.

    DATA lv_lead TYPE ty_coeff VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_idx  TYPE i.
    lv_idx = n.

    WHILE lv_idx > 0.
      READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX lv_idx INTO lv_lead.
      IF sy-subrc = 0 AND abs( lv_lead ) > lc_eps.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      lv_idx = lv_idx - 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_idx = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_deg TYPE i.
    lv_deg = lv_idx - 1.

    IF lv_deg <= 0.
      READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX 1 INTO DATA(lv_c0).
      READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX 2 INTO DATA(lv_c1).
      IF sy-subrc <> 0 OR abs( lv_c1 ) <= lc_eps OR lv_c1 = 0.
        rv_x = 0.
      ELSE.
        rv_x = - lv_c0 / lv_c1.
      ENDIF.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_a0 TYPE ty_coeff VALUE 0.
    READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX 1 INTO lv_a0.

    IF abs( lv_a0 ) <= lc_eps.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_sign_lead TYPE i.
    IF lv_lead > 0.
      lv_sign_lead = 1.
    ELSE.
      lv_sign_lead = -1.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_right TYPE ty_coeff.
    IF lv_sign_lead = 1.
      IF lv_a0 < 0.
        lv_right = 1.
      ELSE.
        lv_right = -1.
      ENDIF.
    ELSE.
      IF lv_a0 < 0.
        lv_right = -1.
      ELSE.
        lv_right = 1.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_left TYPE ty_coeff.
    lv_left = -lv_right.

    DATA eval_right TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA eval_left  TYPE ty_coeff.

    DATA pow2 TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DO.
      DATA pv TYPE ty_coeff.
      DATA idx TYPE i.
      DATA ai TYPE ty_coeff.

      pv = lv_lead.
      idx = lv_deg.
      WHILE idx >= 0.
        READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX ( idx + 1 ) INTO ai.
        pv = pv * lv_right + ai.
        idx = idx - 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      eval_right = pv.

      pv = lv_lead.
      idx = lv_deg.
      WHILE idx >= 0.
        READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX ( idx + 1 ) INTO ai.
        pv = pv * lv_left + ai.
        idx = idx - 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      eval_left = pv.

      IF eval_left = 0.
        rv_x = lv_left.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF eval_right = 0.
        rv_x = lv_right.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( eval_left < 0 AND eval_right > 0 ) OR ( eval_left > 0 AND eval_right < 0 ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      pow2 = pow2 + 1.
      IF pow2 > 200.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_right = lv_right * 2.
      lv_left  = lv_left * 2.
    ENDDO.

    DATA a TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA b TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA fa TYPE ty_coeff.
    DATA fb TYPE ty_coeff.

    a = lv_left.
    b = lv_right.
    fa = eval_left.
    fb = eval_right.

    IF NOT ( ( fa < 0 AND fb > 0 ) OR ( fa > 0 AND fb < 0 ) ).
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA iter TYPE i VALUE 0.
    WHILE iter < lc_max AND abs( b - a ) > lc_tol.
      DATA m TYPE ty_coeff.
      DATA fm TYPE ty_coeff.
      DATA pv2 TYPE ty_coeff.
      DATA idx2 TYPE i.
      DATA ai2 TYPE ty_coeff.

      m = ( a + b ) / 2.

      pv2 = lv_lead.
      idx2 = lv_deg.
      WHILE idx2 >= 0.
        READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX ( idx2 + 1 ) INTO ai2.
        pv2 = pv2 * m + ai2.
        idx2 = idx2 - 1.
      ENDWHILE.
      fm = pv2.

      IF abs( fm ) <= lc_tol.
        rv_x = m.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( fa < 0 AND fm > 0 ) OR ( fa > 0 AND fm < 0 ).
        b = m.
        fb = fm.
      ELSE.
        a = m.
        fa = fm.
      ENDIF.

      iter = iter + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_x = ( a + b ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS find_zero
      IMPORTING
        xs           TYPE STANDARD TABLE
        max_iter     TYPE i     DEFAULT 100
        tol          TYPE f     DEFAULT '0.0000000001'
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_x)  TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_poly_find_zero IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD find_zero.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <xs> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    ASSIGN xs TO <xs>.

    DATA lt_xs TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF f WITH EMPTY KEY.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <c> TYPE any.
    LOOP AT <xs> ASSIGNING <c>.
      APPEND CONV f( <c> ) TO lt_xs.
    ENDLOOP.

    DATA(lv_n) = lines( lt_xs ).
    IF lv_n = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_deg TYPE i VALUE -1.
    DATA lv_coeff TYPE f.
    DATA lv_i TYPE i.

    lv_i = lv_n.
    WHILE lv_i > 0.
      READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX lv_i INTO lv_coeff.
      IF sy-subrc = 0 AND lv_coeff <> 0.
        lv_deg = lv_i - 1.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i - 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_deg <= 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF ( lv_deg MOD 2 ) = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_x0 TYPE f.
    DATA lv_x1 TYPE f.
    DATA lv_f0 TYPE f.
    DATA lv_f1 TYPE f.
    DATA lv_mid TYPE f.
    DATA lv_fm TYPE f.

    DATA(lv_an) = 0.
    READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX ( lv_deg + 1 ) INTO lv_an.
    IF lv_an = 0.
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_scale TYPE f VALUE 1.
    DATA lv_k TYPE i VALUE 0.

    WHILE lv_k < 100.
      lv_scale = lv_scale * 2.
      lv_x0 = 0 - lv_scale.
      lv_x1 = lv_scale.

      lv_f0 = 0.
      DO lv_deg + 1 TIMES.
        DATA(lv_idx0) = sy-index.
        READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX lv_idx0 INTO lv_coeff.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          DATA(lv_pow0) = 1.
          DATA(lv_p0) = lv_idx0 - 1.
          DATA(lv_t0) = 0.
          WHILE lv_t0 < lv_p0.
            lv_pow0 = lv_pow0 * lv_x0.
            lv_t0 = lv_t0 + 1.
          ENDWHILE.
          lv_f0 = lv_f0 + lv_coeff * lv_pow0.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      lv_f1 = 0.
      DO lv_deg + 1 TIMES.
        DATA(lv_idx1) = sy-index.
        READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX lv_idx1 INTO lv_coeff.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          DATA(lv_pow1) = 1.
          DATA(lv_p1) = lv_idx1 - 1.
          DATA(lv_t1) = 0.
          WHILE lv_t1 < lv_p1.
            lv_pow1 = lv_pow1 * lv_x1.
            lv_t1 = lv_t1 + 1.
          ENDWHILE.
          lv_f1 = lv_f1 + lv_coeff * lv_pow1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      IF lv_f0 = 0.
        rv_x = lv_x0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      IF lv_f1 = 0.
        rv_x = lv_x1.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_f0 < 0 AND lv_f1 > 0 ) OR ( lv_f0 > 0 AND lv_f1 < 0 ).
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.

      lv_k = lv_k + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF NOT ( ( lv_f0 < 0 AND lv_f1 > 0 ) OR ( lv_f0 > 0 AND lv_f1 < 0 ) ).
      rv_x = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA lv_iter TYPE i VALUE 0.
    WHILE lv_iter < max_iter.
      lv_mid = ( lv_x0 + lv_x1 ) / 2.

      lv_fm = 0.
      DO lv_deg + 1 TIMES.
        DATA(lv_idxm) = sy-index.
        READ TABLE lt_xs INDEX lv_idxm INTO lv_coeff.
        IF sy-subrc = 0.
          DATA(lv_powm) = 1.
          DATA(lv_pm) = lv_idxm - 1.
          DATA(lv_tm) = 0.
          WHILE lv_tm < lv_pm.
            lv_powm = lv_powm * lv_mid.
            lv_tm = lv_tm + 1.
          ENDWHILE.
          lv_fm = lv_fm + lv_coeff * lv_powm.
        ENDIF.
      ENDDO.

      IF abs( lv_fm ) <= tol OR abs( lv_x1 - lv_x0 ) <= tol.
        rv_x = lv_mid.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF ( lv_f0 < 0 AND lv_fm > 0 ) OR ( lv_f0 > 0 AND lv_fm < 0 ).
        lv_x1 = lv_mid.
        lv_f1 = lv_fm.
      ELSE.
        lv_x0 = lv_mid.
        lv_f0 = lv_fm.
      ENDIF.

      lv_iter = lv_iter + 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_x = ( lv_x0 + lv_x1 ) / 2.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_int_prm_inter_len DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS intersection
      IMPORTING
        interval1 TYPE any
        interval2 TYPE any
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_int_prm_inter_len IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    DATA: lv_s1  TYPE i,
          lv_e1  TYPE i,
          lv_s2  TYPE i,
          lv_e2  TYPE i,
          lv_is  TYPE i,
          lv_ie  TYPE i,
          lv_len TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <t1> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <t2> TYPE STANDARD TABLE,
                   <v>  TYPE any.

    ASSIGN interval1 TO <t1>.
    ASSIGN interval2 TO <t2>.

    IF <t1> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <t2> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE <t1> INDEX 1 ASSIGNING <v>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    lv_s1 = CONV i( <v> ).

    READ TABLE <t1> INDEX 2 ASSIGNING <v>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    lv_e1 = CONV i( <v> ).

    READ TABLE <t2> INDEX 1 ASSIGNING <v>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    lv_s2 = CONV i( <v> ).

    READ TABLE <t2> INDEX 2 ASSIGNING <v>.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    lv_e2 = CONV i( <v> ).

    lv_is = COND i( WHEN lv_s1 > lv_s2 THEN lv_s1 ELSE lv_s2 ).
    lv_ie = COND i( WHEN lv_e1 < lv_e2 THEN lv_e1 ELSE lv_e2 ).

    IF lv_is > lv_ie.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lv_ie - lv_is.

    IF lv_len < 2.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len = 2 OR lv_len = 3.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0 OR lv_len MOD 3 = 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DATA(lv_i) = 5.
    WHILE lv_i * lv_i <= lv_len.
      IF lv_len MOD lv_i = 0 OR lv_len MOD ( lv_i + 2 ) = 0.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 6.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = 'YES'.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_intersection_prim DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS intersection
      IMPORTING
        VALUE(interval1) TYPE any
        VALUE(interval2) TYPE any
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_intersection_prim IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <s1> TYPE any,
                   <e1> TYPE any,
                   <s2> TYPE any,
                   <e2> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_s1    TYPE i,
          lv_e1    TYPE i,
          lv_s2    TYPE i,
          lv_e2    TYPE i,
          lv_left  TYPE i,
          lv_right TYPE i,
          lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_n     TYPE i,
          lv_i     TYPE i.

    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'START' OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO <s1>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'END'   OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO <e1>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'START' OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO <s2>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'END'   OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO <e2>.

    IF <s1> IS ASSIGNED AND <e1> IS ASSIGNED AND <s2> IS ASSIGNED AND <e2> IS ASSIGNED.
      lv_s1 = <s1>.
      lv_e1 = <e1>.
      lv_s2 = <s2>.
      lv_e2 = <e2>.
    ELSE.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT '1' OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO <s1>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT '2' OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO <e1>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT '1' OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO <s2>.
      ASSIGN COMPONENT '2' OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO <e2>.

      IF <s1> IS ASSIGNED AND <e1> IS ASSIGNED AND <s2> IS ASSIGNED AND <e2> IS ASSIGNED.
        lv_s1 = <s1>.
        lv_e1 = <e1>.
        lv_s2 = <s2>.
        lv_e2 = <e2>.
      ELSE.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_s1 > lv_s2.
      lv_left = lv_s1.
    ELSE.
      lv_left = lv_s2.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_e1 < lv_e2.
      lv_right = lv_e1.
    ELSE.
      lv_right = lv_e2.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_left > lv_right.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lv_right - lv_left + 1.

    IF lv_len < 2.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len = 2 OR lv_len = 3.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0 OR lv_len MOD 3 = 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_n = lv_len.
    lv_i = 5.

    WHILE lv_i * lv_i <= lv_n.
      IF lv_n MOD lv_i = 0 OR lv_n MOD ( lv_i + 2 ) = 0.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 6.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = 'YES'.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_prime_intersectio DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS intersection
      IMPORTING
        interval1 TYPE any
        interval2 TYPE any
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_prime_intersectio IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <a> TYPE any,
                   <b> TYPE any,
                   <a_start> TYPE any,
                   <a_end>   TYPE any,
                   <b_start> TYPE any,
                   <b_end>   TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_a_start TYPE i,
          lv_a_end   TYPE i,
          lv_b_start TYPE i,
          lv_b_end   TYPE i,
          lv_start   TYPE i,
          lv_end     TYPE i,
          lv_len     TYPE i,
          lv_i       TYPE i,
          lv_prime   TYPE abap_bool.

    ASSIGN interval1 TO <a>.
    ASSIGN interval2 TO <b>.

    IF <a> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <b> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE <a> TO <a_start>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 2 OF STRUCTURE <a> TO <a_end>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE <b> TO <b_start>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 2 OF STRUCTURE <b> TO <b_end>.

    IF <a_start> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <a_end> IS NOT ASSIGNED
       OR <b_start> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <b_end> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TRY.
        lv_a_start = CONV i( <a_start> ).
        lv_a_end   = CONV i( <a_end> ).
        lv_b_start = CONV i( <b_start> ).
        lv_b_end   = CONV i( <b_end> ).
      CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lv_a_start > lv_b_start.
      lv_start = lv_a_start.
    ELSE.
      lv_start = lv_b_start.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_a_end < lv_b_end.
      lv_end = lv_a_end.
    ELSE.
      lv_end = lv_b_end.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_start > lv_end.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lv_end - lv_start.

    IF lv_len < 2.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len = 2 OR lv_len = 3.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_prime = abap_true.
    lv_i = 3.

    WHILE lv_i * lv_i <= lv_len.
      IF lv_len MOD lv_i = 0.
        lv_prime = abap_false.
        EXIT.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_prime = abap_true.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
    ELSE.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_prime_intersectio DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS intersection
      IMPORTING
        interval1 TYPE string
        interval2 TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_prime_intersectio IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    DATA: lv_s1    TYPE int4,
          lv_e1    TYPE int4,
          lv_s2    TYPE int4,
          lv_e2    TYPE int4,
          lv_left  TYPE int4,
          lv_right TYPE int4,
          lv_len   TYPE int4,
          lv_i     TYPE int4.

    DATA: lt_t1 TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY,
          lt_t2 TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY,
          lv_v1 TYPE string,
          lv_v2 TYPE string.

    rv_result = 'NO'.
    CLEAR: lv_s1, lv_e1, lv_s2, lv_e2, lv_left, lv_right, lv_len, lv_i.

    SPLIT interval1 AT ',' INTO TABLE lt_t1.
    SPLIT interval2 AT ',' INTO TABLE lt_t2.

    IF lines( lt_t1 ) < 2 OR lines( lt_t2 ) < 2.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE lt_t1 INDEX 1 INTO lv_v1.
    READ TABLE lt_t1 INDEX 2 INTO lv_v2.
    CONDENSE lv_v1 NO-GAPS.
    CONDENSE lv_v2 NO-GAPS.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '(' IN lv_v1 WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF ')' IN lv_v1 WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '(' IN lv_v2 WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF ')' IN lv_v2 WITH ''.
    lv_s1 = lv_v1.
    lv_e1 = lv_v2.

    READ TABLE lt_t2 INDEX 1 INTO lv_v1.
    READ TABLE lt_t2 INDEX 2 INTO lv_v2.
    CONDENSE lv_v1 NO-GAPS.
    CONDENSE lv_v2 NO-GAPS.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '(' IN lv_v1 WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF ')' IN lv_v1 WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF '(' IN lv_v2 WITH ''.
    REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF ')' IN lv_v2 WITH ''.
    lv_s2 = lv_v1.
    lv_e2 = lv_v2.

    IF lv_s1 > lv_s2.
      lv_left = lv_s1.
    ELSE.
      lv_left = lv_s2.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_e1 < lv_e2.
      lv_right = lv_e1.
    ELSE.
      lv_right = lv_e2.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_left > lv_right.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lv_right - lv_left.

    IF lv_len <= 1.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len = 2 OR lv_len = 3.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0 OR lv_len MOD 3 = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_i = 5.
    WHILE lv_i * lv_i <= lv_len.
      IF lv_len MOD lv_i = 0 OR lv_len MOD ( lv_i + 2 ) = 0.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 6.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = 'YES'.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

          lv_left  TYPE i,
          lv_right TYPE i,
          lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_i     TYPE i.

    lv_s1 = 0.
    lv_e1 = 0.
    lv_s2 = 0.
    lv_e2 = 0.

    FIND REGEX `-?\d+` IN interval1 SUBMATCHES DATA(lv_m1).
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      lv_s1 = lv_m1.
      FIND REGEX `-?\d+` IN interval1 SUBMATCHES DATA(lv_m2) OCCURRENCE 2.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_e1 = lv_m2.
      ENDIF.
    ENDIF.

    FIND REGEX `-?\d+` IN interval2 SUBMATCHES DATA(lv_m3).
    IF sy-subrc = 0.
      lv_s2 = lv_m3.
      FIND REGEX `-?\d+` IN interval2 SUBMATCHES DATA(lv_m4) OCCURRENCE 2.
      IF sy-subrc = 0.

    ELSE.
      lv_right = lv_e2.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_left > lv_right.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lv_right - lv_left.

    IF lv_len < 2.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len = 2 OR lv_len = 3.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0 OR lv_len MOD 3 = 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_i = 5.
    WHILE lv_i * lv_i <= lv_len.
      IF lv_len MOD lv_i = 0 OR lv_len MOD ( lv_i + 2 ) = 0.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 6.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = 'YES'.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_intersection IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <i1> TYPE any,
                   <i2> TYPE any,
                   <s1> TYPE any,
                   <e1> TYPE any,
                   <s2> TYPE any,
                   <e2> TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_s1  TYPE i,
          lv_e1  TYPE i,
          lv_s2  TYPE i,
          lv_e2  TYPE i,
          lv_l   TYPE i,
          lv_r   TYPE i,
          lv_len TYPE i,
          lv_d   TYPE i.

    ASSIGN interval1 TO <i1>.
    ASSIGN interval2 TO <i2>.
    IF <i1> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <i2> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE <i1> TO <s1>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 2 OF STRUCTURE <i1> TO <e1>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE <i2> TO <s2>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 2 OF STRUCTURE <i2> TO <e2>.

    IF <s1> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <e1> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <s2> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <e2> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    TRY.
        lv_s1 = CONV i( <s1> ).
        lv_e1 = CONV i( <e1> ).
        lv_s2 = CONV i( <s2> ).
        lv_e2 = CONV i( <e2> ).
      CATCH cx_root.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    lv_l = nmax( val1 = lv_s1 val2 = lv_s2 ).
    lv_r = nmin( val1 = lv_e1 val2 = lv_e2 ).

    IF lv_l > lv_r.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lv_r - lv_l.

    IF lv_len < 2.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len = 2 OR lv_len = 3.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0 OR lv_len MOD 3 = 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_d = 5.
    WHILE lv_d * lv_d <= lv_len.
      IF lv_len MOD lv_d = 0 OR lv_len MOD ( lv_d + 2 ) = 0.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_d = lv_d + 6.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = 'YES'.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_intersection DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC .

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS intersection
      IMPORTING
        interval1 TYPE any
        interval2 TYPE any
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_intersection IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <i1_start> TYPE any,
                   <i1_end>   TYPE any,
                   <i2_start> TYPE any,
                   <i2_end>   TYPE any.

    DATA: lv_s1    TYPE i,
          lv_e1    TYPE i,
          lv_s2    TYPE i,
          lv_e2    TYPE i,
          lv_left  TYPE i,
          lv_right TYPE i,
          lv_len   TYPE i,
          lv_d     TYPE i.

    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'START' OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO <i1_start>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'END'   OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO <i1_end>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'START' OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO <i2_start>.
    ASSIGN COMPONENT 'END'   OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO <i2_end>.

    IF <i1_start> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <i1_end> IS NOT ASSIGNED
       OR <i2_start> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <i2_end> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_s1 = <i1_start>.
    lv_e1 = <i1_end>.
    lv_s2 = <i2_start>.
    lv_e2 = <i2_end>.

    IF lv_s1 >= lv_s2.
      lv_left = lv_s1.
    ELSE.
      lv_left = lv_s2.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_e1 <= lv_e2.
      lv_right = lv_e1.
    ELSE.
      lv_right = lv_e2.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_left > lv_right.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_len = lv_right - lv_left.

    IF lv_len < 2.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len = 2.
      rv_result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_len MOD 2 = 0.
      rv_result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_d = 3.
    WHILE lv_d * lv_d <= lv_len.
      IF lv_len MOD lv_d = 0.
        rv_result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_d = lv_d + 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = 'YES'.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_intersection_prim DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS intersection
      IMPORTING
        VALUE(interval1) TYPE any
        VALUE(interval2) TYPE any
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_intersection_prim IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    DATA lv_a_start TYPE i.
    DATA lv_a_end   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_b_start TYPE i.
    DATA lv_b_end   TYPE i.

    DATA lv_start TYPE i.
    DATA lv_end   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_len   TYPE i.
    DATA lv_n     TYPE i.
    DATA lv_i     TYPE i.

    TRY.
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<a_start>).
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 2 OF STRUCTURE interval1 TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<a_end>).
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 1 OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<b_start>).
        ASSIGN COMPONENT 2 OF STRUCTURE interval2 TO FIELD-SYMBOL(<b_end>).

        IF <a_start> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <a_end> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <b_start> IS NOT ASSIGNED OR <b_end> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
          rv_result = `NO`.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.

        lv_a_start = <a_start>.
        lv_a_end   = <a_end>.
        lv_b_start = <b_start>.
        lv_b_end   = <b_end>.
      CATCH cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error cx_sy_assign_cast_illegal_cast.
        rv_result = `NO`.
        RETURN.
    ENDTRY.

    IF lv_a_start > lv_b_start.
      lv_start = lv_a_start.
    ELSE.
      lv_start = lv_b_start.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_a_end < lv_b_end.
      lv_end = lv_a_end.
    ELSE.
      lv_end = lv_b_end.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_start > lv_end.
      rv_result = `NO`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    "Length of a closed interval intersection is (end - start + 1)
    lv_len = lv_end - lv_start + 1.

    IF lv_len < 2.
      rv_result = `NO`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_n = lv_len.

    IF lv_n = 2 OR lv_n = 3.
      rv_result = `YES`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF lv_n MOD 2 = 0.
      rv_result = `NO`.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    lv_i = 3.
    WHILE lv_i * lv_i <= lv_n.
      IF lv_n MOD lv_i = 0.
        rv_result = `NO`.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      lv_i = lv_i + 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    rv_result = `YES`.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_prime_intersectio DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES ty_int_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF i WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS intersection
      IMPORTING
        interval1 TYPE ty_int_tab
        interval2 TYPE ty_int_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(result) TYPE string.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_interval_prime_intersectio IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD intersection.
    DATA: a1  TYPE i,
          b1  TYPE i,
          a2  TYPE i,
          b2  TYPE i,
          l   TYPE i,
          r   TYPE i,
          len TYPE i,
          n   TYPE i,
          d   TYPE i.

    READ TABLE interval1 INDEX 1 INTO a1.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    READ TABLE interval1 INDEX 2 INTO b1.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    READ TABLE interval2 INDEX 1 INTO a2.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.
    READ TABLE interval2 INDEX 2 INTO b2.
    IF sy-subrc <> 0.
      result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    l = a1.
    IF a2 > l.
      l = a2.
    ENDIF.

    r = b1.
    IF b2 < r.
      r = b2.
    ENDIF.

    IF l > r.
      result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    len = r - l.

    IF len < 2.
      result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF len = 2 OR len = 3.
      result = 'YES'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    IF len MOD 2 = 0.
      result = 'NO'.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    n = len.
    d = 3.
    WHILE d * d <= n.
      IF n MOD d = 0.
        result = 'NO'.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
      d = d + 2.
    ENDWHILE.

    result = 'YES'.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF c LENGTH 255 WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    DATA lv_sum TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_x   TYPE c LENGTH 255.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO lv_x.
      DATA lv_num TYPE c LENGTH 255.
      DATA lv_before TYPE c LENGTH 255.
      DATA lv_after  TYPE c LENGTH 255.
      DATA lv_int TYPE i.
      DATA lv_len TYPE i.
      DATA lv_has_dot TYPE abap_bool.

      lv_num = lv_x.
      CONDENSE lv_num NO-GAPS.

      FIND FIRST OCCURRENCE OF '.' IN lv_num MATCH OFFSET DATA(lv_off).
      IF sy-subrc = 0.
        lv_has_dot = abap_true.
        lv_before = lv_num+0(lv_off).
        lv_len = strlen( lv_num ) - lv_off - 1.
        IF lv_len > 0.
          lv_after = lv_num+( lv_off + 1 )( lv_len ).
        ELSE.
          CLEAR lv_after.
        ENDIF.

        CONDENSE lv_after NO-GAPS.
        IF lv_after IS INITIAL.
          lv_int = lv_before.
        ELSE.
          DATA lv_after_nz TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.
          DO strlen( lv_after ) TIMES.
            IF lv_after+sy-index-1(1) <> '0'.
              lv_after_nz = abap_true.
              EXIT.
            ENDIF.
          ENDDO.

          lv_int = lv_before.
          IF lv_after_nz = abap_true AND lv_num(1) <> '-'.
            lv_int = lv_int + 1.
          ENDIF.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        lv_int = lv_num.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sum = lv_sum + ( lv_int * lv_int ).
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_sum = lv_sum.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_values TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    DATA lv_ceiling TYPE i.
    DATA lv_value   TYPE f.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <v> TYPE any.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_values ASSIGNING <v>.
      TRY.
          lv_value = CONV f( <v> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_ceiling = ceil( lv_value ).
      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_ceiling * lv_ceiling ).
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES tt_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY.
    TYPES ty_sum     TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 6.

    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE tt_numbers
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE ty_sum.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    DATA lv_sum TYPE ty_sum.
    lv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO DATA(lv_str).
      DATA lv_num TYPE ty_sum.
      DATA lv_i   TYPE i.
      DATA lv_sq  TYPE p LENGTH 31 DECIMALS 0.

      lv_num = CONV ty_sum( lv_str ).

      lv_i = lv_num.
      IF lv_num > lv_i.
        lv_i = lv_i + 1.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sq = lv_i * lv_i.
      lv_sum = lv_sum + lv_sq.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_sum = lv_sum.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_numbers TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    DATA: lv_val_f      TYPE f,
          lv_trunc_i    TYPE i,
          lv_ceiling_i  TYPE i,
          lv_sq_i       TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS: <n> TYPE any.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_numbers ASSIGNING <n>.
      CLEAR: lv_val_f, lv_trunc_i, lv_ceiling_i, lv_sq_i.

      TRY.
          lv_val_f = <n>.
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_trunc_i = trunc( lv_val_f ).
      IF lv_val_f > lv_trunc_i.
        lv_ceiling_i = lv_trunc_i + 1.
      ELSE.
        lv_ceiling_i = lv_trunc_i.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sq_i = lv_ceiling_i * lv_ceiling_i.
      rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_sq_i.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    TYPES: ty_num TYPE p LENGTH 16 DECIMALS 4,
           ty_num_tab TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF ty_num WITH DEFAULT KEY.

    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ty_num_tab
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE p LENGTH 31 DECIMALS 0.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<lv_val>).
      DATA(lv_trunc) TYPE i.
      DATA(lv_ceil)  TYPE i.

      lv_trunc = trunc( <lv_val> ).

      lv_ceil = lv_trunc.
      IF <lv_val> > lv_trunc.
        lv_ceil = lv_trunc + 1.
      ENDIF.

      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( lv_ceil * lv_ceil ).
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE STANDARD TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.
    DATA: lv_val_f    TYPE f,
          lv_intpart  TYPE i,
          lv_ceiling  TYPE i,
          lv_sq_i8    TYPE int8,
          lv_sum_i8   TYPE int8.

    rv_sum = 0.
    lv_sum_i8 = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      CLEAR: lv_val_f, lv_intpart, lv_ceiling, lv_sq_i8.

      TRY.
          lv_val_f = CONV f( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_move_cast_error cx_sy_conversion_error.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_intpart = trunc( lv_val_f ).

      IF lv_val_f > lv_intpart.
        lv_ceiling = lv_intpart + 1.
      ELSE.
        lv_ceiling = lv_intpart.
      ENDIF.

      lv_sq_i8 = CONV int8( lv_ceiling ) * CONV int8( lv_ceiling ).
      lv_sum_i8 = lv_sum_i8 + lv_sq_i8.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_sum = CONV f( lv_sum_i8 ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_list       TYPE STANDARD TABLE OF string WITH EMPTY KEY
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list INTO DATA(lv_str).
      DATA(lv_val) TYPE string.
      lv_val = condense( lv_str ).

      DATA(lv_pack) TYPE string.
      lv_pack = lv_val.
      REPLACE ALL OCCURRENCES OF ',' IN lv_pack WITH '.'.

      DATA(lv_f) TYPE f.
      TRY.
          lv_f = lv_pack.
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      DATA(lv_ceil) TYPE i.
      lv_ceil = ceil( lv_f ).

      rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_ceil * lv_ceil.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC

      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    DATA lv_ceil TYPE i.
    DATA lv_sq   TYPE f.

    rv_sum = 0.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING FIELD-SYMBOL(<v>).
      lv_ceil = ceil( <v> ).
      lv_sq = lv_ceil * lv_ceil.
      rv_sum = rv_sum + lv_sq.
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        it_list TYPE ANY TABLE
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE i.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    DATA lv_sum_i    TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_num_f    TYPE f.
    DATA lv_floor_i  TYPE i.
    DATA lv_ceil_i   TYPE i.

    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    LOOP AT it_list ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      TRY.
          lv_num_f = CONV f( <lv_any> ).
        CATCH cx_sy_conversion_no_number cx_sy_conversion_overflow.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      lv_floor_i = floor( lv_num_f ).
      lv_ceil_i  = ceil( lv_num_f ).

      IF lv_num_f = lv_floor_i.
        lv_ceil_i = lv_floor_i.
      ENDIF.

      TRY.
          lv_sum_i = lv_sum_i + lv_ceil_i * lv_ceil_i.
        CATCH cx_sy_arithmetic_overflow.
          lv_sum_i = 0.
          EXIT.
      ENDTRY.
    ENDLOOP.

    rv_sum = lv_sum_i.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS sum_squares
      IMPORTING
        lst TYPE any
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_sum) TYPE f.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_sum_squares IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD sum_squares.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lt_any> TYPE ANY TABLE.
    FIELD-SYMBOLS <lv_any> TYPE any.

    DATA lv_val     TYPE f.
    DATA lv_ceiling TYPE i.
    DATA lo_type    TYPE REF TO cl_abap_typedescr.

    ASSIGN lst TO <lt_any>.
    rv_sum = 0.

    IF <lt_any> IS NOT ASSIGNED.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    LOOP AT <lt_any> ASSIGNING <lv_any>.
      CLEAR lv_val.
      CLEAR lv_ceiling.

      TRY.
          lo_type = cl_abap_typedescr=>describe_by_data( <lv_any> ).

          CASE lo_type->type_kind.
            WHEN cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int1
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int2
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_int8
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_packed
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_float.
              lv_val = <lv_any>.
            WHEN cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_decfloat16
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_decfloat34.
              lv_val = CONV f( <lv_any> ).
            WHEN cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_char
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_num
              OR cl_abap_typedescr=>typekind_string.
              lv_val = CONV f( |{ <lv_any> }| ).
            WHEN OTHERS.
              CONTINUE.
          ENDCASE.
        CATCH cx_root.
          CONTINUE.
      ENDTRY.

      IF lv_val = trunc( lv_val ).
        lv_ceiling = trunc( lv_val ).
      ELSEIF lv_val > 0.
        lv_ceiling = trunc( lv_val ) + 1.
      ELSE.
        lv_ceiling = trunc( lv_val ).
      ENDIF.

      rv_sum = rv_sum + ( CONV f( lv_ceiling ) * CONV f( lv_ceiling ) ).
    ENDLOOP.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_nested
      IMPORTING
        !iv_string TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(rv_is_nested) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_nested.
    DATA lv_depth  TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_len    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx    TYPE i.
    DATA lv_c      TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_prev   TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_nested TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    rv_is_nested = abap_false.

    lv_len = strlen( iv_string ).
    lv_idx = 0.
    lv_prev = space.

    WHILE lv_idx < lv_len.
      lv_c = iv_string+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_c = '['.
        lv_depth += 1.
      ELSEIF lv_c = ']'.
        IF lv_prev = '[' AND lv_depth > 1.
          lv_nested = abap_true.
        ENDIF.

        IF lv_depth > 0.
          lv_depth -= 1.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_c.
      lv_idx += 1.
    ENDWHILE.

    IF lv_nested = abap_true AND lv_depth = 0.
      rv_is_nested = abap_true.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_nested
      IMPORTING
        i_string TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_nested.
    DATA lv_depth TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA lv_len TYPE i.
    DATA lv_idx TYPE i.
    DATA lv_char TYPE c LENGTH 1.
    DATA lv_prev TYPE c LENGTH 1 VALUE space.
    DATA lv_has_nested_pair TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    lv_len = strlen( i_string ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_char = i_string+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_char = '['.
        lv_depth = lv_depth + 1.

      ELSEIF lv_char = ']'.
        IF lv_depth > 0.
          lv_depth = lv_depth - 1.

          IF lv_prev = '[' AND lv_depth >= 1.
            lv_has_nested_pair = abap_true.
          ENDIF.
        ELSE.
          lv_depth = 0.
        ENDIF.
      ENDIF.

      lv_prev = lv_char.
    ENDDO.

    r_result = lv_has_nested_pair.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PUBLIC.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_nested
      IMPORTING
        i_string        TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_nested) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_nested.
    DATA depth TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA max_depth TYPE i VALUE 0.
    DATA len TYPE i.

    len = strlen( i_string ).

    DO len TIMES.
      DATA(pos) = sy-index - 1.
      DATA(ch) = i_string+pos(1).

      IF ch = '['.
        depth = depth + 1.
        IF depth > max_depth.
          max_depth = depth.
        ENDIF.
      ELSEIF ch = ']'.
        IF depth = 0.
          r_nested = abap_false.
          RETURN.
        ENDIF.
        depth = depth - 1.
      ELSE.
        r_nested = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    r_nested = xsdbool( max_depth >= 2 ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested DEFINITION
  PUBLIC
  FINAL
  CREATE PRIVATE.

  PUBLIC SECTION.
    CLASS-METHODS is_nested
      IMPORTING
        i_string TYPE string
      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_nested.
    DATA: lv_depth       TYPE i VALUE 0,
          lv_len         TYPE i,
          lv_idx         TYPE i,
          lv_c           TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_found_pair  TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false,
          lv_found_nested TYPE abap_bool VALUE abap_false.

    r_result = abap_false.

    lv_len = strlen( i_string ).
    IF lv_len = 0.
      RETURN.
    ENDIF.

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_idx = sy-index - 1.
      lv_c = i_string+lv_idx(1).

      IF lv_c = '['.
        lv_depth = lv_depth + 1.
        IF lv_depth >= 2.
          lv_found_nested = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ELSEIF lv_c = ']'.
        IF lv_depth > 0.
          lv_depth = lv_depth - 1.
          lv_found_pair = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ELSE.
        r_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    IF lv_found_pair = abap_true AND lv_found_nested = abap_true.
      r_result = abap_true.
    ELSE.
      r_result = abap_false.
    ENDIF.
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested DEFINITION
  PUBLIC

  CREATE PUBLIC.

      RETURNING
        VALUE(r_result) TYPE abap_bool.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_nested.
    DATA(depth) = 0.
    DATA(found_nested) = abap_false.
    DATA(min_depth) = 0.

    DATA(len) = strlen( i_string ).
    DO len TIMES.
      DATA(idx) = sy-index - 1.
      DATA(c) = i_string+idx(1).

      IF c = '['.
        depth = depth + 1.
        IF depth >= 2.
          found_nested = abap_true.
        ENDIF.
      ELSEIF c = ']'.
        depth = depth - 1.
      ELSE.
        r_result = abap_false.
        RETURN.
      ENDIF.

      IF depth < min_depth.
        min_depth = depth.
      ENDIF.
    ENDDO.

    r_result = xsdbool( found_nested = abap_true AND min_depth = 0 AND depth = 0 ).
  ENDMETHOD.
ENDCLASS.

CLASS zcl_is_nested IMPLEMENTATION.
  METHOD is_nested.
    DATA: lv_len        TYPE i,
          lv_i          TYPE i,
          lv_c          TYPE c LENGTH 1,
          lv_level      TYPE i VALUE 0,
          lv_max_level  TYPE i VALUE 0.

    rv_result = abap_false.
    lv_len = strlen( iv_string ).

    DO lv_len TIMES.
      lv_i = sy-index - 1.

      IF lv_c = '['.

          RETURN.

      ELSE.
